INSERT INTO `tincident` VALUES (29,3272905,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'AMB-Telephone Encounters with Multiple Reasons for a Call that Includes Medication Refills Cannot be Routed as Rx Request Messages','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-25 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','SP\"07','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV07','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Showed up as fix under 3374011 Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I757514\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 C7503634\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Changed to \"\"closed\"\" status 2/2/09; included in 11/08 install.\"','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"<HISTORY>Waiting to validate.  Fix went in with July 08 k-packg. No Current Impact, as no regions are currently using the affected functionality. 3/27:   No current patient safety impact.  Incident may result in less timely refill request or workflow inconvenience. 4/10:  Rebecca to follow up.  4/21:  Rebecca to follow up.  4/28:  Waiting for July Kpkg.  5/6:  Per Epic (Jason Ramaker),  the fix - I757514 (C7503634) will be in the July 21 KPackage.  It is a client SU, so no server outage is required.  However, it would require users to be logged off the Citrix server before being installed.  5/8:  Not affected due to not using telephone encounters.  6/5:  Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed).  11/19:  installed w/ July kpackg, will certify w/ Orders Reconcil. 4/09.\r\n\r\n<CURRENT>Changed to \"\"closed\"\" status 2/2/09; included in 11/08 install.\"\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-12 02:16:00','2009-04-16 10:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(52,3626579,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Modified medication orders may display inconsistent details, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, RX, ED, OPT, BEA, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-30 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07, SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K090908',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Both fixes delivered under PR 3696803, Confirmed in Sept K;  fix standard in SP08 IU4\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510075\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 released 8/26/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K090908-C75031015 & E757165\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CLOSED per Kelly / Bill Yee 12/9/08.  Waiting for Sept Kpkg.  No Current Impact','NO CURRENT IMPACT - Order Entry - SP\"07-SP\"08 - Modified medication orders may display inconsistent details, in certain circumstances\r\n\"Description:   With a new SP\"07 feature that allows modification of medication orders, a modified medication order may display inconsistent order details if all of the following conditions are met:\r\nThe medication order is modified from the Medications Activity, Order Review/Inquiry, or Rounding Navigator\r\nModify order functionality is enabled (Allowed Medication Modifies - I LSD 25000). \r\nThe original medication order is placed with a specified frequency and off-schedule first dose. \r\nThe modification occurs within the time specified in the IP Window for Start Now Meds (I LSD 36120) item from the off-schedule first dose. \r\nThe following example workflow illustrates the problem:\r\nThe modify order functionality is enabled and the IP Window for Start Now Meds item is set to 15 minutes.\r\nA medication order is entered with a specified frequency of 2 Times Daily with scheduled times of 0900 and 1800. \r\nA clinician changes the first dose to 1050 and signs the medication order. \r\nAt 1052, a clinician modifies the original medication order. \r\nAs a result, the order information will appear in Order Entry with inconsistent next dose times.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - IP, AMB (dual-mode OE), Rx, ED, OPT, Beacon - SP\"07-SP\"08. Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a Kpackage.  7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic to find out which Kpkg fix will be in.  8/7:  Epic status update-8/27. 8/28:  Fix will be a part of Sept Kpkg. \r\n\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-12 04:01:00','2008-12-09 03:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66,3652623,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Modified Rx order w/ default vols inaccurate     ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-08 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','N','S','P','M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  work group came up with collabortive build config change.  PART will communicate\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Not PS. will track','\"Description:  A user, placing a medication order for neonatal or pediatric parenteral infusions, may modify the order in a way that may result in an inadvertent and unexpected or incorrect concentration. This may occur when the system defaults specified volumes for base solutions that may significantly alter the concentration of medications or other additives, which may be ordered by concentration (units/ml, mg/ml) and/or absolute units (units, mg).\r\nA workflow example, for ERX Record 69526 - IV Fluid Adjustable Fluid Neonatal, may be:\r\nThe physician may order D10W 100ml, Heparin 1 unit/ml, Ca Gluconate 100mg/100ml.  \r\nDuring verification a pharmacist may change the IV bag to D10W 500ml, Heparin 500 units, Ca Gluconate 500mg.  \r\nLater, another physician may change the base solution to D5W.  Because D10W and D5W are supplied in stock volumes including100ml and/or 500ml, alteration of the solution, and by default the volume of the solution, would inadvertently modify the order to D5W 100ml, Heparin 500 units, and Ca Gluconate 500mg, resulting in a five fold dose of Heparin and Ca Gluconate in the solution.  \r\nIn this scenario:\r\n1.  The system defaults a volume of 100ml for each base solution (D10W, D5W).\r\n2.  The additives may be ordered by concentration (units/ml, mg/ml) and absolute units (units, mg).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL, SCAL, and Exempla.  ERx, IP.  Communication has been sent notifying of the issue. A workgroup will be convened to addressed how this problem should be addressed. This is an internal ps issue that deals with how medications are built.  This is more like an enhancement request. 8/18:  Training workaround in place. Waiting for enhancement. 8/29:  per BY: \"Yes, the Heparin order units is now locked down to a concentration.  Drs. Dan Brugger and Allen Fischer are reviewing the other additive components of this mixture to determine if the same remediation can be made.\"  9/4:  per Bill Yee, this issue can be closed. Greying out row. \r\n','Pediatric and Neonatal Physicians (Dr. Dan Brugge and Dr. David Braun) developed a communication, sent 8/7/08, to all physicians ordering solutions for Neonates or Pediatric patients, warning them of this problem, until a more comprehensive resolution is developed.  The National Pharmacy representatives (SCAL-Dennis Kitayama and National-Bill Yee) wrote a similar communication for NCAL and SCAL pharmacists.  National Pharmacy will contact Exempla (Cindy James) to further communicate this issue, at a prescheduled Natl Pharmacy Meeting on 8/8/08.\r\n',NULL,'Pediatric and Neonatal Physicians (Dr. Dan Brugge and Dr. David Braun) developed a communication, sent 8/7/08, to all physicians ordering solutions for Neonates or Pediatric patients, warning them of this problem, until a more comprehensive resolution is developed.  The National Pharmacy representatives (SCAL-Dennis Kitayama and National-Bill Yee) wrote a similar communication for NCAL and SCAL pharmacists.  National Pharmacy will contact Exempla (Cindy James) to further communicate this issue, at a prescheduled Natl Pharmacy Meeting on 8/8/08.\r\n',NULL,'\"Concern:  A neonatal patient may receive an unintended concentration of a medication or additive.  Problem Discovered by:   NCAL (Dr. Brian Hoberman).\r\nEpic Representative / email address:  None (not exactly a flaw with KPHC).  \r\nPediatric and Neonatal Physicians (Dr. Dan Brugge and Dr. David Braun) developed a communication, sent 8/7/08, to all physicians ordering solutions for Neonates or Pediatric patients, warning them of this problem, until a more comprehensive resolution is developed.  The National Pharmacy representatives (SCAL-Dennis Kitayama and National-Bill Yee) wrote a similar communication for NCAL and SCAL pharmacists.  National Pharmacy will contact Exempla (Cindy James) to further communicate this issue, at a prescheduled Natl Pharmacy Meeting on 8/8/08.\r\nRemediation:  None discussed.\r\nAction items:  A special workgroup will be convened by Dr. Dan Brugge (NCAL) and Dr. David Braun (SCAL), to include other Neonatologists, Pediatricians, Neonatal and Pediatric nurses (Kathy Nakaki NCAL), and Natl KP Pharmacy and Exempla Pharmacy, to reach agreement as to how this problem should be addressed. Altering existing ERX records, and or building new ERX records, as well as, possibly eliminating volumes, in certain ERX records, with a hard stop that would force end user entry of specific volumes, will all be considered as options. An enhancement request to EPIC may also be considered.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 11:14:00','2008-09-19 02:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(71,3606904,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Patient-entered MyChart flowsheet data may display incorrectly, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-23 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K090908',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','Y','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Development complete. Confirmed in Sept K;  fix standard in SP08 IU4\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510047\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K090908-E757150\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed 11/19/08.  Gray out. ','Patient-entered MyChart flowsheet data may display incorrectly, in certain circumstances\r\n\"MyChart patient entered flowsheet can show wrong patient data in flowsheet.  An issue has been identified with MyChart Patient Entered Flowsheet data where previously displayed data can then be displayed in other patient accounts.\r\nWorkflow:\r\n1. Chart a patient with PEF data.\r\n2. Chart Review >> Episodes >> view a PEF report, which caches the episode ID in %EA(\"\"XWP\"\",\"\"hsbID\"\").\r\n3. Either use flowsheet hyperlink off the report or open Flowsheets >> MyChart Flowsheet - to see patient\"s PEF data.\r\n4. Chart another patient, with or without PEF data.\r\n5. Open Flowsheets >> MyChart Flowsheet - the cached hsbID from the previous patient will be used to display data.\r\nThe cached episode ID in %EA(\"\"XWP\"\",\"\"hsbID\"\") is set by the print group LPG 32061 that is the only print group used in LRP 32026 MyChart - Patient Entered Flowsheet Episode Report.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL, Hawaii, SCAL.  AMB (MyChart).  National AC (Jenna Ingleson) will work with Regional ACs to implement code (workaround).  Scheduled for production install by 7/24/2008.  Fix (code as workaround) will be included in September K-Package.  No adhoc necessary.  7/24:  Follow up with Ben Fulgencio about code being installed. - - Per Ben, programming point has been installed in production.  7/28:  Ask Apoorva if prg pt is W/A or permanent fix.    7/30:  Per Apoorva,  the programming point indeed fixes the problem. We are working on a more elegant fix which will be the ?permanent? fix and at that point the programming point can be removed. We are working on finalizing the K-Package in which the ?permanent? fix can be delivered but in the meanwhile you should be fine since the programming point has been set. 7/31:  Workaround is fine, waiting for Sept Kpkg (confirmed). Will be installed in Nov install. 9/18:  Waiting for Sept Kpkg. (confirmed). \r\n','Epic will provide a code (programming point) that will fix the issue on 7/23/2008.\r\n',NULL,'Epic will provide a code (programming point) that will fix the issue on 7/23/2008.\r\n',NULL,'NCAL.  IP (Anesthesiology).  Adhoc 4260.  Workaround in place. Tom to follow up with Rosalba regarding Epic\"s query.  7/22:  Two phone reconvenes today to clarify issue and develop workaround.  Dr. Hoberman wants security point 160 replaced with 193, testing now.  Dr. H wants hyperlink relabeled \"Do not click\".  Epic developing a query to identify corrupted order sets. 7/24:  Sent email to Rosalba regarding query status.  7/28:  Per Rosalba, results under review. 7/31:   Per Epic (Maria Spinozzi) - the source log of this issue has been determined to be DLG I756953 / package C7503472.   7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic to find out which Kpkg fix will be in. 8/7:  Maria to send updates by Monday (8/11). \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,37,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 11:52:00','2008-11-21 11:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(73,3545264,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'KPHC-Pharmacy product change of Hospital Medication can inappropriately discharge medication.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rx','','',NULL,'2008-07-01 16:17:30','2008-07-02 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Brian Hoberman',NULL,NULL,'4219','sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','1202-AP-PR3545264-E757827-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3','M',NULL,'JUL08','Y','S','R','B',' ','Y','S',NULL,'Clo',NULL,NULL,NULL,'M','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',60,'2009-01-12 11:39:22',NULL,'Infrastructure Software','PART KPHC','NOTES:  Confirmed in 1/19/09\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510639\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4219):  \n  SP’07 E757827 12/02/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011908\nRISK RANKING:  3','KPHC Environment','Patient Safety issue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Testing passed; on schdule for 1/20 install.','KPHC-Pharmacy product change of Hospital Medication can inappropriately discharge medication.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'File Received.  Rx will continue to remind our users of the proper workaround to avoid this issue\r\nNCAL, SCAL, HI, NW.  IP & Rx.  SP\"07.  Epic to provide status by 7/11/08. Fix requires an outage. Adhoc: 4219 / RFC:  2709113. Workaround communication has been sent.  7/3:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic regarding Kpkg. 7/7:  Tom to follow up with Bill & Minh. 7/9:  per B. Yee:  Dr. Hoberman wants us to push Epic for solution.   7/17 Epic to get back to us on 7/25.  7/21:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic (Maria). 7/28: Tom to follow up with Epic. 7/30:  Per Apoorva, Epic is working on finalizing the design for the fix for the issue. Dr. Hoberman is being kept in the loop regarding progress and to make sure that the design change meets his requirement.   7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic requesting status/updates. 8/4:  no ETA, Sept. install unlikely.  Aiming for November 12.  Dr. Hoberman actively involved with solution. 8/7:  Fix requires an outage. Per Bill Yee, 11/12 install is fine. Workaround is fine. 8/21:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic on 8/22. 8/28:  Tom to follow up with Apoorva to push for fix to be completed. 9/4:  Sharon to follow up with Epic. Per Sharon: Epic R&D will send Dr. Hoberman a GUI preview of the proposed \"07 fix (server-side only) today.  Aiming for Dr. Hoberman\"s approval by 9/8/08; will provide DLG# on 9/12/08.  Urgency reiterated.   9/15:  unknown if fix requires an outage. 9/22:  NCAL working with Epic. 10/16: Check w/Epic (Maria) about getting into Nov install; Tom will followup.  Per Maria: This code will not be available for installation in production by 11/19. 10/20: Rebecca will followup w/Epic. 10/20:  per B Yee--Dr. Hoberman was not happy that it\"s taking so long to get this fixed; however, he would be okay if we wait for the Feb \"09 downtime to install this fix.  In the meantime, Rx will continue to remind our users of the proper workaround to avoid this issue.10/23: Rebecca will followup w/Epic on whether fix is in NOV KPKG. 10/27: Chris (Epic) will followup w/Maria.\r\n11/03: Per Kelly - Need fix NLT 12/5 for testing. Apoorva(Epic) will followup with Maria.\r\n11/6:  Per Epic, fix will be delievered 12/1.\r\n11/10:  full outage unknown, Kpkg unknown.\r\n12/3:  File received.','\"When discontinuing or modifying an order for reasons purely related to pharmacy-only workflows such as \"\"Pharmacist Product Change\"\", the Pharmacist MUST UNCHECK the box in the Related Signed and Held Order in the Confirm Action box.  Minh Nguyen has sent a communication to alert Rx staff. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"When discontinuing or modifying an order for reasons purely related to pharmacy-only workflows such as \"\"Pharmacist Product Change\"\", the Pharmacist MUST UNCHECK the box in the Related Signed and Held Order in the Confirm Action box.  Minh Nguyen has sent a communication to alert Rx staff. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"7/2/08:  Concern:  Patient medication error--patient may not receive discharge meds. Risk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Brian Hoberman.  Problem Discovered by:   N