ULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108 \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759764\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4231):  \n  SP’07 C7503903 7/11/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9/25:  Installed in production. Grayed. ','SP07 with SU-C7503634 installed:   Documented allergens may be overwritten in Allergies section of navigator.  Note that the affected SU is included in the July K-package, but has also been previously released as a dependency for other adhocs. \r\n\"Description:  Allergy information documented in the Allergies section of a navigator may be overwritten and no longer available for interaction checking.  This can happen if SU C7503634 / I757514 is installed.  The Allergies Activity still displays the correct information, however.\r\nExample workflow:\r\nOpen the Allergies navigator section for a patient with more than one allergy.\r\nClick to select one allergy. \r\nWithout changing any data, click to select a second allergy.\r\nEven though no change was made for the first allergy, a prompt displays asking whether to save the changes for the first allergy.\r\nIf Yes is clicked, the second allergy is overwritten by the information from the first allergy. \r\nThe patient now has two entries for the first allergy and no entry for the second allergy. \r\nThe user also cannot add allergies using the navigator section unless the section is closed and reopened. If the user tries to add an allergy (including the overwritten one), a message displays that the allergy is already active.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"Affected Regions:  All (when SU is installed. IP, AMB, ED, Optime. MAS to request adhoc. NCAL to determine when SU will be implemented. Epic (Jason Ramaker) will provide an (I759764) ETA by 7/11/08. 7/7:  Andre to follow up. Per Kelly, The 7/16 Manifest does not include this SU:  C7503634 as a dependency and or as an adhoc.   7/10:  Problematic SU will be a part of July Kpkg.  Fix will be needed before or with July Kpkg install. Adhoc:  4231. 7/11:  adhoc received 0711-PS-PR3548698-C7503903-E756747-Spr07Jul21NS.zip\r\n0711-PS-PR3548698-C7503903-E756747-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z  7/14:   Fix will go in with July K-pkg not as Ad-Hoc but if Ad-hoc 4114 is installed it may induce this patient sfaety issue. Theresa to follow up with who requested the adhoc installed to wits.Adhoc 4223 (contains problematic SU) will introduce this patient safety issue if installed before the fix is installed. Per Katie, waiting for kpkg. 7/18:  Per Epic-Ad hoc #4223 was sent after this issue was initially reported and does include the problematic SU (C7503634).  There are a several more recent ad hocs which will include this SU, but also include the fix SU (C7503903).  Here\"s a summary of all the ad hocs to date which include C7503634.\r\nIncludes both C7503634 and C7503903 (fix):\r\n(Ad hoc# - Delivery date)\r\n4209 - 7/16 (scheduled)\r\n4124 - 7/14\r\n4231 - 7/11\r\nIncludes C7503634 without fix:\r\n4223 - 7/9\r\n3945 - 7/2\r\n4193 - 6/26\r\n4173 - 6/18\r\n4114 - 5/30\r\nPer Theresa:: The issue fixed by the code described below will be introduced by ad hoc code  (0709-AP-PR3557111-C7503865-E756655-Spr07Jul21NS.zip and 0709-AP-PR3557111-C7503865-E756655-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z) being installed tonite into WITS2 and WITS3.   The code being installed has a dependency [C7503634/I757514] which introduces the issue.  Once this ad hoc is installed and verified, Andre Mure will replicate the issue and send notification regarding replication.   If replicated this ad hoc can then be installed into WITS2 and WITS3.  As a note to all if a determination is made to install the ad hoc  4223 which introduces the issue prior to September, this ad hoc 4231 will also need to be installed to prod. 7/21:  Andre has not yet been able to replicate-will continue and try to replicate in WITS 2&3. 7/24:  Andre & Arturo unable to replicate issue. Andre to follow up with Jason R from Epic regarding replication. Kelly notified to hold off on installing problematic adhoc (Kelly has informed SCAL and Bryan Yagar). 7/28:  per Andre:  replicated in WITS 3, need to proceed with testing adhoc.  7/31: Andre working with Epic on testing.  AMB looking to use code that introduces problem. Fix to be installed in WITS3. 7/31:  Both fixes have to go to CAB at the same time.  Aiming for Sept install. 8/4:  testing to start 8/8.  8/11:  Installed in WITS3. 8/18:  Testing in progress. 8/21:  Passed testing. Sched for 8/25 CAB.  9/18:  Scheduled for install 9/25 along with PRL. 9/25:  Installed in production. Grayed. \"\r\n','\" Two choices:  \r\n1. Do not install SU C7503634 (I757514) until the fix for this problem is received.\r\n2. Disable the edit functionality of the Allergies section of the navigator.  This is the recommended workaround, the one implemented by MAS.  \"\r\n',NULL,'\" Two choices:  \r\n1. Do not install SU C7503634 (I757514) until the fix for this problem is received.\r\n2. Disable the edit functionality of the Allergies section of the navigator.  This is the recommended workaround, the one implemented by MAS.  \"\r\n',NULL,'\"Concern:  Allergy info for a patient may appear incorrectly or lost. Risk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Allan Rogers.  Problem Discovered by:   Another Epic client.  Epic Representative / email address:  Jason Ramaker / jramaker@epicsystems.com.  \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 12:37:00','2008-10-28 01:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(76,3560389,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Potential Patient Safety SLG#288985: Release Interval Displays Incorrect in Order Review When Free Text Interval Is Changed','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ED, IP, Rx, Optime, Beacon,','','',NULL,'2008-07-08 08:04:16','2008-07-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Wiesenthal','',NULL,'','sp04-sp07','','','','','','','K011909','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9','M',NULL,'JUL08','N','L','N','N',' ','N','S',NULL,'Clo',NULL,NULL,NULL,'M','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',60,'2009-04-09 15:01:32',NULL,'Infrastructure Software','PART KPHC','NOTES:  confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I765642 & I7510220\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757715 & C75031171\nRISK RANKING:  9','KPHC Environment','Patient Safety issue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/12:  per Johnette / JAngel--fix in production, can close. ','Potential Patient Safety Issue Reported By EPIC: SLG#288985: PSE - Release Interval Displays Incorrect in Order Review When Free Text Interval Is Changed',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'04/24/09:  Code fix E757715, C75031171, DLG I7510220 installed on 2/21/09 - recommend asking AMB and IP to verify and then close \r\nNO CURRENT IMPACT.  AMB orders--could affect Inpatient, ED, OpTime, Beacon. Jason from Epic will run another query to possibly identify any historical orders that may have been affected by this issue (not expected to find any.).  Epic working on a long-term fix that will be a part of the Sept. Kpkg. 7/10:  Tom to follow up with AMB (notifying about not changing settings until fix in place). 7/24:  Carol has been notified and is aware about not changing settings. 7/28:  waiting for Kpkg.  7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic to find out which Kpkg fix will be in. 9/29:  Waiting for Nov Kpkg. 11/10: Believed to be in Jan KPKG.  Rebecca will confirm.\r\nTEST123','None\r\n',NULL,'None\r\n',NULL,'\"Regions Affected:  No current impact due to no region having the required settings.   Concern:  Manually modified release intervals for orders might revert back to the default, resulting in release intervals other than what the provider intended. Suites Affected:    AMB orders--could affect Inpatient, ED, OpTime, Beacon.  Risk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Andy Weisenthal.  Problem Discovered by:  Epic testing.  Epic Representative / email address:  Jason Ramaker / jramaker@epicsystems.com.  Remediation: Epic has run a query to identify affected regions.  No region has the settings necessary to allow the issue to manifest.  Epic (Jason) will run another query to identify possibly affected historical orders, although it is unlikely any will be discovered, as such orders would have required settings in the past different from those today. Epic is working on a long term fix; expectation is the fix will be in the September K-package.  No region has asked for an adhoc.   PART will track progress of the fix. \r\n\r\n\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'1215529575?Z236766?Robin R Dugan\n\nAffected Products\nEpicCare Ambulatory, EpicCare Inpatient, ASAP, Specialties, EpicLab, EpicWeb, OpTime\n \nAffected Versions\nSpring 2008\nSpring 2007\nSpring 2006\nSummer 2005\nSpring 2005\nFall 2004\nSummer 2004\n \nProblem Summary\nWe have identified a scenario where Order Review and/or Order Inquiry (EpicLab) displays the incorrect release interval for standing orders. This can lead to confusion about when instances of procedures should be released.\n \nAll of the following must be true in order to be affected by this issue:\n(A)  You place outpatient-mode orders\n(B)  You place both auto-release and manual-release standing orders\n(C)  You allow free text intervals for manual-release standing orders\n(D)  You have procedures and/or procedure categories that default in the following:\n(1)  Status: Standing\n(2)  Release: Manual\n(3)  Interval: <any value>\n \nA procedure or procedure category record can be set to have a default status of standing and a discrete release i',736,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 12:45:00','2009-05-12 11:01:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(77,3562378,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient - Start times not updated in Arrival Navigator, if specific code fix has been installed',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-07 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4337','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'TD31230','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  This fix to be released before the end of August is a dependency of another SU (I758993)\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758893\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008 -E757255\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 - Closed, adhoc 4337 TD31230 installed on 9/25 and verified.  ','SP\"07 Inpatient - Start times not updated in Arrival Navigator, if specific code fix has been installed\r\n\"Description:    The start date and time of signed and held orders may not be updated when the orders are released from Arrival Navigator.  This problem occurs only if Epic code fix DLG I757560 (E755790) has been installed.\r\nThis issue only occurs if DLG I757560 (E755790) has been installed.  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NO CURRENT IMPACT.  IP- SP\"07. Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a Kpackage.     7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic to find out which Kpkg fix will be in.8/28:   Fix will be Nov Kpkg. NCAL will wait for Kpkg. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 12:59:00','2009-04-14 02:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(78,3577341,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Allergy alerts may not fire correctly',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-15 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers',NULL,NULL,'4240','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0911-AP-PR3577341-E756905-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z\r\n','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'7',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  National finishing testing as of 10/27/08; code should be installed within 3 weeks ( end of Nov). After code install and FDB load is complete, then cleanup.Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759822\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4240):  \n  SP’07 E756905 9/11/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008\nRISK RANKING:  7',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/8: Per Sylvia Fong\'s 6/4 email allergens are being looked at weekly and working with FDB and Epic to run searches for NCAL and SCAL.  Weekly searches will continue.','SP\'07 - Allergy alerts may not fire correctly \r\nDescription:   Due to an FDB data load issue introduced by SP\'07 code, allergy alerts may not fire or may fire incorrectly.  Specifically, ELG items 500 (Primary Allergen Groups) and 505 (Cross Sensitivity Groups), and 450 (multiple item type - Nddf\\g-standard Identifiers) do not load correctly, causing alerts to misfire.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/29/09:  per BYee, original issue is closed, clean-up utility not yet correct.  Greying out, closing.  \r\n5/29/09:  per BYee, Technically, PART Issue 3577341 should be closed.  There was a clean up step that we wanted to use a utility but that never worked for any of the regions.  Currently each region now has to work with their Epic TS to run reports and manually fix the records on an ongoing basis. (but the original issue itself is fixed).  Per BYee 1/27: The RA is being tested before run in Production.  I?ll let you know when it is all said and done.RA 1553 approved by Zheng Huang (1/15).  Per BY: The fix will be loaded into PROD by National on 11/25/08.  NCAL remediation is already finished.\r\nAll Regions.  IP, AMB, Rx, OpTime, ED, Beacon. Adhoc authorized by Kevin Isbell (4240).  Workaround in place, but doesn\"t completely cover the issue.   7/17 Per Syliva Fong eta for fix about 2 weeks away. Ad Hoc has been approved. 7/21:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic regarding ETA.  7/28:  per Sylvia Fong.  the fix had to be changed after Epic understood what the problem was.  Epic needs validation from FDB--the original fix would have caused too many false positives.  No eta at this point, Michael Bries is the epic contact.   7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic regarding ETA.  Sent email to Sylvia, waiting for response. 8/3/08:  Per Sylvia,  continuing to run weekly reports after the FDB load to check for new missing allergens. 8/4: Epic still developing fix.  9/11: File Received. 9/18:  Tom to follow up with Rx regarding adhoc testing as well as Theresa. 9/22: Nat\"l team following up with Epic.  9/25:  Per Bill Yee, Nat\"l testing code fix/working with Epic. 9/29:  Per Sylvia, workaround still in place (weekly batch job is still being run). Adhoc received and currently in testing phase. 10/16: Confirm testing status w/Sylvia.  Per Sylvia:  still in testing. 10/20: Kelly sent email re: all region install. 10/23:  Per Sylvia & Michael B (Epic) emails:  The ad hoc is not a sync package and can be taken by the region with their next outage.10/23: Followup on whether it will be in 11/19 install.Theresa will talk to Bill Yee or Cheryl Tran today; Email sent. 10/26:  All Regions currently impacted byt this PS issue. Once National installs this code fix in PRODNAM and runs the full FDB load for ELG , this issue should be resolved for ALL regions. NCAL and or any other regions can install this code fix at a later date.  National should let NCAL know when they plan to install this code fix into PRODNAM. 10/27: Followup w/Sylvia (Kelly) for a date. Code fix should be installed within 3 weeks into PRODNAM. After code is installed and FDB load is completed, cleanup is the next step.  Bill Yee to work with PART regarding cleanup <important>. 10/30: Waiting for Rx to coordinate installation of fix with Regions. 11/03: Timing will be determined by Nat\"l Pharmacy. Workaround is airtight. 11/10: Followup w/Bill Yee on timeframe.11/13: Timeframe UNK for fix.  Natl waiting for Regional input.  11/19:  Per BY: The fix will be loaded into PROD by National on 11/25/08.  NCAL remediation is already finished.\r\n','\"Workaround(s):  Until the fix is installed, a full (not incremental) database load of the FDB DAM (Drug Allergy Module) will be run in PRODNAM on a weekly basis.  With this workaround, 106 records were not corrected & 120,000 messages were created. National Intraconnect (Kevin Isbell) performed the workaround by 5pm PST 7/14/08.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Workaround(s):  Until the fix is installed, a full (not incremental) database load of the FDB DAM (Drug Allergy Module) will be run in PRODNAM on a weekly basis.  With this workaround, 106 records were not corrected & 120,000 messages were created. National Intraconnect (Kevin Isbell) performed the workaround by 5pm PST 7/14/08.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'4/2  per B Yee:  The fix is installed but the clean up utility did not work (see below) and then this ticket got over shadowed by PART #4245688.  In any case, this utility was built to clean up patients with the bad allergens attached.  (Right now the bad allergens just fire nuisance alerts so the clean up is a lower priority)\r\nNCAL has 115 patients affected and instead of trying to fix the utility I will ask our team to manually fix these patient (No ETA since it\'s a lower priority task at this time).\r\n\r\nConcern:  If a clinician administers to a patient without realizing that the allergy alert may be incorrect, patient care could be impacted. Risk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Allan Rogers. Problem Discovered by:   SCAL.  Epic Representative / email address:  Michael Breis / MBreis@epicsystems.com.  Remediation: From a list of selected ELG (allergen) records provided by Epic (Michael Breis), National Pharmacy (Elissa Liong) will identify those medications or medication components with potential impact for harm and prepare a list for regional review. Action items (immediate):  Adhoc authorized by Kevin Isbell.  Epic will provide an ETA for a code fix (I759822/E756905; No Outage Needed) by 7/16/08.  Action items (future):   Epic to run queries to identify patients that may have incorrect orders, and to identify orders that may contain affected ELGs.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:04:00','2009-06-08 01:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(79,3600433,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Defaulted order sets are duplicated and show  incorrect medication amounts, including delivery',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-21 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','N','S','F','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Epic recommends that the older impacted method of copying order sets not be used; instead they recommend the newer approach.  Per Epic, NCAL changed to newer method,but Exempla still wants the fix. Epic confirmed that other KP regions will not use impacted method in future; Both E & C fix found in K111008 but not under this dlg or PR\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510978\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4260):  \n  SP’07 C75031073 & E757251 9/19/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'04/14/09 - Closing - Code installed in prod fixed with configuration.  ','Defaulted order sets are duplicated and show  incorrect medication amounts, including delivery\r\n\"Defaulted order sets are duplicated and show incorrect medication amounts, including delivery.  Multiple anesthesiologists in Hayward reported that for orders saved as defaults and later accessed, duplicate orders were created.  In some cases, the order set dosages were changed.  The example given was for Torodol, as an anesthesia PACU order set.  Trudy David was able to replicate in at least two NCAL deployments.  It took 3 hours for the oncall Epic rep to access KPHC.  \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL.  IP (Anesthesiology).  Adhoc 4260.  Workaround in place. Tom to follow up with Rosalba regarding Epic\"s query.  7/22:  Two phone reconvenes today to clarify issue and develop workaround.  Dr. Hoberman wants security point 160 replaced with 193, testing now.  Dr. H wants hyperlink relabeled \"Do not click\".  Epic developing a query to identify corrupted order sets. 7/24:  Sent email to Rosalba regarding query status.  7/28:  Per Rosalba, results under review. 7/31:   Per Epic (Maria Spinozzi) - the source log of this issue has been determined to be DLG I756953 / package C7503472.   7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic to find out which Kpkg fix will be in. 8/7:  Maria to send updates by Monday (8/11).  8/14:  No remediation needed. 8/28:  No longer need fix because configuration has changed. Targeting November Kpkg. \r\n','Remove security point to prevent user level copying. \r\n',NULL,'Remove security point to prevent user level copying. \r\n',NULL,'\"Concern:  Patients potentially could be administered incorrect medication dosages. Risk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Hoberman.  Problem Discovered by:  NCAL in production.  Epic Representative / email address:  Dan Gruett / dgruett@epicsystems.com,  Maria Spinozzi / mspinozz@epicsystems.com.  Remediation:  Based on Epic queries.  Corrupted order sets have been manually removed by Trudy David.  Affected Applications:  Anesthesiology      04/14/09:  per SWQ - fix is C75031076,RN 155968\r\nEpic has confirmed this is a code problem, and is researching. It is suspected that the error is related to 7/16 install; Epic to verify. Adhoc 4260 was authorized by Dr. David Bliss, but there is no ETA for the fix at this time.  \r\nSecurity point 160 has been replaced by security point 193.  Security point 160 allows users to use the ?save default order sets hyperlink? and security point 193 allows users to use the ?edit order sets hyperlink.?  The hyperlink for security point 160 will be renamed ?Do Not Click Me,? so users will not use that hyperlink.  \r\nWith the hyperlink ?edit order sets?active and used as a part of the workaround, NCAL will restore ability to use the hyperlink ?save default order sets.? Using the ?edit order sets? hyperlink will not cause corrupt records.\r\nEpic?s query identified 26 affected order sets in NCAL that have been deleted by Trudy David.  Epic is to run a query to see if any of the 26 affected order sets were corrupted before July 16, 2008.  Those results will be sent to Rosalba Carrillo-Vassel.  \r\nEpic Reps:  Jason Eigsei & Maria Spinozzi \r\nRisk Assessment:  Severe, Frequent, Limited (Assigned by Dr. Brian Hoberman)\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:10:00','2009-04-15 08:47:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(80,3623288,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'In Med Doc navigator, reviewing medications using ALT+R shortcut may replace Sig under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-29 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','su05-sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510200\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757392\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/20: Per Andre Mure OK to close.','Inpatient / AMB / ED:  SU05->SP07:  In Med Doc navigator, reviewing medications using ALT+R shortcut may replace Sig under specific circumstances.\r\nIf the user is using free text sigs and adds a historic or patient-reported medication to the Medication Documentation navigator section, edits the default sig, and then reviews the medications list by using the ALT+R shortcut without leaving the field, the default sig replaces the modified sig. If there wasn\"t a default sig, the text ?None Entered? replaces the user\"s sig. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09:  in prod asking Andre Mure to verify RN 158771\r\nAndre Mure will investigate whether ALT+R shortcut is used in NCAL.  7/31:  Andre to follow up. 8/4:  Andre to try to replicate. 8/14:  Andre waiting for Epic for assistance in replicating issue. Unable to located any users that use the shortcut (in Sac facility). 8/18:  Andre replicated issue.  This workflow is not being taught in training. 8/21:  Review method is used rather than shortcut. 9/17:  Epic is testing fix. No ETA. Next status-10/1/08. 9/29:  Waiting for Kpkg. 10/16: Waiting for Nov Kpkg\r\n','Click \"Review\" instead of ALT + R shortcut, to review medication documentation.  This must be communicated to facilities where ALT + R shortcut is used. \r\n',NULL,'Click \"Review\" instead of ALT + R shortcut, to review medication documentation.  This must be communicated to facilities where ALT + R shortcut is used. \r\n',NULL,'If ALT+R shortcut is used, communication must be set to facilities to use \"Review\" button instead.  No ETA for fix, no adhoc requested. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:14:00','2009-04-20 10:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(81,3620187,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Reordered meds may not appear as current ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-28 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','Y','S','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Fix on track for early Oct; server outage likely; dont know what version fix is standard in, but all regions targeting SP07 fix\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510483\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008- E757392\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 fix in prod - current config settings prevent problem and notified Aditi Vakil ','SP\"07 - SCAL only - Reordered medications may not appear as current medications, under certain circumstances\r\n\"A reordered medication may be given an end date so far in the future (e.g., 2176) that it does not appear in the current medications list in Chart Review or other medication views such as SnapShot, various SmartLinks, and certain Print Groups.\r\nThe future end date for the reordered medication occurs if both of the following conditions are in place:\r\nThe original order has an end date but no start date\r\nThe system definition setting for \"\"Copy End Date for Reorder\"\" is set to null or 1-Yes.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'only SCAL affected.  NCAL NOT AFFECTED due to current config settings (= airtight workaround).   7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic to find out which Kpkg fix will be in. 8/7:  Epic status update-8/17. 9/25:  Waiting for Nov Kpkg. \r\n','Current config settings in NCAL are airtight workaround. \r\n',NULL,'Current config settings in NCAL are airtight workaround. \r\n',NULL,'Waiting for fix K-package info. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:17:00','2009-04-16 10:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(82,3626555,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Edited diagnosis not saved properly from certain Navigator sections',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, OPT, ED, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-30 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','sp08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   fix standard in SP08 IU5 so will not impact KP: closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I765701\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 Closed, no impact will be tested with Sum09 testing','NO CURRENT IMPACT - SP\"08 - Edited diagnosis not saved properly from certain Navigator sections\r\n\"Description:   Changes to diagnoses that have been edited in certain navigators may not be saved.  This can occur if both of the following conditions are in place:\r\nThe diagnosis is edited by typing over a previous entry.\r\nCertain navigators with diagnosis sections are used (27031-SEC_ER_DIAGNOSES or 55100-SEC_MR_DIAGNOSES_WITH_STAGING or duplicates).\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - IP, AMB, ED, OPT. Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a Kpackage. 7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic to find out which Kpkg fix will be in.  8/7:  Epic status update-9/3. 9/22:  Waiting for Nov kpkg. 4/14/09:  Fix dlg I765701, E760663 Spr08.  ','',NULL,'',NULL,'Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:19:00','2009-04-14 03:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(84,3461169,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'In a specific workflow, meds ordered thru the discharge navigator, signed and released,  then discontinued may be dispensed to patient',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-03 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','A','M','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  The code fix for this issue is coming from EDI/interfaces and not inpatient. I believe the fix is that NCALs custom interface will be removed and they will revert back to the standard interface.\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed 11/19/2008.  Gray out. ','(Config issue) In a specific workflow, meds ordered thru the discharge navigator, signed and released,  then discontinued may be dispensed to patient. \r\n\" In the discharge navigator for a hospital encounter, for discharge medications previously released to the Pharmacy, if a provider wishes to discontinue (DC) a med, s/he can go to the Action Menu and click on Medications, then discontinue the med.   If the order is signed / held, the DC will occur as expected; however, if the order is signed / released, PIMS will autoreject with a UD (undelivered discontinue) message to the interface.  In the latter case, PIMS is expecting the discontinuing provider name in the ORD-10 record and it is null.   The order will not be discontinued and the provider will not be notified.  The med will be available for pick-up by the discharged patient.  \r\nThis issue has been replicated by Susan Taylor in both the WITS and production environments.  It is apparently caused by configuration code between PIMS and the interface.   In NCAL, the PIMS error has appeared in the logs upwards to 100 times / day, although not all occurrences of the error are due to this particular workflow problem.  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Lisa Pfeifer is working with Epic to determine if config chg needed.  6/5/08: AMB is working with Epic.  Susan to start an email chain regarding where error messages are originating. Configuration is an interface change that is owned by AMB.  NCAL bridge to be set for a time to gain additional information. 6/9:  Per Rosalba,  Jansin to review with Lisa  before reconvening additional bridge.  6/12:  Jansin working with Epic. Workflow errors have been found.  6/19:  Dhea to follow up with Jansin. Susan to follow up with Tony.  Dr. Bliss to follow up with Rosalba. 6/23:  Brian to review report regarding \"1 days worth\" of errors. 6/24:  per Brian G:  After checking the reports, we found that NO orders were dispensed AFTER the DC was done. It appears that items on the report are OLD orders that were being DC\"d during MedRecon in the Discharge Navigator - which had originated from a prior admission. 6/30:  Per Rosalba, This is on hold until after 7/16.  Tom to follow up with Brian and find out how many days were reviewed. Tom to follow up with Susan.  7/10:  Per Toni Jetti, this is not a critical issue at this time. 7/17 David O to follow up w/ Rosalba.  7/18:  Per Rosalba, a change was made in production that will reduce the amount of rejects.  Rosalba requested Brian to get a recent (after 7/16) log of rejects.  7/24:  Per Brian, For the time period 7/16-7/20 there are 641 UD (Unable to DC) messages due to MISSING ENTERED BY PROVIDER reason. 7/28:  per Rosalba,\"I am not comfortable with the number of rejects - this is still a high number to be dealt with manually.   We do need to do another round of analysis to confirm the root cause of the rejects   From the previous round, we do know that there are a couple of valid IP workflows that were causing the bulk of the rejects - we might need to change the PIMS logic so these cases do not reject.\"    7/31:  Sent email requesting status to Rosalba & Toni.  8/7:  Bill to follow up with Toni.  8/14: Research reveals error fall in several categories.  Epic will work on fix. Email summary from Rosalba received.   8/18: workaround in place but do need to address causes of errors. 8/21:  Tom to follow up with Rosalba for an update from workgroup meeting. 8/24:  Per Rosalba, an additional meeting was needed and has been re-scheduled. 9/3: per Rosalba, Jansin, Maria Spinozzi and Rosalba reviewed the proposed logic changes, Maria has updated the changes document and sent to Jansin for review.  Next steps: 1) Jansin to review the updated document and provide feedback to Maria  2) After Jansin approves changes, Rosalba to schedule meeting with PIMS, Bridges to discuss testing, implementation timelines.  9/18:  Tom to follow up with Rosalba-request status.  9/26: note resent to Rosalba requesting status.  9/26: per Jansin: \"Rosalba and I along with the pharmacy IT and business have discussed this and came up with a proposal.  Epic is making modifications but we have not received the change yet.\" 10/9/08:  per Jansin via Johnette: \"Epic delivered the fix.  Susan Taylor is in process of testing\" 10/16:per Susan T:  shooting for this to go with the November Release Cab.  I will be testing it over the next weeks.  The fix itself only takes a few minutes, however the regression aspect should take another week.   This is a interface change, want to give it extra attention. The fix is RA553 - Backout of RA448. 10/22:  Sent email to susan requesting status. 10/22:  Per Susan, The RA553 was delivered and tested and is on Jansin plate for approval.  The first testing round was denied by her and we have sent additional data for her approval. 11/12:  Per Jansin,  targetting to install during the December release (12/10).  \r\n\r\n','None identified\r\n',NULL,'None identified\r\n',NULL,'Lisa Pfeifer is reviewing the affected RA.  She will work with Kristie Reimer from Epic to determine why the config was originally set up as it was.  If a config change is determined necessary to correct, the change will be owned by AMB.  Fix is a config change.  No code change forthcoming from Epic.  Epic will work with Lisa / AMB until issue is resolved.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:43:00','2008-11-21 12:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(85,3473000,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'When placing additional orders from a Navigator Order Section, there is a specific workflow under which changes made to a medication order?s dose units may not be saved. This problem only occurs for orders when all three of the conditions are met',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, RX, ED, OPT','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-06 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K090908',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in Sept K\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759416\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 C7503899 available 7/14/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K090908-C7503899\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CLOSED per Kelly / Bill Yee 12/9/2008 Waiting for Sept Kpkg (confirmed).  No Current Impact since affected setup is not used by NCAL.  ','When placing additional orders from a Navigator Order Section, there is a specific workflow under which changes made to a medication order?s dose units may not be saved. This problem only occurs for orders when all three of the conditions are met\r\n\"Description: This problem only occurs for orders where all three of the following conditions are met:\r\nOrder Composer automatically opens when the order is entered\r\nOrder has multiple allowed order units\r\nOrder has a Required field which hasn?t been addressed\r\n When these conditions occur, changes to the order?s dose units are not saved during the workflow below:\r\nFrom an Navigator order section, enter an order using the ?Search for Orders? field. \r\nClick on the Dose field and update the dose amount. (Note: In order to recreate the problem, you cannot click on any other field prior to the Dose field after entering the order.)\r\nClick on (or tab to) the unit field, and change the units to something other than what was defaulted.\r\nClick on (or tab to) another field in the composer.\r\nAt this point the order?s dose units appear to have been updated.  However, when signing or closing the order composer section the dose units will revert back to what was originally defaulted.\r\nConcern:  Wrong dosage could be administered.  \r\nRisk Assignment Made by:  Dr .Wiesenthal  \r\nRemediation: None discussed\r\nAction items: Regions to check settings  \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, Exempla.  IP,Rx, OpTime ED.  Regions are to check settings.  6/9: Andre to follow up with IP,ED.  6/12:  Current workflow causes issue to occur, but is rarely used.  Andre to follow up.  Tom to follow up with Yolanda regarding workaround. 6/13: per YL and Aditi: NCAL doesn\"t have the setup of order composer opening automatically- so this issue doesn\"t affect us. 6/17:  Per Epic (Gary Hartman), fix ETA 7/18/08 (if wanted). 6/19:  Will wait for Kpkg. 7/15/08:  Fix will be in Sept Kpkg (adhoc available, but NCAL will wait for Kpkg). 9/18: Waiting for Sept Kpkg (Confirmed).   \r\n','\"Prior to installing  a fix, one of following workarounds can be used to prevent this issue from occurring.\r\nChange the profile so that the Order Composer is never opened automatically (Profiles (LPR)> Medication, Allergy, Imm, etc.>Display in Order Entry>Medication-Specific Display in Order Entry) , or\r\nTrain the users to always press Enter after entering a dose unit and/or use the drop down list to select the dose unit.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Prior to installing  a fix, one of following workarounds can be used to prevent this issue from occurring.\r\nChange the profile so that the Order Composer is never opened automatically (Profiles (LPR)> Medication, Allergy, Imm, etc.>Display in Order Entry>Medication-Specific Display in Order Entry) , or\r\nTrain the users to always press Enter after entering a dose unit and/or use the drop down list to select the dose unit.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'Problem Discovered by: Epic Client. Epic Representative / email address: Greg Hartman <ghartman@epicsystems.com>. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:46:00','2008-12-09 03:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(87,3486492,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'User-printed Nursing Snapshot reports may contain incorrect patient order information',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, RX, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-12 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K090908',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759491\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 E756697 available as of 7/11/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756697\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CLOSED per Kelly / Bill Yee 12/09/2008  Waiting for Sept Kpkg.  NCAL does not use affected workflow.  ','SP\"07 - User-printed Nursing Snapshot reports may contain incorrect patient order information\r\n\"Description:  When printed from a server, Nursing Snapshot (a.k.a. Kardex, or PER) reports may display order information for the wrong patient.  Follow up will be performed to verify NCAL does not have this programming point (LPP34351) set up.  NCAL users are not trained with this specified workflow. Issue occurs if the reports are printed from ?hyperlink? and does not occur if the reports are printed from the ?client.?\r\nThe problem is illustrated in the following workflow:\r\nInitiate a server print of the Nursing Snapshot report for patient A.  This step may be done from either of the following: \r\n- the Patient Report option from Patient Lists (using a copy of print group 46665-  \r\n   IP Print Report from Hyperlink)\r\n- a customized Hyperspace menu record (copy of E2N 34675-\r\n   IP_IT_MAR_ALLSECTIONS).\r\nRepeat step 1 for one or more different patients.\r\nRepeat step 1 for patient A.  Orders from the other patients may appear on patient A\"s report.\r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Andy Wiesenthal\r\nRemediation:  None discussed\r\nAction items (immediate):  Verify NCAL does not have specified programming point set up. \r\nAction items (future):   Epic will provide a code fix ETA by 6/18/08.  \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'(Potentially) NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, CO, and Exempla.  Inpatient, Pharmacy, ED.  Epic will provide code ETA 6/18/08. Does NCAL have programming point set up (if not then NCAL is not affected).  6/17:  Per Ryan Lambert, NCAL does not use this workflow. 6/19:  David to follow up with Rebecca regarding Kpkg. (sent email). 6/23:  Rebecca to provide an update 6/24. 7/2: Fix will be in Jul Kpkg (090908). Adhoc has not been requested-if adhoc is wanted, it can be ready by 7/11. <outage info in col D>. Waiting for Jul Kpkg. 9/22:  Jul Kpkg needs to be confirmed. 10/23: Will be in the Jul KPKG per Rebecca. Waiting for July Kpkg. \r\n\r\n','Disable the caching of order information by modifying the report setup programming point.\r\n',NULL,'Disable the caching of order information by modifying the report setup programming point.\r\n',NULL,'Concern:  Nursing Snapshot (a.k.a. Kardex, or PER) reports may display order information for the wrong patient.  Problem Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing.  Epic Representative / email address:  Maria Spinozzi / MSpinozzi@epicsystems.com.  7/2:  Outage info:  You can install this Special Update while most users are on the system. Users using Order Information reports using setup LPP 34350 or 34351 might be affected during the install of this Special Update, and we strongly recommend that you install this Special Update at a time when user activity in this area is absent.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:54:00','2008-12-09 03:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(88,3493280,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Reports using certain print groups for Review Flowsheets may display data incorrectly',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-13 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','su05-sp08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K072108',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'2',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108; fix standard in SP08 IU3\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759439\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4243):  \n  SP’07 E756558 8/08/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756558\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2/2/09 - Melanie - According to previous Ambulatory response on 7/8 by Carol Devlin there is no impact to Amb. ','Reports using certain print groups for Review Flowsheets may display data incorrectly  \r\n\"Data displayed in reports using certain print groups for Review Flowsheets may appear in the wrong column and cell.  This problem occurs if both of the following conditions are in place:\r\nThe string of data retrieved for the Review Flowsheet report exceeds 32,000 bytes. Note: This limitation is for the entire flowsheet and not just a given cell or column.  Character limitations for any given cell or column cannot be defined.\r\nAt least one of these Review Flowsheet print groups is used:\r\n77200 \r\n51919\r\n51929\r\nStored data is not affected, as this is a display issue only.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CLOSED per Kelly / Bill Yee 12/09/2008  Waiting for July Kpkg.  Affected print groups not being used. \r\n\"All regions are impacted or potentially impacted.  Affects Inpatient, AMB, versions SU05 thru SP08.   6/19:  NCAL is using at least one of affected print groups. Andre M to follow up.  Kelly to follow up to find out with print group is affected. Per KR:  I spoke to Epic - Johnathan Allen.  Drew Davies ran a query for NCAL production to determine if NCAL was using the affected print groups and or reports.  Please see the attachment below and let us know the production impact.  There is a tab for each production instance within NCAL. 6/22:  Per Isaac Santos-Print groups (77200, 51919, 51929) are not used in ED. 6/23: Armando Bravo and Isaac Santos both confirmed that we are not using the print groups that may display the incorrect data in reports.  6/30:  Rebecca to follow up. 7/3:  Tom to follow up with AMB regarding print groups. 7/8:  per Carol Devlin: \"\"Per Bill Yu, we are not using 77200 or 51919.   Neither he or I were able to find #51929.\"\"  7/31:  Confirmed in July Kpkg. Waiting for July Kpkg. ','Use the Review Flowsheet activity (which is not affected) instead of the report  to view data documented in flowsheets.\r\n',NULL,'Use the Review Flowsheet activity (which is not affected) instead of the report  to view data documented in flowsheets.\r\n',NULL,'Epic (Jonathan Allen) will provide a code fix and inform PART of its ETA by 6/16/08; PART Communications (Christine Okon) will then notify regions. NW (Nick Socotch) authorized the ad hoc fix. NCAL (Kelly Ragan), SCAL (Anson Chapman), CO (Michael Dupont), and Exempla (Mark Mardis and Leslie Jagoea) will install the ad hoc or KPackage.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:56:00','2009-02-05 02:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(89,2561553,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Link to Custom History data may be lost when patient records are merged',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','I744838/E743494','',NULL,NULL,'2007-08-14 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'0710','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  NCAL test defects re merge shared with Epic. If deemed patient safety will contact PART. Confirmed in K071607\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  SP06 (I744838/E743494) and SP07 (I751798/E751503)\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’06 K071607-E743494\n  SP’07 K071607-E751503\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No further action per Dr. Bliss. 4/30/09:  Closing.  See Comments.','\"If two patient records are merged together, with at least one of the records containing custom history data, links to the custom history data (not the entire history section) may be lost during the merge.  This issue does not pertain to ChartSync.\r\n\"Regions should contact PART Communications (Sharon) if they would like to discuss this incident. Update 9/20: Need to merge and unmerge, testing to to chk with Ron Daly, due to scope.  10/22/07:  Failed testing. Rod Dayley is working with Epic (Dan).  TD25051 = test defect.  From Ted Lynch:  as to whether we plan to move forward with Merge, the response is a qualified \"yes.\"  The Physician Leadership Team agreed that we should proceed with merging the 56% of records where there is no clinical impact.  The PLT also agreed  to move forward with the proposed Inpatient solution to address the \"John Doe\" admissions, pending Brian Hoberman\"s final approval.  As for the remaining records (the 44% with clinical data), the decision was to hold off on merge those records until the recently discovered EpicCare issues were resolved.  Again, Rod can provide you with the details. 10/23/2007: from R Dayley: This is at Epic being reviewed.  We have been in communication and trying to determine whether it is a code issue or if it is related to a wrong configuration. 10/29/07:  Currently being researched. 11/5/07: Affects unmerged. 11/29/07:  Project has ended-per Don.  This row will be colored yellow.  3/3: No further action per Dr. Bliss.  3/17:  Leaving issue \"yellow\" to track. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' SU\"04 - SP\"07--NO CURRENT IMPACT--fix in July k-pckg.  Update 9/7:  K071607 in RENC, ETS is currently testing - awaiting Rod Dayley.  10/22/07:  Failed testing. Rod Dayley is working with Epic (Dan).  TD25051= test defect.  10/29/07:  Per D. Martin, currently being researched. 11/5/07:  Affects unmerged. 11/12:  per Don, testing has been postponed.  11/29/07:  Project has ended-per Don.  This row will be colored yellow. Update 1/10: Dr. Bliss to contact Jansin for an update. 1/24:  Per Dr. Bliss, it\"s a merge of clinical data.  2/25 Per Dr. Bliss-No further action needed. 3/3: No further action per Dr. Bliss.  3/17:  Leaving issue \"yellow\" to track. 8/18/08:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic regarding fix. Tom to follow up with Jan Sherman regarding merge status.  Email sent. 8/26: per Jan Sherman: \"Clinical merge is NOT a dead issue.  Two merge efforts underway: We are on track to merge MRNs without clinical data both in catchup mode (ie, those stored since the last run in Dec 2007) and then in ongoing, realtime mode.  Both will occur before the end of this year. Evan Felter has recently joined KPHC heading up the new group that will be doing clinical chart correction work.  His group will also working with the clinical data merges. There is no automatic clinical merge functionality planned for NCAL at this time - those cases will be handled on a case by case basis via Evan\"s group.\" \r\n\r\n',' The combination of the use of custom history questions and patient record merge is very rare. No regions were shown to have affected records and are thus not currently impacted.  However, all regions could be potentially impacted should they begin to use the affected functionality without implementing the recommended fix.  \r\n',NULL,' The combination of the use of custom history questions and patient record merge is very rare. No regions were shown to have affected records and are thus not currently impacted.  However, all regions could be potentially impacted should they begin to use the affected functionality without implementing the recommended fix.  \r\n',NULL,'4/30/09:  Issue has been open for a year since Dr. Bliss said no action necessary.  CLOSING.  Regions should contact PART Communications (Sharon) if they would like to discuss this incident. Update 9/20: Need to merge and unmerge, testing to to chk with Ron Daly, due to scope.  10/22/07:  Failed testing. Rod Dayley is working with Epic (Dan).  TD25051 = test defect.  From Ted Lynch:  as to whether we plan to move forward with Merge, the response is a qualified \"yes.\"  The Physician Leadership Team agreed that we should proceed with merging the 56% of records where there is no clinical impact.  The PLT also agreed  to move forward with the proposed Inpatient solution to address the \"John Doe\" admissions, pending Brian Hoberman\"s final approval.  As for the remaining records (the 44% with clinical data), the decision was to hold off on merge those records until the recently discovered EpicCare issues were resolved.  Again, Rod can provide you with the details. 10/23/2007: from R Dayley: This is at Epic being reviewed.  We have been in communication and trying to determine whether it is a code issue or if it is related to a wrong configuration. 10/29/07:  Currently being researched. 11/5/07: Affects unmerged. 11/29/07:  Project has ended-per Don.  This row will be colored yellow.  3/3: No further action per Dr. Bliss.  3/17:  Leaving issue \"yellow\" to track. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 01:58:00','2009-04-30 04:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(90,3507311,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Notes added manually to Patient Instructions navigator section may be overwritten by SmartSet default Patient Instructions, in specific conditions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SP07','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4257','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0109-AP-PR3507311-E757978-C75031247-Spr07Jan19NS.zip\r\n0109-AP-PR3507311-E757978-C75031247-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','N','L','P','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510825\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4257):  \n  SP’07 E757978 & C75031247 1/09/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757978 & C75031247\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Issue resolved (per AMB).','\"SP?07 - AMB - Notes added manually to Patient Instructions navigator section may be overwritten by SmartSet default Patient Instructions, in specific conditions\r\n\"\"Description:   Notes entered manually to the Patient Instructions section in a navigator may be overwritten by defaulted SmartSet Patient Instructions or combined (using PRL converted SmartSets) with defaulted or manually added SmarSet Patient Instructions. This occurs if all of the following conditions are in place and either of the following two workflows are used: \r\n\r\nConditions:\r\nThe SmartSet is defaulted to include Patient Instructions or the user checks the Patient Instructions in the SmartSet; \r\nThe SmartSet is LGQ based (Workflows #1&2) or PRL based (workflow #3);\r\nRTF formatting is enabled for the Patient Instructions;\r\nThe user has documented in the Patient Instructions section of the Visit Navigator and does not close the Patient Instruction section before accessing the SmartSet . \r\nWorkflow #1 (Single User):\r\nA Provider documents in the Patient Instructions section in a navigator and leaves that section open.\r\nWithout closing the section, the Provider places an order through the Order Entry activity.  \r\nThe order triggers a BPA with a link to a SmartSet that contains defaulted Patient Instructions.  \r\nThe Provider accesses that SmartSet or checks the Patient Instruction section of the Smart Set, and signs.  In a similar workflow, the Provider may access a SmartSet with default Patient Instructions directly from Order Entry without submitting an order. \r\nThe manually entered Patient Instructions in the navigator section are replaced by the SmartSet\"s Patient Instructions and are not saved.\r\nWorkflow #2 (PRL SmartSets)\r\nA Provider documents in the Patient Instructions section in a navigator and leaves that section open.\r\nWithout closing the section, the Provider places an order through the Order Entry activity.\r\nThe order triggers a BPA with a link to a PRL converted SmartSet that contains defaulted Patient Instructions.   \r\nThe Provider accesses that SmartSet or checks the Patient Instruction section of the Smart Set, and signs.  In a similar workflow, the Provider may access a PRL converted SmartSet with defaulted Patient Instructions directly from Order Entry without submitting an order. \r\nThe manually entered Patient Instructions in the navigator section are combined with the SmartSet\"s default or added Patient Instructions. \r\n\"\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Dan Bailey) will provide a code fix for SP\"07 and inform PART of its ETA by 6/27/08.PRL conversion of SmartSets resolves the problem identified in Workflows #1 but introduces a second problem described in Workflow #2. 6/23:  Dan Bailey to provide search results by 6/27. AMB able to replicate workflow #2, but unable to replicate workflow #1.  6/30:  Per Apoorva, workflow #2 is not a patient safety issue. Per Epic search provided by Dan, NCAL is affected. Tom to follow up with AMB if NCAL has VPA (also, can be manually entered defaults).  NCAL is not affected once PRL is implemented. 7/8:  per Carol Devlin: We don\"t use BPAs in order entry.  Our BPAs are used outside of Order Entry so this issue isn\"t a problem for No Cal. 7/10: Re-discuss this issue on monday with Apoorva. 7/14:  Can any smart set w/ defaulted instuctions affect this issue? To follow up w/ Carol Devlin. Sent email to Carol. 7/16/08:  Comments regarding additional workflow in col. D. 7/18:  Per Carol, AMB was able to replicate the issue using the additional workflow described by Apoorva (listed in col. D on 7/16). 7/21:  Requesting adhoc-authorized by Dr. Bliss. Adhoc 4257 created.  7/28:  Tom to follow up with Carol if this workflow is often used. 7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic for ETA. Sent Carol email regarding golive and users using this workflow. 8/1: per CD \"I spoke with Phil Peabody who is with Ambulatory training about the information that is taught regarding patient instructions and smartsets.  He said that per the training manual the sections of a smartset are covered very generically.   Based on what Phil said, it doesn\"t sound like workflows are taught with regards to smartsets and that the focus is on the functionality\".  8/4: Doesn\"t sound like AMB uses workflow.   8/28: PRL install delayed - date unsure. 9/18:  Verify issue does not exist after PRL install. 9/25:  Waiting for AMB to verify. 10/6:  Issue found with LGQ subsets. Still in testing. Johnette to follow up.  10/16:  per Johnette, issue is resolved--fix confirmed in prod, LGQ subsets are not an issue.  Greying out row. \r\n','\"To ensure that changes are saved, close the Patient Instructions section before accessing SmartSets.\r\nDo not use Rich Text Formatting (RTF) for Patient Instructions.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"To ensure that changes are saved, close the Patient Instructions section before accessing SmartSets.\r\nDo not use Rich Text Formatting (RTF) for Patient Instructions.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Epic (Dan Bailey) will provide all regions with the results of a search that identifies SmartSets that contain Patient Instructions. Andrea Thorup will review the results to determine the exact scope of impact. CO (Brina David) authorized the ad hoc fix.Discovered by:  CO in production.  Physician Representative:  Dr. Howard Landa.  Epic Representative:  Dan Bailey / DBailey@epicsystems.com. PRL conversion of SmartSets resolves the problem identified in Workflows #1 but introduces a second problem described in Workflow #2.  7/16/08:  Additional workflow-The workflow will be to open an Ambulatory encounter, enter patient instructions for the encounter, do not close the patient instructions section and add a smartset that contains default patient instructions in it and choose the patient instructions from the smartset. You will notice that the patient instructions from the smartset overwrites the patient instructions that you had manually entered before opening the smartset.\r\n \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 02:00:00','2009-01-09 10:45:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(92,2718493,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient mode Smartsets Not signed',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-08-31 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'PRL','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Need to be using PRL &  DM Order entry which is not planned by any region, \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I755104\nAD HOC DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 C7503137 12/05/07\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011408-C7503137\nRISK RANKING:  8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Closed out per Dhea 12/29','\"In encounters whose departments are configured for dual-mode Clincian Order Entry, inpatient-mode orders are not signed although dual-mode orders are signed. Specifically, if a selected inpatient order in a Protocol-based (PTL) SmartSet is open while a dual-mode order is signed, no inpatient-mode orders are signed when the SmartSet is signed.\r\nTo Reproduce:\r\nOpen a patient encounter in a department for which dual-mode order entry is enabled.\r\nOpen a protocol-based SmartSet that contains inpatient-mode orders.\r\nSelect an inpatient-mode order.\r\nGo to the Order Entry activity.\r\nSelect and sign an order.\r\nReturn to the SmartSet and attempt to sign the selected order.\r\nNote that the inpatient-mode order is not signed and no order (ORD) record is created.\r\nNote: If the user\"s profile is set to not use provider defaulting, the provider form will appear when trying to sign the SmartSet, and the signing process will be canceled when accepting the provider form. In this case, you will not be able to sign the SmartSet.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SP07   - 10/8: Code status due 10/9 from Epic.  11/01/07:  Fix in Jan Kpkg.  I755104.  Ok to wait until March for install.  1/16/08:  Confirmed in K011408 Spr07,  I755104, C7503137.  1/28:  Annotation needed. 2/4:  per AM: RN 135583, 115118, 132108, 134056, 134057  Annotated for ED.  RN134062 is Ambulatory.  2/7/08:  Annotated for ED, RN134056, 134057.  Testing to start on monday (2/11). 2/14:  in testing. 2/21:  Passed Testing.  3/28 AMB FAILED in production--ED, IP to retest.  Reopen w/ Epic?  3/31:  AMB reports fix failed in PROD. Kelly will contact AMB to confirm EPIC fix for PRL on 6/20/08. 4/3:  Per Andre, unable to test. June 20th is when validation will be performed.  5/5/08:  New date for validation is July 16th, 2008.  6/12:  PRL Go-Live is set for August 27, 08. 6/19:  Questions per Apoorva: Was the issue replicated in the testing environment before installation of the fix and did the fix pass testing in the testing environment? Also, why was testing performed in production instead of a non-production environment? WITS3 testing is needed once installed into WITS3. David to follow up. (sent email regarding retest).  Per KR: Epic provided a fix for this Patient Safety issue with the January Kpackage, which was installed as part of the Spring07 Upgrade on 3/15/08.  The NCAL Patient Safety team and myself asked the Suites to validate that the issue was resolved in production following the upgrade.  Ambulatory tested this item and reported that it failed.  The reason for failure is that PRL is NOT in production today.  PRL is scheduled for an August Implementation. Ambulatory will perform extensive PRL testing in WITS3 community. The PRL Conversion is scheduled to occur in WITS3 on 6/23/08.  This Patient Safety item should be included in the WITS3 Ambulatory PRL testing - that will take place following the conversion on 6/23/08. 7/31:  Dual Mode order entry is needed for this issue to occur.  Rebecca to follow up with Epic. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 02:38:00','2008-12-29 03:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(93,2273435,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'BPAs cause unexpected patient orders',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-03-05 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'PRL','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  fixes received at different time--latest fix was on 8/08/07 \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  S751635\nAD HOC DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 C752013 & E752013 8/08/07\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051407-C7501009 & 091007-E752013 & C7501009\nRISK RANKING:  8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Closed out per Dhea 12/29','In SP\"07, a user may configure a Best Practice Alert (BPA) to suggest a single order as a follow-up action for the alert.  When using the Navigator to place that order, two copies of the order appear, instead of one.  Even if the user tries to clear all of the orders or the suggested BPA follow-up order in the Navigator, the BPA follow-up order is still placed and could be signed. This could lead to unexpected patient orders being placed.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"SP07  - Confirmed code is in K051407 Spring07.  11/01/07:  Not yet tested. Will be tested with upgrades.  Surekha will research further. 12/20/07:  Waiting for Annotation. Update 1/3/08: Kelly checking the release notes - has the same RN as PR 2272971. Update 01/07/08: Surekha will verify testing.  1/14/08:  Currently in testing.  There are multiple RN IDs. 1/21:  testing in progress--some holdups due to Pyxis.  1/28:  Testing in progress.  2/4/08:  Dhea to follow up.  2/7/08:  Annotated for ED & IP.  Per Rosalba - PRL needs to be tested to be sure they work with recent configuration changes and work with the interfaces-RN 119897, 115956, 119902, 115753, 119908, 115956, 115977, 119900. Build not ready for certain RN to be tested.  Build will be ready Feb 22nd.  PRL will go in May.  2/21:  code goes in 3/14, dormant until golive.  6/12:  PRL Go-Live is set for September 4th.  Cant\" validate in production until PRL golive. \r\n\"\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'\"Epic (Kelly Miller) is planning to provide a code fix in an upcoming KPackage, in time to test and implement prior to SP\"07 go-lives. Epic will inform PART of the KPackage release date, and then PART Communications will inform potentially impacted regions. It would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix as part of the KPackage when it becomes available, to prevent any future impact. 11/01/07:  Not yet tested. Will be tested with upgrades.  Surekha will research further.  12/20/07:  Waiting for Annotation. 1/14/08:  Currently in testing.  There are multiple RN IDs.  Pyxis.  1/28:  Testing in progress. 2/4/08:  Dia to follow up.  2/7/08:  Annotated for ED & IP.  Per Rosalba - PRL needs to be tested to be sure they work with recent configuration changes and work with the interfaces-RN 119897, 115956, 119902, 115753, 119908, 115956, 115977, 119900.  Build not ready for certain RN to be tested.  Build will be ready Feb 22nd.  PRL will go in May. \r\n\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 02:45:00','2008-12-29 03:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(94,2488966,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1782121,'HPI added stops Notewriter text',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-06-05 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'3336','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NOV07','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I753276\nAD HOC AVAILABLE (AUTH # 3336):  \n  SP’07 C7501263 available 6/18/07\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K071607--C7501263\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2/11/2009: CLOSED per Andre. ','Notewriter text can stop generating if a new HPI (history of prior illness) is added to a new note, under specific conditions.\r\n\"Text may stop generating in a new note created in Notewriter if the user leaves and returns to Notewriter without sharing, pending, or accepting the note and then adds a new HPI (History of Prior Illness) template to the note.  The specific workflow is when a clinician:\r\nUses Notewriter to create a new note for a patient\r\nSwitches activities or workspaces without pending, sharing, or accepting the note.\r\nReturns to the note and adds an HPI template. At this point, text stops generating, and information documented after this point is lost.\r\nNo other templates are affected by this problem.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<06/2007 - - Notewriter>NO CURRENT IMPACT:  This is SP07 Notewriter issue, not SP06 per R. Pingel. In 7/16 K-pckg Update 9/25/07:  E752233, C7502026 included in K091007 Spring07 UPDATE 10/8:  Notewriter build in WITS per Andre Mure.  ETS needs to know if in GG/CA or both?  Per Andre WITSCA2.  10/29:  Passed testing Udate 12/27: Notewriter for ED is on hold per Andre Mure. 2/4/08:   No update until march 08.  Code will be installed with upgrade because of July Kpkg. 3/3 ED has passed testing. 3/17:  Notewriter install needs to be certified to resolve this issue. 5/8:  Andre to follow up. 6/12:  Per Andre-Fixes (E752233) & (C7502026) are in production. No validation until functionality turned on. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'\"Epic (Kelly Miller) will provide status on the code fix to PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair), who will record this information in the PART tracking report which is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix as part of the KPackage when it becomes available. Update 9/20: test will be completed before implementation.  Update 10/29:  PASSED testing.  2/4/08:   No update until march 08.  Code will be installed with upgrage because of July Kpkg.  3/17:  Notewriter install needs to be certified to resolve this issue. \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 02:57:00','2009-02-17 08:13:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(95,2557854,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'In Specific Prolonged Workflows, Medication Orders Can Be Unintentionally Backdated and Not Appear on the MAR','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-06-27 00:00:00','2009-08-11 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'3353','SP\"06, SP\"07','','','','','','0927-AP-PR2557854-E744326-Spr06Nov05NS.tar.Z\r\n','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','S','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  order validation programming pt that will flag orders that have a problem--some false positives flagged-code fix to programing point fix desired by NCAL- Epic research indicated fix to programming point not possible with current data structure\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I746003, I754696\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3353):  \n  SP’06 E744326 9/27/07\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’06 K110507\n  SP’07 K110507\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/11/09: In prod since 2007; won\'t be able to replicate, closing.','In Specific Prolonged Workflows, Medication Orders Can Be Unintentionally Backdated and Not Appear on the MAR.\r\n\"If a new order is being placed using a specified or non-specified frequency, and the ordering user tells the system to start scheduling times now by typing the current time into the At: __ field instead of using the letter \"\"n\"\" or the \"\"Include Now\"\" button, it is possible for this first time to become back-dated (scheduled in the past) if the new order sits in the order composer for longer than the amount of time specified in system definitions item LSD 36120 - Adjust start time if within __ minutes of now. If a scheduled time for an order becomes back-dated, it will not appear as an administration time on the eMAR. \r\nExample: Item LSD 36120 is set to Adjust start time if within 15 minutes of now. A physician places an order for a Vancomycin IV Piggyback that has a default non-specified frequency of Every 12 Hours, with a default start time of 1100, continuing for 7 days. The physician wants the first administration to be now and types the current time, 0948 instead of typing \"\"n\"\" into the frequency time field. The physician leaves the order composer open for 16 more minutes and then signs the order. \r\nIn this scenario, the eMAR will show only 13 administration times instead of 14 because the administration time 0948 will not show up. \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: according to Chris R, fix was in 11/5/07 K-package. Dhea to replicate / close. \r\nPer Kirk, this is not a beacon issue.. must be an IP issue.  Waiting for SP08? \"(June) SP06 - SP07 -- replication completed. BK to discuss with Rx team.  Adhoc requested. See Col D--no ETA yet.  Check w/ Epic to see if prob is occurring in NCAL. 8/13--BK to check with Tom Sharkey. Fix in Nov K-pckg. Update 9/27:  Fix arrived 0927-AP-PR2557854-E744326-Spr06Nov05NS.tar.Z  Update 10/10:  Per Katie Volpe:  For Beacon we have determined that this should not be an issue as we used the correct record for doxorubicin. In addition, the preference lists we are using for IP orders is up to date. OK to wait till 11/28. 10/15: Passed testing, need to  come to CAB.  11/01/07:  Code failed.  Fixes one issue and creates another issue. 11/08:  BK says fix can go in without PP.  11/12/07:  Confirmed in the K110507 Spr07 - RN ID 129355  12/3/07:  Beatrice to speak with Tom Sharkey.  12/20/07:  Waiting for programming point. Ok to wait for Kpkg. 1/31 BK to speak with Epic about programing point alert misfiring.  2//4/08:  Adhoc failed testing.  4/21:  Tom to follow up.  5/8:  Long term fix will be in SP\"08. Katie to follow up with Macy regarding PP. 5/12/08:  Per Macy -  there is NO impact to Beacon Team or Users. This fix is not needed for Beacon.\r\nLong term fix is coming in Sp08 per Beatrice Kuhn. We do have a pp fix but we are not using it, the scenario can still occur but it is not common. The plan is to wait for SP08 unless Epic can retro the fix. Order compose is left open 31 minutes or more, past due times. Workflow/timing issue for x1 medications - yes we have updates users in STR. PP was not installed for inpatient. Is this an issue for STR users, have we educated them? 6/12:  Fix is not needed in NCAL, since no impact to Beacon users and can wait until SP\"08.  7/31:  sent email to Katie requesting status.  8/3:  Per Macy, no change in status. \r\n11/30:  11/26- Per Kirk This must be an inpatient issue - not Beacon.  We were was not aware that this existed.\r\n','Make sure LSD 36120 - Adjust start time if within __ minutes of now is set to a long enough period of time to be able to catch times that were probably meant to be scheduled and not back dated. The default time for this setting is fifteen minutes.  Note:  NCAL has setting set to 30 minutes. \r\n',NULL,'Make sure LSD 36120 - Adjust start time if within __ minutes of now is set to a long enough period of time to be able to catch times that were probably meant to be scheduled and not back dated. The default time for this setting is fifteen minutes.  Note:  NCAL has setting set to 30 minutes. \r\n',NULL,'\" If a region requires fix, it must ask for an adhoc or wait for K-pckg. Update 7/24: The code fix for this issue is quite complex and Epic is not yet able to determine its ETA.  Therefore, while developing the code fix, Epic is also looking into two possible workarounds to ensure the safety of our patients in the meantime.  Specifically: Epic is researching the feasibility of a workaround in which an Order Validation Programming Point is adjusted to prevent the problem from occurring.  They will update us on its feasibility during the week of 7/30.  In case this workaround proves to be unfeasible, Epic is looking into creating a new appropriate Order Validation Programming Point.  Update 8/27:  fix in Nov. K-pckg Update 9/25:  Per Victoria -  workflow will be rare but could happen.  Fix is included in K071607, She is okay with waiting for prod install 11/28/07 if Beatrice and Dr. Bliss agree. Update 9/27:  Fix arrived 0927-AP-PR2557854-E744326-Spr06Nov05NS.tar.Z.  11/01/07:  Code failed.  Fixes one issue and creates another issue. 11/08:  BK says fix can go in without PP. 12/03:  BK to speak with T. Sharkey. 12/20/07:  Waiting for programming point. Ok to wait for Kpkg. 2//4/08:  Adhoc failed testing.  0927-AP-PR2557854-E744326-Spr06Nov05NS.tar.Z\r\nSp 07 Nov K RN 129355.  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:02:00','2009-08-11 11:10:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(96,3277062,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2436770,'KPHC Potential Patient Safety Issue: Reported By EPIC Brief Summary: When order composer values are changed',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','I758803 - available 6/30/08','',NULL,'2008-03-26 14:36:28','2008-03-26 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'3945','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0702-AP-PR3277062-C7503858-E756655-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z\r\n','K072108',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'4','M',NULL,'BCON','N','S','P','L',' ','N','S',NULL,'Clo',NULL,NULL,NULL,'M','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',60,'2008-11-26 08:38:10',NULL,'Software Services','PART KPHC','NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758803\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3945):  \n  SP’07 C7503858 & E756655 7/02/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  4','KPHC Environment','Patient Safety issue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Per Katie V, this issue resolved.  CLOSED','KPHC Potential Patient Safety Issue: Reported By EPIC Brief Summary: When order composer values are changed for treatment plan orders from the Treatment Plan Manager, the changed values will not be validated if a user keys in the value and selects the hyperlink to open the order composer for another order or selects another section in the treatment plan.\r\n \r\nDescription:\r\nWhen order composer values are changed for treatment plan orders from the Treatment Plan Manager, the changed values will not be validated if a user keys in the value and selects the hyperlink to open the order composer for another order or selects another section in the treatment plan.  In both cases, the order composer for the original order will close and the changed value will not be respected.  This issue affects all fields within the order composer for both Simple Treatment Plans and Beacon Treatment Plans.\r\n \r\nChanged values will be validated if the user selects Accept, Release, Sign, clicks any white space on the s',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3/26/08 - SP\"06/\"07. Epic will provide code status 4/11/08.  Kpkg not known at this time.  3/27:  Workaround is in place &  has been communicated by Kirk.  4/21:  NCAL does not use this workflow.  Rebecca to follow up with epic on adhoc. 5/8:  Fix in the July Kpkg. 5/12/08:  Per Macy/Sheryl No Ad Hoc is needed for this issue at this time, considered low priority low impact. This was a Patient Safety issue found by another client where they don\"t press \"Accept\" or \"Right Click\" to save the changes.  This is replicated in our environment.  Fortunately, we train our folks to always either ACCEPT or RIGHT CLICK on white area.  It\"s like Word or Excel.  If you exit and don\"t save, nothing is saved.  When they get a fix, we should install.  Risk is low at this time, if users are trained appropriately. This will be in July Kpackage, Dustin will follow up as of yesterday , DLG number delivered. 6/12:  Waiting for Kpkg. Low impact per Katie.  Rebecca to follow up with Epic regarding outage.  6/27:  The DLG for the fix is I758803 and it will be available on Monday, 6/30/08. 7/2:  Code received. 7/14 Ad-hoc also introduces problematic SU that affects PR 3548698. Per Katie, waiting for kpkg. 7/3:  0702-AP-PR3277062-C7503858-E756655-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z . 7/31:  Fix confirmed in July Kpkg. 8/27:  per KV, we are working with Mark Okimoto, Beacon AC who will pull these release notes for review and testing purposes. 10/23: Send Katie email for status.  11/30:  11/14 Per Sheryl Balicanta, Beacon AC this is no longer an issue per Ambulatory, this was resolved with a fix. ','If a user directly keys in order composer values for a treatment plan order in the Treatment Plan Manager, one of the following actions should be taken to validate the changes: select Accept, Release, Sign, click any white space on the screen, or press Enter after changing a value.\r\n',NULL,'If a user directly keys in order composer values for a treatment plan order in the Treatment Plan Manager, one of the following actions should be taken to validate the changes: select Accept, Release, Sign, click any white space on the screen, or press Enter after changing a value.\r\n',NULL,'Epic will provide code status 4/11/08.  Kpkg not known at this time;  Kirk Ryan to communicate workaround to Santa Teresa clinicians.\r\n',NULL,'1206571870ï££Z236766ï££Robin R Dugan\n\nConf in Dr, David Bliss for NCALï£¢1206572732ï££K225996ï££Daniel R Gaudreau\n\n.ï£¢1207092984ï££K241509ï££Closing aging recordsï£¢',736,736,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:05:00','2008-12-29 03:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(97,3509257,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NoteWriter may not generate HPI text, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Notewriter','DLG  I759537  Client C7503832 ','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers',NULL,NULL,'','sp06-sp08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0709-PS-PR3515805-C7503832-E756747-Spr07Jul21NS.zip\r\n','K072108',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','A','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   Confirmed in K072108 (I759537) as fix to 3515805;  fix standard in SP08 IU4\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759537\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4186):  \n  SP’07 C7503832 7/09/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-C7503832\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2/2/9 - Melanie - According to previous Ambulatory response on ?/? By Michael Cobarrubia there is no impact to Amb.','SP?06-SP?08 - - NoteWriter - NoteWriter may not generate HPI text, in certain circumstances\r\n\"Description:  NoteWriter may not generate HPI text in the following workflow when a user:\r\nCreates a new note using the HPI or SFHPI SmartBlock;\r\nDocuments multiple HPI complaints that share the same text generation template (QuickForm or SmartForm); \r\nNavigates between NoteWriter and other Epic activities (e.g., Chart Review);\r\nReturns to NoteWriter and documents additional complaints. For these recent complaints, Notewriter will not generate text.\r\nMultiple HPI complaints can share the same text generation template if the following are used:\r\nA generic template \r\nCertain released forms, for example LQF\"s 50209 - ED SF HPI PED - General Injury, 50292 - ED SF HPI PED - Arm Injury, 50295 - ED SF HPI PED - Burn, 50298 - ED SF HPI PED - MVA, and 50302 - ED SF HPI PED - Facial Injury.\r\nThe data is saved, but not displayed.\r\nCO, SCAL, NCAL, NW, and HI 