ED-FOREIGN BODY\r\n      50324 ED SF HPI PED-FOREIGN BODY IN EAR\r\n      50325 ED SF HPI PED-FOREIGN BODY IN NOSE\r\n     HGN: 49741 is used by forms:\r\n      50194 ED SF HPI PED-DIFFICULTY BREATHING\r\n      50317 ED SF HPI PED-WHEEZING\r\n     HGN: 49771 is used by forms:\r\n      50277 ED SF HPI PED-ALTERED MENTAL STATUS\r\n      50308 ED SF HPI PED-SEIZURES\r\n     HGN: 49809 is used by forms:\r\n      50209 ED SF HPI PED-GENERAL INJURY\r\n      50291 ED SF HPI PED-HAND INJURY\r\n      50292 ED SF HPI PED-ARM INJURY\r\n      50293 ED SF HPI PED-ANIMAL BITE\r\n      50295 ED SF HPI PED-BURN\r\n      50296 ED SF HPI PED-FOOT INJURY\r\n      50297 ED SF HPI PED-FALL\r\n      50298 ED SF HPI PED-MVA\r\n      50301 ED SF HPI PED-LACERATION\r\n      50302 ED SF HPI PED-FACIAL INJURY\r\n      50303 ED SF HPI PED-MOUTH INJURY\r\n     HGN: 49835 is used by forms:\r\n      50183 ED SF HPI PED-CONSTIPATION\r\n      50322 ED SF HPI PED-BLOOD IN STOOL\r\n     HGN: 49838 is used by forms:\r\n      50244 ED SF HPI PED-MUSCULOSKELETAL PAIN\r\n      50312 ED SF HPI PED-SICKLE CELL PAIN\r\n      50318 ED SF HPI PED-BACK PAIN\r\n      50326 ED SF HPI PED-KNEE PAIN\r\n\r\n\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CLOSED per Kelly / Bill Yee 12/09/2008  Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed).\r\nAmbulatory, Inpatient, ED, Anesthesia.  Epic (Brendan Krueger) provided regions with search results that identified complaints mapped to the same text generation template. Epic (Robyn Pingel) will run an additonal search for all affected QuickForm and SmartForm text generation templates that may have impacted patients, and provide PART with the results by 6/27/08. Epic (Brendan Krueger) will provide a code fix (for both QuickForms and SmartForms) and inform PART of its ETA and KPackage by 6/27/08.  6/23:  This does not affect ED at this moment because ED has not yet gone Live (7/26/08).  David to follow up with Carol Devlin regarding AMB (sent email).  Adhoc has been requested. Per Michael Cobarrubia, AMB is not affected since History of Present Illness is freetexted (or use a smartphrase).   QuickForm or Smart Form within Analyzer is in Notewriter is not used. (What about Anesthesia and Inp?).  6/30:  Epic search results state NCAL not affected. Rebecca to follow up with adhoc ETA. ED to adhoc. ED expected to not be affected after 7/21.  6/30:  ETA 7/9/08 (fix is in last stages of testing as of today), DLG  I759537  Client C7503832, No outage needed, in 072108 KPackage.  7/3:  Adhoc:  4186 - ETA 7/9. Not affected in ED at this time. Aiming for August install. 7/10:  Adhoc received.  7/14/08:  Per Theresa, this PS issue is resolved by the fix for PS PR3515805. 7/17: to go into WITS 2 & 3 tonight. 7/18:  During testing, Epic noticed that it is possible for double documentation to occur with the fix.  For example, at SCAL, the concepts for bronchitis and cough are mapped to the same text generation template.  Before, if I would document on bronchitis, switch to another activity, then switch back to NoteWriter and document on cough, the text wouldn\"t generate properly for cough.  With the fix it will, however, I could have text for both bronchitis and cough repeated. Development has started to address this, but Epic felt double documentation in those rare instances is better than missing documentation and they didn\"t want to delay the package. 7/28:  Per Andre, waiting for Kpkg (NCAL will not be impacted-smart forms will be used and not the defected smart blocks will not be used). AMB & ED will wait for Nov install. 7/31:  Confirmed in July Kpkg. \r\n','None identified\r\n',NULL,'None identified\r\n',NULL,'SCAL (Ruben Robles) authorized the ad hoc code fix.Discovered by:  Epic, during testing.  Physician Representative:  Dr. Allen Rogers.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:11:00','2009-02-05 02:48:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(99,2210753,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Cumulative Dose Tracking totals with weight and/or height based units may not update correctly under certain circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-02-06 00:00:00','2009-09-28 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'BCON','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I745007, I745130, I752923, I753080\r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP06 K071607 E743477 & E743627\r\n  SP07 K071607\r\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28/09: 9/28/09: CLOSING PR 2210753 as PS, leaving TD 28703 open as non-PS (SBalicanta notified by email)','The Cumulative Dose (a.k.a., Lifetime Dose) total of  a chemical tracked with weight and/or height units may not be updated correctly.  The conditions for this to happen are if a medication order with the chemical is placed or released before the patient\"s height and/or weight is documented in the same patient encounter.  For example, this may occur if a chemotherapy order from a treatment plan with height/weight associations for dosing is released to a new encounter where height/weight has not been recorded.  Another example is if the medication order is placed directly in Order Entry and the missing height/weight messages are ignored. \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: 8/10/09: email sent to Lori R / Sheryl B, asking for approval to close PR, leave TD open.  4/6:  Per Alex:  Defect Status -  TD 28703 Deferred. This issue is related to Ambulatory Beacon and assigned to Beacon AC - Sheryl Balicanta.Waiting for July KPKG. All releases, FA\"04 to SP\"07.  CUM DOSE TRKING CURRENTLY not currently SCHED  will wait for K-pckg (Jul/Sept)  DLG, I745007 E743477, Rel Note ID\"s 118231   118403   118405 In July k-pckg, prod 11/28.  11/08/07:  Testing in progress. TESTING COMPLETED 11/9. 11/29/07:  Code install for SP\"06 confirmed by Kelly.  12/20/07:  Passed testing for SP\"06.  Waiting for SP\"07 to be tested. Update 1/7/08: Surekha will verify testing with Beacon.  1/14/08:  Currently in testing & Beacon testing will be verified. 1/17 Will not be tested for SP07 fix will go in per Don Ly. Per Kelly track until new test environment is ready.  1/28:  Beatrice to check.  2/4/08:  A follow up with Katie V.  Environment not available until March 3rd to test.  Per KV:  ask Macy or Beatrice.  2/7:  BK to follow up with Macy.  2/21:  RN 135376 has not yet passed testing. RN 135375 has passed.   2/25 Surekha to get update from Macy. 2/28: Will not affect functionality for March 14th [Surekha]. 3/3: Code will be installed, minor defect, Still testing.  3/6 Surekha to check w/ Macy regarding test defect. 3/10: Test defect will not impact NCAL per Surekha.  4/17:  No impact at this time. Not using merging.  Fix in prod.  Beatrice to follow up.  Per Surekha:  the merge is still not going in, the code is installed, but can we move it to Beacon tab and keep it yellow. so that when we close the defect we can close the issue.  Per Carolyn Rogers, the lead for the MRN project, stated that the clinical data will notbe merged when patients are merged.  (Issue closed, but defect stays open).  4/21:  Test defect will remain open until clincal data merge.  Yellow Row.  5/8:  SP\"06 passed testing.  SP\"07 has 1 TD.  Only an issue when \"Clinical Merge\" goes live.  6/12:  Possible TDs:  28703. 7/31:  Sent email to Katie requesting status.  8/3:  Per Macy, no change in status. 10/30: Waiting for July KPKG.11/30:  11/26- Per Kirk Ryan - This issue pending fix.  The way NCAL has this built - the cum dose function is functioning correctly - this does not affect us unless the provider uses the button (the bottom/last button) where it asks for the dose to be recalculated each time.  Waiting for July Kpkg. \r\n\r\n','Epic (Kelly Miller) will provide a fix in a future KPackage and inform PART of its ETA by 03/01/07.  Epic (Kelly Miller) will inform Pharmacy (Beatrice Kuhn) if a programming point for Height will be made available (one already exists for Patient Weight).  These programming points ensure that values for a patient\"s height and/or weight are entered. \r\n','','Epic (Kelly Miller) will provide a fix in a future KPackage and inform PART of its ETA by 03/01/07.  Epic (Kelly Miller) will inform Pharmacy (Beatrice Kuhn) if a programming point for Height will be made available (one already exists for Patient Weight).  These programming points ensure that values for a patient\"s height and/or weight are entered. \r\n',NULL,'Pharmacy (Beatrice Kuhn) will work with other Pharmacy team members to collaboratively decide on implementing the KPackage alone or submitting a change request to acquire the Patient Height programming point if it becomes available. It would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix as part of the KPackage when it becomes available, to prevent any future impact.  Update 3/1:  per BK, still waiting for Epic.  Can wait for fix as long as no cumulative dose tracking.  Update 3/5:  per Joy (Epic):  no ETA yet. Update 3/29:  Beatrice to research plans for Cumulative DT.  6/20/07:  DLG I743337, E742842, RN #\"s  114292   114295   114298.   10/29/07:  Testing in progress.  11/9  PASSED testing. 11/29/07:  Code install for SP\"06 confirmed by Kelly.  Row will be added to SP\"07 Tab.  12/20/07:  Passed testing for SP\"06.  Waiting for SP\"07 to be tested.  1/14/08:  Currently in testing & Beacon testing will be verified.  1/28:  Beatrice to check. 2/4/08:  A follow up with Katie V.  Environment not available until March 3rd to test.  Code will be installed but not activated.  2/7:  BK to follow up with Macy.  3/17:  TD-28703.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:12:00','2009-09-28 01:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(101,3390816,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Print Group 2024 may Display Incorrect Code Status',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-07 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07, SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'wait for Kpckg','','K072108',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Two part fix.  Major part in testing and expected in July Kpackage.  Minor fix date TBD  (workaround available and no current impact so not a high priority) Confirmed in K072108; SP08 fix standard in IU3 so doesnt impact KP for SP08\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759398, I759415, I759389\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756528\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2/2/9 - Melanie - This report already shows there is no current impact.','Description:   Print Group 2024 may display an incorrect code status for a patient, as in the following scenario:  \r\nA patient that has an indicated code status in an outpatient context, e.g. an office visit, and is admitted as an inpatient.\r\nIt is expected that the code status be a blank (because no code status has been indicated for this inpatient admission).\r\nHowever, the print group 2024 inappropriately displays the most recent code status, e.g. the one entered in the office visit.\r\nThe correct display should be a blank until the user indicates a code status for the inpatient context (not the office visit, in this example).\r\nPotential Impact:  All regions (NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, OH, GA, MAS, CO, and Exempla) could be impacted if they implement print group 2024 without a fix.\r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of  the 071208 KPackage and inform PART Communications (Sharon Carroll) of the status by May 23, 2008.\r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. \r\nDiscovered by:   Epic, during internal testing\r\nReported by:   Epic (Dustin Foster)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Changed to \"closed\" status 2/2/09; included with 11/08 install.\r\nWaiting for July Kpkg (confirmed).  No Current Impact. \r\n5/7/08:  NO CURRENT IMPACT -- IP, Ambulatory, ED -- SP\"07, SP\"08.  Per Epic (Dustin Foster), fix will a part of 071208 Kpackage (confirmed). \r\n','None',NULL,'None',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:22:00','2009-02-05 02:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(102,3390126,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Review Flowsheet may display incorrect data or no data under very specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-08 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP06, SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K072108',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758289\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 E756100 available as of 5/20/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756100\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2/2/9 - Melanie - This report already shows there is no current impact.','Description:   Review flowsheets may display incorrect data or no data, under the following specific circumstances:\r\nSP\"06 with SU E744470 installed or SP\"07 with SU E753618 installed.\r\nOne of the flowsheet rows is set up to display data from a Documentation Flowsheet row of type Custom List.\r\nThe aforementioned row is not the last row to be displayed in the Review Flowsheet. The aforementioned row uses either flowsheet format (FSF) 8068-Doc Flow Custom List Abbr or 8069-Doc Flow Custom List Title to format the value of the row. However, no regions are currently impacted. \r\nFeatures:   Review Flowsheet format 8068 and 8069\r\nSCAL was previously impacted because they had the SU installed and were using a specific flowsheet, that met the criteria to be affected.  However, the affected flowsheet (Wound Nonsurgical) was \"soft-deleted\" in October 2007 and the flowsheet was \"unreleased\" today by SCAL (Vicky S. Miller) so SCAL will not ever be impacted.  The flowsheet utilized specific rows that were also soft-deleted, so nothing would have ever occurred.\r\n2 more Review Flowsheet (FSH) records at SCAL were potentially affected by the issue, discovered after initial PART bridge call:\r\nFSH record WOUND SURGICAL\r\nFSH record PRESSURE ULCER\r\nThey were both using format (FSF) 8069-DOC FLOW CUSTOM LIST TITLE and 8068-DOC FLOW CUSTOM LIST ABBR to format the doc flowsheet data.\r\nSCAL (Vicky S Miller) did an analysis of the flow rows in these flowsheets and confirmed that the flow rows are inactive. SCAL \"unreleased\"  these two Flowsheets 5/8/08.  SCAL also informed the team not to use the formatting rows - 8069-DOC FLOW CUSTOM LIST TITLE and 8068-DOC FLOW CUSTOM LIST ABBR.\r\nAdditionally, National (Mary Seggerman) verified that those two newly reported flowsheets had been \"retired\", so SCAL is not impacted.\r\nMAS, GA,OH, CO, HI, NW, Exempla, and NCAL are potentially impacted if they load the impacted SU and use the affected flowsheet as described above.\r\nEpic (Betsy Radtke) will provide a code fix as part of July KPackage and will inform PART Communications (Sharon Carroll) May 9 of the fix status.\r\nDiscovered by:   Epic, during internal testing\r\nEpic Representative:  Betsy Radtke  608-271-9000  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Changed to \"closed\" status 2/2/09; included as part of 11/08 install.\r\nWaiting for July Kpkg (confirmed). No Current Impact.\r\nNo Current Impact. 5/8/08:  SP\"06-SP\"07, IP & AMB.  NCAL has SU E753618 installed and is still not impacted. 5/15:  Package # E756100.  6/2:  Fix expected in July Kpkg (confirmed).\r\n','Remove the formatting records 8069-DOC FLOW CUSTOM LIST TITLE and 8068-DOC FLOW CUSTOM LIST ABBR from the flowsheets, until the fix is available and implemented.',NULL,'Remove the formatting records 8069-DOC FLOW CUSTOM LIST TITLE and 8068-DOC FLOW CUSTOM LIST ABBR from the flowsheets, until the fix is available and implemented.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:27:00','2009-02-05 02:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(103,3423930,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Alternative medications ordered from Discharge Navigator order sets may not display correct SIG',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K090908',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  pkgd with 3354673 fix and is in Sep Kpkg ; reordering inpatient to outpatient orders workflow still has issues. Confirmed in Sept K\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759712\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K090908-E757063\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2/2/9 - Melanie - N/A for AMB.','SP\"07 -- IP & ED -- Alternative medications ordered from Discharge Navigator order sets may not display correct SIG\r\n\"Detail Description:  Alternative medications ordered from Discharge Navigator order sets may not display correct SIG.  Alternative medications ordered from a Discharge Navigator order set will be linked to the directions (SIG) of the original medication.  If clinical action is based on incorrect medication directions, patient care could be impacted.  NCAL is currently impacted since it has instances of alternative medications ordered from Discharge Navigator order sets. Per Elissa Liong, no adhoc is needed at this time since the workaround is in place.  Alternative medications ordered outside of Discharge Navigator orders sets are unaffected.  Per Epic (Thomas Sharkey), PRL will be in use by the time an adhoc would be available.  Epic will provide a code status on June 5th, 2008.  \r\nExample:  If a clinician orders the DVT Prophylaxis medication Enoxaparin 40 mg Syrg, Fondaparin 7.5 mg Syrg is suggested as the preferred alternative.  If Fondaparin is ordered, the correct name is displayed but the directions (SIG) will be for the original medication Enoxaparin.  \r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Mike Krall\r\nRemediation:  None discussed\r\nAction items (future):  Discussion if NCAL will request an adhoc or wait for the fix in a K-Package (Targeting the July K-Package).\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Changed to \"closed\" status 2/2/09; included as part of 11/08 install.\r\nWaiting for Sept Kpkg.  Workaround in place. \r\n5/23/08:  NCAL - IP, ED.   Workaround implemented & Elissa Liong to follow up with Clinical Content. Per Elissa, adhoc not necessary. Fix targeted for July Kpkg (not confirmed in July Kpkg). 7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic. 9/18:  Waiting for Sept Kpkg (confirmed). \r\n','Workaround in place. To prevent further occurrences, remove instructions (SIG) from order sets used in Discharge Navigator. NCAL National Pharmacy (Elissa Liong) removed alternative medications from order sets used in Discharge Navigator.\r\n',NULL,'Workaround in place. To prevent further occurrences, remove instructions (SIG) from order sets used in Discharge Navigator. NCAL National Pharmacy (Elissa Liong) removed alternative medications from order sets used in Discharge Navigator.\r\n',NULL,'5/23/08:  Concern:  Medication directions would be incorrect for the altered medication. Problem Discovered by:   NCAL Pharmacy. Epic Representative / email address:  Thomas Sharkey / TSharkey@epicsystems.com.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:33:00','2009-02-05 02:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(104,3486063,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Modified Oncology Treatment Plan Medications Do Not Immediately Appear on the MAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-11 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K072108',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108;  fix standard in SP08 IU3\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759243\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 E756466 available 6/13/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Closed per Dorinda Wong 1/26/09','SP\"07-SP\"08 - - Modified Oncology Treatment Plan Medications Do Not Immediately Appear on the MAR\r\n\"Description\r\nIn Spring 2007, MAR grouping was enhanced to support oncology treatment plan grouping, which displayed medication orders that were released from an oncology treatment plan together under a header with the treatment plan name. In the following identified workflow, a modified treatment plan medication order does not appear on the MAR until the discontinued medication lookback period has passed. \r\nThe discontinued MAR lookback setting controls how long to keep discontinued medications orders grouped in an active medication section on the MAR before moving the medication orders to the discontinued/completed section. \r\nSetup conditions:\r\n IP MAR grouping enabled (IP - MAR Display Meds by Group (I LSD 34552) or IP - MAR Display Meds by Group (I DEP 24552) set to (Yes) \r\nMAR discontinue medication lookback greater than 0 hours (IP - MAR Lookback for Discontinued Order Group (I LSD 34554) or IP - MAR Lookback for Discontinued Order Group (I DEP 24554) >0)\r\nWorkflow steps: \r\n1) You release a medication from an oncology treatment plan and the medication order appears grouped under the treatment plan on the MAR. \r\n2) You modify the released medication order such that the original order is discontinued and a new order is created. (The modify function can be used from the Order Review activity, Medications activity, or Orders navigator section.) \r\n3) The discontinued medication order appears as discontinued and grouped under the treatment plan on the MAR. 4) The new medication order does not appear on the MAR until the discontinue lookback period has passed.\r\nPotential Patient Safety Issue - 3 - June 2, 2008\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NO CURRENT IMPACT.  Beacon - SP\"07 & SP\"08.  Fix will be in July Kpkg.  6/12:  Waiting for July Kpkg. 6/17:  Fix for this issue has been released (i759243/e756466) - also in July Kpkg (confirmed). \r\n','\"Disable MAR grouping.\r\n Configure the discontinued MAR lookback to 0 hrs.\r\n Instead of modifying medication orders, discontinue the original order and use the Reorder button to enter the new order. The new medication order will not be grouped under the Treatment Plan name, but will appear in the active orders section.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Disable MAR grouping.\r\n Configure the discontinued MAR lookback to 0 hrs.\r\n Instead of modifying medication orders, discontinue the original order and use the Reorder button to enter the new order. The new medication order will not be grouped under the Treatment Plan name, but will appear in the active orders section.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'Epic reference #:  280946. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:34:00','2009-02-02 03:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(105,3443190,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Conflict checking not occurring',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, OpTime ','I758805, I764360','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-27 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Scott Adelman',NULL,NULL,'4124','SU05 thru SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0714-PS-PR3443190-C7503898-E756865-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z','K072108',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','I','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108; not sure what version of SP08 fix is standard in, but all regions targeting fixing it in SP07\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758805, I764360\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4124):  \n  SP’07 C7503898 & E756865 7/14/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756865 & C7503898\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Changed to \"closed\" status 2/2/09; included in 11/08 install.','A diagnosis listed in the patient\"s past medical history as a pertinent negative may not be removed if that diagnosis is later added to the patient\"s problem list, resulting in conflicting documentation.  This problem may occur if the provider enters a diagnosis to the problem list via any of the following activities:\r\nOrder Entry\r\nEpisodes\r\nProblem List without then accessing the patient\"s history (SP\"07-SP\"08 only).\r\nFor example:\r\nIn June 2007, hyperthyroidism was indicated as a pertinent negative on a patient\"s chart.\r\nIn January 2008, Provider X adds hyperthyroidism to the patient\"s Problem List in the chart using the Order Entry Problem List view.\r\nThe user exits the patient workspace without accessing the History Activity or History navigator.\r\nThe patient\"s chart is not accessed for several months.\r\nIn April 2008, Provider Y, uses a dot phrase to bring the patient\"s pertinent negatives from the history activity into his progress note and sees that hyperthyroidism is still listed as a pertinent negative, and then exits the patient\"s chart.\r\nIn May 2008, Provider Z opens the patient chart and views the patient\"s problem list, he then also accesses the History Activity, and sees that hyperthyroidism is no longer listed as a pertinent negative. (Accessing the problem list and the History activity within the same period of time the chart is open causes the Pertinent Negatives and the Problem List to synch up correctly).\r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Scott Adelman\r\nProblem Discovered by:   Another Epic Client\r\nRemediation: If the utility reports indicate past records are impacted, the regions will determine the appropriate historical remediation actions.\r\nAction items (immediate):  Epic (Jason Ramaker) is creating a utility to identify and reconcile patients with affected medical history.\r\nAction items (future):   Epic (Jason Ramaker) will provide information about the utility and the code fix DLG I758805 status by 6/6/08.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed). 5/27/08:  SU\"05-SP\"08--AMB, IP, ED, and OpTime -- All Regions. Epic is creating a utility to identify affected patients and will have a status regarding the utility and code fix by 6/10/08.  5/29:  Adhoc authorized by Dr. Bliss. - Adhoc:  4124 / RFC:  2609702.  Epic (Jason Ramaker)  research indicated that an additional fix is needed to resolve this problem (3352339).  In additon to the fix in the January KPackage (DLG I755860), impacted regions will also need to install DLG I758805, which has not yet been released. Epic will provide updated information on this fix by June 6.  Please note that DLG I758805 is also the fix to PART incident 3443190.  6/2:  Status on adhoc & utility 6/6/08.  6/9:  The search utility was completed earlier this week by Epic (Jason Ramaker), who reports that NW and NCAL were not affected. 6/19:  David to follow up with Tom. (Sent email to Rebecca to ensure statement above is correct). 6/23:  Per Rebecca, NCAL is not impacted.  7/14/08:  File received & will be included in July Kpkg. 7/18:  Dhea requesting to discuss this PR. 7/21:  Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed). \r\n','Regions will determine how the Epic (Jason Ramaker) suggested workaround will be appropriately utilized and/or communicated - Access the History Activity or History Navigator any time a new diagnosis is added to the patient\"s problem list.',NULL,'Regions will determine how the Epic (Jason Ramaker) suggested workaround will be appropriately utilized and/or communicated - Access the History Activity or History Navigator any time a new diagnosis is added to the patient\"s problem list.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:36:00','2009-02-02 03:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(106,2793484,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'IP Medication Reorders using Discrete Sigs may not be Scheduled under specific circumstances','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-09-13 00:00:00','2009-08-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'SIGS','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I754384\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K110507-E753288\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/10/09: 8/10/2009--Issue over 2 yrs old.  Fix was in 11/2007 k-package.  Discreet Go-Live expected 2010. Elissa Liong has approved closure','\"When reordering a ?prior to admission medication? for an inpatient in the Admission Navigator, using the Ambulatory Discrete Sigs functionality, if an outpatient frequency is used which is not set up to be scheduled, the medication is ordered but no doses are scheduled.\r\nApplications:   IP, Pharmacy, OpTime, and ED.\r\nReleases:  SP\"06 - SP\"07\r\nFeatures:   Reorders in the Admission Navigator using Ambulatory Discrete Sigs \r\nRegions:  No regions are currently impacted.  Ambulatory Discrete Sigs is being considered by National Pharmacy for SP?08.  If National Pharmacy implements, any Inpatient regions (NCAL, SCAL, HI, and NW)  that choose to use the affected functionality could be potentially impacted in the future.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"SP\"06 - SP\"07\r\nNO CURRENT IMPACT - 11/12/07:  Confirmed in K110507 Spr07, RN ID\"s 129531, 129533, 129539, 129544 Update 12/27: Testing is being done with SP07. Assigned to Elissa w/Nat testing team.  6/12:  Discreet Go-Live expected 2010. \"\r\n','Configure outpatient frequencies with scheduling information. (not relevant unless using Discrete Sigs with Ambulatory)  These will schedule properly when reordered in an inpatient setting.\r\n',NULL,'Configure outpatient frequencies with scheduling information. (not relevant unless using Discrete Sigs with Ambulatory)  These will schedule properly when reordered in an inpatient setting.\r\n',NULL,'\"Epic (Dustin Foster) currently has a SP\"07 fix in progress (that will be available in a KPackage), and this will be fixed in the SP?08 release.\r\nEpic (Kelly Miller) will provide status on the code fix to PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair), who will record this information in the PART tracking report which is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nInpatient Regions (NCAL, SCAL, HI, and NW)  may choose to be proactive by implementing this fix as part of the KPackage when it becomes available.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:37:00','2009-08-10 11:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(107,2360112,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SU05 - SP07:  Patient Chart Merge causes some LDA information to',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-04-06 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','SP?06 K071607',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'7',NULL,NULL,'NOV07','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I752115\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3333):  \n  SP’06 E743709 7/02/07\n  SP’07 E7515387 6/11/07\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’06 K071607\n  SP’07 K071607\nRISK RANKING:  7',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2/11/2009:  CLOSED per Andre Mure. ',' Notewriter clinician notes that contain the terms microcephalicor macrocephalic may be overwritten if the Notewriter macro default is set to include either of those terms.  For example, if the Notewriter default macro is set for macrocephalic,and the physician writes  microcephalic in the note and then invokes the macro to complete the note, the noted term microcephalicis overwritten by the default, macroencephalic.  Only these two terms are affected.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SP06-SCAL ONLY.  NCAL DOES NOT USE NOTEWRITER.  Fix in July K-pckg.  Adhoc fix received 7/6.  Notewriter ED sched for 10/17. Passed testing ED, need followup on AMB.  Update 9/13: Sched for prod 9/22.  Update 9/24:  Code installed in PROD 9/22 - validated ','Until the fix is applied, do not use the terms microcephalic or macrocephalic in Notewriter macros or notes. ',NULL,'Until the fix is applied, do not use the terms microcephalic or macrocephalic in Notewriter macros or notes. ',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,37,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:40:00','2009-02-17 08:13:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(108,3442521,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'KPHC PPS: PSE 279663 - Result Note May not be seen by Recipient if using Result Notes In Basket Messages with Responsibility.','','',NULL,NULL,'Inpatient, ED','','',NULL,'2008-05-27 12:12:45','2008-05-27 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','SU05 thru SP08','','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'P',NULL,'9','M',NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',' ','Y','S',NULL,'Clo',NULL,NULL,NULL,'M','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',60,'2009-02-26 15:13:10',NULL,'Infrastructure Software','PART KPHC','NOTES:  Fixed in SU09: no fixes planned for SP07 or SP08 due to complexity, but airtight workaround available\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  143333 & 141443\r\nRISK RANKING:  9','KPHC Environment','Patient Safety issue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/01/09: 3/18/09: Per e-mail from Bill (Yu), NCAL Ambulatory is not using this feature. SU \'09 install is 10/2010','KPHC Potential Patirnt Safety Issue: PSE 279663 - Result Note May not be seen by Recipient if using Result Notes In Basket Messages with Responsibility.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Airtight workaround available.  F/u with Johnette to see if needed. Fix being planned to be standard in SU09.Fix still in progress (Epic).  Status 11/17/2008.  5/27/08:  SU\"05-SP\"08 / AMB, IP, ED - - NO CURRENT IMPACT - Epic (Jason Ramaker) will provide a code fix as part of a Kpackage.  5/29:  Andre to follow up. 6/3:  Per AM: The documentation provided by Epic states that if we had the Definition 1044-Result Note with Responsibility or a copy configured to use Result Notes with Responsibility, that this configuration should be changed to the configuration we currently have set,  Message Type Result Notes (44).  7/31:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic on 8/25. Status from Epic 9/22. 9/29:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic on 10/20/08.  10/27: Report back from Epic in one month on current status.\r\n3/2:  Airtight workaround available.  F/u with Johnette to see if needed. Fix being planned to be standard in SU09.','Epic (Jason Ramaker) suggests that regions Disable Responsiblity for Result Note In Basket Messages, until a fix is available.  Whether or not responsibility is enabled for a given message type is dictated by the Message Type Definition associated with that message type at the system level.  To Disable responsibility, do the following:\r\nIn the Clinical Administration Menu (d ^LC) go to 1-Management Options > 11-In Basket Setup > 9-Epic-Wide Settings and page down to the Message Type Defaults screen.\r\nLook at the row for Message Type Result Notes (44)\r\nIf the Definition for this row is 1044-Result Note with Responsibility or a copy you are configured to use Result Notes with responsibility.\r\nReplace this Definition with 44-Result Note or a copy to turn off responsibility for Result Notes.','','Epic (Jason Ramaker) suggests that regions Disable Responsiblity for Result Note In Basket Messages, until a fix is available.  Whether or not responsibility is enabled for a given message type is dictated by the Message Type Definition associated with that message type at the system level.  To Disable responsibility, do the following:\r\nIn the Clinical Administration Menu (d ^LC) go to 1-Management Options > 11-In Basket Setup > 9-Epic-Wide Settings and page down to the Message Type Defaults screen.\r\nLook at the row for Message Type Result Notes (44)\r\nIf the Definition for this row is 1044-Result Note with Responsibility or a copy you are configured to use Result Notes with responsibility.\r\nReplace this Definition with 44-Result Note or a copy to turn off responsibility for Result Notes.',NULL,'',NULL,'1212535478ï££D111116ï££Resolution Action:  Upgraded Application\nResolution Description:  \nCause Code 1:  Business Partner\nCause Code 2:  \nCause Description:  ï£¢',736,NULL,NULL,141,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:40:00','2010-06-14 12:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(109,2682564,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Discrete Sigs May Appear Unexpectedly in Beacon (Oncology) Treatment Plans under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-08-15 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Jul 08 Kpckg',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SIGS','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  NCAL to pilot Beacon on 11/1 but discrete sigs not going in until later; no regions implementing discrete sigs before SP07\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I757687\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Changed to \"closed\" status 2/2/09; included in 11/08 install.','\"If a user creates a treatment plan using a Beacon (Oncology) protocol or order group configured with a discrete sig (where discrete sig ordering is not yet enabled and then enabled), the treatment plan might unexpectedly show the discrete sig.  However, regions have not enabled discrete sig ordering to be impacted by this incident.\r\nThere are two scenarios that cause the problem to occur:\r\nScenario #1\r\n1. In Clinical Administration, set the Method for entering medication information field (I LSD 9615) to 1-Order Free Text, Build Discrete.\r\n2. Build an order group with a discrete sig and free-text sig to match.\r\n3. In Hyperspace, add the order group you built to a treatment plan, change the free-text sig, and sign the order.\r\n4. Exit Hyperspace.\r\n5. In Clinical Administration, change the Method for entering medication information field to 3-Discrete Sigs.\r\n6. Log back in to Hyperspace and view the order. The discrete sig appears, even though the free-text sig is changed and the order is signed.\r\nScenario #2\r\n1. In Clinical Administration, set the Method for entering medication information field to 1-Order Free Text, Build Discrete.\r\n2. Build a protocol with a discrete sig and free-text sig that don\"t match.\r\n3. In Hyperspace, create a treatment plan using the protocol you built. Don\"t sign or modify the order.\r\n4. Exit Hyperspace.\r\n5. Set the Method for entering medication information field to 3-Discrete Sigs.\r\n6. Log back in to Hyperspace and view the order. The discrete sig appears until the order is signed, at which point the discrete sig is removed.\r\nAfter discrete sig ordering is active, newly entered treatment plans are not affected.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Discrete Sigs Go-Live expected 2010. Track until then.SP\"06, SP\"07--Beacon Update 12/27: Rebecca will talk with Dustin about this issue - Surreka will confirm when this will go in.3/6/08 Rebecca to check for item in May k pac.  4/30--per Epic, fix will be in July K-package.  6/12:  Discrete Sigs Go-Live expected 2010. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Kelly Miller) will provide status on the code fix as part of a KPackage to PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair), who will record this information in the PART tracking report which is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. To prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix as part of the KPackage when it becomes available. NCAL is going live with Beacon (Oncology) 11/1/07 but will not be implementing the Discrete Sig functionality at that time. Update from EPIC due 9/25/07 (KM)\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:41:00','2009-02-03 02:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(110,3427624,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Case or log SmartForm data may be lost, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, OpTime, Anesthesia',' I758973','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-28 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07, SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K072108',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108;  fix standard in SP08 IU3\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758973-E756189\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756189\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed 11/19/2008.  Gray out. ','Description:  Encounter-specific SmartForm data that is documented for a surgical or procedural visit may be lost while filing to concepts.  This can occur if the user does any of the following:\r\nDoes not specify a surgery date when the case is created and then schedules the case on any day other than the current; \r\nChanges the date of a standalone surgical or procedural log;\r\nChanges the date of a case.\r\nWhen the date of a case or standalone log is changed, the contact date in EPT is moved to a new date reflecting the new day of the visit, but the SmartForm data is not moved. As a result, SmartForm answers may be missing.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Inpatient, OpTime and Anesthesia.  Radiology (Radiant) can only be affected in IR cases in SP\"08. Epic (Ben Sherman) will provide a code fix (DLG I758973-E756189) as part of  the 072108 Kpackage. 5/29:  David O & Rebecca to follow up regarding correct PR. 6/2:  No regions are currently impacted as they aren\"t using Smart Forms to document within surgical cases or logs.  6/19: Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed). \r\n','None--NCI',NULL,'None--NCI',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:42:00','2008-11-21 11:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(111,3427634,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NoteWriter SmartBlock data may not be saved, in specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0620-PS-PR3427634-C7503810-E756274-Spr07Jul21NS.zip\r\n','K072108',NULL,'2008-08-20 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108; fix standard in SP08 IU3\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759077\nAD HOC DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 C7503810 & E756274 5/20/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production. ','\"Description:   NoteWriter data documented in SmartBlocks may disappear if in the following scenario where the user:\r\nCreates a new NoteWriter note.\r\nDocuments findings in a SmartBlock (e.g., Physical Exam)\r\nOpens another activity (e.g., Results Review).\r\nReturns to NoteWriter and documents on the same SmartBlock.\r\nReviews previously documented information on the SmartBlock.\r\nAs a result, all findings documented in #4 will disappear from the SmartBlock in #5.\r\nEpic (Brendan Krueger) will provide a code fix as part of  the 072108 KPackage\r\nFeatures:   NoteWriter with SmartForm SmartBlocks.  SP\"07 NoteWriter implemented with Review of Systems (\"\"ROS\"\":) SmartBlock record HHS 147 and no custom SmartBlocks are not impacted.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SP\"07-SP\"08 / IP, AMB, ED, Anesthesia - NO CURRENT IMPACT -   Epic (Brendan Krueger) will provide a code fix as part of  the 072108 Kpackage. 6/2:  Currently no regions are using smartblocks.  Andre to follow up to verify check if smartblocks will be used in the future. Tom to follow up with AMB. 6/10: It has been confirmed that no regions are currently affected by this issue.  To be impacted, regions must be using NoteWriter with SmartForm SmartBlocks with this ProgID:  E_MR_EMRNOTEWRITER75_MRNWSFHOST. 6/19:  NCAL Not affected - we are not using smartblocks. 6/23:  Adhoc fix arrived 0620-PS-PR3427634-C7503810-E756274-Spr07Jul21NS.zip, 0620-PS-PR3427634-C7503810-E756274-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z . Requires outage.  Want to get into July install, will miss last CAB date.  Andre M to expedite.  ED to implement SmartBlocks 7/26. Will we need workaround if we miss July outage? - - - Per Andre Mure, this code fix is NOT required for the 7/16/08 Release. The physicians are being trained to NOT use the Smart Blocks listed below.  Andre has spoken with Epic to have them run another query to determine if there are any additional SmartBlocks that could be effected on 7/26/08. 6/26:  Code will be in WITS2 on June 30th. 7/10:  Testing in progress. 7/14 To be submitted to CAB for 9/17 install as item requires outage.7/17 Going to CAB on Monday per Dhea possible install 8/20 if item doesn\"t require an outage.  7/21:  Per Andre, deferred to 7/28 CAB-8/20 install is fine (outage is not required-dependencies are already installed). 7/23:  Passed testing. 7/28:  CAB today. 7/31:  Passed CAB. 8/7:  Sched for Prod 8/20. \r\n','NoteWriter SmartBlock data may not be saved, in specific circumstances\r\n',NULL,'NoteWriter SmartBlock data may not be saved, in specific circumstances\r\n',NULL,'\"Discovered by:   Another Epic customer\r\nReported by:   Epic (Brendan Krueger).  6/23:  Per Andre Mure, this code fix is NOT required for the 7/16/08 Release.  \r\nThe physicians are being trained to NOT use the Smart Blocks listed below.  Andre has spoken with Epic to have them run another query to determine if there are any additional SmartBlocks that could be effected on 7/26/08.  Results will be received later today.  \r\nPER PART on 6/10: To be impacted, regions must be using NoteWriter with SmartForm SmartBlocks with this specific ProgID:  E_MR_EMRNOTEWRITER75_MRNWSFHOST.\r\nThis ProgID is most commonly used to customize generic SmartForms (not ROS/PE/HPI).  It is also included in the following Epic-released SmartBlocks which no regions are currently using:\r\n12013 - ANES EVAL\r\n12012 - ANES PHYSICAL EXAM\r\n12010 - ANES PLAN LINK\r\n12011 - ANES ROS / MED HX\r\n35202 - IP POST-OP ASSESSMENT & PLAN\r\n35201 - IP POST-OP OJBECTIVE\r\n35200 - IP POST-OP SUBJECTIVE\r\n156 - REVIEW_OF_SYSTEMS_CV\r\n157 - REVIEW_OF_SYSTEMS_ED (not currently used at regions)\r\nThis code fix requires a FULL OUTATGE and will be scheduled for Sept 17th Release.  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-13 03:46:00','2008-10-29 10:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(112,2587403,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Cancelled Historical Medication Information using Discrete Sig may be inaccurate depending upon certain circumstances','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-07-13 00:00:00','2009-08-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SIGS','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’06 K091007\n  SP’07 K091007\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/10/2009--email sent to BYee, Elissa Liong.  This issue fixed in 09/2007 k-package.  CLOSING. ','\" Cancelled Historical Medication Information using Discrete Sig may be inaccurate depending upon certain circumstances\r\n\"\r\n\"  When using the Medication Documentation navigator section to add a patient\"s historical medication, the medication information may be incorrectly saved. \r\nThis may occur with the following scenario, when a user:\r\nAdds a patient\"s historical medication, using the Medication Documentation navigator section, a discrete sig window appears.\r\nData is automatically populated (e.g. dose, frequency, instructions) in this window, according to the information associated with the medication record.\r\nClicks \"cancel\" (default data) in the Discrete Sig window, the information from the default is saved to the medication, instead of being discarded.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'(July) SP06 - SP07  NO CURRENT IMPACT no regions are currently using the affected functionality. 6/12:  Discreet Go-Live expected 2010. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide status on the code fix as part of a KPackage (SP\"07) to PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair), who will record this information in the PART tracking report which is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. Update 9/25:  No DLG available yet - not included in K091007\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NUL