he MAR.  Notice that the first administration that was linked (prednisone 10 mg) still appears as due on the pharmacy order even though the medication was administered.  The override pull appears as completed, but also does not display the administration. For the second linked administration (prednisone 20 mg), the administration information appears correctly on the pharmacy order with the icon indicating that it was linked to an override pull. Since the override pull for the second administration was linked correctly, the override pull no longer displays on the MAR.\r\nWorkflow 2:\r\nAn additional barcoding and linking medication workflow exists that may be confusing to an end user, which could result in medication administrations not being documented.  In this workflow the data is saved correctly, but the user may not realize that the medication administrations they started documenting on were not accepted and saved.  The workflow under which this occurs is as follows:\r\n1. Scan and documents multiple administrations without accepting\r\n2. Scan and select a pharmacy order which has a corresponding override pull\r\n3. On the linking form, change the selected Due time ? e.g., in this case change the selected Due time from 1640 to 1800 and click Accept\r\n4. When a Due time is changed, the user is returned to the MAR rather than continuing on to the MAR administration form.  The previous medications that were scanned and documented on are discarded as the user does not have the opportunity to accept the MAR administration form.  As expected, the MAR will continue to display these medications as ?Due? since the administrations were not accepted.  \r\nDuring this workflow, the end user may not realize that their previous medication administration information was not saved which could result in administrations not being documented on the MAR.\r\nAdhoc authorized by Bill Yee.\r\nConcern:  Administration for the medication is not visible on the MAR\r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Scott Adelman\r\nProblem Discovered by:   Another Epic Client\r\nEpic Representative / email address:  Maria Spinozzi /mspinozz@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation:   None.  Epic is developing a search, but NCAL will not be impacted until \r\n                      4/16/08.   \r\nAction items (future):   Epic will provide a fix ETA by 4/11/08. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fix installed, func turned off--periodic check with Andrea to see if func will be turned on.  04/04/2008 --  SP\"07 - IP, Rx, ED, Beacon, Op-time.  Adhoc: 3980--RFC:  CHG000002462078.  4/7:  Issue has to be replicated. Epic will provide a fix ETA by 4/11/08. Not planning to implement barcoding linkage feature (stated as workaround). Currently, functionality is not in use. Replication in progress.  4/14:  This functionality will not be inserted until fix is available.  4/21:  ETA for code status 4/25.  4/23:  received 0423-AP-PR3302762-E755860-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z.  4/28:  Unable to replicate.  Fix not yet moved into testing environment.  Surekha to follow up. 5/1/08:  Fix will be moved in to testing on Monday (5/5/08).  1 workflow replicated, 2 workflows not replicated. 5/5:  Fix will be installed into testing tonight.   5/8:  Code is installed in testing.  IP wants to wait until July to install.  Both fixes have to be installed at the sametime.  Expected SU:  i758650 (2nd fix).   5/15/08:  Fix will be tested with May Kpg and 2nd fix will be an adhoc expecting to be received. rebecca to follow up.  5/29:  Adhoc will be received on 6/10/08.  6/9: Yolanda to follow up with 2nd fix.  Per Yolanda, Not received from Epic as of yet, was due 6/10. 6/19:  2nd fix, cache & client installed in WITS2.  6/26:  Andre working with Beatrice on dependecy config  to have code tested.  Target install aiming for Sept.  6/30:  Passed testing (1st Fix), 2nd Fix Failed testing (being researched).  7/7:  Tom to follow up with AMB.  7/8:  from Carol Devlin: \"According to Cheryl Tran, Inpatient is testing this.  Macy Shia states that this workflow has to do with the new pyxis override linking to the original order functionality.    Macy also states that we don\"t have pyxis in ambulatory yet.   Based on this information, there is no way that ambulatory can test this.\"   7/21:  Code installed, but not yet configured.  Waiting for an update from Andrea regarding \"business sign-off\" (nursing board). 7/28:  Follow up with Andrea. 7/30:  Andrea tested this enhancement several times and is now comfortable with how it works. Andrea will perform a live demonstration at their meeting as requested by Bettianne. Due to the SAC go-live this cannot be done until the second Monday in August. So, we are still waiting for their approval. 8/7:  Andrea will present the proposed enhancement on Monday (8/11).  8/20:  per Andrea, on the agenda for next Monday, August 25th. 8/21:  Not impacting NCAL due to current configuration. 8/28:  Andrea to follow up with Epic. 9/4/08:  Presentation was not successful. Enhancement is not functioning properly.  Not affected due to enhancement not being turned on. Andrea to follow up with Epic. 9/11:  per AT: I am working with EPIC to see if we can make the documentation detail clearer. As it stands now Bettianne says this problem is a show stopper. 9/22:  Andrea still researching. 9/29/08: No Current Impact until functionality turned on.  10/27: Since not affected until functionality is turned on, moving row to No Current Impact Tab.  Andrea will notify if enhancement will be implemented. \r\n','Do not use the multiple administration barcoding workflow ? i.e., instead of scanning and documenting multiple administrations before accepting, accept each medication individually, or\r\n· Disable the capability to link override pulls to pharmacy orders. This can be done system wide using the System Definitions setting, or it can be done on a department by department level.\r\n',NULL,'Do not use the multiple administration barcoding workflow ? i.e., instead of scanning and documenting multiple administrations before accepting, accept each medication individually, or\r\n· Disable the capability to link override pulls to pharmacy orders. This can be done system wide using the System Definitions setting, or it can be done on a department by department level.\r\n',NULL,'Fix is in PROD (July 2008).  Functionality is not yet turned on.  Periodically check with Andrea Thorup if func. will be turned ON.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 01:44:00','2009-02-03 02:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(123,3322307,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2609690,'Race condition can cause overwrites of data in orders if using patient based order pre-allocation',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','I758565','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-11 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-08-04 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4121','All',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0530-AP-PR3322307-E756083-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z','K072108',NULL,'2008-09-17 00:00:00','N','P','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'7',NULL,NULL,'APR08','Y','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758565\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4121):  \n  SP’07 E756083 5/30/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  7',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8/7:  Sched for Prod install Sept 17th. ','Due to a race condition if two separate processes create an order record at the same time it is possible for both processes to use the same ORD record.  When this happens some data from one of the orders will be overwritten with data from the other order.  Another symptom of this issue is duplicate order IDs in ORD 19000.  If the order type for the shared ORD record is a medication (999) then the MAR will error out when loading your medications.  To be affected by this issue a region must be using patient based order pre-allocation.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'All versions, all apps affected.  Andre Mure is checking the NCAL configuration setting for ORD_PreAlloc. 4/14:  A&I will work on the config change as a workaround.  4/21:  Kelly to follow up.  4/24:  One affected patient found. Kelly working with Sandra to remove a performance enhancement config currently in production.  4/28:  A&I testing in progress.  Kelly to check with Sandra.  5/1/08:  Performance enhancement has been backed out.  Workaround in place. 5/8:  Fix in the July 08 Kpkg. 5/21:  Adhoc is available-has not been requested yet. 5/22 Adhoc will be requested per Kelly R. 5/29:  Adhoc:  4121 / RFC:  2609690. 6/2:  Adhoc has been received. Fix will be installed in WITS 2&3.  6/5/08:  WITS2 already installed & WITS3 will be installed 6/5.  6/9: Theresa to follow up. 6/19:  Installed in WITS3 on 6/5. Will be submitted to CAB on monday.  Passed AMB testing. 6/26:  IP to test.  Target install date aiming for Sept.  Outage required. 7/3:  Waiting for Testing status from Susan Taylor. 7/7:  Testing in progress. 7/17 Per Dhea testing in progress for IP. 7/28:  Passed testing, going to CAB today. 7/31:  Defferred in CAB. Going to CAB 8/4. 8/7:  Sched for Prod install Sept 17th. 9/24: vadidated, grey out\r\n','Epic presented the following workaround as \"airtight\".   Epic (Kristie Reimer) suggests that impacted regions (NCAL, SCAL, and HI) may turn off patient based order pre-allocation (by setting the mnemonic (ORD_PreAlloc) equal to 0, and this will prevent this issue from occurring.  Although this feature is to enhance system performance, setting this configuration will not severely degrade the system\"s performance.',NULL,'Epic presented the following workaround as \"airtight\".   Epic (Kristie Reimer) suggests that impacted regions (NCAL, SCAL, and HI) may turn off patient based order pre-allocation (by setting the mnemonic (ORD_PreAlloc) equal to 0, and this will prevent this issue from occurring.  Although this feature is to enhance system performance, setting this configuration will not severely degrade the system\"s performance.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 01:48:00','2008-10-29 10:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(124,3352339,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Pertinent Negative Entries may be Inaccurate in Past Medical History under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'All',' I758805 ','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-23 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Weisenthal ',NULL,NULL,'','SU05 thru SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'wait for Kpckg','0714-PS-PR3443190-C7503898-E756865-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z','K011408, K072108',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  involves two fixes, one in Jan Kpackag and one in July Kpackage Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I755860, I758805 \nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’06 E744917\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011408-E753827  & K072108\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed 11/19/2008.  Gray out. ','SU\"05-SP\"07 - - Pertinent Negative Entries may be Inaccurate in Past Medical History under specific circumstances.  Pertinent negative entries, under the Pertinent Negatives Tab in History Activity, may unexpectedly move to the Past Medical History. \r\nSample scenario of occurrence: \r\n1.  In loading patient history information, the problem list is checked against the list of pertinent negatives for conflicts.\r\n2.  If a conflict is found, then the conflicting diagnosis is automatically removed from pertinent negatives and added to past medical history.\r\n3.  If a patient has a diagnosis in the pertinent negatives that is not a default diagnosis to a medical history question and has a pertinent negative lower in the list of pertinent negatives that conflict with the problem list, then incorrect entries in pertinent negatives can unexpectedly move over to medical history every time the activity is opened.\r\nRisk Assignment Made by:  Dr. Andy Weisenthal\r\nProblem Discovered by:   Another Epic Client\r\nEpic Representative / email address:  Jason Ramaker / JRamaker@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation:  Queries are being run by Epic (Jason Ramaker), who will work with regional ACs, to identify any affected patient charts, to ensure Past Medical Histories are correct for all regions.  It is anticipated that the queries will be completed by 4/26/08.\r\nAction items (immediate):  SP\"07: E753827 (sent in January KPackage; therefore, fix believed to be in NCAL production).\r\n       SP\"06: E744917 (has not yet been delivered to Kaiser)\r\n       SU\"05: E734126 (has not yet been delivered to Kaiser)\r\nAction items (future):    Wait for the query to be completed by Epic.  NCAL should try to replicate the problem in production; should not be able to do so.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"4/23/08:  All regions affected--Ambulatory, Inpatient, ED, OpTime, Beacon,  EpicWeb, and MyChart.  Wait for the query to be completed by Epic.  NCAL to replicate.  4/24:  Andre to replicate.  4/28:  Unable to replicate.  Andre to follow up with Epic regarding query.  4/29: According to Epic (Jason Ramaker), the searches have completed in all regions except SCAL.  In summary: Not affected - GA, HI, NW, NCAL, OH, MAS; Affected - CO; Search pending - SCAL. 5/1/08:  Epic follow up states there are different variations of this incident (listed in col D).  Andre will follow up with Epic.  5/5:  NCAL doesn\"t have any records affected.  Graying row. 5/29:   Epic (Jason Ramaker)  research indicated that an additional fix is needed to resolve this problem (3352339).  In additon to the fix in the January KPackage (DLG I755860), impacted regions will also need to install DLG I758805, which has not yet been released. Epic will provide updated information on this fix by June 6.  Please note that DLG I758805 is also the fix to PART incident 3443190. Colored the row \"\"White\"\" due to this comment.  Should this be re-opened or gray? 6/9: per Rebecca, second fix will be in July K-pckg (7/21). 7/7: (2nd part of issue/fix) Per Apoorva, NCAL is not affected. NCAL will be waiting for July Kpkg. 7/14/08:  Per file description, this PS issue is resolved by the fix for PS PR3443190.  File Received & included in July Kpkg (confirmed). ','None',NULL,'None',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 01:50:00','2009-01-12 12:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(126,3373034,1,'OPT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'In the anesthesia workflow conductor, patient responses to certain QuickForm questions are not pre-populating from previous encounters',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Anesthesia','E756092','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-30 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4045','SP07, SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0522-AP-PR3373034-E756092-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z','K072108',NULL,'2008-09-17 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,'APR08','Y','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  National has a config workaround that was propagated to NCAL & SCAL on May 1. Confirmed in K072108. Epic confirmed regions can install ad hoc and keep WIP until national completes work.\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758833\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4045):  \n  SP’07 E756092 5/22/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production.','Detail Description:  For SP07, SP08--In the anesthesia workflow conductor, patient responses to certain QuickForm questions are not pre-populating from previous encounters.   The areas affected are adult evaluations, pediatrics evaluations, and updates.   The info is not displaying incorrectly; it is missing.  \r\nThere are five questions known to be affected, including:\r\n1.  ASA rating\r\n2.  Emergency status\r\n3.  Anesthesia alerts\r\n4.  Patient interview status\r\n5.  Documented by\r\nConcern:  Critical patient information may be missing during surgery \r\nSuites Affected:    Anesthesia, Optime, Inpatient \r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. George Peredy\r\nProblem Discovered by:   NCAL anesthesiologist in Walnut Creek / Antioch. \r\nRemediation:   No remediation was discussed.\r\nAction items (immediate):   NCAL and SCAL regions must communicate to anesthesiologists to be alert to the possibility of missing patient responses in the workflow conductor.  The workaround (item #271) will be implemented by the National team within 24 to 48 hours.   Dr. Bliss has approved an adhoc, #4045.  \r\nAction items (future):   Epic is working on a fix, will provide an ETA for delivery by May 7.  Item #271 must be reset when the code fix is installed in production.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'  8/4: per Apoorva:  As we discussed during the meeting, installing the fix code E756092 is not expected to have any negative impact on the current workaround. After installing the fix code, the workaround should be kept in place until National makes the intended change. 8/7:  The ad hoc fix (E756092) is available and is being tested by Natl OpTime AC\"s.  Epic (Apoorva Agarwal) confirms that installing the fix will not affect the workaround.  After installing the fix, regions should keep the workaround in place until National makes the intended change.','There is an item #271, a QuickForm field, which determines whether the application accesses local or National default programming point values.  It will be set to permit the former (local programming point access.)  Item #271 will not affect NCAL?s build and will protect patients for now. ',NULL,'There is an item #271, a QuickForm field, which determines whether the application accesses local or National default programming point values.  It will be set to permit the former (local programming point access.)  Item #271 will not affect NCAL?s build and will protect patients for now. ',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 02:09:00','2008-10-29 11:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(128,3374011,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Duplicate allergies--if one of the duplicates is deleted, none of the duplicates may show on a remote deployment',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-30 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4090','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0516-CE-PR3374011-E756114-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z   Please note this does not fix the workflow issue #3 - this will be fixed as part of the July Kpackage.  This fix must go in first, in order to prevent the deletion of the duplicate allergy record.  ','K072108',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  At of 5/27/08, no region has requested the second fix as an ad hoc so it will be delivered in the July Kpackage. Confirmed in K072108 which all regions will install as part of SP07 \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758851/I757514\nAD HOC DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 E756114  5/16/08 & C7503634 as of 6/11/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Changed to \"closed\" status 2/2/09; included in 11/08 install.','Detail Description:  Normally duplicate allergy records for one allergen are not allowed.  Today, however, chart merge, among other causes, can create duplicate allergies (i.e., two allergy records pointing to the same allergen) for a patient.   An admin person can run a query and identify duplicate allergies, then attempt to delete one of the allergy records in the patient\"s home deployment.   In this situation, neither of the duplicate allergy records will show on a remote deployment.   Note:  must be an admin person who deletes the duplicate, as end users do not currently have that ability.  Ability will be available to end users with the July K-package to delete duplicate allergies.   \r\nConcern:  Allergy info for a patient may be missing on a remote deployment\r\nSuites Affected:   Care Everywhere \r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Andy Weisenthal\r\nProblem Discovered by:   Epic testing for July 08 K-package\r\nRemediation:  Epic (Robert Shimmin) is working on an RA to identify and correct historically affected records, will work with Colin Parker.  \r\nAction items (immediate):   Regions must communicate to administrators not to delete duplicate allergy records.  Fix is expected to be in the July K-package, when the ability for end users to delete duplicate allergy records will be enabled.  \r\nAction items (future):   Epic is working on a fix..  No adhoc has been requested as yet.  Robert and Colin will work together to determine the need for remediation.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed). 7/21:  Tom to follow up with Epic (Robert).  7/23:  per Robert Shimmin, \"the provider may find themselves unable to delete all of the documentation  for ?No Known Allergies.?  However, they are still able to document any additional allergies they wish.  The patient chart will then include both ?No Known Allergies,? and the newly documented allergies.  This situation is less than ideal, but NCAL providers are aware of it and have seen it for years.  After the client fix in the July K-package, providers will be able to mark all duplicate allergy documentations, including ?No Known Allergies? documentations, as ?Deleted? in a patient?s chart. As this has been an ongoing issue since NCAL has been live on Hyperspace, we don?t feel that an accelerated delivery of this SU (which has 90 client dependencies and 1200+ server dependencies) would justify the gain of installing a couple of months ahead of the July K-package.\" 7/31:  Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed). ','Only workaround is to inform administrators not to delete duplicate allergy records.   Colin Parker, CE manager for NCAL and SCAL, will review the records to determine if they can be tied back to a user. ',NULL,'Only workaround is to inform administrators not to delete duplicate allergy records.   Colin Parker, CE manager for NCAL and SCAL, will review the records to determine if they can be tied back to a user. ',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 02:17:00','2009-02-02 03:17:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(129,2967951,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Patient Chart Merge causes some LDA information to be hidden','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-11-29 00:00:00','2009-09-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','sp08','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','Y','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'STANDARD IN RELEASE:  SP08\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/10/09: Per Y. Lassiter\'s 9/10/09 email, validation of fix in prod cannot be done; install of fix was confirmed.','SU05 - SP07:  Patient Chart Merge causes some LDA information to be hidden.\r\n\"When a Line/Drain/Airway (LDA) documentation flowsheet  is added to a patient?s chart, and that patient chart is later merged into another existing patient chart, some of the original information regarding that LDA is not available to the end user.  Specifically:\r\nThe original properties (e.g., incision site and time) of the LDA do not display either in the Documentation Flowsheet activity or in print group 46550 - IP Active Lines/Drains/Airways. \r\nThe LDA is not listed under existing LDAs when you try to add an LDA of the same type. \r\nThe properties info is not lost if it appears in the target chart; it is only lost when the info is in the source chart. \r\nThe assessment information entered into individual time columns from the Documentation Flowsheet activity or the flowsheet section of a navigator is not affected and is fully visible to the end user. \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'07/22/09: Per Chris Russell: associated with PR 3212027.  This was delivered in the 5/12/08 K-Package. Dhea to certify and close\r\nFix is slated for SP08 which is planned for NCAL in 2009.  VB to check with Caroline Rogers re workaround config for chrt merge, and Dr. Hoberman re communication to users.  Were the workarounds applied in NCAL?  Update 01/09/08:Per Caroline Rogers - The K Package has been installed and configured in Production.  The setting is to only allow a merge to the Target Patient while admitted (the setting will prevent merging  to a Source Patient that was currently admitted).   Update 1/10: Workarounds applied. Ok to wait until SP08.','\"Epic recommended the regions activate a configuration setting available with the March 07 K-package.  The setting prevents chart merging when the source MRN is admitted to a facility.   This will help reduce the likelihood of the patient safety condition.   The LDA info can also disappear if merging occurs during patient discharge, but this was considered more of a medical / legal issue than patient safety.   \r\nThe other suggestion offered was, when merging, to make sure the LDA data to be saved is in the target chart, as opposed to the source chart.    \r\nRemediation:  Epic tech support can run a \"\"rough\"\" utility which will remediate an individual patient chart, if it is suspected that the LDA info for that single patient was lost in a merge.  \"\r\n','','\"Epic recommended the regions activate a configuration setting available with the March 07 K-package.  The setting prevents chart merging when the source MRN is admitted to a facility.   This will help reduce the likelihood of the patient safety condition.   The LDA info can also disappear if merging occurs during patient discharge, but this was considered more of a medical / legal issue than patient safety.   \r\nThe other suggestion offered was, when merging, to make sure the LDA data to be saved is in the target chart, as opposed to the source chart.    \r\nRemediation:  Epic tech support can run a \"\"rough\"\" utility which will remediate an individual patient chart, if it is suspected that the LDA info for that single patient was lost in a merge.  \"\r\n',NULL,'\"Victoria will speak off-line with Diane Arterberry and Melissa McCormick to determine how NCAL can set the configuration setting to disallow chart merging during admissions, as recommended by Epic. Update 01/09/08: Per Caroline Rogers: Diane Arterberry\"s response is listed below:   \r\nAny LDA data on a flowsheet for the customized rows could be impacted if the data is on the Source record.  It could impact past and current LDA data in that record.  The data is still at the database level but may not be visible to the end user.\r\n  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 03:25:00','2009-09-10 03:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(130,2957575,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'IntraConnect (Care Everywhere) Print Group - Incorrect order information may display for a patient admitted in remote deployment, in certain circumstances','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'CE','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-11-21 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','sp08','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','Y','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'STANDARD IN RELEASE:  SP08\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09:  Closing.  See note in Next Step History from Chris Russell @ Epic. ','IntraConnect (Care Everywhere) Print Group - Incorrect order information may display for a patient admitted in remote deployment, in certain circumstances\r\n\" Medication or procedure order information for a patient admitted in a remote deployment is displayed instead as the details of another order from a different MRN, under specific circumstances.  This occurs in the remote location if the standard remote hospital admissions report, which is not designed to work with hyperlinks, is customized to include print groups with hyperlinks that link to print groups with hyperlinks.   \r\nThe same information displays correctly in the patient\"s home deployment. Results information is unaffected. \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Per Chris Russell: \"We have no Epic record (SLG, QAN, DLG) for this incident, but we do have record (emails) that this was resolved with proper configuration.  Since this was a setup problem, no fix is necessary.\"  All versions, affects SCAL, NCAL.  W/A in place in both. Waiting for SP08.','\"Workaround:   In the remote hospital admissions report, replace print groups containing hyperlinks with recommended print groups that provide similar functionality.  Although affected regions can make the changes, the print groups must be propagated and validated by Collaborative Build/EMFI.\r\nSCAL (John Mattison) and NCAL (Victoria I Burbidge) immediately applied the workaround as a temporary solution.  \r\nIntraConnect (Gayatri Aravindakumar and Kevin Isbell) worked with SCAL and NCAL ACs to propagate the replacement print groups, completing on 11/21/07.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Workaround:   In the remote hospital admissions report, replace print groups containing hyperlinks with recommended print groups that provide similar functionality.  Although affected regions can make the changes, the print groups must be propagated and validated by Collaborative Build/EMFI.\r\nSCAL (John Mattison) and NCAL (Victoria I Burbidge) immediately applied the workaround as a temporary solution.  \r\nIntraConnect (Gayatri Aravindakumar and Kevin Isbell) worked with SCAL and NCAL ACs to propagate the replacement print groups, completing on 11/21/07.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'A permanent fix still needs to be planned.  PART (Chris Okon) will initiate a bridge the week of 11/26/07 with Epic, SCAL, and NCAL to review requirements for a permanent code fix.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 03:28:00','2009-07-22 02:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(131,2587007,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'\"Blue-Style\" Print Groups may be Inaccurate under certain circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-08-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','sp08','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'P',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  KP does not plan to use IE 7 in SP07, so will be impacted. Workaround is communication to not use more contiguous set characters than will fit on one line of printed page. \r\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: Waiting for SU09.  ','\"Blue-Style\" Print Groups may be Inaccurate under certain circumstances\r\n Print groups that use the\"blue-style\" feature for report printing may be inaccurate if using more contiguous characters than can fit on one line on the printed page (depends on font, character size).  Although the information displays properly on screen and in the database, the information is \"truncated\" or \"cut-off\" when printed, dropping all lines of the report beyond the report width.  Additionally, there is an interdependency of using any Microsoft Internet Explorer version before version 7.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'SP06--occurred in MAS in AMB setting. Confirming with Jansin if NCAL affected. Jansin says we can wait for SP07. - Per PART - Fixed in Spring08. 10/22/07:  Confirm with Jansin to wait until SP\"08 & Check IE version conflicts with Kelly.   10/29/07:  Don Martin will check with physician leadership & see if it is ok to wait until SP\"08.  Decision for waiting for SP08 will be made 11/13.  11/19/07:  ok to wait & pick up in SP\"08.','\"Impacted regions (CO, Exempla, GA, MAS, NCAL, OH, and SCAL) could send out a communication to inform users to not use more contiguous characters than could fit on a one line on a printed page and to review a report prior to distribution,  for \"\"blue-style\"\" reports.\r\nRegions should contact PART Communications if they would like to discuss this incident.\"\r\n','','\"Impacted regions (CO, Exempla, GA, MAS, NCAL, OH, and SCAL) could send out a communication to inform users to not use more contiguous characters than could fit on a one line on a printed page and to review a report prior to distribution,  for \"\"blue-style\"\" reports.\r\nRegions should contact PART Communications if they would like to discuss this incident.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"This problem is corrected with SP\"07 if Regions are using Microsoft Internet Explorer version 7 formatting.  Update 8/13:  TS spoke with Lynne Moore who reported prob in MAS.  Issue occurred when a long string > 80 chars used to divide reports.  Confirming w/ Jansin if NCAL affected. Jansin says this problem is known and affects more than just blue style.  Can wait for fix but asks for Dr. Bliss to confirm.    Update 9/7: Blue Style Print groups:  Per Epic could be refreshable smartlinks. The text that is blue is ?refreshable? which means that you can right click on the blue information to refresh the note with the most recent patient data.  Per Kim Rich of KP: It is a configuration, that can be made with the Report Master file that is changed to Blue in the Stylesheet prompt.  By changing the report to Blue, changes the style/display to this new bluestyle view. The config is done within any Report that you want to display in bluestyle.  10/17/07:  PART request to know if we will wait until SP\"08. Notified PART-Yes. 10/22/07:  Confirm with Jansin to wait until SP\"08 & Check IE version conflicts with Kelly. 11:08am: Per Marco Lopez-If IE7 (Internet Explorer 7) formatting is not used when upgrade to Spring 07, then we will potentially be affected by this issue if we use contiguous set of characters than can fit on one line on a printed page.\r\nIE7 would only be supported by Epic beginning version Spring 07. While in Spring 06 or lower, it should be communicated to used not to use contiguous set characters than may NOT potentially fit on one line on the printed page.  10/29/07:  Don Martin will check with physician leadership & see if it is ok to wait until SP\"08.   11/19/07:  ok to wait & pick up in SP\"08.  Kaiser is not planning on using IE7. \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 03:30:00','2009-12-02 11:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(132,2657112,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Non-telephone pended med orders routed to a physician\"s Inbasket and refused may still be approved and sent to the Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-08-07 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','sp08','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'P',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'SU09','A','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Code is only partial fix. Regions need to keep config workaround in place until SP08 release.\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I745266, I752887\r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP06 K071607 E743652\r\n  SP07 K071607 E751705\r\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: Waiting for SU09.  Workaround in place.','Non-telephone pended med orders routed to a physician\"s Inbasket and refused may still be approved and sent to the Pharmacy. \r\n\" Under certain configuration setups, a medication order which a Clinician marks as \"\"refused\"\" may show up  incorrectly as \"\"accepted\"\".  In a potential scenario, a nurse would open an orders-only encounter in Visit Navigator, order and pend the medication,  and then route it to a physician\"s In Basket for approval.  If a physician refuses the medication, it will incorrectly appear as signed and approved in both Order Entry and Chart Review.  The order goes through order transmittal and will display to Pharmacy as an approved medication order.\r\nPreliminary Epic research indicates that this occurs when a region\"s visit navigator template contains a ROUTTEL section (allowing you to route medication for approval) and a non-telephone encounter type is configured in an EpicCare profile. A non-telephone encounter is one other than telephone or refill that is NOT listed in the profile item which allows you to enter types that should behave as a telephone encounter. \r\nNote that this problem was reported earlier under PR 1492224 in April, 2006, but was closed, as no regions were found to have configurations which allowed the problem to occur.     \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'SU05 thru SP07--NCAL workaround in place, no adhoc expected.  Track until SP08.','\"Epic suggested two workarounds: \r\n1.  Enter non-telephone encounters in profile item, 2.  Remove ROUTTEL navigator section (this is NCAL\"s solution, as selected by Carol and Lisa) \"\r\n','','\"Epic suggested two workarounds: \r\n1.  Enter non-telephone encounters in profile item, 2.  Remove ROUTTEL navigator section (this is NCAL\"s solution, as selected by Carol and Lisa) \"\r\n',NULL,'\"NCAL AMB has made the appropriate workaround changes.  Carol Devlin and Lisa Pfeifer have previously indicated to PART that we can live with the workaround until we receive the standard fix in SP08 (2009?).  \r\nEpic says fix is standard in SP08.   No adhoc previous to SP08 is forthcoming. \r\nPer Carol 8/10: the \"\"routtel\"\" section of the RX Request encounter in the CCM profile (5110) was removed.   10/17/07: PART states: Code is only partial fix. Regions need to keep config workaround in place until SP08 release.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 03:35:00','2009-09-28 03:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(133,2690857,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'PTA Meds mistakenly reordered ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-08-20 00:00:00','2009-08-11 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','sp08','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','A','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  okay to wait for SP08 considering incident mildness\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/11/09: Consensus to close.','Prior To Admission (PTA) medications may be mistakenly reordered under a very specific workflow \r\n\"In the Orders section of the Admission Navigator, it is possible to mark Prior to Admission (PTA) medications as Order and Don\"t Order.  If a clinician opens and closes the order section a minimum of 4 times to order or to cancel a PTA medication for the same patient, it could result in the clinician signing an unintended order, which was meant to have been marked Don\"t Order.  There is no problem if the clinician simply opens and closes the Orders section without making any changes to the patient\"s orders, even if this is done multiple (4 or more) times.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: Per Chris Russell:  fixed with med rec in ?08, also SUed to ?07, in the May \'08 K-package.  Dhea to certify / close. \r\nSP\"06 - SP\"07--Epic plans to fix in SP08 Highly improbable, PART is requesting NCAL PART for feasibility for retro-fix to SP07 - 10/11/07 - victoria pls confirm okay to wait till Spring08 - per VB okay to wait - unlikely workflow.  10/22/07:  Waiting until SP\"08.','',NULL,'',NULL,'Given the unlikely nature of this workflow, no fixes are planned, however, this problem will be fixed in the SP\"08 release. Update 9/17 from PART (Laurel): The original thought was that we could wait for SP\"08 to fix this, since it was so improbable.  However, I understand that NCAL requested that we look into the feasibility of including a fix in a KPackage for SP\"07.We talked with Epic and learned that Epic is working right now on the SP\"08 fix.  So far they know that it involves a client change and appears to be complex, but they don\"t yet know how complex, and can\"t yet predict how long it would take to retrofit.So, we are once again in a situation where we need to carefully balance the amount of effort involved in retrofitting to SP\"07, comparative to the risk posed to our patients.   Knowing that this is most likely a pretty complex fix, that would take Epic some time to develop, do you still feel that this incident is worthy of encouraging Epic to provide a SP\"07 fix? Update 9/20: Dr. Bliss checked with VB, ok to wait for SP08, pls verify with VB. 10/10 PART requesting NCAL  response.  10/17/07:  PART requested response to wait?-Notified PART we will wait.  10/22/07:  Waiting until SP\"08.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 03:42:00','2009-08-11 11:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(134,2585056,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Print Groups using IP \"Adjust Individual Times\" hyperlink may be inaccurate depending on specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-07-12 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'3375','sp08','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'P',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  \r\n\r\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: Waiting for SU09.','Print Groups using IP \"Adjust Individual Times\" hyperlink may be inaccurate depending on specific circumstances\r\n\"A procedure with multiple occurrences can have individual times adjusted using the Adjust Individual Times hyperlink from a Patient Summary report.  If this hyperlink is used to adjust times for released orders so that two occurrences are scheduled on the same day and time (a user error), then the Patient Summary report will only show one of the duplicate occurrences, leading to the potential for the patient to receive one less occurrence than intended. In addition, if the procedure has a task attached, one of the tasks that would correspond to the duplicate time will disappear. \r\nFor example:\r\n· Patient is scheduled for a hematocrit at 10 am, 12 Noon and 2 pm.\r\n· The 12 Noon time is released but not yet performed.\r\n· A user inappropriately adjusts the 2 pm time to 12 Noon.\r\nConsequently, the patient receives the 12 Noon scheduled procedure and is not given the 2 pm procedure.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'SU05 thru SP07:  affects procedures, not meds. Marc Flagg-- \"This is a critical part of the Inpatient Lab workflow.  We can not deactivate this functionality.\" Update 9/11:  Victoria and Marc Flagg both agree after meeting with Epic, this is not Critical for NCAL, see Column D, 9/18 from PART are we waiting for ADHOC? No not waiting for adhoc. 10/22/07:  Waiting for SP\"08.',' Deactivate (or otherwise, remove, not use) the \"adjust individual times\" hyperlink.  Taking the workaround completely protects the patient from this problem occurring.   \r\n','',' Deactivate (or otherwise, remove, not use) the \"adjust individual times\" hyperlink.  Taking the workaround completely protects the patient from this problem occurring.   \r\n',NULL,'\"NCAL must decide if we want to take the workaround.   NCAL is the only region using the hyperlink.   \r\nEpic is working on the fix.  Do we wish to adhoc?  Epic does not yet know when the fix will be ready, or in which K-package it will be delivered.  Epic is waiting for NCAL to determine how urgently we need the fix--i.e., can we live with the workaround until the future K-package is installed? \r\nUpdate 8/29:  KP notifed Epic that proposed workaround does not work for NCAL and they would like to proceed with ad hoc. Epic discussed with LAK 8/22. LAK (Laurel Kerrihard) (PART) to contact NCAL re: this issue. Update 9/7:  PART notified Epic, NCAL would like adhoc.  Workaround does not work for NCAL. Update 9/11:  From VB -  NCAL ranked this as \"\"High Impact\"\" due to the fact that the workaround recommended by Epic which is to remove the hyperlink is not viable in NCAL.   An adhoc was requested to receive an expeditious fix.  Today, I met with Apoorva and Dustin from Epic to obtain deeper understanding on this issue.   After the meeting, I am agreeing with Epic that this is not a high priority.  My reasons are as follow:\r\n1.   The workflow is rare where an end user will change 2 different scheduled time occurrences to the one scheduled time.  Less likely that an end user will change 2 different scheduled time to the same time such as scheduling a 10am to 2pm and 6pm to 2pm.  If erroneous, the end user can re-schedule using the reschedule hyperlink\r\n2.   No impact to the ancillary messages.  Once the test is released to the ancillary, the procedure will be performed\r\n3.  When the frequency is displayed in the PERO, the scheduled time is displayed.  End user can view the time and correct if erroneous\r\n\r\nPer Dustin, the fix  is not slated until SP08 but will let us know if able to add to a K-Package.\r\n10/22/07:  Waiting for SP\"08.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 04:04:00','2009-09-28 03:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(135,2557863,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'I/O table time columns misaligned','','',NULL,NULL,'IP, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-06-27 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','sp08','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'P',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','S','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Severe , workaround to be implemented by regions until SP08 where fix is standard. \r\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: Waiting for SU09.',' It is possible for the time columns displayed in the Intake/Output table to become temporarily misaligned. When this happens, all of the data columns will be shifted one column to the right, while the Date and Time header remains fixed. \r\n\"For this issue to occur, the following conditions must be met: \r\na. The table must be in a two column per day view - either the 12-hour interval or shift interval option (with two shifts per day as defined in the shift start time section of the department record). \r\nb. There must be a 3 day or more gap in the recorded intake or output data. \r\nWhen these conditions are met and the date navigation arrow is used to jump from a time frame with data to one without and then to the earliest timeframe with data, the columns with data will be misaligned with the Date and Time header of the table. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Update 9/7:  NCAL using 8 hour shift intervals.  NCAL not impacted.  11/19/07:  Waiting for SP\"08. SP06 - SP07--has been replicated.  Epic will fix in SP08 until a region adhocs. No region has adhoced. Update 9/7:  NCAL using 8 hour shift intervals.  NCAL not impacted.  11/19/07:  Waiting for SP\"08. \r\n','Selecting the Refresh button or leaving the table and then returning will correct the misalignment. \r\n','','Selecting the Refresh button or leaving the table and then returning will correct the misalignment. \r\n',NULL,' If a region requires fix, it must ask for an adhoc or wait for K-pckg.  11/19/07:  Waiting for SP\"08. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-14 04:09:00','2009-09-28 03:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(136,3662974,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Antibiotic administration times may not display properly with certain print group','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-12 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Fixed in IU4 so wont impact KP; closed out\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, SP08 only, does not affect SP07, fixed in SU09.  ','\"Description:  Administration times of antibiotics in Intra-op Anesthesia may display incorrectly or not at all if Print group 89056-ANESTHESIA INTRAOP ABX or a copy is used in any of the affected applications.\r\n \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Waiting for SP08.  No Current Impact.  SP\"08 - Intra-op Anesthesia - Antibiotic administration times may not display properly with certain print group\r\nIP, ED, OpTime, ANES. NO CURRENT IMPACT.  Fix will be a part of a Kpkg (per Dustin Foster).  NCAL, NW, Exempla, and CO could be potentially impacted if they do not install the fix when they upgrade to SP\"08.\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'\"Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing. \r\nPhysician Representative:  N/A (no current impact incident)\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-15 09:06:00','2009-07-22 02:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(137,3195855,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Panels in Order Sets and Navigators with Multiple Alternatives Not Loading All Alternative Orders','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-02-19 00:00:00','2009-08-11 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510479\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757795/C75031192\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/11/09: Consensus to close.','SU?04 ? SP?07 - IP Only-No Current Impact - Panels in Order Sets and Navigators with Multiple Alternatives Not Loading All Alternative Orders\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: Per Chris Russell:  07 SU (I7510479/E757795/C75031192) associated with TD 30624, in the 1/19/09 K-Package, ad hoc on 12/3/08.  Dhea to certify / close.   \r\n\"No Current Impact  SU?04 ? SP07 / Inpatient, Epic RX, ED, Optime, Oncology.  No Adhoc requested. NCAL will not be utilizing affected Ordersets or  Preference Lists. 2/27:  Fix will be standard in SP\"08. 2/28: Dhea will followup with Inpatient to confirm impact [Alice] 3/3: Dhea confirmed with Inpatient and will not install. 3/10: No status change. 3/13:  Ok to wait until SP\"08.\r\n\"\r\n','\" In the panel record, set Suppress Alternate Checking to ?Yes? so alternatives do not appear for the medications or procedures when they are placed as part of a panel.\r\nAnother option would be to switch the medications/procedures in the panel so that the panel directly references the alternatives rather than the meds/procedures they currently contain.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\" In the panel record, set Suppress Alternate Checking to ?Yes? so alternatives do not appear for the medications or procedures when they are placed as part of a panel.\r\nAnother option would be to switch the medications/procedures in the panel so that the panel directly references the alternatives rather than the meds/procedures they currently contain.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\" SU?04 ? SP?07 / Inpatient, Epic RX, ED, Optime, Oncology.  IP Only-No Current Impact - Panels in Order Sets and Navigators with Multiple Alternatives Not Loading All Alternative Orders.  No Adhoc requested.NCAL will not be utilizing Ordersets or  Preference Lists. 2/27:  Fix will be standard in SP\"08. 3/13:  Ok to wait until SP\"08.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-15 09:15:00','2009-08-11 11:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(138,3272887,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Discontinuing a Signed & Held Discharge Order from Print Group 34220 Puts Canceled Order in Order Entry under specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-25 00:00:00','2009-09-28 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No regions impacted as long as dont put impacted print group in place. Epic to inform us of SP08 fix\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758342\nAD HOC DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 E756367 & C7503789 6/18/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’06 K072108-- E758670 & C7503789\nRISK RANKING:  8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28:  CLOSING. Yolanda asked via email to let us know if we should reopen.  ','SU05 - SP07--IP & Ed (only): Discontinuing a Signed & Held Discharge Order from Print Group 34220 Puts Canceled Order in Order Entry under specific circumstances\r\n If a user signs and holds a discharge order and then, discontinues the signed and held order (through an enabled\"Discontinue\" hyperlink), the order appears in order entry.  The user may then sign the order (from order entry), but nothing happens to the order.  It remains in its discontinued state.  Only after the user leaves the patient chart, does the order appear as discontinued.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'07/22/09: Per Chris Russell:  installed 9/17/08.  Part of July 08 K-package.  Dhea to certify and close.  No Current Impact-SU05 - SP07--IP & Ed (only)-could be impacted if - a) using the Print Group 34220 AND b) have it configured (enabled) to display the Discontinue hyperlink. 3/27: Dhea to communicate to IP that this print group should not be used.  4/10:  Per Dhea the print group will not be used. Fix standard in SP\"08-ok to wait. \r\n','If using Print Group 34220 (and/or copies), configure parameter -IP Take Home Meds to not display the \"Discontinue\" Hyperlink.\r\n','','If using Print Group 34220 (and/or copies), configure parameter -IP Take Home Meds to not display the \"Discontinue\" Hyperlink.\r\n',NULL,'No regions are currently using the affected print group with the \"Discontinue\" hyperlink enabled. Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a SP\"08 code fix and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-15 09:20:00','2009-09-28 02:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(139,2793398,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Creatinine Clearance in Patient Header may not be Accurate under certain circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'IP, BEA, ED, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-09-13 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'P',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SU09','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No current impact because no one using header; no fix planned until SP08\r\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: Waiting for SU09.','\"Inpatient, Epic RX., ED, Oncology\r\nCreatinine Clearance in Patient Header may not be Accurate under certain circumstances\"\r\nThe patient header may not properly calculate Creatinine Clearance when using programming point record 34605-IP Patient Header - Configurable. The Creatinine Clearance that appears in the header is always calculated using the patient\"s actual weight instead of the patient\"s adjusted or ideal body weight. This incorrect information could potentially lead to inappropriate medication dosing.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'SP06 - SP07 -NO CURRENT IMPACT,  No regions are using the 34605 ? IP Patient Header 10/18: Any plans to use this in Beacon?   RX and IP/ED does not use and no plans to use.  11/01/07:  IP, Beacon, ED, AMB do not use header. Fix standard in SP\"08. Waiting for SP\"08.  \r\n','\"If a region were to implement the affected functionality prior to the fix being delivered, one of the following EpicRx released patient header programming point records could be used to display CrCl: \r\n85450-Rx Patient Header - Ht/Wt/BSA/CR - HOV/DC Support \r\n85455-Rx Patient Header - Name,MRN,Loc,A,S,Dx,Allg,Ht,Wt,BSA,CrCl \r\n85460-Rx Patient Header w/ FYI\"\r\n','','\"If a region were to implement the affected functionality prior to the fix being delivered, one of the following EpicRx released patient header programming point records could be used to display CrCl: \r\n85450-Rx Patient Header - Ht/Wt/BSA/CR - HOV/DC Support \r\n85455-Rx Patient Header - Name,MRN,Loc,A,S,Dx,Allg,Ht,Wt,BSA,CrCl \r\n85460-Rx Patient Header w/ FYI\"\r\n',NULL,'Epic (Kelly Miller) will provide status on the code fix as part of a KPackage to PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair), who will record this information in the PART tracking report which is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. To prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix as part of the KPackage when it becomes available with SP\"08. SP?06 ? SP?07 are only affected if the following special updates are installed: Programming point record 34605-IP Patient Header - Configurable. 10/11/07:  Epic fixing in Spr08.  34605 Pt Header - not used in RX.  Inpatient?  Yolanda sent Andre and Victoria email 10/11 at 8:14AM, Victoria does not believe Inpatient is using this header.  Check with AMB? 10/17/07:  PART request to know if we are waiting until SP\"08? Standard in Spring08 as no one is using this header and no plans to do so. 11/01/07:  IP, Beacon, ED, AMB do not use header. Fix standard in SP\"08. Waiting for SP\"08.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-15 09:21:00','2009-09-28 03:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(140,2456363,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'AMB Mid-Atlantic region reported for customized encounters using the telephone navigator with the DOCTEL section, QuickNote documentation may be lost','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-05-17 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'STANDARD IN RELEASE:  SP08\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: Closing, see note in Next Step History from Chris Russell ','AMB Mid-Atlantic region reported for customized encounters using the telephone navigator with the DOCTEL section, QuickNote documentation may be lost \r\n\"Mid-Atlantic region reported they have lost QuickNote documentation in the following situation: \r\n1.  they are using customized encounters using the telephone navigator with the DOCTEL section\r\n2.  encounters are listed as other than telephone type encounters in the profile\r\n3.  QuickNotes were used to document the encounter\r\n4.  a user entered the encounter and then\r\n5.  exited the workspace. \r\nIt is believed that use of DOCTEL section (items 113, 124, 34009) in ANY navigator (i.e., not just the telephone navigator) under the above conditions will cause the problem (loss of QuickNote documentation) to occur.  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Per Chris Russell @ Epic:  \"We have no Epic record for this incident, but we do have record that MAS reported the issue and NCAL was not affected.\"  All--conclusion by Hochhalter, Epic:  NCAL NOT impacted, however Epic recommends to list encounter type 61 as a Telephone Encounter type. - 6/15/07 Email sent to AMB - Sandra/Jansin is encounter type 61 listed as a telephone encounter type, 9/18 Update: According to Natl PART (Rebecca)  NCAL is impacted and PART is awaiting NCAL status. Update 10/8:  Jansin is not familiar with this.  Sent email to Sandra and Carol Devlin. Per Carol Devlin - If I am reading and understanding the documentation correctly regarding this issue, DOCTEL should only be associated with telephone encs which appears to be the case with Northern California.  I did check several non-telephone navigators and did not find DOCTEL in them. Carol would like Sandra to confirm.  Awaiting Sandra\"s feedback. 10/11/07:  Sent email to Don Martin and Sandra Francisco with all details per email from Dr. Bliss.  10/29/07:  NCAL not Affected.  Fix standard in SP\"08. \r\n','Workaround is to change the configuration setting, to define affected encounters as telephone type encounters.  Epic needs to provide the steps for NCAL to determine if we are affected. If affected, Epic will need to assist regions with remediation.  Data over thirty days old is lost, as this info is not journaled.  Data less than thirty days old could be retrieved from the journal.  NCAL must determine if it is affected.  Brad Hochhalter / Carol Devlin from NCAL AMB were on the call and are checking.  \r\n',NULL,'Workaround is to change the configuration setting, to define affected encounters as telephone type encounters.  Epic needs to provide the steps for NCAL to determine if we are affected. If affected, Epic will need to assist regions with remediation.  Data over thirty days old is lost, as this info is not journaled.  Data less than thirty days old could be retrieved from the journal.  NCAL must determine if it is affected.  Brad Hochhalter / Carol Devlin from NCAL AMB were on the call and are checking.  \r\n',NULL,'\"Mid-Atlantic region reported they have lost QuickNote documentation in the following situation: \r\n1.  they are using customized encounters using the telephone navigator with the DOCTEL section\r\n2.  encounters are listed as other than telephone type encounters in the profile\r\n3.  QuickNotes were used to document the encounter\r\n4.  a user entered the encounter and then\r\n5.  exited the workspace. \r\nIt is believed that use of DOCTEL section (items 113, 124, 34009) in ANY navigator (i.e., not just the telephone navigator) under the above conditions will cause the problem (loss of QuickNote documentation) to occur.  \r\nUpdate 9/18 from PART: Searches run by Epic (John Zook) have revealed that all regions except NW are affected by this issue.  Search results were sent to each region\r\n* Potential Clinical Impact:  \r\nProbable Clinical Severity:  Moderate in that some patient encounter notes may be lost.  However, many clinically severe notes are likely to be documented elsewhere (e.g. allergies).\r\nLikely Rate of Occurrence: Periodic, likely to occur sometimes\r\n* Potentially Impacted Areas:  \r\nApplications:   Ambulatory primarily, Inpatient\r\nReleases:  FA\"04-SP\"07\r\nFeatures:  Customized encounters notes (QuickNote), Visit Navigator, and encounters not identified as telephone encounters in the profile\r\nWork needs to be done with regional Epic TS to seek assistance, 30 patient encounters can be retrieved for examination, >30 days old, is lost.  10/29/07:  NCAL not Affected.  Fix standard in SP\"08. \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-15 09:22:00','2009-07-22 02:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(142,3530932,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Data entered in a Documentation Flowsheet navigator section can be lost.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-26 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'July K-pckg','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K072108',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','Y','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I757459 (C7503773) \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-C7503773\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CLOSED per Kelly / Bill Yee 12/09/2008  Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed). Workaround in place.  Testing in progress.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Affected regions must work with Epic tech support to implement the VCN workaround (for NCAL, point person = Andre Mure).  Fix causes another issue with the 80-row limit in the flowsheet which must be corrected by National.  Mary Seggerman is working to make changes at the National level so the July K-package fix can go in.  6/30:  Row count is different than 80 row limit. Andre to follow up regarding workaround. Apoorva to check if AMB is affected. Chris and Andre to work together. 7/3:  Waiting for July Kpkg (confirmed). Workaround in place. 8/7:  Testing will occur after WITS2 refresh.  10/23: Testing in progress (not completed per Alex).\r\n','Affected regions must work with Epic tech support to implement the VCN workaround (for NCAL, point person = Andre Mure).  Fix causes another issue with the 80-row limit in the flowsheet which must be corrected by National.  Mary Seggerman is working to make changes at the National level so the July K-package fix can go in.   ',NULL,'Affected regions must work with Epic tech support to implement the VCN workaround (for NCAL, point person = Andre Mure).  Fix causes another issue with the 80-row limit in the flowsheet which must be corrected by National.  Mary Seggerman is working to make changes at the National level so the July K-package fix can go in.   ',NULL,'Regions must change the VCN setting so the row detail pop-up window will not open (this will save the data).   ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-19 10:49:51','2008-12-09 03:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(150,3682698,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Comments in SmartForm Tristate Controls may be Deleted by Visual Cue under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','I7510342','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-20 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510342\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-C75031085\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 Closed, fix installed. No Current Impact since NCAL not planning to use \"recommended icons\" - FYI to Andre Mure','NO CURRENT IMPACT - Comments in SmartForm Tristate Controls may be Deleted by Visual Cue under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'All regions (NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, OH, GA, CO, Exempla, and MAS) are potentially impacted if they build custom Smart Blocks displaying \"recommended icons\" in NoteWriter. Epic (Austin Guentner) ran searches in all regions and none are using the feature to be impacted. 8/25:  per Andre M, NCAL not planning to use \"recommended icons\".  8/28:  Status will be received 9/2. 9/4:  Fix will be  a part of Nov Kpkg. NCAL will be waiting for Nov Kpkg. \r\n','Disable the visual cues (recommended icon) functionality until the fix is available and implemented.\r\n',NULL,'Disable the visual cues (recommended icon) functionality until the fix is available and implemented.\r\n',NULL,'\"Epic (Austin Guentner) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Communications (Sharon Carroll) of the status by 9/2/08.\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-20 03:46:00','2009-04-14 03:14:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(151,3690536,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Beacon treatment plan order details may not be saved in specific workflow.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-21 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Alan Rogers',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0912-PS-PR3690536-C75031063-E757251-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z\r\n','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','N','M','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   SP07 fix in Nov K & fix standard in SP08 IU4\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510174\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4340):  \n  SP’07 C75031063 9/12/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-C75031063 & E757251\nRISK RANKING:  6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/2:  per Katie: \"This fix was actually installed in Production as a dependency for PRL, this issue was resolved and we are not able to replicate.\"  Greying the row','SP07: Beacon treatment plan order details may not be saved in specific workflow. 9/12:  Fix will be delivered 9/12. (adhoc 4380). \r\n\r\nChanges to Beacon treatment plan order details changes may not be saved in the following workflow:\r\nOpen the treatment plan navigator section in edit mode for a patient encounter with an existing treatment plan configured to recalculate doses each time weight or height is documented.\r\nExit the treatment plan navigator section, but keep the navigator open.\r\nDocument updated height or weight vitals information. This can be done by the same user or a different user.\r\nOpen the treatment plan navigator section in edit mode.\r\nModify order details to a treatment plan order.  \r\nThe order detail changes will appear to the end-user, but may not be saved to the treatment plan order.  The original treatment plan order details which were loaded when the treatment plan navigator section was first loaded in step 1 are respected. If the order is released, they may appear as pended with the changed order details, but if the user exits the navigator and re-enters, the order may display as released with the original order details without the changes.  Automatic order detail changes to doses which are calculated based on the height or weight values may appear to the end-user, however, they may not be saved to treatment plan orders.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'  NCAL will probably want the adhoc; Dr. Bliss must approve.  Epic is working on a fix, no ETA at this time.   Adhoc = 4340.  8/25:  per KV, \"the workflow can be done in Beacon, however it is not common. I don\"t know of may providers who use the recalculate option when dosing, and if they do the workflow is that the height and weight is taken before the provider enters into the tx plan (by the MA or RN).\" 9/8/08:  ETA on 9/11.  9/11:  Fix arrives 9/12.  9/12:  received 0912-PS-PR3690536-C75031063-E757251-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z,  0912-PS-PR3690536-C75031063-E757251-Spr07Nov10NS.zip. 9/22: Code is on hold-not yet in testing (code freeze in WITS3). 10/2:  per Katie: \"This fix was actually installed in Production as a dependency for PRL, this issue was resolved and we are not able to replicate.\"  Greying the row. \r\n',' Changes will be saved to order details for treatment plan orders after updates to height and weight documentation if the this workflow is followed:  if the navigator is a fixed activity tab for patient workspaces, exit the patient workspace completely and re-open the patient workspace before opening the treatment plan navigator section to make changes to order details.\r\nNote:  per Epic, the workflow is uncommon, not taught and not recommended.  It is unlikely that the user would be entering the height and weight daily nor would height or weight change in a short period of time, instead, the default (using the treatment plan weight or height based on last date they were entered is carried through until the next time the weight or height is entered) is used \r\n',NULL,' Changes will be saved to order details for treatment plan orders after updates to height and weight documentation if the this workflow is followed:  if the navigator is a fixed activity tab for patient workspaces, exit the patient workspace completely and re-open the patient workspace before opening the treatment plan navigator section to make changes to order details.\r\nNote:  per Epic, the workflow is uncommon, not taught and not recommended.  It is unlikely that the user would be entering the height and weight daily nor would height or weight change in a short period of time, instead, the default (using the treatment plan weight or height based on last date they were entered is carried through until the next time the weight or height is entered) is used \r\n',NULL,'Epic (Liz) is working with Christy Reimer to create and run a query to identify all active treatment plans set to recalculate dosages based on height / weight.  Results will be sent to PART, and PART to distribute to Dr. Bliss, Katie Volpe in NCAL. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-08-21 04:44:00','2008-10-28 01:05:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(152,3711522,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Questions missing in PRL order sets ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-29 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'1437','SP\"07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','\"0911-PS-PR3711522-C75031060-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z\r\n0911-PS-PR3711522-C75031060-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.zip\"\r\n','K090908',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','A','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758891 \nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4377):  \n  SP’07 C75031041 9/11/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K090908-E756908 & C7503959\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9/25:  Installed in production and validated.graying row/closed','SP07:  Questions in a user copy of a PRL-converted order set can be lost\r\nIf a provider makes a copy of a PRL-converted order set and changes the default answer to at least one question, then closes and opens the order set, only the changed question(s) will appear in the order set copy.  The unchanged questions will be lost. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\" PRL team to test, install the fix before turning on PRL. 9/4: Fix for this (PR3711522) is the same fix as PR3711161. 9/5:  This fix caused other issues for SCAL, but not for NCAL. Currently in testing. 9/8/08.  9/11:  Received file 0911-PS-PR3711522-C75031060-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z, 0911-PS-PR3711522-C75031060-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.zip.  9/15: in testing.  9/18:  Fix will be installed along with PRL (9/25).  Passed testing. \r\n\"9/25:  Installed in production and validated.\r\n','\"Suggested workarounds include:\r\n1.  turn off the ability to create user order sets\r\n2.  flag order sets with questions with \"***\" in the comment area.  These questions then will be saved. \"\r\n',NULL,'\"Suggested workarounds include:\r\n1.  turn off the ability to create user order sets\r\n2.  flag order sets with questions with \"***\" in the comment area.  These questions then will be saved. \"\r\n',NULL,'Epic has delivered a fix, C75031041, which requires an outage.  It is assumed this fix corrects the issue, as Epic cannot replicate the issue with this fix installed.   The fix was delivered to SCAL in response to 3 test defects:  TDs 30977, 31230, and 30791.   Dhea Maloney stated that PRL in NCAL may require a special outage before or around 9/25 to install this fix.   It is unlikely the fix can be tested and included in the manifest for the 9/17 scheduled outage.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-02 02:30:00','2008-09-25 01:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(153,3703902,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'IO Total Rows May Display Totals on the Wrong Contact, in specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-27 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   fix standard in SP08 IU4\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I7510289\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757411\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 code fix installed, no impact not using prog points listed.  FYI:  Aditi Vakil ',' Documentation Flowsheets rows may display IO totals for the wrong contact if all of the following conditions are met:\r\nA surgery is linked to an admission as a related encounter;\r\nThat surgery shares the same inpatient data (INP) record as the admission.\r\nDocumentation Flowsheet rows are built with any of the following programming points:\r\n? 34640 - IP Flowsheet Intake Cumulative Total\r\n? 34637 - IP Flowsheet Intake Total\r\n? 34642 - IP Flowsheet Net I/O Cumulative Total\r\n? 34639 - IP Flowsheet Net I/O Total\r\n? 34641 - IP Flowsheet Output Cumulative Total\r\n? 34638 - IP Flowsheet Output Total',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SP\"07, SP\"08. Epic searches have shown that no regions are currently impacted because they do not use the affected programming points. 10/23: In Nov Kpkg.\r\n','None necessary',NULL,'None necessary',NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix (DLG I7510289) as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-02 02:31:00','2009-04-15 10:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(154,3711482,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Beacon-Weight-based doses recalculated only for unsigned medication orders',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-29 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP\"07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K090908',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','N','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in Sept K, under PR PR 3643328 & 3696728\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I758021/E756908 \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K090908-E756908 & C7503959\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Closed per Dorinda Wong 1/26/09','SP\"07 - Beacon - Weight-based doses recalculated only for unsigned medication orders\r\n\" If enhanced weight-based dosing (new in SP\"07) is enabled, medication orders within treatment plans configured to recalculate doses each time new weight or height values are documented will only recalculate doses for unsigned medication orders and not signed medication orders. Currently, providers are instructed to enter height and weight before treatment plans are opened.  Seven patient records are potentially affected. \r\n\r\nThe following workflow illustrates the issue:\r\nOpen an existing treatment plan configured to recalculate doses each time weight or height values are documented.\r\nSign a weight or height based dosed medication order.\r\nExit the treatment plan and document new height or weight values which would affect the dosing calculation of the signed medication order.\r\nReturn to the treatment plan to the view the signed medication order.\r\n\r\nThe dosage is not recalculated.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Kirk Ryan will review, remediate seven identified records from Epic query.  9/04:  Tom to follow up with Beacon.  9/11:  Per Katie, workaround is acceptable and communication has been sent.  9/15:  Waiting for Sept Kpkg (confirmed). \r\n','Verify the doses are appropriate prior to releasing treatment plan medication orders. Disable enhanced weight based dosing functionality by setting LSD 7620 = 0.\r\n',NULL,'Verify the doses are appropriate prior to releasing treatment plan medication orders. Disable enhanced weight based dosing functionality by setting LSD 7620 = 0.\r\n',NULL,'Query Review:  Queries have been run by EPIC.  Seven patient records were identified that could be potentially impacted and require further review.  The query was run, based on the application design workflow, however KP\"s workflow is different.  These records may be \"false positives\" and require more review.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-02 02:33:00','2009-01-26 02:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(155,3711161,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'In Vitals documentation section of the navigator, HC application expects height to be entered in metric units, but displays incorrectly in English units',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-28 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4368','sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','A','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510330\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4368):  \n  SP’07 C75031061 & E757220 9/12/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008 \nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/12: closed PR; inquired but did not receive response re status of fix.','SP07:  In Vitals documentation section of the navigator, HC application expects height to be entered in metric units, but displays incorrectly in English units. \r\n\"An SU (C7503804) included in the July 2008 K-package and also as part of the adhoc for PR3548698, causes incorrect display of height info entered through the vitals documentation section of the navigator.  With certain system settings, the application expects the height info to be entered in metrics.  However, the application displays the info entered in English units (e.g., meters and centimeters are displayed as feet and inches).   The system settings for this to occur are:\r\n1. profile has height default = metrics.\r\n2. profile set to height not required (LPR 2136) \r\n3. system default set to height not required (LSD 34057)\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14.09:  Asking AMB to verify, installed 9/25/08.  Work around in place; can\"t be validated in Feb 09.\r\nFix for this issue had a bug and could possibly created another patient safety issue. Melanie Grange will determine if NCAL is affected.  Epic is working on a fix, no ETA.  9/4:  PR3548698 has been removed from 9/17 manifest. IP/AMB to confirm workaround in place. Problematic SU will be introduced by critical adhoc that is needed. Outage required.  Adhoc 4368.  9/8:  Dhea and Andrea to work together and Andrea to work with Mary Segerman. NCAL not affected until 9/24. As long as unit entry  is required, NCAL will not be affected (even after 9/24).  Work around in place. 9/10:  Adhoc will be available 9/12.  9/12:  received 0912-PS-PR3711161-C75031061-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z,  0912-PS-PR3711161-C75031061-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.zip   9/15:  Workaround implemented.  Will recheck with AMB/IP after PRL implementation. 9/18:  Not impacted due to build. Do not want code installed. Waiting for Nov Kpkg.  9/29/08:  Fix for this issue had a bug and could possibly created another patient safety issue. Melanie Grange will determine if NCAL is affected. 10/16: Followup required w/Melanie Grange, email sent.   10/26:  (Melanie\"s follow up email:  Ambulatory reviewed this issue on 9/2 and reported in response to an email from Rosalba Carrillo-Vassel that we are unaffected.) After AMB\"s review, we are not affected 10/27:Waiting for Nov Kpkg.\r\n',' Epic recommends changing the settings.  Setting #2 above should be set to \"Yes\" (i.e., height required.)  Setting #3 should be set to \"Yes\" (i.e., height required.)  Epic AMB Tech Support (TS) will assist the ACs with the setting changes.  This forces the users to specify the units when height info is entered. \r\n',NULL,' Epic recommends changing the settings.  Setting #2 above should be set to \"Yes\" (i.e., height required.)  Setting #3 should be set to \"Yes\" (i.e., height required.)  Epic AMB Tech Support (TS) will assist the ACs with the setting changes.  This forces the users to specify the units when height info is entered. \r\n',NULL,'\"SCAL to authorize adhoc.  Regions need to be aware when they will be affected by this problem.  For NCAL, fix for PR3548698 is scheduled for installation 9/17.  The July K-package is scheduled for installation in mid-November, 2008.  Regions should work with Epic TS to make the recommended setting changes.  9/2: Epic says these adhocs contain the broken SU:                                                                                                                                                           0709-AP-PR3557111-C7503865-E756655-Spr07Jul21NS\r\n0711-PS-PR3548698-C7503903-E756747-Spr07Jul21NS\r\n0714-PS-PR3443190-C7503898-E756865-Spr07Jul21NS\r\n0716-AP-PR3466180-E756506-C7503803-Spr07Jul21NS\r\n0805-AP-TD31089-E756728-C7503866-Spr07Sep08NS\r\n0811-AP-PR3652673-E757059-C7503967-Spr07Sep08NS\r\n0811-AP-PR3651819-C7503900-E756747-Spr07Jul21NS\r\n0813-AP-TD31263-C7503924-C7503956-E757059-Spr07Sep08NS\r\n0829-AP-TD31230-C75031041-E757255-Spr07Sep08NS\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-02 02:40:00','2009-05-12 03:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(156,3704383,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Code Status Context may be Set Incorrectly when using Outpatient Order Mode',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','143170','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-28 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','A','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   fix standard in SP08 IU4 Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510538, \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757600\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09  - code in prod, unable to test closing',' SP07 / SP08:  Code Status Context may be Set Incorrectly when using Outpatient Order Mode\r\n\"When ordering code status in an ED or HOV visit using outpatient order mode, the code status may not be set with an outpatient context.  Instead, the context may be set as ED or HOV respectively and the code status will end when that encounter ends. \r\nThe following workflows are examples that may cause the problem:\r\n1.  Place a Full Code Status order on an ED patient using the Discharge Orders section of the ED Orders Navigator section.\r\n2.  The code status will update to Full Code for that patient.\r\n3.  Discharge the patient.\r\n4.  Open the Chart of the patient and open the Demographics activity.  \r\n5.  Open the Clinical Information Tab. \r\n6.  Click on the hyperlink to view the Code Status history.\r\n7.  The Full Code status order will appear inactive and will have a context of ED when instead it should have a context of Outpatient.\r\n----------------------------------------------------------\r\n1.  Place a Full Code Status order on an HOV patient using the Discharge Orders section.\r\n2.  The code status will update to Full Code for that patient.\r\n3.  Close the HOV encounter.\r\n4.  Open the Chart of the patient and open the Demographics activity.  \r\n5.  Open the Clinical Information Tab. \r\n6.  Click on the hyperlink to view the Code Status history.\r\n7.  The Full Code status order will appear as inactive and will have a context of HOV when instead it should have a context of Outpatient.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"Epic is working on a fix, no ETA. 9/4:  ETA Sept 12. Tom to follow up with AMB regarding replication. Per SF: \"\"Ambulatory does not set code status.  We did not give our providers the security point to allow this. Only Inpatient/ED sets code status. When this goes for regression testing by BIO Testing, they should include order entry and discharge medications in the scenarios.\"\" 9/8/08:  Could possibly affect ED/IP. Andre to replicate. Per AT: \"\"Ambulatory doesn\"t set code status ever. The orders are specifically hospital admission orders.  The surgeons have full code pre-selected. The HBS and Critical Care orders require an entry by using a hard stop. So I think we are more than covered.\"\" 9/15:  Workaround in place. Waiting for Nov Kpkg. \r\n\"\r\n','As a workaround, regions may create an Order Validation Programming Point that will restrict Code Status orders from being placed as Outpatient Ordering Mode orders.  This may be done by duplicating LPP 34496 and setting the Order Mode Parameter to Outpatient and then set the Order Type parameter to the Code Status order type.  Once this LPP is created, the region will need to add it to the relevant profiles as an Accept Order Validation LPP to make sure that users are prevented from placing a code status order as a outpatient order.   Epic (Brendan Krueger) is prepared to work with each Epic Regional TS to implement the workaround.  \r\n',NULL,'As a workaround, regions may create an Order Validation Programming Point that will restrict Code Status orders from being placed as Outpatient Ordering Mode orders.  This may be done by duplicating LPP 34496 and setting the Order Mode Parameter to Outpatient and then set the Order Type parameter to the Code Status order type.  Once this LPP is created, the region will need to add it to the relevant profiles as an Accept Order Validation LPP to make sure that users are prevented from placing a code status order as a outpatient order.   Epic (Brendan Krueger) is prepared to work with each Epic Regional TS to implement the workaround.  \r\n',NULL,' No adhoc requested.  Epic TSs to work with the regions to implement workaround if desired.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-02 02:42:00','2009-04-14 03:28:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(157,3710141,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'I/O Activity \"Net Since Admission\" data may be inaccurate','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-28 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'4443','SP07, SP08','','','','','NCAL','0422-PS-PR3710141-E758578-C75031379-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z\r\n0422-PS-PR3710141-E758578-C75031379-Spr07May18NS.zip\r\n0422-PS-PR3710141-E758578-C75031379-Spr07May18NS-EpicWeb.zip','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'2',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   (also see 3731128) confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510663\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4443):  \n  SP’07 E758578 & C75031379 4/22/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/09: Consensus to close; not able to validate in prod.','SP07, SP08:  I/O Activity \"Net Since Admission\" data may be inaccurate\r\n\r\nWhen related encounters are configured to display in the Intake/Output activity, the net I/O from all related encounters will appear in the \"Net Since Admission\" row.  In some cases, the system may include data from previous encounters that is no longer relevant to the Intake and Output for the current encounter, resulting in totals much higher than expected.  \r\nAn example:  \r\n\"Net Since Admission\" row may display the net from all Related Encounters (e.g. an old admission from several days prior).\r\nThe end result is a \"Net Since Admission\" daily total (e.g. In of P.O. - Oral intake P.O. - ml or Out of Urine - ml/kg/hr) that may be much higher than expected and no indication that the value includes data from a previous encounter. \r\nEpic query reveals 17 to 24 affected encounters per deployment in NCAL.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: Andrea to certify after install\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).  Per Dhea, Bettianne has decided to wait for the May kpackage rather than pursuing the ad hoc\r\n3/26 Adhoc over 5 mos old. Do we cancel? Waiting to hear from EPIC.NCAL has replicated 1/12/09:  Per Epic, more complicated than anticipated so taking longer. (also see 3731128) No K-pkg yet\r\nEpic working on a fix, no ETA. 9/4:  NCAL unable to replicate and no workaround available. Tom to follow up with Chris Russell from Epic.  Per Chris:  no fix ETA, fix \"likely\" to be in Nov k-pckg.  The searches run identified profiles with a setting allowing users to view related encounters.  There is no data corruption and no remediation required, it is a display issue. 9/8/08:  Issue has NOT been replicated (by Andre). Andre/Andrea to follow up with Bettianne. 9/11:  No alerts will be sent per Bettianne/Brian H, until issue replicated. Nov K-pckg seems reasonable.  9/18:  Per Andre, unable to replicate.  Andre to follow up with Epic (Chris R). 9/26:  per C. Russell,  Here?s where we stand.  There?re two different issues to test here: 1. Encounters may pull in I&O Net Since Admission values from previous, related encounters: This seemed to me to be easier to reproduce since it?s just linking encounters and documenting, but I have had no luck.  I?ve emailed the folks who raised this PSE to see if I am missing something. Linked encounters with I/O documented on the same date incorrectly calculate the Net Since Admission row: I created an HOV and admission for today and documented on them both.  The thing with this scenario is that you need to be able to scroll through the days in the I/O activity, so I will need to wait a few days since there is only one day to display at the moment. 10/13:  Dr. Bliss authorized adhoc. Adhoc 4443 / RFC (shell) 3007349. 10/20: Arturo will followup w/Andrea. 10/23:This is a rare occurrence per Andrea and will not be a major impact to the nurses workflow. Epic will communicate w/PART on 10/24.\r\nComments from related PR (3731128): 10/22:  Andrea & Bettianne agree that this is unlikely to ever occur because the nursing work flow in ambulatory settings does not include documentation of urine output. The nurses send the patients to the bathroom prior to the procedure and to the recovery room after the procedure.  They feel that it would be very, very rare for a nurse to document output and sending an alert would confuse staff. 10/23: Epic will communicate w/PART on 10/24. 10/27:Fix started per Chris; Fix will take longer no date set; Will followup w/PART with date (est.2-3mos). Rebecca will communicate with Dustin as well based on the risk ranking. \r\n11/03: Tied in with 3731128.\r\n','Must communicate to departments identified in Epic query.  \r\n','','Must communicate to departments identified in Epic query.  \r\n',NULL,'Must communicate  to facilities, SCAL to adhoc.   Epic (Chris) to provide query to Andrea Thorup and Andre Mure\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-02 02:59:00','2009-09-08 02:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(158,3731357,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'ANES module-QuickForm edits made in Workflow Conductor are not displayed, in specific workflow',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Anesthesia','DLG: I7510869 ','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-05 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Bejamin Broder',NULL,NULL,'4383','SP\"06, SP\"07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Authorized by Dr. David Bliss/Canceled','','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','Y','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confimed In K011909 as fix to 4060703\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510869\nAD HOC AVAILABLE (AUTH # 4383):  \n  SP’07 E757753 & C75031182 available\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757753 & C75031182\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/28: Verified with Darryl Gill; ok to close.','SP\"06, SP\"07 --Anesthesia module - QuickForm edits made in Workflow Conductor are not displayed, in specific workflow\r\n\" Description:  QuickForm edits made in the Workflow Conductor may not be displayed if a user is documenting in the Workflow Conductor and a second user simultaneously changes the scheduled date of surgery to a different day.  The following workflow illustrates this issue:\r\nAn Anesthesia user makes edits in a QuickForm in the Workflow Conductor and does not close the log.\r\nAt the same time, a second user in a different workstation reschedules the case to a different day and does not close the log.\r\nAny Quickform edits that are saved by the first Anesthesia user will be filed incorrectly and will not be displayed. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code fix installed 4/8/09 E757753, C75031182, testing passed on 3/26, recommend closing or verify with Optime. \r\nANES.  Epic will provide PART with a status on 9/12/08 regarding fix eta. Adhoc authorized by Dr. Bliss. ANES support has been notified of issue.  9/8:  Follow up with ANES -  Does NCAL want the programming point and is any remediation needed? 9/10:  Adhoc 4383 / RFC:  2909310.  Epic (Ben Sherman) ts sent us screen shots of the error message that can be generated and NCAL/SCAL are trying to determine what the error message should say. 9/11:  Per Kim Starks, NCal, Scal agreed on new error msg.  Per Darryl Gil re: prog pt.:  \"nothing in production just yet that i know of\".  9/15:  Tom to follow up regarding programming point. 9/17: per D Gil:  Adegboyega George will be working on this issue.  I will be his back up. Adam [Sauder] forwarded the code today. Exact install date into PROD, not yet known as we need to test. 9/18:  Tom to follow up with M Wilson:  does ANES want Prog pt?  Email sent. 9/22:  Per M Wilson, PP will be installed but a date has not yet been determined. 9/25:  Follow up with Michael Wilson. 9/30:  per Boyega, This [PrgPt] is currently slated for November\"s release date. 10/2:  per Boyega, PP sched for next week. 10/9:  per Boyega, PP going in tonight. 10/10:  Per Boyega, PP was sucessfully installed and currently no issues.  Boyega will monitor incoming tickets. 10/13:  PP is airtight - Waiting for Kpkg. 10/16: Waiting to hear back from Epic on Kpkg. 10/20: Rebecca will followup with Epic about KPKG delivery date.10/27: Followup needed 10/30: Will get status on next meeting from Epic & PART.  Adhoc Canceled.\r\nWaiting for Jan Kpkg:  PP is airtight.','\"Epic (Ben Sherman) provided a programming point that will prevent a case from being scheduled if any (not just Anesthesia) log is open.\r\nNCAL AC (Darryl Gill) and SCAL AC (Tashe D Chambers) will work with the Epic TS to implement the programming point.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Epic (Ben Sherman) provided a programming point that will prevent a case from being scheduled if any (not just Anesthesia) log is open.\r\nNCAL AC (Darryl Gill) and SCAL AC (Tashe D Chambers) will work with the Epic TS to implement the programming point.\"\r\n',NULL,'NCAL (David Bliss) authorized the ad hoc code fix. Discovered by:  Epic during testing.  Physician Representative:  Benjamin Broder.  Package (server): E757753 \r\nPackage (client): C75031182 \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-08 02:06:00','2009-04-28 01:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(159,3731128,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'I/O Activity \"Net Since Admission\" data may be Inaccurate under specific circumstances (2nd issue)','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-05 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Wiesenthal','',NULL,'4442','SP07, SP08','','','','','4/27:  adhoc 4442 canceled, fixed under adhoc 4443','related to 3710141 (files received, but waiting for May k-pckg)','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   (also see 3710141) Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510663\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4443):  \n  SP’07 E758578 & C75031379 4/22/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/09: Consensus to close; not able to validate in prod.',' SP\"07 and SP\"08 --I/O Activity \"Net Since Admission\" data may be Inaccurate under specific circumstances\r\n\"Description:  The \"\"Net Since Admission\"\" row in the I&O activity may display inaccurate data based on related encounters.  When profile settings are configured to view data for related encounters, the net totals may calculate incorrectly, when some of the related encounters have I/O documentation for the same date(e.g- an HOV visit and an Inpatient or ED visit on the same day). \r\nThis issue may occur under the following circumstances:\r\n· Patient has related encounters.\r\n· Some of the related encounters have I&O documentation for the same date (e.g. an admission and a hospital outpatient visit are related and both have I&O documentation on Day 1)\r\n· When reviewing the input and output data in the I&O activity, and the date where both encounters have I&O data isn\"t visible on the screen (e.g., the I&O activity display shows information from Day 2 and Day 3, but there are also two related encounters that have I&O documentation on Day 1.  Day 1\"s data is not visible on the screen).  \r\nSample Scenario:\r\nWhen this occurs, the I&O data from at least one of the visits may not be added correctly or may be calculated incorrectly, in the Net Since Admission total. \r\nOn Day 1 there were two related encounters with I&O documentation with a total intake of 8 ml.  On Day 2 an additional 4 ml is documented resulting in a Net Since Admission total of 12 ml. This total is accurately shown when the date range of Day 1 - Day 3 is selected.\r\nHowever, when the date range is changed to Day 2 - Day 3 (Day 1\"s data is not visible),  the Net Since Admission incorrectly shows the total as 8 ml for Day 2 instead of 12ml.  The total Net Since Admission, on Day 3 should be 16ml but the total displayed is only 12ml.\r\nNote:  This incident is virtually identical to an issue reported by EPIC 8/28/08 -  PART Incident #3710141.  This issue (#3731128) was discovered during additional testing for the previous issue (#3710141).  The critical difference is that issue #3710141 displayed inaccurate information by totaling previously documented I/O data, for episodes of related encounters, that would appear to be the total for the current day of the current admission.  This second incident #3731128 identifies inaccurately calculated data, when I&O data was documented during at least 2 related encounters, in an episode, which occurred on the same day.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: Andrea to certify after install.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).  Per Dhea, Bettianne has decided to wait for the May kpackage  rather than pursuing the ad hoc\r\n3/26 Adhoc over 5 mos old.  Do we cancel?  Waiting to hear from EPIC.   NCAL has replicated; problem not as severe-workflow is rare. Epic (Chris) notification by mid-November to update code status.\r\nIP, ED, & OpTime.  SCAL authorized an adhoc. Adhoc status eta on 9/12/08. 9/8/08:  Andre to replicate. 9/11:  Communication to not be sent until replication has occurred. 9/18:  Per Andre, unable to replicate.  Andre to follow up with Epic. 9/26: per C. Russell, Here?s where we stand.  There?re two different issues to test here: 1. Encounters may pull in I&O Net Since Admission values from previous, related encounters: This seemed to me to be easier to reproduce since it?s just linking encounters and documenting, but I have had no luck.  I?ve emailed the folks who raised this PSE to see if I am missing something. 2. Linked encounters with I/O documented on the same date incorrectly calculate the Net Since Admission row: I created an HOV and admission for today and documented on them both.  The thing with this scenario is that you need to be able to scroll through the days in the I/O activity, so I will need to wait a few days since there is only one day to display at the moment. 10/7:  SCAL did not request an ad hoc.  Does NCAL want one? 10/9:  Andre to replicate. 10/13:  Andre to attempt replication in STAGE.  Dr. Bliss authorized adhoc.  Adhoc 4442 / RFC (shell) 3007300. 10/16: NCAL has replicated; problem not as severe; checking with Dr. Hoberman & BettiAnn; Epic will provide broader fix; Will communicate w/Apoorva on Monday. 10/20: Arturo will followup with Andrea to confirm next steps.10/22:  Andrea & Bettianne agree that this is unlikely to ever occur because the nursing work flow in ambulatory settings does not include documentation of urine output. The nurses send the patients to the bathroom prior to the procedure and to the recovery room after the procedure.  They feel that it would be very, very rare for a nurse to document output and sending an alert would confuse staff. 10/23: Epic will communicate w/PART on 10/24. 10/27:Fix started per Chris; Fix will take longer no date set; Will followup w/PART with date (est.2-3mos). Rebecca will communicate with Dustin as well based on the risk ranking. 10/30:Dustin to followup with R&D-Epic to provide a faster delivery date. 11/03: Epic (Chris) & PART will send notification by mid-November on updated code status. 11/10:Chris will provide code status by this Friday.\r\n','\"NCAL, SCAL, NW, and Exempla will send a communication to the users that there may be inaccurate data if they use the I/O flowsheet row labeled \"\"Net Since Admission\"\" totals, and have profiles configured to view related encounters data, when at least 2 of those encounters occurred on the same date.  This is the only suggested workaround.\r\nUntil fixes are released, Epic (Chris Russell) suggests that impacted regional (NCAL, SCAL, NW, and Exempla) users should rely on data in the daily totals for rows, rather than the Net Since Admission row in the IO activity.\r\n\"\r\n','','\"NCAL, SCAL, NW, and Exempla will send a communication to the users that there may be inaccurate data if they use the I/O flowsheet row labeled \"\"Net Since Admission\"\" totals, and have profiles configured to view related encounters data, when at least 2 of those encounters occurred on the same date.  This is the only suggested workaround.\r\nUntil fixes are released, Epic (Chris Russell) suggests that impacted regional (NCAL, SCAL, NW, and Exempla) users should rely on data in the daily totals for rows, rather than the Net Since Admission row in the IO activity.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'Regions:  NCAL, SCAL, NW, and Exempla are impacted.  CO and HI are potentially impacted. SCAL (Kimberly Nida) provided and authorized an ad hoc code fix. Epic (Chris Russell) will provide an ad hoc code fix and a fix for SP\"07 and SP\"08 as part of a KPackage and inform PART Communications (Sharon Carroll) of the status on 9/12/08.  Discovered by:  Epic, during Testing . Physician Representative:  Andy Wiesenthal . \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-08 02:10:00','2009-09-08 02:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(160,3732210,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Departmental frequency settings may override schedule times for specified frequencies, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-05 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. John Kang',NULL,NULL,'','SP\"05, SP\"06, SP\"07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   fix standard in SP08 IU4; Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I7510463\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 E757535 available 10/16/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757535\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 - fix installed, closing with FYI to Bill Yee (Per Bill Yee, not causing clinical harm). ','SP\"05-SP\"08 - Departmental frequency settings may override schedule times for specified frequencies, in certain circumstances\r\n\"Description:  Specified frequency settings at the department level (I DEP 24020) may override schedule times for specified frequencies for Procedure and Medication orders.  Specifically, orders with a start time in the future are signed and held in one department but later released in a department with different schedule times. As a result, procedures or medications may be scheduled incorrectly or even missed. \r\nWorkflow:\r\nSign and hold an order with a specified frequency for a patient in department A.\r\nTransfer the patient to department B which has the schedule time earlier than the department A\"s scheduled time.  \r\nPrior to the department A\"s start time, release the order.\r\nThe scheduled times will be calculated from department A\"s start time of the order.\r\nExample:\r\nOn 9/5, sign and hold a Lasix order with a Daily specified frequency scheduled for 7 AM starting on 9/6.\r\nOn 9/5, transfer the patient to a department which has an override for the Daily specified frequency to occur at 5 AM.\r\nOn 9/5 release the signed and held Lasix order.  \r\nThe schedule times are calculated from the original start time of the order (7 AM 9/6) and finds the next 5 AM time which is on the 9/7, the next day.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, Rx.  Epic (Greg Hartman) is developing a code fix and will inform PART of its status by 9/12/08. NCAL (Andrea Thorup), will review query results and decide whether to request and ad hoc code fix or wait for the KPackage. 9/8:  Andrea & Cheryl to review query. 9/11:  per AT--Bill Yee says we are at very low risk, but Cheryl and I haven\"t gone over the new print-out because of the length.. We need to ask Bill what he recommends. 9/15:  Question for Bill:  In facilities, are NCAL frequency settings the same among the transfers? Andrea to follow up. 9/18:  per B Yee, we are still analyzing the department times against the facility times. 9/24: per AT,  Bill Yee has taken over this issue. 9/25:  It is believed at this time that the issue is not causing clinical harm. NCAL waiting for Kpkg. 10/6: DLG #I7510463, Available by 10/20/08, in 111008 KPackage. 10/13:  Per Bill Yee: Waiting for Nov Kpkg. \r\n','\"Affected regions may implement either or both of the following workarounds:\r\nRemove overrides.  \r\nCommunicate issue to clinical staff.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Affected regions may implement either or both of the following workarounds:\r\nRemove overrides.  \r\nCommunicate issue to clinical staff.\"\r\n',NULL,'Discovered by:  Epic during testing / Physician Representative:  John Kang.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-08 02:16:00','2009-04-15 11:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(161,3738340,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Components in reordered medications may not display in Order Entry, in specific circumstances ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, OPT, BEA','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-09 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,'','SP04 - SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','Y','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  National pharmacy implemented the workaround by re-emphasizing the approved workflow (check with DF to find out standard fix release); Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510525\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757492\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 code fix installed 1/21/09 with adhoc 4476 (PR 3890835 PS) FYI sent to Sylvia Fong/Elissa Liong','Description:  A component added to a medication mixture with no TYPE specified at pharmacy verification may not display later in Order Entry when the medication is reordered.  The component will however be displayed in the Products to Dispense box.  \r\nWorkflow:\r\n1. Pharmacy receives an order with instructions to add a component to a mixture.\r\n2. The pharmacist adds the component without specifying TYPE.\r\n3. The pharmacist adds other information and verifies the order.\r\n4. The order is later changed or reordered.\r\n5. When viewed again in Order Entry, the added component is not displayed.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, Optime, Beacon. NCAL, SCAL, Hawaii.  NCAL AC(s) to review query with Epic. Who to implement workaround? Epic will provide a code status by 9/18. 9/11: Follow up with Rx if workaround communication been sent.  Per Howard Switsky: \"in NCAL and SCAL we have continually emphasized to the pharmacists that they are NOT to add components to orders in verification; the approved workflow is for the pharmacist to DC the order that needs to be changed and create a new order in OE.  The only action that pharmacy is taking is to re-emphasize the approved workflow in a communications that is scheduled to be distributed at the end of this week\".9/22:  Yellow row. 10/20: Waiting for Nov KPKG.\r\n',' Inpatient Pharmacy (Howard Switzky) suggested that all pharmacy personnel be instructed to discontinue orders requesting additional components and to create new orders specifying component TYPE.',NULL,' Inpatient Pharmacy (Howard Switzky) suggested that all pharmacy personnel be instructed to discontinue orders requesting additional components and to create new orders specifying component TYPE.',NULL,'Discovered by:  Epic, during testing. Epic Representative:  Michael Bries. Physician Representative:  Ben Broder.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-15 03:41:00','2009-04-14 03:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(162,3740532,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Dischrgd meds using dischrg nav incorrect',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','I759357','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-09 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DLG I759357 and part of July K-pckg E756546 will fix this problem.  ','',NULL,'2008-09-17 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'10',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Delivered as fix under 3452496 which was not a patient safety incident\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759357\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756546\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9/24: validated, grey out.  ','Description:  When ordering discharge medications using the discharge navigator from an inpatient application, several problems may occur, if that medication has an alternative alert and the alternative alert \"pop-up\":\r\nthe order name selected may appear with incorrect sig (may be that of the original order,\r\nthe opposite may occur where it is the correct sig but the order name is incorrect, or\r\nif selecting an alternative alert, the entire name is what is presented from the original sig.\r\nThis may also occur from the admissions navigator if someone is ordering \"prior to admission\" (PTO) meds.\r\nThis was triggered by loading the July 21 KPackage, I754286/E756106.  Although similar to PART Incident # 3109704, this is a different issue.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, Rx. NCAL, SCAL. Dr. Hoberman stated workaround is fine, will review query sent by Liz, and will wait for code fix to be installed with sept release. 9/10:  \"Group\" to work with Epic regarding workaround/fix. Epic asked NCAL to remove Prog Point. NCAL would like to keep the programming point and has asked Epic to review with the development team in order to determine if there is another solution. Issue has been replicated (Britt, S. Taylor)  Tom sent email to Liz N, asking about wrk/around. 9/15:  Workaround is not needed. Fix has been approved and will be installed on 9/17.   9/24: validated, grey out.  \r\n','Turn off alternative alerts',NULL,'Turn off alternative alerts',NULL,'Epic (Liz Nickels) reported that the ad hoc code fix (I759357) and part of July KPackage (E756546) will correct the problem.  The original PR #3452496 is the original remedy ticket these fixes were associated with.  Reported by:  SCAL (Dr. Ben Broder). Physician Representative:  Ben Broder.  Epic Representative:   Liz Nickels, 608-271-9000. Per Liz: \"NCAL is in a unique situation as they have an after-defaulting programming point plugged into the 1000 profile that defaults the sig from the IP order in IP to OP reordering workflows.  This programming point doesn?t take into account an alternative alert has triggered.  Without the fix, to the user it appears that the alternative didn?t accept at all.  They get the original ERX with the defaulted sig of the IP med.  With the fix installed, however, users will start seeing the alternative ERX mixed with the defaulted sig of the IP med.  We?ve suggested taking out this programming point when the fix is installed and Maria is looking into what it would take to get this programming point fixed to respect the alternative.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-15 03:54:00','2008-10-13 02:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(163,3752833,1,'OPT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'OpTime - Possibly overwriting an existing implant when creating a new implant ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-12 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,'','SP06, SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','Y','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510621\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4447):  \n  SP’07 C75031099 10/17/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-C75031099\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09:  fix in prod, Per K Metzger: leaving w/a config in place, may close.   Remediation complete.','Description:  It is possible that a user could overwrite an existing implant when creating a new implant.  This can be a potential issue if you are using the pop-below implant form in Log Entry that allows you to see the existing implants at the top of the window and create a new implant at the bottom of the window. \r\nIf you are creating a new implant but have not yet clicked the file button to save it and you click one of the existing implants at the top of the window, you will get a pop-up warning that says, \"You are already editing some data in the lower portion.  If you go ahead with this selection, that data will be lost.  Are you sure you want to go ahead?\"  If you press No, it will keep the information for your new implant at the bottom of the window and the implant that you clicked on above will stay highlighted.  If you then click File with the existing implant above still highlighted, it saves the new implant in the surgical log and removes the existing implant you clicked on in the top portion of the window\r\nEpic states print group 68410 is problematic and currently in use by NCAL. Print group 68412 is considered a workaround according to Epic and is also in use by NCAL.    \r\nEpic stated there are 80 affected records in NCAL and possibly 40-50 more affected records',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"NCAL, SCAL, Hawaii, Colorado, Exempla.  OpTime.  NCAL OpTime AC to determine next steps in regards to implementing the workaround and deciding if an adhoc will be necessary. Kirk from OPT will build/test/implement and send communication. 9/15: per K. Metzger, workaround implemented; remediation \"\"will be up to Michael Wilson, EPIC and the sites\"\". 9/18:  Email sent to M Wilson about remediation. 9/22:  Per M Wilson, Remediation is needed. most of the Implant records were \"\"caught\"\" by the nurse doing the documentation and remediated at the time the surgery was occurring. At this point it appears that approximately 47 Implant records may or may not be linked to a patient\"s chart.  The affected facilities will need to check their paper tracking documents for the days in question and then cross reference to the KPHC documentation. These Implants may or may not be in the patient record.  A cross reference with the paper Implant Log  to find the individual patients will need to be done at the facility and then the KPHC documentation checked to ensure that the Implant is in the system of record.  9/25:  Adhoc requested by Colorado. NCAL will wait for Kpkg since workaround is in place. 10/2:  MWilson will be contacted (again) regarding 47 records to be remediated. 10/6: Per MWilson, facilities are still researching.  10/9: TS spoke with MW, MW will recontact the facility area directors for a status. 10/13:  per MW, no response yet. 10/16: No response from FAC to validate remediation; awaiting ACK from DSA 10/20: Tom will followup to confirm remediation with facilities. 10/26:  Waiting for a reply regarding remediation. 10/27: No reply yet; will followup w/ phone call.  40 of 47 logs have been remediated/documented correctly. 10/30 Dr Bliss to contact M Wilson. 11/06: M Wilson stated unable to locate 7 implant records;  Dr. Bliss, MWilson & Tom meet for bridge call.11/10: Remediation is complete as of today; Awaiting Nov KPKG.\r\n\"\r\n','Remove print group 68410 and replace with 68412',NULL,'Remove print group 68410 and replace with 68412',NULL,'\"Concern:  If implants aren?t linked then this could potentially affect patient care (possibly-unable to notify do to recall). Risk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Ben Broder. Problem Discovered by:   Another Epic Client. Epic Representative / email address:  Ben Sherman / bsherman@epicsystems.com. Remediation:  NCAL remediation will be handled differently since the log ID is included with implant. (possibly: add a file addendum with implant info) ? work in progress. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-15 04:02:00','2009-04-15 01:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(164,3691766,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Incorrect Medication Dose When Placing Outpatient Prescription Order ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  5/20/09 (DF)\nNOTES:  Confirmed in Sept K; but also received ad hoc as part of May 09 K; C75031357-E758430 -update regional status\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510336\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K090908-E757244 & K051809-C75031357 & E758430\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed 11/19/08.  Grey out. ','SP07,  No Current Impact (NCAL):   Incorrect Medication Dose When Placing Outpatient Prescription Order\r\n\"Conditions:\r\n1. PTA medications are being reordered as inpatient medications.\r\n2. Inpatient medications, initially entered as PTA meds, are being reordered as outpatient prescriptions.\r\n3. Outpatient IMS is not turned on. (mnemonic: MR_USE_IMS\"=1)\r\nNote: The inpatient medication must be modified for the problem to manifest itself.\r\nExample\r\n1. In the PTA Medication section of the navigator enter Lipitor 10mg PO Tabs.\r\n2. In the Admission Navigator reorder this PTA medication as an Inpatient medication.\r\n3. From the Medication activity modify the Inpatient medication and change the dose from 10mg to 40mg.\r\n4. In the Discharge Navigator prescribe the Inpatient 40mg Lipitor medication order as an Outpatient discharge order. The display name will appear as 10mg, even though the dose listed in the medication is 40mg:\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic working on fix.  NCAL must decide to take fix or wait for K-pckg.  8/25: Epic confirms--NCAL query results (impacted orders) are false positives--no reconvenes necessary. 8/28:  NCAL will wait for Sept Kpkg. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,' Epic is developing a fix--should be ready by 8/25.  NCAL will receive fix, decide if it should be installed or wait for K-package.  Likely K-package = September.  8/22:  Epic query reveals NCAL orders affected.  8/25:  Epic (Dustin) confirms query orders were false positives, issue is NCI.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 11:44:00','2008-11-21 11:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(165,3583980,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'After an IV fluid bag is scanned, the volume of the IV bag is displayed on the MAR as the rate for the IV fluid',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, BEA, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-16 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Mike Krall',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K051208',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','N','L','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  PR has a 2-part fix. client fix was del under different PR.  If region just installed server, it created a problem which resulted in this PR. \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208-C7503780\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Graying row (install successful).  ','After an IV fluid bag is scanned, the volume of the IV bag is displayed on the MAR as the rate for the IV fluid.\r\n\"Description:  This Patient Safety issue was introduced by the March K-Package being installed on July 16, 2008. After an IV fluid bag is scanned, the volume of the IV bag is displayed on the MAR as the rate for the IV fluid. For example, when a LR 1000 mL bag with an ordered rate of 125 mL/hour was scanned, the rate on the MAR displayed as 1000 mL.  \r\nDue to client not being installed, a Patient Safety issue has re-occurred (previous\r\n3254342).\r\nThere is an SU in the March K-package that changes the default logic that is used to match a \r\nbarcode scanned medication to a orders for the patient.  This SU returns the behavior to the \r\nstandard logic and adds settings to control how long discontinued medications will match to a \r\nscanned med. This June 26th code brings in E756434 (June 12th code) as a dependency code.\r\nPer Thomas Sharkey at Epic, the E756434 code over writes the fix delivered on March 26th ?\r\nE755523.  The new fix is the July K-Package Ad Hoc delivered on 6/12/08, C7503780.  The new\r\nfix is client rather than server (cache). Testing reported there concerns about these codes, \r\nhowever it was determined over several meetings that the June 26th Adhoc could be installed. \r\nThis exact scenario would not have been caught in testing, because we had the June 12th Ad-\r\nhoc installed in WITS2.  In production, we do not have this adhoc installed.  Per Epic C7503780, \r\nwill correct the PS issue 3583980 reported today July 16th. To install the necessary code (client), \r\nan outage is not required because the dependencies that do require an outage are already \r\ninstalled in production.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL, SCAL. IP, Beacon, ED.  Issue has been replicated in Staging Environment.  Staging & PSUP install needed. Production Install aiming for either Monday (7/21) or Tuesday (7/22). 7/17 per dhea install aiming for Friday 7/18.  7/21:  Graying row (install successful). \r\n','\"After scanning an IV bag, take the following steps: \r\n1. In the MAR Administration window, review the Rate field. \r\n2. If the correct rate is not displayed, manually enter the correct Rate. \r\n3. A MAR Alert window opens with the message Entered rate is more than rate ordered. Select either Override reason. Click the Accept button. \r\n4. On the MAR in the Time Column, confirm that the correct rate is displayed. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"After scanning an IV bag, take the following steps: \r\n1. In the MAR Administration window, review the Rate field. \r\n2. If the correct rate is not displayed, manually enter the correct Rate. \r\n3. A MAR Alert window opens with the message Entered rate is more than rate ordered. Select either Override reason. Click the Accept button. \r\n4. On the MAR in the Time Column, confirm that the correct rate is displayed. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Concern:  Patient possibly receiving incorrect IV medication dosage.Risk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Mike Krall.  Problem Discovered by:   NCAL in Production.  Epic Representative / email address:  Thomas Sharkey / TSharkey@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation:  None discussed.  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 01:38:00','2008-10-28 01:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(166,3591681,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,' Drug-Allergy Interactions May be Missing Importanct Data',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, BEA, ED, AMB, Rx','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-07-18 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','sp07, sp08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUL08','N','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' NO CURRENT IMPACT. Config fix only. No code necessary.  Graying row. ','SP\"07, SP\"08.  Drug-Allergy Interactions May be Missing Importanct Data in specific circumstances\r\n\"Description:   Override reason and/or comment, may be specified, if required per interaction type in Interaction Settings (FIS).  This was supported by adding an extra piece to ^ delimited item FIS 1710 that stores the other pieces of data in this table for quick retrieval, in SP\"07 DLG 112464.  With drug-allergy alerts it is expected that FIS 1710 will have four pieces.  If this item only has three pieces, the alert will display with an importance of \"\"N/A\"\".  If a large number of alerts are displayed,  the ordering provider may focus on those with a high level of importance, potentially missing the drug-allergy alerts since they will have importance of \"\"N/A\"\".  It is a display pop-up issue only, not a database storage issue.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'All Regions Potentially Impacted.  Rx, IP, Ambulatory, Beacon, ED.  SP\"07, SP\"08.  Issue occurs only upon upgrade to SP\"07.  The problem is corrected by finding the interaction record, opening it and closing it. Epic (Vikram Mekala) corrected the problem for the NW and no further action is required.  7/28: Per PART/ each Regional Epic TS ran a search in each region (HI, NCAL, SCAL, Exempla, NW, CO, GA, MAS, and OH)  and only NW had FIS 1710 in use to be impacted. 7/31:  NO CURRENT IMPACT. Config fix only. No code necessary.  Graying row. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'It would be rare for a clinician to receive so many alerts that he/she doesn\"t look at each.  Our standard workflow is for clinicians to look at all alerts, regardless of importance, thereby ensuring patient care. Discovered by:  Epic, during Testing.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 01:51:00','2008-11-04 02:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(167,3466258,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Non-version related: Premature cumulative dose tracking alerts triggered by incorrect dose ratio for Epirubicin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-06-05 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'JUN08','N','M','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No code fix from Epic is necessary. Remediation complete.  Standard in SP08.  Greying out.   ','Non-version related: Premature cumulative dose tracking alerts can be triggered by incorrect dose ratio for Epirubicin \r\nA one-time data entry (human) error with an incorrect dose ratio of 1:2 instead of 2:1 in the medication record for Epirubicin (an anthracycline drug used for chemotherapy) may result in premature alerts that the patient was nearing maximum dosage.   As the drug is a chemotherapy type, a provider may stop treating a patient with this drug therapy, thinking the patient was reaching close to maximum dosage, when in actuality, this is not the case and this may impact patient care.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regions must remediate.   Macy Shia will perform for NCAL.  No code fix from Epic is necessary.  6/9:BK to follow up. 6/10:  per Macy Shia, remediation is complete.  Greying out.  \r\n','Original incorrect data entry has been corrected. \r\n',NULL,'Original incorrect data entry has been corrected. \r\n',NULL,'\"Epic has run a query back to November 1, 2007 and identified 21 orders in NCAL affected by this problem.   Macy Shia is reviewing the orders for NCAL and will contact the providers for patients affected.  The providers will correct the equivalencies in the patients\" cumulative dose function (Action -> Cumulative Dose).  \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 03:09:00','2008-10-28 01:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(168,2926967,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'HH1 SmartPhrase Conversion may result in Inaccurate Records under specific circumstances','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2007-11-16 00:00:00','2009-08-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Resovled with K051208\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I757256\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208-\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/10/09: 8/10/2009:  fix in prod w/ May 2008 k-pckg, HHI conversion delayed indef\'ly.  CLOSING.  ',' HH1 SmartPhrase Conversion may result in Inaccurate Records under specific circumstances\r\nWhen running the HH1 SmartPhrase conversion, any SmartPhrases that include text beginning with a period (\".\"),  may result in the data being converted to display an \"@\" sign in place of the period.  For example, if a SmartPhrase includes the text \".5cc\" or \"..broccoli\", results after the conversion will be \"@5cc@\" and \"@broccoli@\".  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SP06 - SP07--no NCAL impact until we run HH1 SmartPhrase conversion.  11/19/07: AMB may implement in 2nd quarter of 08. 12/10/07:  Only configuration change is needed, code is not needed as a fix.  Update 1/10: The configuration changes must be made prior to the implementation of HH1.  2/28: Will followup with Sandra Francisco.3/3: No code fix needed - configuration changes required. Susan Taylor will check w/Sandra Francisco. 3/6:  per SF, NCal is deferring the HH1 conversion indefinitely.8/18:  Fix standard in SP\"08. \r\n','\"Epic (Dustin Foster) suggests that general documentation conventions with values (e.g. \"\".55cc\"\") be preceded with a zero (e.g. \"\"0.5cc\"\") to limit confusion when reading.  Data entered with a leading zero doesn\"t result in the described SmartPhrase conversion.  Additionally, it isn\"t possible for the conversion to \"know\" whether or not the values entered as such are referencing a smartlink or if they are indicative of clinical data.\r\n(Confirm with regions) Potentially impacted regions (HI, NCAL, SCAL, Exempla, CO, OH, and GA) plan to use the workaround and work with Charles Selhorst to ensure the conversion is run, correct it and rerun the conversion to ensure patient safety.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Epic (Dustin Foster) suggests that general documentation conventions with values (e.g. \"\".55cc\"\") be preceded with a zero (e.g. \"\"0.5cc\"\") to limit confusion when reading.  Data entered with a leading zero doesn\"t result in the described SmartPhrase conversion.  Additionally, it isn\"t possible for the conversion to \"know\" whether or not the values entered as such are referencing a smartlink or if they are indicative of clinical data.\r\n(Confirm with regions) Potentially impacted regions (HI, NCAL, SCAL, Exempla, CO, OH, and GA) plan to use the workaround and work with Charles Selhorst to ensure the conversion is run, correct it and rerun the conversion to ensure patient safety.\"\r\n',NULL,'National Collaborative Build IntraConnect Team (Charles Selhorst) has been working closely with most regions to assist with pre-conversion preparations and conversion schedule, particulary GA and is recommending that the conversion in PRODGAM be delayed.. 11/19/07:  AMB may implement in 2nd quarter of 08. 12/10/07:  Only configuration change is needed, code is not needed as a fix.  Fix is a configuration change and will be standard in sp\"08.  Both AMB & IP will be impacted when conversion is implemted. 3/6:  per SF, NCal is deferring the HH1 conversion indefinitely. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 04:35:00','2009-08-11 03:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(169,3273107,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Bridges (EDI) - Component information of incoming results may be overwritten or altered, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-26 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Epic not planning to do a May 06 Kpackage unless regions request it.: confirmed in K051208\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758154, I746968\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208-E755765\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Neither AMB or IP affected by this issue. - Graying row','SU\"05-SP\"07-NO CURRENT IMPACT - AMB & IP.  Bridges (EDI) - Component information of incoming results may be overwritten or altered, in certain circumstances\r\n\"Potential Problem Description:    Component information of incoming results messages may be overwritten or altered if both of the following conditions are in place:\r\nThe Incoming Results Interface is configured with either:\r\nPULL_FWD set to option 1 or 2, or\r\nPULL_FWD_MICRO set to TRUE, and\r\nResults messages have either:\r\nthe same component ID and sub-ID combination in non-consecutive OBX segments, or\r\nthe same component ID and null sub-ID in consecutive OBX segments.\r\nSample Scenario:  Two incoming messages have the same component ID and sub-ID to comprise Component1. The first message has Component1 with Value1 and Value2.  The second message has Component1 with Value3 and Value4 in non-consecutive segments.  When the second message files, the Values are not updated or stored correctly, i.e., Value1 remains the same and Value3 is not stored.   Different scenarios produce other incorrect results.\r\nDiscovered by:   Another Epic customer\r\nReported by:   Epic (Dan Kempf)\r\n Remediation Action Plan:     Fix:  \r\nEpic (Dan Kempf) is developing a code fix for SP\"06 and SP\"07 and will inform PART by 3/28/08 of its status and KPackage.  The fix will be standard in SP\"08 and later.\r\n PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. \r\nPhysician Representative:  N/A (no current impact incident)\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3/26/08:  SU\"05-SP\"07 No Current Impact-AMB & IP.  No regions are currently impacted, as an Epic search revealed that no regions have the affected configuration. Fix will be standard in SP\"08.  3/27:  IP (Yolanda) & AMB (Susan) will confirm the configuration will not be used.  4/10:  Surekha to follow up regarding AMB. Per Yolanda, IP is not impacted-but will monitor. 5/5:  Not currently impacted.  Neither AMB or IP affected by this issue. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'3/26/08:  SU\"05-SP\"07 No Current Impact.  No regions are currently impacted, as an Epic search revealed that no regions have the affected configuration.  NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, Exempla, CO, OH, GA, and MAS could be potentially impacted if they implement the affected functionality.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 04:39:00','2008-10-29 02:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(170,3230290,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'If ED user double clicks an icon that takes them directly to an activity (rather than the navigator), the wrong patient is opened',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-10 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0310-AP-PR3230290-C7503446-E755220-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z, 0310-AP-PR3230290-C7503446-E755220-Spr07May12NS.zip\r\n','K051208',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'10',NULL,NULL,'MAR08','A','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Doesnt impact SP08 fix that KP will receive. Confirmed in K051208\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I757472\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3901):  \n  SP’07 C7503446 3/10/08 & E754904 3/28/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production.','SP07:  in the ED if a user double clicks an icon that takes them directly to an activity (rather than the navigator), the wrong patient is opened.\r\nSP07 & 08: In the ED Trackboard, if the provider highlights patient A, and clicks on unacknowledged orders icon for patient B, patient A\"s unacknowledged orders will display.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3/11: Covered in PS call. Andre will followup w/current status; NCAL must communicate workaround to facilities.  3/13:  Passed Testing.  Passed CAB. Will be installed 3/21.  3/24:  Per Yolanda, Successfully installed into production. Graying row. \r\n','Double check the patient header for verification of the correct patient, and double check the order pane\r\n',NULL,'Double check the patient header for verification of the correct patient, and double check the order pane\r\n',NULL,'per Andre M, NCAL affected 3/11:  Adhoc delivered on 3/10 per Andre.  Files 0310-AP-PR3230290-C7503446-E755220-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z, 0310-AP-PR3230290-C7503446-E755220-Spr07May12NS.zip.  3/13:  Passed Testing.  Passed CAB. Will be installed 3/21. 3/21:  Issue will not impact SP\"08. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 05:04:00','2008-10-29 11:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(171,3235153,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Scrolling in the documentation flowsheet activity may result in misaligned row data',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-11 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP\"06, SP\"07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K071607',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAR08','A','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I750663\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K071607-C7501228\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Unable to replicate.  Graying row.','SP\"06 & SP\"07:  Scrolling in the documentation flowsheet activity may result in misaligned row data\r\nSP06 & SP07: KPHC - Patient Safety - Scrolling down in the documentation flow sheet activity before enabling the last filed value column might cause the rows to misalign. Values could be misinterpreted; A blood pressure, weight, I/O, could potentially be displayed incorrectly.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"3/11:Covered in PS Call. Inpatient Suite will communicate with end users the proper workflow.  3/13:  Issue has to be replicated & discuss workflow with operations.  3/17:  Rebecca to follow up with exact workflow, so issue can be replicated. 3/20:  Unable to replicate.  Graying row. \r\n\"\r\n','Continue to scroll down to prevent misalignment or click last filed button first\r\n',NULL,'Continue to scroll down to prevent misalignment or click last filed button first\r\n',NULL,'\"per Epic Will be fixed in SP08. 3/13:  Issue has to be replicated & discuss workflow with operations.  3/17:  Rebecca to follow up with exact workflow, so issue can be replicated. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 05:11:00','2008-10-29 11:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(172,3255578,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Notewriter - Physical Exam macros can overwrite or add text to findings',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, AMB, Notewriter','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-20 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'3832','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0320-PS-PR3255578-E755302-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z\r\n','K051208',NULL,'2008-04-16 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'MAR08','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051208\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  E755302 (I757598)\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3832):  \n  SP’07 E755302 3/20/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208\nRISK RANKING:  4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Scheduled production date-April 16th','\"SP\"07 Notewriter - Physical Exam macros can overwrite or add text to findings .\r\n\"\r\n\"Detail Description:  Due to an error introduced with SP\"07 special update (E754967 - I757272), findings that a user has manually documented in Notewriter using certain SmartBlock macros, Physical Exam (HHS 148) or Physical Exam by Age (HHS 49001) can be altered in either of these two ways:\r\n1. Overwritten, if normal findings are documented with an abnormal (positive) macro;\r\n2. Normal text is pended, if abnormal findings are documented with a normal macro.\r\nThe problematic SU is included in the March Kpackage and two March adhocs.  One of the Adhocs, Ambulatory has requested for the April 16th Release.  Adhoc (3832) has been requested to get the fix and the code is due on 3/21. \r\nNCAL plans on installing this code immediately, so that NCAL can include with the April 16th Release.\r\nConcern:  If a user manually documents in Notewriter using certain SmartBlock \r\n                macros, Physical Exam or Physical Exam by Age, can be altered. \r\nSuites Affected:    Ambulatory, Inpatient, ED\r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Ben Broder\r\nProblem Discovered by:   Epic during internal testing\r\nEpic Representative / email address:  Rachel Logan / RLogan@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation:  None discussed\r\nAction items (immediate):  Epic (Brendan Krueger) released code fix E755302 (I757598) 3/20/08 & was authorized by SCAL\r\nAction items (future):   Expedite NCAL process so fix (adhoc-3832) can be installed with the April 16th release\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"3/20/08:  Affects-NCAL, SCAL, SP\"07, Notewriter,Suites: Ambulatory, Inpatient, ED.  SCAL authorized adhoc-3832.  3/21:  IP has replicated issue. Is AMB affected? 3/24: Melanie Grange is testing from AMB (hasn\"t been replicated yet). Adhoc delivered. No outage required. 3 sets of code need to be installed 4/16. NCAL not affected until 4/16.  3/31:  Code failed for AMB.  Apoorva will have Epic AMB rep to contact NCAL AMB AC.  Per Drew Davey (4pm):  Epic reviewing problem-The problem stems from the custom copy of the Physical Exam (PE) and Review of Systems (ROS) SmartBlocks which are currently in use @ NCAL.   4/3: Passed testing.  4/10:  Scheduled production date-April 16th. \r\n\"\r\n','Avoid using the affected macros until the fix is installed. \r\n',NULL,'Avoid using the affected macros until the fix is installed. \r\n',NULL,'\"3/20/08:  Affects-NCAL, SCAL, SP\"07, Notewriter,Suites: Ambulatory, Inpatient, ED.  SCAL authorized adhoc-3832.  3/21:  IP has replicated issue.  Is AMB affected?  4/3:  Passed testing:  0320-PS-PR3255578-E755302-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z . \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 05:31:00','2008-10-29 11:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(173,3254342,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'IV Fluid Orders showing incorrect dose when trying to administer',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-18 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0326-AP-PR3254342-E755523-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z\r\n','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'10',NULL,NULL,'MAR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fix installed in prod.  Graying row. ','SP07 - IP2 SSC SP07: IV Fluid Orders showing incorrect dose when trying to administer\r\n\"Workflow:  Nurse scans med on mar, Admin form that comes up is pre-populated with wrong rate.  E.g. 1000 ml displays, which is more of a dose.  Users can accept form with wrong rate w/o warning.\r\nBarcode on the mfg bag itself is causing the problem.  Large volume bags are premixed--no default rate as part of bar code..\r\nAppear to be pulling dose into rate field.  So far, affecting SSC, Santa Rosa, Antioch, WCR and Beacon in Santa Theresa.   \r\nNcal only phase 2 sites are impacted -- they use barcodes, no other regions do.  Occurred in NCAL, replicated in NCAL PSUP.\r\nSome patients impacted...verified that I/O is ok, \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Affects SP07 IP2 sites in NCAL, Beacon. Adhoc (3935) fix due 3/25. 3/31:  Fix installed 3/26 in WITS. Currently in testing. Scheduled for CAB on 4/1/08. 4/2:  When testing the fix for the PS issue for Barcode Scanning, Beatrice detected another issue.  Epic has found the root cause of the problem and is working on an additional fix.  No ETA however they are aware this is a Patient Safety issue.  Per ETS, passed testing.  Adhoc 3976 created to correct TD 29020, found when testing Patient Safety fix.  4/10:  Expected date to receive fix for adhoc 3976 on April 15th. Workaround is in place.  4/21:  Passed Testing.  (Second fix:  0414-AP-TD29020-E755690-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z) Both the fix and the \"fix to the fix\" are going to CAB today.  4/28:  Fix installed in prod.  Graying row. \r\n','\"After scanning an IV bag, take the following steps:\r\n1. In the MAR Administration window, review the Rate field.\r\n2. If the correct rate is not displayed, manually enter the correct Rate.\r\n3. A MAR Alert window opens with the message Entered rate is more than rate ordered.  Select either Override reason.  Click the Accept button.\r\n4. On the MAR in the Time Column, confirm that the correct rate is displayed.\r\nAfter scanning an IV bag, take the following steps:\r\n1. In the MAR Administration window, review the Rate field.\r\n2. If the correct rate is not displayed, manually enter the correct Rate.\r\n3. A MAR Alert window opens with the message Entered rate is more than rate ordered.  Select either Override reason.  Click the Accept button.\r\n4. On the MAR in the Time Column, confirm that the correct rate is displayed.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"After scanning an IV bag, take the following steps:\r\n1. In the MAR Administration window, review the Rate field.\r\n2. If the correct rate is not displayed, manually enter the correct Rate.\r\n3. A MAR Alert window opens with the message Entered rate is more than rate ordered.  Select either Override reason.  Click the Accept button.\r\n4. On the MAR in the Time Column, confirm that the correct rate is displayed.\r\nAfter scanning an IV bag, take the following steps:\r\n1. In the MAR Administration window, review the Rate field.\r\n2. If the correct rate is not displayed, manually enter the correct Rate.\r\n3. A MAR Alert window opens with the message Entered rate is more than rate ordered.  Select either Override reason.  Click the Accept button.\r\n4. On the MAR in the Time Column, confirm that the correct rate is displayed.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"IP phase 2 sites are affected in NCAL.  Fix due 3/25.  WrkAround Communicated.  3/26: 0326-AP-PR3254342-E755523-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z received, in WITS.  4/3: Adhoc 3976 created, required to correct TD 29020, found when testing Patient Safety fix.  4/21:  Passed Testing--0326-AP-PR3254342-E755523-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 05:36:00','2008-10-29 11:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(174,3279408,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Preference Lists Default Dose Count for Medication Orders may be Inaccurate',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-28 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K030308',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'MAR08','N','S','P','M',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I755757\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3959):  \n  SP’07 E755030 3/28/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K030308\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' Installed into Production.','SP\"07 IP - NCAL & SCAL Only - Preference Lists Default Dose Count for Medication Orders may be Inaccurate. \r\n\"CPOE Domain and Facility Preference Lists with Medication Entries with a Count Type of Number of Doses may be impacted. When these medication orders are selected in CPOE, the number of doses may be removed and the order may be active indefinitely.\r\nMedication preference lists may not display the dose count that was specified in the ERX build. The Medication Display Name is accurate however, the count displays as indefinite (e.g. until discontinued).  For example, a medication assigned a default of 4x/day will display the Medication Name appropriately, however, the default count is not used, instead it displays ?until discontinued? which may mean indefinitely. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SP\"07 IP - NCAL & SCAL Only--Rx (BK) sent immediate communication notifications to Pharmacists 3/27/08 about the incident. Critical items were fixed 3/27/08 for NCAL and SCAL, continuing with other items 3/28/08, until fix is provided. Per BK, DB remediation (pref list) completed, no further intervention required.  3/31:  Per BK, fix is in WITS. Testing in progress. 4/3:  Installed into Production.\r\n','\"During Verification, the Pharmacist should contact the physician to clarify the number of doses that should be dispensed, until a fix is available.\r\nNCAL ? For example, pharmacists should be aware that all PeriOP orders ?x #? doses will not discontinue after one or two doses and he/she will have to clarify with the physician how many doses were to be administered.\r\nSCAL ? For example, pharamcists should be aware that the majority of the vaccine orders are ?x #? doses and he/she will have to select ?For: 1 Dose? in the Order Composer.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"During Verification, the Pharmacist should contact the physician to clarify the number of doses that should be dispensed, until a fix is available.\r\nNCAL ? For example, pharmacists should be aware that all PeriOP orders ?x #? doses will not discontinue after one or two doses and he/she will have to clarify with the physician how many doses were to be administered.\r\nSCAL ? For example, pharamcists should be aware that the majority of the vaccine orders are ?x #? doses and he/she will have to select ?For: 1 Dose? in the Order Composer.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Epic (Joy Mayfield) will provide a code fix by 3/28/08 (Included in 0303 KPackage). National Pharmacy (Sek Shia) provided an ad hoc code fix authorization 3/27/08.  API will work with NCAL and SCAL to implement the code fix in production on 3/31/08, after it is available and tested. 3/28:  per BK, The Database team has completed manual remediation on all the affected items in several NCAL preference lists @ 11:30AM today. Root cause has been determined and fix is forthcoming.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 05:48:00','2008-10-29 12:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(175,3279981,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Specific ED Physical Exam Navigator Section Documentation may not Display or Save depending upon certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-28 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0402-PS-PR3204175-C7503474-E755569-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z0402-PS-PR3204175-C7503474-E755569-Spr07May12NS.zip0402-PS-PR3204175-C7503474-E755569-Spr07May12NS-EPICWEB.zip0402-PS-PR3204175-C7503474-E755569-Spr07May12NS-HOMEHEALTH.zip\r\n','K051208',NULL,'2008-06-08 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'7',NULL,NULL,'MAR08','N','S','F','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051208\nAD HOC DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 C7503474 & E755569  4/02/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208- C7503474 & E755569\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production.','SP\"07 - Specific ED Physical Exam Navigator Section Documentation may not Display or Save depending upon certain circumstances\r\n\"There may be a problem with clinical findings documented in 2007 for Physical Exam forms, that were not fully moved to be properly used by the Physical Exam navigator section (LVN 27001).  Consequently, certain findings or comments may not be displayed in the section\"s closed view print group and may not be pulled into notes correctly with the .PENAV SmartLink.   \r\nSpecific concepts that are affected include:\r\nBasic tab - The \"Guaiac Tested\" tri-state on the basic tab of the Physical exam for male patients will not save or display comments left on the tri-state. This only affects the section that shows for a male patient. If you enter the comment on the detailed GU form it will display properly, if you try to delete it from the basic tab the comment will not really be deleted. If you delete the comment from the GU tab it will behave normally. \r\nAlso from the Basic tab, findings for right and left eye \"Discharge\" do not show in the closed section if there is only a comment on the neutral tri-state for either. \r\n\"Scleral icterus\" does not appear. \r\nHENT tab - Ears - \"Hemotympanum\" findings do not appear.\r\nEyes tab - Visual fields findings do not appear.\r\nMusculoskeletal tab -The findings for \"Lateral Malleous Tenderness\" on the right and left ankles do not appear.\r\nAlso the findings of \"Ecchymosis\" for both the right and left knees appear as \"Crepitus\".\r\nNeurological tab -On the Neuro tab, If you select \"Alert\" as well as \"Muscular Strength 5/5 and Symmetric\" and switch to the Basic tab, \"Alert\" becomes unchecked and does not save.   Instead, the user may manually addend a note.\r\nPlease note that in all affected tabs the documented findings are not displayed, but are saved in the chart, with the exception of the Basic and Neurological tab.  Those findings documented in the Neuro tab and some in the Basic tab are not saved.  On closing and reopening the chart, all findings or observations documented do appear in the chart, except the Neuro and certain Basic findings.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NO NCAL CURRENT IMPACT - IMMINENT for NW - CLINICALLY SEVERE - FREQUENT- LIMITED - SP\"07.  3/31:  Issue will be resolved with Notewriter install on 4/24. Workaround is the PE section removed. 4/3:  The fix for 3279981 the same as the fix for 3204175. 4/10:  Decision has been made to wait for the fix in the May Kpkg.  5/19: Decided to pursue Adhoc- 3884. submitted to CAB for 5/19. 5/22: Passed CAB approved for 6/8 install.  6/9 Installed on 6/8/08\r\n',' The user may document, close the chart, and reopen the chart to double check the chart.\r\n',NULL,' The user may document, close the chart, and reopen the chart to double check the chart.\r\n',NULL,'\"Epic (Robyn Pingel) will provide a status update about the SP\"07 code fix by 4/14/08 and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair).  NCAL also uses this navigator and is not impacted because they stopped using this section upon upgrading to SP\"07 (due to previous Patient Safety Incident) and are currently in the process of implementing NoteWriter in the ED.  NW to adhoc.  4/10:  0402-PS-PR3204175-C7503474-E755569-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z0402-PS-PR3204175-C7503474-E755569-Spr07May12NS.zip0402-PS-PR3204175-C7503474-E755569-Spr07May12NS-EPICWEB.zip0402-PS-PR3204175-C7503474-E755569-Spr07May12NS-HOMEHEALTH.zip.\r\n \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-16 05:54:00','2008-10-29 12:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(176,3258515,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Treatment plan first dose scheduling  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-03-20 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'3928','su05-sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','\"0505-PS-PR3258515-E755992-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z\r\n\"\r\n','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'BCON','N','S','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3928):  \n  SP’07 E755992 5/05/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' Fix installed in production (with May Kpkg).  Graying Row.  ',' Fall\"04-SP\"07 (Beacon) - First dose scheduling for Treatment Plan Orders using Specified frequencies may not be respected\r\n\"Detail Description:  A Treatment Plan order can be configured with a first dose based on the released time (include now) or based on the frequency scheduled times.  If specified frequencies are used, when released, the first scheduled instance/dose setting (EFQ 150) from the frequency will be respected instead of the order setting.  The total doses will remain accurate, but the schedule times will unexpectedly change when the order is released.\r\nFor example, an order in a Treatment Plan has a scheduled frequency of Daily at 7:00AM for 4 doses.  The Daily at 7:00AM specified frequency is configured with a first scheduled instance based on the scheduled time (not Include Now).  On Wednesday at 7:45AM a user changes the order to \"\"Include Now\"\" and signs the order, which changes the scheduled occurrences to Wednesday 7:45AM, Thursday 7:00AM, Friday 7:00AM, and Saturday 7:00AM.  Normally, even if the order was released at a later time such as Wednesday 11:00AM, since Include Now was selected, the first scheduled dose would start at the release time of Wednesday 11:00AM.\r\nDue to this issue, when the order is released, the order scheduling will not respect the include now, and instead schedule based on the frequency setup to follow the scheduled time of 7:00AM.  As a result if the order is released Wednesday 7:45AM, the 4 doses will be scheduled at Thursday 7:00AM, Friday 7:00AM, Saturday 7:00AM, and Sunday 7:00 AM.\r\nIssue affects Santa Teresa (only) & there are 22 affected records. \r\nAdhoc authorization made by Dr. Bliss.\r\nConcern:  Treatment may be given at an incorrect time.\r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Bob Dolin\r\nProblem Discovered by:   Another Epic Client\r\nRemediation:  None discussed\r\nAction items (immediate):  Workaround to be communicated\r\nAction items (future):   Epic will provide a fix (adhoc) ETA on April 2nd, 2008.  \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3/20/08:  Affects-NCAL (Santa Teresa), SU\"05-SP\"07, Beacon.  Fix (adhoc) status provided by Epic 4/2/08.  Adhoc requested: 3928.  RFC created:  CHG000002420153. 3/31:  Programming point rejected. Communication sent. Rebecca will follow up for Thursday meeting (4/3). 4/9:  Is the workaround in place/communicated? 4/10:  Per Macy, comunication has been sent.  4/14:  Waiting for Epic to provide fix.  4/21:  Rebecca to follow up.  5/1/08:  Fix expected 5/5/08.  5/5:  Per Apoorva, Server fix only. Per Sheryl Balicanta, 6/7/08 install is ok.  Per Macy, users are aware not to use \"Include Now\".  5/8:  Fix received &  installed into WITS 3 on 5/7/08.  5/12/08:  Per Katie-Confirmed and replicated the issue.  Fix did  come, Ad Hoc available. Per Theresa this will go into WITS3 enviro 5/8. Waiting for fix to drop into test environment.  RFC created by Alex Strabinsky. When will this go to CAB? Per Bliss we need to push forward for June 8th prod drop. 5/28:  when will fix be installed into production? 6/12:  Tom to follow up with Kelly.  7/31:  sent email to Yongmei request to know if fix has been installed in production. 8/3/08:  Per Yongmei, Fix installed in production (with May Kpkg).  Graying Row. \r\n','\"A validation programming point can be used to prevent the signing of orders in the Treatment Plan if orders have first dose scheduling which is different from the first scheduled dose in the selected frequency. The Orders can be placed from Order Entry instead of the Treatment Plan if a different first dose scheduling needs to be selected.  \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"A validation programming point can be used to prevent the signing of orders in the Treatment Plan if orders have first dose scheduling which is different from the first scheduled dose in the selected frequency. The Orders can be placed from Order Entry instead of the Treatment Plan if a different first dose scheduling needs to be selected.  \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"3/20/08:  Affects-NCAL (Santa Teresa), SU\"05-SP\"07, Beacon.  Fix (adhoc) ETA provided by Epic 4/2/08.  Adhoc requested: 3928.  RFC created:  CHG000002420153.  4/3: Per Liz Nichols, the fix is underway but not completed, more info by 4/9/08.\r\nThe log number is I758114.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 09:32:00','2009-03-05 04:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(177,3703895,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Vaginal Bleeding Section may not generate NoteWriter Text without Vaginal Discharge Finding','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-27 00:00:00','2008-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Only impacts SP08. Fix is a part of SP08 IU4; Closed out\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, SP08 only, does not affect SP07, fixed in SU09.  ',' NO CURRENT IMPACT - SP\"08 - Vaginal Bleeding Section may not generate NoteWriter Text without Vaginal Discharge Finding\r\n\"The Acute Abdomen Syndrome text that contains the text for all statements relating to vaginal bleeding uses a rule which is too restricted and may only generate text if the \"\"Vaginal Discharge\"\" finding is also selected.\r\nWorkflow Example:  Create a new Notewriter note using the History of Present Illness (HPI) or SmartForm History of Present Illness (SFHPI) SmartBlock in your note template.\r\nOn the HPI tab, add the chief complaint that is mapped to the Acute Abdomen HPI Template.\r\nSelect a positive finding for Vaginal Bleeding in the Primary Symptoms section.  The text generated indicates a primary symptom of Vaginal Bleeding.\r\nDocument symptom-specific details on the Vaginal Bleeding subsection.  Data entered in the Vaginal Bleeding subsection doesn\"t generate text.\r\nSelect the positive finding for Vaginal Discharge in the Primary Symptoms section.  The data entered from step 4 now generates text in the note.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL not affected because not yet using SP08.  No fix info available.  SP08: NCAL not affected because not yet using SP08 (will we use this functionality in SP08)   \r\n','Regions may use previously released Abdominal Pain pediatric and adult templates 50164 - ED SF PED - Abdominal Pain and 50030 - ED SF HPI - Abdominal Pain instead of 50543 - ED HPI SB - Acute Abdomen.\r\n',NULL,'Regions may use previously released Abdominal Pain pediatric and adult templates 50164 - ED SF PED - Abdominal Pain and 50030 - ED SF HPI - Abdominal Pain instead of 50543 - ED HPI SB - Acute Abdomen.\r\n',NULL,'Epic (Brendan Krueger) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 09:56:00','2009-07-22 02:01:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(178,3703882,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Smart Form Scripting-Concept Lists may Clear other Components while Loading under specific circumstances','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-26 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Impacts SP08 but standard in versions KP is implementing. Closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I767360\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, SP08 only, does not affect SP07, fixed in SU09.  ','\"Smart Form Scripting - Concept Lists may Clear other Components while Loading under specific circumstances\r\n\"\r\n\" In SP\"08, data may be lost after a SmartForm script is run.  When a SmartForm uses a script to check the value on a Concept ID List component and then sets the value on another component, the value on the second component may be lost in the following workflow:\r\nOpen a patient\"s chart and access a Smart Form that contains the following components:\r\nA list component that is data bound to a Concept ID List - Component A\r\nAnother component - Component B\r\nA SmartForm script that sets a value on Component B if Component A has nothing selected\r\nSelect a value for Component A that causes the SmartForm script to be executed.\r\nSelect a value for Component B.\r\nClose the form (i.e. exit out of the SmartForm, close the SmartForm navigator section, or jump to another activity if the affected SmartForm is in the Notewriter).\r\nReturn to the same SmartForm in the same patient encounter.\r\nClose the form.\r\nReturn to the form.  Notice the value on Component B no longer appears.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Follow-Up:  Per Epic (Austin Guentner) SP\"08 SU is through testing and is being prepared for release.  The SU number for this incident is  is C7600652.  This is SP\"08 only, so there is no SP\"07 SU.  This fix will be in the March 16 KPackage.  Not an issue until SP08.  Waiting for fix info.\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster or Austin Guentner) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 09:59:00','2009-07-22 01:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(179,3292210,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Patient log documentation may be overwritten if 2 users click ?file? (save) simultaneously within Op-time, Notewriter & Smartforms under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0408-PS-PR3292210-E755672-Spr07May12NS-Docs.doc, 0408-PS-PR3292210-E755672-Spr07May12NS-Rel.doc:  outage required \r\n','K051208',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051208 for SP07; not for SP06\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I746990\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3975):  \n  SP’06 E745068 4/28/08\n  SP’07 E755672 4/08/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'no region currently has any HLV records affected by this issue. \"','SP06, SP07--Patient log documentation may be overwritten if 2 users click ?file? (save) simultaneously within Op-time, Notewriter & Smartforms under specific circumstances.\r\n\"Detail Description:   Patient log documentation may be overwritten by 2 users clicking ?file? (save) simultaneously within Op-time, Notewriter & Smartforms under specific circumstances.  Op-time:  Surgical log documentation for patient A may be overwritten with patient B?s info if two clinicians save surgical log info simultaneously.  Notewriter: If a user saves documentation in an HLV record for patient A, then that documentation may be overwritten by a 2nd user documenting in an HLV record for patient B if both users save simultaneously.  Smartforms:  If a user saves documentation in a Smartform for patient A, then that documentation may be overwritten by a 2nd user documenting in a Smartform for patient B if both users save simultaneously.  \r\nFor Optime the affected records are ?dynamic implant records?.   The Antioch facility is the only known NCAL facility where this issue has occurred (2 separate instances in January 2008, discovered by Epic query.)   It is possible for this issue to occur in any NCAL facility with SP06 - SP07 Op-time, Notewriter (depending on the level of implementation) & Smartforms.   It is possible for the 1st user to be using a different form than the 2nd user (example:  OB documentation may be overwritten by Orthopedics documentation). Users may or may not be documenting the same patient.  An occurrence of the Notewriter / Smartforms issue has not yet been observed in NCAL. \r\nExample:  Op-time-If a user saves documentation for a hip replacement? in the surgical log for patient A, then that documentation may be overwritten by a 2nd user documenting a ?pacemaker? in the surgical log for patient B if both users save simultaneously.\r\nConcern:  Patient documentation may be overwritten & lost. \r\nSuites Affected:    Op-time, Notewriter, Smartforms (SP06 & SP07)\r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Scott Adelman\r\nProblem Discovered by:   Epic Testing\r\nEpic Representative / email address:   Ben Sherman/ bsherman@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation: None\r\n\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"4/1/08:  Op-time, Notewriter, Smartforms (SP06 & SP07).  Epic is working on a  fix.  Ben thinks the fix should be ready for delivery on 4/4/2008.   Hawaii to adhoc. 4/3:  No queries received. Tom to follow up with Epic (Ben).  NCAL requested adhoc since unsure if Hawaii requested the adhoc. Adhoc requested:  3975. 4/7:  Unable to replicate.  Working with Epic. PART to follow up regarding fix delivery. 4/8: fix received. 4/10:  Code installed into WITS 2.  Install target date is April 16th.  4/14:  Passed testing. Approved in an emergency CAB on friday (4/11).  Received from PART:  Information from Epic (Betsy Radtke) - The searches for affected HLV records have been run at all the regions, and no region currently has any HLV records affected by this issue.\r\n\"\r\n','None.  Epic recommended parallel paper documentation which later can be reconciled with the info entered into HealthConnect. \r\n',NULL,'None.  Epic recommended parallel paper documentation which later can be reconciled with the info entered into HealthConnect. \r\n',NULL,' Epic will provide an Op-time query 4/1/2008, to identify any additional occurrences of this issue.     A query for Notewriter/Smartform will be ready by 4/2/2008.   Hawaii will submit an adhoc request.  Epic is working on a  fix.  Ben thinks the fix should be ready for delivery on 4/8/2008.  4/8: received 0408-PS-PR3292210-E755672-Spr07May12NS-Docs.doc, 0408-PS-PR3292210-E755672-Spr07May12NS-Rel.doc--outage required. 4/14: FOLLOW-UP Information from Epic (Betsy Radtke) - The searches for affected HLV records have been run at all the regions, and no region currently has any HLV records affected by this issue. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 11:01:00','2008-10-29 10:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(181,2515219,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Checkmark Defaults for Meds with Past End Dates ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0911-PS-PR2515219-E744089-Spr06Nov05NS.tar.Z\r\n','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'10',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','N','L','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I753515, I745435, I735332\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3295):  \n  SP’06 E744089 9/11/07 & E744347 9/26/07\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’06 K110507\n  SP’07 K110507\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Graying row.','Taking Checkmark Defaults for Medications with Past End Dates \r\n\"Historical medications may be incorrectly flagged (e.g., in print groups or the Medications Activity) as \"\"Taking,\"\" even if the patient no longer is doing so, if both of the following conditions are met:\r\n1. A provider signs a medication order that has a past end date.\r\n2. The system definition default for new medication orders is set to Mark as Taking.\r\nNote:  The term \"\"Taking\"\" has replaced \"\"Active\"\" and is not the same as \"\"Current.\"\"\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"(June) All versions; Epic to update PART by 6/20 - - 6/18/07 Adhoc 3295 Created.  ETA 8/31.  - Update 9/7:  K110507 Package, Update 9/11:  Code arrived 9/11 Update 9/13: ETS replicated 9/13/07 Update 9/25:  code instaled into RENC 9/19 , awaiting regression testing. Update 10/10:  Per Katie Volpe - OK to wait till 11/28 - per Dr. Bornstein.  11/01/07:  Regression testing in progress. 11/08:  problem in testing, believed due to missing Unix patch. KR checking which servers have patch.  11/15: ETS testing in NBay server, to CAB today on contingency.  11/19/07:  This was not a kp problem from beginning. Fix will go in because it\"s needed for another issue. Dr. Bliss will contact Lisa Phiefer.  12/20/07:  Ok to wait until SP\"07.  2/4/08:  Adhoc failed testing. TD24131.   2/7/08:  Annotated for ED & IP.  RN125377, 125379. 2/25 Working with Epic on fix. 2/28: Workaround in place. 3/6/08 per Surekha item to go in w/ SP07.  4/21:  Tom to work with Kelly on validating fix install. Tom to contact Sheryl. 5/8:  Per Katie, this functionality is not built in our AMB dept.  Issue is not a Beacon issue.  Tested for IP. Surekha to follow up. Tracking on May Tab. (Moved to May tab - Issue was reported in June\"07, but there is not a June\"07 tab). - - Per Surekha, Fix went in with Spring 07. We need to get the fix validated by Alex Koppel or ADiti Vakil. Defect is still open, so we cannot close the issue. But the defect is not a major impact.   5/12/08:  Per Katie:  We don?t use taking check marks. Per Sukreta this was tested for Inpatient and went in in november. Is this in PROD, yes if from NOV K Package.   5/15/08:  Current TD 28322 for SP\"07--Does not affect NCAL.  5/19: per dhea, still waiting on Alex K. 5/22: Alex K to discuss with Epic.  6/2:  Apoorva to follow up. 6/9/: Apoorva waiting for answer from Christie will have by next meeting.  6/19:  Per Apoorva-Kristie is waiting for clarification from Aditi and Alex Koppel. Dhea to follow up. 6/26:  Alex contacted Epic.  Waiting for a response from Epic. 6/30:  Apoorva to follow up with Kristie. 7/2:  per Dhea: Alex and Kristie discussed this defect and this does not impact Inpatient.   Per Alex, Ambulatory may want to review the defect and see if it impacts them.  Tom forwards Dhea\"s note to Sandra F/Carol D.  7/7:  IP not viewing this TD as PS. Tom to follow up with AMB. 7/8:  from Carol Devlin: \"\"Per Katie Volpe, we do not use the taking check marks in Beacon.  She states that this is not a Beacon issue nor is the functionality built in ambulatory\"\".  7/10:  Graying row. ','\"Special Updates will be created for necessary versions that will not set the \"\"taking\"\" flag if a user signs an order with a past end date.\r\nWorkaround\r\n(1)     Ask users to uncheck the \"\"taking\"\" flag when placing historical medication orders with past end dates.\r\n(2)     Set the field to 1-No Change and ask users to manually check the \"\"taking\"\" flag when placing any medication order.  Note that if a provider fails to check \r\nthe \"\"taking\"\" flag, this may result in a provider placing a duplicate therapy order if they rely on this flag as a visual indication of what medications the patient is currently on.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Special Updates will be created for necessary versions that will not set the \"\"taking\"\" flag if a user signs an order with a past end date.\r\nWorkaround\r\n(1)     Ask users to uncheck the \"\"taking\"\" flag when placing historical medication orders with past end dates.\r\n(2)     Set the field to 1-No Change and ask users to manually check the \"\"taking\"\" flag when placing any medication order.  Note that if a provider fails to check \r\nthe \"\"taking\"\" flag, this may result in a provider placing a duplicate therapy order if they rely on this flag as a visual indication of what medications the patient is currently on.\"\r\n',NULL,'\" NCAL - Victoria Burbidge will bring the issue to management to decide whether an Adhoc is warranted and will be requested. At this time no Adhoc has been requested. Epic is investigating whether this will be included in the next K-pack delivery. Epic will determine when the eta is and report back to part by Wed 6/20/07.  0911-PS-PR2515219-E744089-Spr06Nov05NS.tar.Z.  UPDATE 9/28:  Per ETS, Ambulatory wants regression testing. ETS indicated it has passed testing. ETS will be able to run a regression cycle along with Sep K package RN items in RENC CAM from Oct 15 to 11/02 which will be definitely covering the medications function cross suite. ETS can include this patient safety issue and regress the function around this.\r\nUpdate from ETS 9/27, passed testing Update 10/4 from ETS PS issue tested and passed  ETS will be regression testing this function as part of Sep K regression from Oct 15 - Nov 02 in RENC CAM.  11/01/07:  Regression testing in progress.  11/08:  problem in testing, believed due to missing Unix patch.  KR checking which servers have patch.  11/12/07:  Confirmed in K110507 Sp07 RN\"s 125377, 125379.  11/19/07:  This was not a kp problem from beginning. Fix will go in because it\"s needed for another issue. Dr. Bliss will contact Lisa Phiefer. 12/20/07:  Ok to wait until SP\"07.   2/4/08:  Adhoc failed testing. TD24131.  0911-PS-PR2515219-E744089-Spr06Nov05NS.tar.Z.     2/7/08:  Annotated for ED & IP.  RN125377, 125379.  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 11:22:00','2008-10-29 10:33:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(182,3390483,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Neonatal Dose Checking Alert may not Occur if Gestational Age is Missing under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ip, rx','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-08 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','sp06, sp07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  FDB & Epic ,working with National Pharmacy developed a BPA solution that is being implemented.\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Gray out','SP?06-SP?07 - -  IP, Rx - -Neonatal Dose Checking Alert may not Occur if Gestational Age is Missing under specific circumstances\r\n\"Description:  Neonatal Dose Checking Alert may not Occur if Gestational Age is Missing under specific circumstances.  First Data Bank (FDB) requires a new condition, the gestational age field, to be completed in order for the Epic Dose Checking Module to fire a neonatal dose checking alert.  If gestational age isn\"t documented in the appropriate field (not simply as text in a note), the neonatal dose checking alerts do not fire.\r\nReleases:  SP\"06 and SP\"07 when the March KPackage is loaded (5/16) in Prodnam for community tracked items.  Once Prodnam loads the FDB data for dose checking (5/22) including gestational age requirement, Regions will be impacted after 5/27 once the data is propagated.  Gestational age is required to be entered in the Epic Inpatient application at the regional level, in order for the neonatal dose checking alerts to fire.  \r\nNCAL, SCAL, HI, and Exempla are potentially imminently impacted, when the March KPackage is loaded (5/16) AND the FDB data is loaded, currently scheduled for 5/22/08.  \r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr.  Andy Weisenthal\r\nProblem Discovered by:   National Pharmacy \r\nEpic Representative / email address:  Joy Mayfield / JMayfield@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation:  None discussed \r\nAction items (immediate):  National Pharmacy (Howard Switzky, Bill Yee and Elissa Liong) will work with FDB and Epic (Joy Mayfield) to determine a long-term solution for the gestational age condition requirement necessary for dose checking alerts to fire.\r\nAction items (future):   TBD (FDB & Epic). Follow up regarding workaround. \r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL, SCAL, HI, and Exempla. IP & Rx.  5/15/08:   IP testing a code workaround. Testing a code to autopopulate GA, results in week of 5/19.  Andre Santana working on Best practice alerts.  5/20:  Epic fix not yet available and is a work in progress. 5/22 Arturo to let us know status update on Mon. 5/23:  Per Andre Santana, National creating a new row which will only allow the gestational age to be entered one way-which is the agreed solution between NCAL & SCAL. This one row will be added on Tuesday as a part of the workaround. 5/29:  Andre & Arturo to follow up regarding best practice alerts.  6/2:  Best practice alerts have been installed.   Beatrice to find out which person from National Rx is working on the issue. 6/9: Apoorva to follow up withTom Sharkey. Short term fix is in place waiting for long term fix from FTB and Epic. 6/16: per Apoorva  The meetings between FDB, KP and Epic have already happened. Tom Sharkey will be getting in touch with Beatrice to provide clarification and answer her questions. 6/19:  The call with Beatrice has happened and all the clarifications have been made. KP should not be waiting for anything from Epic and Beatrice has closed the issue. Waiting for long term fix from FDB and Epic. 6/30:  Closed, per Beatrice: \"FDB will not be change their data eg including gestational age in their dosing alert tables. EPIC developers of the interaction/alert code, believes the current EPIC code is appropriate, eg taking into consideration the gestational age data coming from FDB.\"  Greying out. \r\n','Work-in-Progress.  Attach a ?Best Practice Alert? so the user is then alerted.  Workaround information: As communicated earlier, the use of the BPA is the recommended workaround for this incident. Epic (Joy Mayfield) is following up with Rx R&D to provide measures to facilitate efficient maintenance of the BPA. The BPA shouldn\"t need to change unless First Data Bank (FDB) adds or removes a generic name from the list. It\"s not tied to ERX so it shouldn\"t be changed weekly with every FDB load, but there is some maintenance involved.\r\n',NULL,'Work-in-Progress.  Attach a ?Best Practice Alert? so the user is then alerted.  Workaround information: As communicated earlier, the use of the BPA is the recommended workaround for this incident. Epic (Joy Mayfield) is following up with Rx R&D to provide measures to facilitate efficient maintenance of the BPA. The BPA shouldn\"t need to change unless First Data Bank (FDB) adds or removes a generic name from the list. It\"s not tied to ERX so it shouldn\"t be changed weekly with every FDB load, but there is some maintenance involved.\r\n',NULL,'Concern:  User will not be alerted if the gestational age is not populated.  6/2: Epic contacts:  Tom Sharkey & Joy Mayfield.  6/13:  Long term fix information: A long term fix requires collaboration between EPIC and FDB.  FDB must configure their medication concepts to confirm the gestational age information required by the EPIC application.  Per Sek Shia, KP Natl Pharmacy representatives are actively working with EPIC and FDB to reach a resolution.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 11:25:00','2008-10-29 10:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(183,3433560,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Chart Synch - Data is not Synchronized Between Deployments.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-05-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','sp06-sp08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0612-CE-PR3482308-E756390-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z  (Requires outage) \r\n','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAY08','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Epic & regions running cleanup in production on a weekly basis; no ad hoc authorized. Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759190\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 E756390 available as of 6/11/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production. ','SP?06-SP?08 ? Chart Synch - Data is not Synchronized Between Deployments.  \r\n\"Detail Description:  Chart Synchronization, in certain identified cases, the generation index which stores item groups to be synchronized between deployments can contain extra delimiters that prevent those groups from being synchronized.  Data is updated at the editing deployment, but at other deployments that have a copy of the records, the modified data is not received and the records are not updated.  Clinical Data Affected:  52 in Central / 86 in Golden Gate / 111 in South Bay.  \r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. George Peredy \r\nRemediation:   None discussed\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"5/23/08:  NCAL, SCAL - Chart Synch.  Adhoc authorized by Collin Parker (SCAL). DLG:  i759190.  Adhoc ETA is June 10th, 2008.  Fix will also be in the July K-Package.  Fix will require an outage.  5/28:  Will NCAL pursue adhoc? 5/29:  Rebecca to follow up with Epic regarding utility. 6/2:  per KR: The Seach and Cleanup utility has been developed and tested in SCAL by Robert Shimmin on 5/30/08.  NCAL Testing will occur this week. Emily Jenkins will work with NCAL on testing. Once successful, the utility will be used for production. I have asked Emily to keep me updated. 6/9: Yolanda to follow up. Per Yolanda I looked up the DLG 759190 and under PR3482308 (E756390) which is scheduled delivery date is 6/11/08 and it has not arrived yet. This ad hoc prevents a situation where GI nodes in chart sync globals become misformatted, causing synchronization in dynamic data. 619: PR3482308 installed in WITS2. Per Margaret, code for 3482308 fixes this patient safety issue (3433560). Margaret and the CE testing team will test this on Friday 6/20 and will submit CAB spreadsheet to Peg today 6/23/08. 6/23:  Going to CAB today.  \r\n7/28:  Row Grayed out.  \"\r\n','\"Epic will be running a temporary clean up utility once a week (unless requested otherwise) to correct the index and re-send information.  Clean-up will be performed until fix is implemented.\r\n\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Epic will be running a temporary clean up utility once a week (unless requested otherwise) to correct the index and re-send information.  Clean-up will be performed until fix is implemented.\r\n\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,'5/23/08:  Concern:  Patient data not being synchronized-which will cause modified data to not be available. Epic Representative / email address:   Emily Jenkins / emjenkin@epicsystems.com.  Problem Discovered by:   Epic. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 11:27:00','2008-10-29 10:22:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(185,3304296,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'System default times override WHEN (one-time) frequencies saved to Preference Lists or Smart Sets',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, ED, Beacon',' SP\"07 DLG  I758305/ E755698','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-08 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'3987','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K051208',NULL,'2008-06-08 00:00:00','N','P','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'APR08','Y','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051208\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I758305/E755698\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3987):  \n  SP’07 E755698 4/18/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208-E755698\nRISK RANKING:  6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production.','SP\"07 IP -  System default times override WHEN (one-time) frequencies saved  to Preference Lists or Smart Sets (MAR, Preference Lists, Order Sets, protocols). If a provider changes the frequency of a medication order to a WHEN  frequency (i.e., one-time or STAT) while saving the order to his or her Preference List, the system will still use the default date and time as configured in system definition settings.  If the default date and time, based on system definition settings, ends before the medication is administered, the medication drops off the MAR without alerting the clinician.  \r\nFor example: At 10am, a provider uses his/her personal Preference List to order a medication to be administered at 1pm that day, using a medication order whose frequency was previously changed to WHEN.\r\nThe system definition setting for the medication specifies an end time of 12:30pm.\r\nAt 12:30 pm, the medication drops off the MAR with no notice.\r\nThe clinician never realizes that the provider ordered an administration for 1pm.\r\nThis occurs only when WHEN frequencies are saved to User Preference Lists, not those of Facility or Department. Epic ran searches showing that a number of records in NCAL and SCAL have been impacted; although no active patient records were identified. Epic (Michael Bries) will provide a code fix by 4/18/08.  Fix info: SP\"07 DLG  I758305/E755698; outage required. Epic (Michael Bries) provided instructions for building the programming point.  When the code is installed, Epic will provide information whether the programming point will have to be removed. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rosalba working to install prog pt.  Kelly has submitted adhoc req. #3987.  ETA for fix 4/18. 4/9: Rosalba et al are testing the programming point. 4/10:  Issue has been replicated and programming point currently in testing. Regression testing in progress. Programming point will be removed once the fix has been installed into production.  4/11:  LPP (prog pt) has passed testing.  4/14:  Passed emergency CAB.  Install date April 16th. 4/21:  Fix installed in Prod & validated.  Graying row. 4/24:  ungreyed row--fix was not installed in prod, prog pt (= workaround) was installed.  Per KR:   The fix was delivered on 4/18/08, and should be in testing.  Installed in WITS2 on 4/22 with RFC 2497641.   4/28:  Fix currently in testing.  IP to research if programming point will last until June.  5/1/08:  Testing in progress.  5/5:  Passed Testing. Next step is CAB.  Fix requires outage. Possible install date of June 7th. 5/8:  Dhea to submit for CAB on 5/19/08.  5/22 Approved for install 6/8, Per Epic, 3227370 & 3304296 have no relation. 5/29:  Ready for install 6/8/08. 6/11: Targeted for 7/16/08 per Yolanda. 7/28:  per Kelly, installed on June 8th. Graying row. ','Instructions for creation of a programming point have been received from Epic by NCAL.  Rosalba is working to test the programming point before installation into production.  Once installed into production, it will remove the affected area and the medication will not fall off of the MAR. ',NULL,'Instructions for creation of a programming point have been received from Epic by NCAL.  Rosalba is working to test the programming point before installation into production.  Once installed into production, it will remove the affected area and the medication will not fall off of the MAR. ',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 01:28:00','2008-10-29 10:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(186,3227370,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Composer-Based Preference List Import Might Incorrectly Match Order Panel Records with Order Template Records',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'inpatient','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4022','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0422-PS-PR3227370-E755826-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z.','May 08 Kpckg',NULL,'2008-07-16 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'10',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production.','Fix #1: Previously, the LPF,1000-Preference List Import import specification, used to import composer-based preference lists into Chronicles, occasionally resulted in an order panel record correlating with an incorrect order template record. When this happened, if you selected a procedure from the Order Lookup window, a different procedure appeared in order entry. The same situation could have happened with medications and certain order panels. Now, order panel records link to the correct order template record. \r\nFix #2: The standard import specification LPF,1000-Preference List Import is used to create and update records in the Preference List (LPF) master file. The following field has now been added to this import specification: 201001-Enable Soft Del. If this field is set to 1, you can import soft-deleted order panel (ORX) records, which prevents order panel records from linking to the incorrect order template (OTL) record. \r\nFix #3: Previously, when importing medication preference lists, an issue in the medications processing code could cause medication records with a value of 4-Occurrences in the Count Type field to fail during import under the following circumstances:                                                                             ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KR created adhoc request 4022.  Fix received 4/22, 0422-PS-PR3227370-E755826-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z.  4/26:  Fix will be installed in testing tonight.  4/28:  Currently in testing.  Fix was installed into WITS2 & WITS3 on 4/23.  5/1/08:  Fix in production. This issue is tied to PR 3304296.  5/5:  Passed Testing.  Green Row. 5/8:  This is a pre-req for row  (3304296).  5/15/08:  Will be going to CAB with (3304296) on 5/19/08.  5/21:  Per Epic, 3227370 & 3304296 have no relation. 5/22 Passed CAB but on hold until new fix passes testing. Requires outage or wait until July.  5/29:  Target install date aiming for July,16 08. 6/9: Andre to follow up tp see if in Prod. 6/19:  will be installed July 16th with May Kpkg. 7/28:  per Dhea The code was owned by Don Ly so I think he is the best position to do validation. Tom sent email to Don, requesting validation. \r\n','None--install the fix',NULL,'None--install the fix',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 01:45:00','2008-10-29 10:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(187,3352620,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Notewriter with HPI PEDS - Past medical history of difficulty breathing and wheezing may be displayed incorrectly',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, ED, Notewriter','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-23 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allen Rogers',NULL,NULL,'4029','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K051208',NULL,'2008-06-18 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','L','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051208\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4029):  \n  SP’07 E755984 4/30/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208\nRISK RANKING:  6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed into production on June 18th. Graying row. ','SP\"07 Notewriter with HPI PEDS - Past medical history of difficulty breathing and wheezing may be displayed incorrectly. The text generated for the past medical histories of pediatric patients with difficulty breathing and /or wheezing may not be correct.  Specifically, positive history will show as negative, and negative will show no past history for these afflictions.  Epic currently has a code fix in testing.\r\n\r\nThe problem occurs if all of the following conditions are in place:\r\n? SP\"07 is installed with code fix E753533 in 011408 KPackage\r\n? Notewriter with HPI PEDS is used\r\n? Text generation phrase HGN 49764 - ED HPI PED - DIFFICULTY BREATHING - ASSOCIATED MEDICAL HISTORY is used.  Also a problem for WHEEZING.  \r\nSuites Affected:    Notewriter (Inpatient, Ambulatory, ED)   For NCAL, only AMB Notewriter is active in production. \r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. Allen Rogers\r\nProblem Discovered by:   SCAL in Production\r\nEpic Representative / email address:  Brendan Krueger / BKrueger@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation:  Query has been written by Epic, is being run for SCAL.  Query will be run for the other affected regions within the next few days, to determine if remediation is needed.  \r\nAction items (immediate):   Epic is requesting adhoc authorization prior to providing fix.   Need to check with NCAL AMB to see if we are affected.  \r\nAction items (future):   Receive fix, test, install in production.  Remediation will occur if determined to be necessary by Epic query.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/23/08:  SCAL is impacted. NCAL, NW, HI, MAS are potentially impacted.  Exempla, OH, and MAS are not impacted. Notewriter (Inpatient, Ambulatory, ED)   For NCAL, only AMB Notewriter is active in production.  4/24:  per SF, There is no need for an ad hoc.  NCal Ambulatory does not have this risk as we use custom controls.  4/28:  Function not in use.  Yellow row. 4/30:  received fix file 0430-PS-PR3352620-E755984-SPr07May12NS.tar.Z.  5/1/08:  Fix will be moved into testing - WITS2 & WITS3 for ED testing.  5/5:  Andre to replicate for ED.  Fix will be installed in WITS & WITS 3. 5/8:  Andre will perform tesing. Fix is in WITS.  5/15/08:  AC tested and passed. submitted for 5/19/08 CAB. Target install date June 18th. 5/22 Passed CAB approved for June 18th install.  6/19:  Installed into production on June 8th. Graying row. ','A configuration change can be used as a workaround for Smartforms-only.',NULL,'A configuration change can be used as a workaround for Smartforms-only.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 01:56:00','2008-10-29 11:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(188,3356409,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'If shift times are set between 0001-0059, the ?Net Since Admission? row will not calculate correctly in the Intake/Output activity screen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-24 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-05-27 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Bliss',NULL,NULL,'4032','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0512-PS-PR3356409-E756038-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z','K072108',NULL,'2008-06-18 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'8',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','L','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K072108\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758756\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4032):  \n  SP’07 E756038 5/12/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756038\nRISK RANKING:  8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/19:  Installed in production on 6/18.  Graying row. ','SP?07 -- If shift times are set between 0001-0059, the ?Net Since Admission? row will not calculate correctly on the Intake/Output activity screen. Epic said the problem only occurs when the start shift time for the I&O activity falls between 0001-0059 and recommended changing the start shift time to 0000.  However, this could cause problems with the paper MAR.  \r\nThis appears to be a display problem only, not a problem with data storage.  Problem appears to have originated with SP?07.  Epic ran a query and the issue appears to only be a problem in NCAL due to configuration and usage. \r\nConcern:  Actions based on incorrect cumulative I&O totals could harm patient. \r\nRisk Assignment Made by:   Dr. David Bliss\r\nProblem Discovered by:   NCAL (South Sacramento Physician)\r\nEpic Representative / email address:  Tom Brown / tbrown@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation:  No remediation necessary after fix is installed\r\nAction items (immediate):  Adhoc authorized by Dr. David Bliss.  Action items (future):   Epic working on a fix-no ETA.  Fix believed to be server side and not client side.  No outage necessary.\r\nPART UPDATE:  5/8/08- - The I/O activity will calculate totals incorrectly under certain circumstances.  Epic (Chris Russell) has identified a few scenarios that may cause errors:\r\n1.     When shift times start between 12:00 am and 1:00 am (i.e. 12:01am)\r\n2.     When shift times do not start on a whole hour and duplicable I/O rows have data documented between the whole hour and the start time.\r\n3.     When surgeries are linked to an admission using a related encounters programming point (automatically linked when using LPP 5005 in the profile), and those surgeries use the same INP as the admission.  You may also be affected if you?re using the option to link all Episodes as Related Encounters, since this allows anyone to create a Related Encounter in the Episodes activity.NCAL is impacted due to criteria 1, 2, and 3.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/24/08:  NCAL is the only region affected.  IP & ED.  Workaround to be communicated.  Adhoc:  4032 / RFC:  CHG000002518491.  4/28:  Workaround (to use Quicklook) communication has been sent. 4/28: Delivery date: Monday, 5/12/08, DLG number: I758756, KPackage: 072108.  5/1/08:  Replication in progress. 5/5:  Unable to replicate.  5/8:  Replicated in production but not WITS.  Code scheduled to arrive May 12th. Code will be installed into WITS 2 & 3.  PART Updated info in col. L. 5/12:  received 0512-PS-PR3356409-E756038-Spr07Jul21NS.tar.Z.  5/15/08:  will be installed in testing friday 5/16.  5/19:  ETS unable to replicate. Andre to work with Surekha regarding type of testing. 5/22: Submitted for 5/27 CAB. 5/29:  Passed cab will be install 6/18. 6/11: Targeted for 6/18/08.  6/19:  Installed in production on 6/18.  Graying row. ','To use Quicklook instead of Intake/Output Activity Screen',NULL,'To use Quicklook instead of Intake/Output Activity Screen',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 02:09:00','2008-10-29 11:28:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(189,3352470,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Installation of the Medication Reconciliation Special Update May Affect the Functionality of some SmartLinks and Print Groups',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ED, OPT, Rx, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-17 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0407-AP-PR3248569-C7503537-E755634-Spr07May12NS.tar.Z; 0407-AP-PR3248569-C7503537-E755634-Spr07May12NS.zip','K051208',NULL,'2008-07-16 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Delivered as fix under 3248569, the same PR that caused the problem; affected smartlinks/printgroup should not be used during installation; might be best to install during downtime; Confirmed in K051208\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758592\nAD HOC DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 E755879 4/23/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051208\nRISK RANKING:  8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production.','Description:    After installation of Special Update Packages (E755634 and C7503491) which deliver the new Medication Reconciliation navigators and associated functionality, certain SmartLinks and Print Groups may be affected as described below:\r\nSmartLink 340-PTMEDDISCHARGE and print group 46165-IPO Patient Take-Home (Discharge) Medications (and copies):  These no longer pull in the discharge data taken from the Discharge Navigator, except for new discharge orders.\r\nSmartLink 788-MEDDISCHARGE (and copies): This SmartLink displays a message indicating the PTMEDDISCHARGE SmartLink should be used.\r\nPrint group 34221-IP Prior to Adm Meds (and copies): this print group displays nothing.\r\n In addition, previously released Special Update package E753841 contains SmartLink code that is affected by the installation of Special Update packages E755634 and C7503491. There were no standard SmartLink records released with Special Update E753841, but if update E753841 has been installed and SmartLinks built, such SmartLinks are also affected by this issue.  SmartLinks created for this Special Update E753841 also no longer pull in the discharge data taken from the Discharge Navigator, except for new discharge orders.  Release Note 134535-Creating Medication Charts and Self-Administration Sheets for Patients has information regarding the building of these SmartLinks.\r\nDiscovered by:   Epic, during internal testing Reported by:   Epic (Dustin Foster)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<RELATED to 3413564> SP\"07 - IP, ED, OPT, Rx, AMB.  NO CURRENT IMPACT.  Affected codes are not in production. 5/29:  NCAL will wait for Kpkg. 6/2:  This becomes an issue on July 16th without additional adhocs. 6/4:  per Dhea,  passed testing and is in regression testing. 6/5/08:  This fix will go to CAB & be installed along with fix for 3413564.  69: Per Alex Testing still in progress. 6/11: Targeted for 7/16/08.  6/19:  Passed regression testing & will be installed with May kpkg. 7/28:  Dhea will confirm code validation with Aditi.  7/30:  Per Dhea, Validated in production. Graying Row. ','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 02:21:00','2008-10-29 11:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(190,3413564,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Unverified, discontinued medications would still be available/active.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-04-15 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-06-23 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4091','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'2008-07-16 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'10',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production.','Patient Safety Full Description - Per Beatrice Kuhn and Bill Yee, \"Yes, this should be considered a patient safety issue, because medications would be available for administration, until the discontinued order was verified by the pharmacist!!\r\n a. These unverified, discontinued medications would still available in Pyxis\r\n b. When 24 hr supply is created, these unverified, discontinued medications would still be \"active\"\r\n c. These unverified, discontinued medications would still populate the paper MAR in Phase1 Site \r\n This is a common workflow in Phase2 - eg verify orders in verification queue, HOWEVER, this is a huge issue for the Phase1 sites - Fourteen Sites.   They NEVER go to the verification queue, with the only exception Hayward since they double check their order entry for QA issues.\"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<RELATED to 3352470> Rx - Will receive info from Dhea regarding Rx PS info. NO CURRENT IMPACT at this moment. Fix has been received. This fix will go to CAB & be installed along with fix for 3352470 .6/9: Per Alex Testing still in progress. 6/19:  Going to CAB on 6/23. 6/26:  Passed CAB. Will be installed on 7/16. 8/7:  Per Bill, validated. Graying row. ','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 02:32:00','2008-10-29 11:33:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(191,3109704,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Alternative meds selected from the Inpatient / AMB discharge navigator may have mismatched med name / Sig',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-01-24 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0129-AP-PR3109704-E754798-Spr07Mar03NS.tar.Z + fix from L. Nickels','K030308',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,'APR08','N','S','F','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I757130\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 3757):  \n  SP’07 E754799\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K030308\nRISK RANKING:  6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production.','Certain meds ordered from the Inpatient / Ambulatory (i.e., dual) discharge navigator will allow the clinician to choose an alternative med via a pop-up window.  In SP07, if the alternative med is selected, the navigator will order the original med with the Sig for the alternative med.  In NCAL there are approximately 69 meds for which an alternative pop-up window will appear, and these are routinely ordered.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Affects SP07--SCAL to adhoc.   1/28/08:  Per Epic (Liz Nickels)-The fix ETA for this issue will be Tuesday, January 29th.  DLG#: I757130, K-Package: K030308.  1/30/08:  Fix file received.  Per Surekha, REPLICATED. 2/4/08:  Testing in progress.  2/7/08:  Passed Testing.  Install date 3/14.  4/10:  Validation needed. 4/10:  Yolanda to follow up. ---5/1/08:  Added to April Tab for additional tracking.  Issue scope revised by NW.  Replication needed. From Epic (Liz Nichols):  The fix will work for any medications, procedures, or panels, and thus still works given the additional information to the below PART Incident. 5/5:  Passed Testing.  Graying row. ','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 02:49:00','2008-10-29 11:34:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(193,3775540,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Two lab result codes in the same HL7 message mapped to a single LRR record may produce interface error messages under specific circumstances ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Lab interface NCAL','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-19 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'2008-09-25 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','N','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Closing item.  Messages have been resubmitted. ','SU E755765 (5/12/08 K Pkg) was developed to address Epic Care Concern Q-610051 where lab result components may be overwritten when the same id and sub id are used in OBX with PULL_FWD configured.  When this SU is loaded, these messages may result in interface error 6142 (duplicate component in id received) as an alert that multiple lab result codes may be mapped to a single LRR record. These interface error messages function as designed. This issue is a KP mapping issue and not an EPIC code issue. These error messages should be addressed by regions requesting  additional LRR records from the National CMT team, and mapping single lab result components to a single LRR record.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"Regions may request sufficient LRR records so that all laboratory result codes can be mapped 1:1 to single LRR records.\r\nNCAL plans to complete the fix by 9/25/08. A PART bridge was not convened with Regions, since this was a known mapping issue in NCAL and only NCAL is experiencing this problem.  Any region that would like to convene to discuss this incident, may notify PART.  9/22:  Tom to follow up with Kelly.  9/26:  request for status sent to Marc Blaker. 9/30:  Marc stated he confused this issue with another, is not working on it.  Contacting Georgina Kurtovich from CMT.  10/1: per GK, check with Tina Nowling in AMB.  Per Tina:  last requested LRR records pushed out to NCAL prod 10/1, remapping to occur today.  10/2:  per TN, M Blaker is resubmitting the failed result messages to date (in progress). 10/7:  per M Blaker, messages have been resubmitted.  Can we close? 10/9/08:  Graying row. ','Epic (Greg Faber, Jason Ramaker) suggests that potentially impacted regions (SCAL, HI, NW, MAS, Exempla, CO, GA, and OH) check their interface error queue for error 6142 and manually override the message to post the result in the patient chart.  \r\nThe lab may also notify the provider by phone of the result.\r\nNCAL will not implement the workaround of overriding interface messages. Instead, the lab will notify the provider by phone of the results.  NCAL opts to install the fix, by 9/25/08.',NULL,'Epic (Greg Faber, Jason Ramaker) suggests that potentially impacted regions (SCAL, HI, NW, MAS, Exempla, CO, GA, and OH) check their interface error queue for error 6142 and manually override the message to post the result in the patient chart.  \r\nThe lab may also notify the provider by phone of the result.\r\nNCAL will not implement the workaround of overriding interface messages. Instead, the lab will notify the provider by phone of the results.  NCAL opts to install the fix, by 9/25/08.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-19 04:38:00','2008-10-28 11:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(194,3782352,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'IntraConnect -  Changes to patient chart data may be lost if made during Chart Merge ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Weisenthal',NULL,NULL,'','SP06, SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  5/18/09 (GH)\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510876\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757628\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 - fix in prod. Per Jeremy Greene, can close. No certification needed. ','SP\"06, SP\"07 - IntraConnect -  Changes to patient chart data may be lost if made during Chart Merge\r\n\"Description:   Changes made to a patient\"s record just before or during Chart Merge may be lost when transferred to the target instance although the information is retained at the source.  This issue affects only user-initiated clinical documentation; interface data filing is not impacted.\r\nFor example:\r\nA provider updates a patient chart after an office visit or during a patient hospital admission.\r\nAfter completing documentation, the provider closes the patient\"s chart, and Chart Merge activities occur immediately.\r\nThe changes are kept at the source instance but are not recorded in the target instance.\r\n\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL, SCAL. IP, AMB.  Epic (Robert Shimmin) will provide PART with a code fix status update by 9/29/08.  9/25:  Follow up with Margaret requesting info regarding merge details 10/1: per ML, \"If NCAL starts the merge in Nov the merge should not proceed if it finds contacts other than the registration contacts in patient chart.  The testing on this should be in progress or has been completed. The workaround that Epic recommended would not be needed when the above statement is true.  It will not hurt to implement the workaround, but additional testing will be required. I will defer the final decision to Evan.\"  10/6:  Per Evan, no clinical data will be merged anytime soon. Skeletal records (records with no clinical data) will be merged late Nov 08. Evan to check with Jan Sherman if a workaround will be necessary. 10/16: per Jan Sherman, skeletal merge delayed until Jan 19, no clinical merge planned.  Any accidental clinical merges before then will be corrected manually by Evan. Evan aware of PS issue, no workaround necessary.  10/20: Jan k-pckg won\"t go in until June 09.  What does that mean for clinical merge? Will followup. 10/21:  Fix will be in Nov Kpkg. DLG/package: I7510876/E757628.  Outage: If taken as an ad hoc, installation will require an outage of the chart synchronization queues, but not the environment.  From error log monitoring, the issue has not occurred in the time since the initial escalation. Yellowing - NCAL doesn\"t do clinical merge.\r\n','Change Ambulatory configuration setting to prevent merges occurring on same day as a patient\"s appointment.\r\n',NULL,'Change Ambulatory configuration setting to prevent merges occurring on same day as a patient\"s appointment.\r\n',NULL,'Epic will review a cache error log on a daily basis and will work with affected regions to remediate any records as needed.Currently, Chart Merge is prevented on inpatient records if the \"source\" is admitted.Discovered by:  Another Epic client.  Physician Representative:  Andy Wiesenthal. It was stated on the call that NCAL is planning to begin some chart merge activity possibly as early as mid-November, 2008 (this is unconfirmed.)   \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-22 03:01:00','2009-04-17 03:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(195,3776533,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Some lab results don\"t display in certain print groups prior to SP07 ORD conversion 133588',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, ED, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-23 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Scott Adelman',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'not needed','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','N','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  4/27/09 GH email on 5/7\nNOTES:  Confirmed in K111008; Epic conversion still running in production per GH on 5/07/09\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510584\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757539\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 - fix installed closing.  No longer affected since conversions have completed. ','Some laboratory or procedural (e.g. radiology interpretations, EKG) results (preliminary or final), prior to the SP07 upgrade, may not display in specified print groups under specific circumstances. Regions are affected if all of the below are true\r\nUpgraded to SP07\r\nSU I756713/E754605 is installed\r\nORD conversion 110704 was not complete before installing the SU above\r\nORD conversion 133588 has not yet completed\r\nIf the above conditions are met, the following print groups may fail to show results for orders that were resulted before the upgrade to SP07:\r\n45050 - IP RESULTS (RICH TEXT)\r\n75192 - ED NOTEWRITER RESULTS (RICH TEXT)\r\n75193 - ED NOTEWRITER EKG RESULTS (RICH TEXT)\r\n75181 - ED LAB RESULTS WITH PREVIOUS VALUES (RICH TEXT)\r\n75182 - ED IMAGING RESULTS (RICH TEXT)\r\n75183 - ED EKG RESULTS (RICH TEXT)\r\n75282 - ED IMAGING RESULTS W/RESULTER AND WET READS\r\nThis is a display problem, not a database storage issue. Regions will not be affected by this issue after the completion of ORD conversion 133588. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'A SP\"07 fix is currently in development.   Epic (Maria Spinozzi) will provide an ETA 9/26/08.  Regions will no longer be affected once conversion 133588 is complete; the historical results will display appropriately.  Regions are advised to install the fix even after the conversions have completed. 10/6: Waiting for conversion to complete. 10/8:  per M Galvan: I\"d say they should complete in approximately two more weeks. 10/16: per Maria Spinozzi, no risk of exposure since remaining conversions are running in \"Running After Code\" status. 10/20: Followup with Melanie about conversion completion. 10/26:  Per Maria, NCAL\"s decision to close this item, but there will be a fix and it will  be in the Nov Kpkg (DLG I7510584). 10/27:  No longer affected.  Waiting for Nov Kpkg. \r\n','Use Results Review when viewing results data, until the conversions complete in the impacted regions (NCAL - all instances, SCAL - one instance, and NW - one instance.  The conversion, once initiated takes several weeks to complete.)  For NCAL per API -  Stephanie Bonifacio, it may take several weeks to complete the conversion which is scheduled to begin week of 09/29/2008.',NULL,'Use Results Review when viewing results data, until the conversions complete in the impacted regions (NCAL - all instances, SCAL - one instance, and NW - one instance.  The conversion, once initiated takes several weeks to complete.)  For NCAL per API -  Stephanie Bonifacio, it may take several weeks to complete the conversion which is scheduled to begin week of 09/29/2008.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-23 03:19:00','2009-04-14 03:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(196,3794211,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Duplicable Flowsheet row or Group names for related encounters may display incorrectly if certain print groups are used ','','',NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, OPT','I7511269 / E758085','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-25 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Bejamin Broder','',NULL,'','SP\"06, SP\"07','','','','','','','K031609','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','A','M','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I766351/E761294, I7511269\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609-E758085\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/09: Consensus to close; not able to validate in prod.','SP\"06 & SP\"07 - - Duplicable Flowsheet row or Group names for related encounters may display incorrectly if certain print groups are used\r\n\"Description:  Displays names for duplicable flowsheet rows or groups for related encounters may be incorrect. if any of the following print groups are used:\r\nIP Intake & Output By Row - Native HTML (LPG 45751) \r\nIP I/O Detail ? Rich Text (LPG 45724)\r\nIP I/O Detail ? Native HTML (LPG 45725) *Not used in SP\"08\r\nThe display names for groups and rows in the current encounter (i.e., the encounter being accessed) are correctly shown.  Data is also displayed correctly in the Flowsheet Documentation activity, Intake & Output activity, and Accordion reports. \r\nFeatures:  Related encounters; use of any of these print groups:\r\nIP Intake & Output By Row (LPG 45751)\r\nIP I/O Detail ? Rich Text (LPG 45724)\r\nIP I/O Detail ? Native HTML (LPG 45725) \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: A. Thorup will find out who works with these print groups to confirm NCAL not affected.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (March-confirmed).\r\nWaiting for Kpkg.  No Current Impact (per Epic-NCAL not affected).\r\nNo Current Impact - IP, ED, and OpTime. NCAL, SCAL, and NW.  A SP\"07 fix is currently in development, and by 10/10/08 Epic (Maria Spinozzi) will provide an update for an ETA of the fix and identify the KPackage that will contain the fix .Adhoc authorized by Dr. Bliss. 9/26:  per M Spinozzi, NCAL not affected. It only affects copies of printgroups 45724 and 45725 if the 11th and 12th parameters are set. 10/20: Rebecca will followup on KPG delivery date w/Epic. 10/27: Waiting for KPKG.\r\n','Epic suggests (Maria Spinozzi) that impacted regions may view correct information in the Flowsheet Documentation activity, Intake & Output activity, or Accordion reports.\r\n','','Epic suggests (Maria Spinozzi) that impacted regions may view correct information in the Flowsheet Documentation activity, Intake & Output activity, or Accordion reports.\r\n',NULL,'Physician:  Dr. Ben Broder.  Epic Representative: Maria Spinozzi 608-271-9000. Discovered by:  Another Epic customer.    Epic Representative: Maria Spinozzi 608-271-9000.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-25 11:39:00','2009-09-08 02:47:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(197,3810456,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Results from cross-deployment orders may not appear in provider\"s InBasket ','','',NULL,NULL,'IntraConnect, IP, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-09-30 00:00:00','2009-01-26 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Wiesenthal','',NULL,'','sp07','','','','','','0317-AP-PR3810456-E758405-Spr07Mar16NS.tar.Z\r\n1104-CE-PR3810456-E757689-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z\r\n1209-AP-PR3810456-E759558-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,'SEP08','Y','S','F','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7510788\r\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4428):  \r\n  SP?07 E757689 11/04/08 E758405 3/17/09\r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP?07 K031609\r\nRISK RANKING:  4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/21/09: Closed per KR/M Lin 1/26/09 ','SP\"07 & Prior - Results from cross-deployment orders may not appear in provider\"s InBasket\r\n\"Description:  Results or result components of orders that are placed by a provider in a deployment other than his or her home deployment may not appear in the provider\"s InBasket.  Due to a race condition during synchronization of the message contacts, this problem may occur if all of the following conditions are met:\r\nXDM (cross deployment) messaging protocol is used\r\nThe provider places an order in a deployment other than his or her home deployment\r\nMultiple message updates are made in quick succession.\r\nResults appear correctly in Chart Review or Results Review; only InBasket display is affected.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'The fix scheduled for Feb 09 with a known issue. \r\nTesting is in pending status-waiting for reponse from Epic.  Queues have been bounced. Epic will notify if there are any trapped records, which would require queues to be bounced.\"IntraConnect, IP, AMB.  NCAL only affected. NCAL is currently impacted since it uses XDM Messaging; in addition, Epic (Emily Jenkins) identified affected records in NCAL deployments.Epic (Emily Jenkins) will run a daily search for impacted records and retrigger results messages to be sent to the provider\"s InBasket. Fix status 10/7/08. 10/2:  Adhoc Auth by Dr. Bliss.  Communication? Dr. Bliss asked M Lin to run RA ASAP. 10/3: per MLin: got the RFC approved for testing.  We will test the code (10/3) and get the approval for production run tomorrow night.  10/6:  Waiting for Dr. Bornstein to decide on retriggering. 10/13:  Retriggering was approved and checking on status of retriggering. 10/15:  Margaret H Lin working with Epic:  Incremental retiggering occurred 10/13 evening.  10/14 incremental search is still running as of 5:11PM 10/14.  10/15 they are going to adjust the Search time. Adhoc 4428 requested. 10/16: Re-triggering is during weeknights only; Currently ok; Tom will confirm w/Jansin if remediation is necessary (email sent).  Per JL: query results are in Dr. Connaly and Dr.  Merl\"s hands 10/20: Jansin identified related issue; Patient Identifiers are missing on some remote order records; Margaret Lin working with Epic; will followup with Jansin to get PS incident open. 10/20: Followup with Margaret Lin or Jansin Lee.  Epic recommends bouncing the queues to release failed recs. 10/21:  Margaret researching and will provide status. 10/27: Followup w/Margaret.  Fix ETA first week of November (DLG I7510788). This code will fix 2 bugs found.  Fix requires an outage. Queues were bounced last week.  Epic will notify if there are any trapped records, which would require queues to be bounced. 10/30: Rebecca will followup w/Epic and get status on a delivery date. 11/03: Required full outage; aiming to install on 12/10.  11/4: received 1104-CE-PR3810456-E757689-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z 11/06: Margaret Lin is holding off moving adhoc fix into WITS. 11/10: per ML:  I have identified the correct steps to reproduce the issue so we are ready for the code to be installed to WITS2.  Please expedite the install as well.  11/17:  Per Theresa, installed and passed testing.  \r\n11/20/08:  Per Theresa, Margaret stated: testing is pending for epic to respond on unexpected testing results and may not make 12/10 release.\r\n','\"Epic (Emily Jenkins) has provided two workaround options:\r\n**Retrigger affected results messages that were identified in scheduled queries done by Epic; this will ensure that results are sent to the provider\"s InBasket.\r\nAdvise providers to use Results Review or Chart Review, and not just the InBasket, to view results.\"\r\n','','\"Epic (Emily Jenkins) has provided two workaround options:\r\n**Retrigger affected results messages that were identified in scheduled queries done by Epic; this will ensure that results are sent to the provider\"s InBasket.\r\nAdvise providers to use Results Review or Chart Review, and not just the InBasket, to view results.\"\r\n',NULL,'\"Emily Jenkins will provide a code fix and inform PART of its developmental status by 10/7/08.  Physician Representative:  Andy Wiesenthal.  Epic Representative:  Emily Jenkins / emjenkin@epicsystems.com\r\n.  Discovered by:  Another Epic customer.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-30 11:17:00','2009-12-21 02:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(198,3809900,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Barcode scanning - Concentration of scanned package may not display on MAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   fix standard in SP08 IU4\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510627\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757608\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09 fix installed, closed with FYI to Bill Yee.  No plans to use functionality. ','If a scanned medication package matches an order with a different concentration, the MAR displays the concentration of the ordered package but not that of the scanned.  In addition, the dose field contains a dose derived from the scanned product, creating a potentially confusing mix of information that may require clinicians to manually calculate the proper administration amount.\r\nThis issue occurs if the item Match Across Concentrations (I ERX 24180) -- which allows barcode scanned medications to match across different concentrations -- is set to 1-Yes for the scanned medication. \r\nMatch Across Concentrations (I ERX 24180) was introduced in SP\"08 and made available in SP\"07 in SU E754891. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NO CURRENT IMPACT. No regions using affected functionality. NCAL does not use affected configuration. 10/26:  Status from Epic 10/29.  Waiting for Kpkg.  10/30: Per Bill Yee - No plans to use.\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.  Rebecca will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-02 02:15:00','2009-04-14 03:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(199,3809981,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Interaction Setting Editor may cause certain override settings to be lost','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-01 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','SP08','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Fix in IU4 so wont impact KP; closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I766220\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, SP08 only, does not affect SP07, fixed in SU09.  ',' Settings for override buttons and override requirements could be lost if an Interaction Setting record (FIS) is opened in Hyperspace in SP\"08 IU3 and forward. \r\nSpecifically, the Interaction Setting Editor clears the information in the Importance/Override Requirement table on the Importance/Override tab and the Override Reason buttons on the Suppress/Sort tab. If changes are made to the record, original override information in the  Importance/Override Requirementtable and Override Reason buttons will be lost.  As a result, medication interaction alerts will appear without an \"importance,\" which could lead to a provider missing an alert. \r\nThis issue does not occur if text side screens for editing interaction setting records are used instead.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Joy Mayfield) will provide code fix I766220 as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\nThe fix is standard in SP\"08 IU5 and SU\"09.','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-02 02:31:00','2009-07-22 01:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(200,3809886,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Generic MEDID Product Indicator may contain incorrect data ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-02 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','Epic 2002 ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Problem happened in Epic 2002, regions need to work with their Epic TS to run the utility once the Kpackage is installed \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510587\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757478\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/2: per Don Ly, the utility to fix was executed in production. Closed this issue 6/2/09.','In an issue that was introduced in Epic 2002 (and later fixed in Epic 2002 MU2), the line count in the Generic MEDID Product Indicator (ERX item 210) would be set to one even with multiple lines of data in the item.  As a result, the item would be incorrectly indexed and processed as generic equivalent or not generic.  The subsequent introduction of FDB into KP HealthConnect may have triggered corruption of data records, although recent Epic query results have shown that no region has any affected ERX records in Production.  Nevertheless, Epic will run a utility that will correct any corrupted records without the need for a code fix.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/16:  per Sylvia Fong: Don Ly is setting up the SR to run <the utility> in a test environment.   SR 3558062\r\n4/14/09 - code fix installed 2/21/09.  Verify with Joy Mayfield or Chris Russell from Epic if utility was run. Waiting for word from Epic that utility has been successfully run. 10/13:  No corrupted clinical data. 10/27: Chris from Epic will followup w/Joy.\r\n10/30:  After installing fix/kpkg, Epic will run a utility to clean up any data. Waiting for Kpkg. ','N/A',NULL,'N/A',NULL,'A utility to correct the corrupt data in all versions after Epic 2002 MU2 is currently under development. Epic (Joy Mayfield) will run this utility for all regions, and no code fix is required.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-02 02:59:00','2009-06-02 02:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(201,3809892,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Order Entry - Rate rounding factor from the override context is not respected ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-02 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   fix standard in SP08 IU4\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510615\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008- E757594\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7/14: CLOSED per BYee','The rate rounding factor specified in a context override record for a medication is not respected if all of the following conditions are met:\r\nContext-based overrides for medications are used in which the rate rounding factor is smaller than the factor specified in the base medication record;\r\nThe medications can be ordered in non-rate-based dose units;\r\nThe medications are configured so that rate is calculated based on volume and duration. \r\nNote: If changes are made (e.g., changing frequency) in verification that retrigger a rate calculation, then the context override rate rounding factor is respected. Otherwise, it is possible to verify orders that do not respect the rate rounding factor specified in a context override record.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/14/09:  fix installed.  waiting for national to make final ERX change after 6/20/09.  (GA 6/20, NW 5/05/09)Waiting for code fix in K-pckg. 10/6:  Bill Yee and Nat\"l to be notified. 10/8:  Per Sylvia, the current configuration will not meet the conditions for this to occur.  No current plans to populate the rate rounding factor in the override context records.  12/4: Testing to be done by AC in NATL environment. If pass testing, have to wait for all regions to install nov k pkg before implenting Erx changes.\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-02 03:58:00','2009-07-14 10:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(202,3812502,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Volume for ordered medication mixtures may be calculated incorrectly in Rx Order Verification under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-02 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','All',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510643 \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757465\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/27:  CLOSED, per Bill Yee ','The volume for ordered medication mixtures could be calculated incorrectly in Pharmacy Order Verification, possibly resulting in incorrect dispense doses.  This occurs if a component (base or additive) is ordered with a volume based unit (e.g. mg/ml) and contributes to the volume of the mixture.  If changes are made manually during Pharmacy verification to make the corrections for dispense dose, the activity recalculates the dispense amounts of the components and will dispense the proper amount.\r\nConditions for impact:  At least one component of the mixture must be ordered with a volume unit (i.e. mL, L); without this condition no calculation can occur for other ordered components. A component must be ordered with a volume based unit (mg/mL) and must contribute to the volume of the mixture. There are two places where contribution to volume can be determined: 1) in the component table in the Mixture medication record or as 2) a setting in the component record itself.\r\nSearches run by Epic (Michael Bries) determined the only current potential for impact at KP to be if a user was allowed to add a base component (that satisfied condition #2 during Order Entry to a mixture that, by default, would allow multiple base selections or was set up to always select a certain base component (satisfying condition 1).  Five mixture ERX records meet these criteria.\r\nNo orders were returned during search for NCAL, and orders returned in other regions did not satisfy condition #2. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"Epic working on a fix, no ETA or K-package at this time.  DLG I7510643. 10/3:  per B. Yee: Technically this could happen but unlikely (as evidenced by the Epic data search).  Even if it did occur the pharmacy would have difficulty preparing and dispensing such a product (i.e. IV with two different base solutions).  Assessment:  No ad hoc needed.  The SU should be installed when available.  10/6:  Epic has provided an explanatory flowchart and important settings detailing their tracked status (all important settings are controlled at a national level by the pharmacy team). 10/13:  Per Bill Yee, low risk-no workaround needed.  Waiting for Kpkg. 10/20: Waiting for Nov KPKG.Per Bill Yee, low risk-no workaround needed.  \r\n\"\r\n','Do not allow medication components to contribute to volume.  This can be accomplished in any of the following workarounds:\r\n1.  Hide the Add button, specify for some of those records - one of the components - always selected.\r\n2.  Change the ERX configuration',NULL,'Do not allow medication components to contribute to volume.  This can be accomplished in any of the following workarounds:\r\n1.  Hide the Add button, specify for some of those records - one of the components - always selected.\r\n2.  Change the ERX configuration',NULL,' It appears NCAL has been protected by workflow and configuration.  No regions have asked for an adhoc.   Regions need to decide if they wish to implement the workaround.    \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-03 02:15:00','2009-04-27 01:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(203,3873021,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3063623,'KPHC Patient Safety Issue-Signed and Held Prescriptions Appear Released',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','I7511053, which includes E758172 and C75031291','',NULL,'2008-10-21 15:04:15','2008-10-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4589','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'adhoc 4478 closed','0202-AP-TD33410-E758172-C75031291-Spr07Mar16.tar.Z\r\n0202-AP-TD33410-E758172-C75031291-Spr07Mar16.zip\r\nper Chris Russell email 3/9, these files fix the PR','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'8','M',NULL,'MedRec','N','N','N','N',' ','Y','S',NULL,'Clo',NULL,NULL,NULL,'M','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',60,'2008-12-22 11:42:22',NULL,'Infrastructure Software','PART KPHC','NOTES:  Fix standard in SP08 IU6; Per Epic, this is a build issue; there is only a problem if configured in a way Epic never intended. Programmatic fix will be to put checks in place to prevent improper build; ad hoc 4589 delivered on 2/02 fixes this incident; Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511053\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4589):  \n  SP’07 E758172 & C75031291 2/02/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609\nRISK RANKING:  8','KPHC Environment','Patient Safety issue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code installed on 4/8/09 and verified by Sherry Ellis / Fay Vafai - unable to test because build prevents issue from occurring.  Recommend closing','KPHC Patient Safety Issue- SLG 310720 - Signed and Held Prescriptions Appear Released\r\nInvolves signed and held discharge prescriptions.  This issue only impacts the new med rec functionality introduced in the Spr08 release and retrofitted to SP07.  No regions currently use this functionality although SCAL is considering testing it.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3/9:  Per Chris R, adhoc 4589 fixes this, delivered 2/2.  3/10 per Dhea, \"The fix files received on 2/2 have passed testing.  However, we did not test for PR3873021.  I am not sure if we will be able to test for PR3873021 though, since we have prevented it with our build.\"\r\nPer Epic, this might be a build issue. Adhoc requested by Dhea and authorized by Dr. Bliss-critical for MedRecon. NO CURRENT IMPACT - AMB & IP, SP\"07 & SP\"08.  No regions are currently impacted because they have not currently implemented Medication Reconciliation using the features described. Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a Kpackage 10/23:Followup with AMB \r\n10/27:  Waiting AMB\"s reply. 10/30: Adhoc 4478.  Need in prod before or by Jan 21; critical for MedRecon team. 11/06: Believed to be a build issue.Dhea will followup w/MedRecon team about build reqs. 11/10: Per Dhea MedRec will not occur until End of March 09; Can build where it will not be an impact. Dhea will followup w/ MedRecon team. 11/13: MedRecon date is in April; Dhea will still confirm with MedRecon team. 11/17:  Dhea to follow up. 11/20:  Adhoc is still wanted.\r\n\r\n','An affected discharge navigator will be configured as described in Features, above.  Remove the Sign & Hold button from the navigator configuration used by the IP Ord Rec Discharge Summary navigator section.\r\n',NULL,'An affected discharge navigator will be configured as described in Features, above.  Remove the Sign & Hold button from the navigator configuration used by the IP Ord Rec Discharge Summary navigator section.\r\n',NULL,'No regions are currently impacted because they have not currently implemented Medication Reconciliation using the features described. Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing. Physician Representative:  N/A (no current impact incident). Epic Representative:  Dustin Foster    608-271-9000.  \r\n',NULL,'1224705172ï££D111116ï££Resolution Action:  Upgraded Application\nResolution Description:  \nCause Code 1:  Business Partner\nCause Code 2:  \nCause Description:  ï£¢',NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 10:53:00','2009-04-29 10:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(204,3873013,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Free text Sig changes not saved in Med Rec Navigator ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rx, ED, OPT, IP, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07, SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Fix will be standard in SP08 IU6\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I7510597\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757563 & C75031136\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/12: Closed.  Cannot validate fix because Discrete Sigs not being used. Notified Thong Dang.','\"Description:    With the new Medications Reconciliation navigator, modifications to a medication\"s free text sig may not be saved.  This occurs if both of the following conditions are in place:\r\nThe sig is modified in the new Prior to Admission (PTA) Medications navigator section or in the new Home Medications navigator section\r\nDiscrete sigs are