unctionality, recommend closing. \r\nNO CURRENT IMPACT - AMB & IP - SP\"07.   No regions are currently impacted, as Epic searches revealed that no region is configured to use Quick Filters. Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a Kpackage\r\n','N/A',NULL,'N/A',NULL,'\"Features:   Chart Review, Quick Filters. Discovered by:   Another Epic customer. Epic. Representative:  Danielle Dyer    608-271-9000  \r\nPhysician Representative:  N/A (no current impact incident). \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 11:03:00','2009-04-28 02:09:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(206,3873030,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Net Since Admission Intake/Output information may be inaccurate if interval start time is greater than or equal to 1200','','',NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, OPT','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-22 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','SP07, SP08','','','','','','','N/A','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Also fixes other PRs; Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I766317 I7510663; \nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4443):  \n  SP’07 E758578 & C75031379 4/22/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809\nRISK RANKING:  8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/09: Consensus to close since NCAL does not have the affected confuguration; not able to validate in prod.','Description:    Net Since Admission Intake/Output information may be inaccurate if the interval start time for the first shift -- set at either the departmet or EMR Systems Definition level occurs during 1200 to 2359.  When displaying data by shift times, the totals are calculated starting from the first shift time.   \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: A. Thorup will certify after 8/19 install.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).\r\n3/27: fix in SP08, no SP07 fix planned.  No Current Impact\r\nNO CURRENT IMPACT - IP, ED, OPT - SP\"07 & SP\"08.  According to Epic searches, no regions have builds with the affected configuration and are thus not currently impacted.  Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a Kpackage\r\n','N/A','','N/A',NULL,'\"Features:   Intake/Output Activity. Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing.  Epic Representative:  Dustin Foster    608-271-9000. \r\nPhysician Representative:  N/A (no current impact incident).  \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 11:06:00','2009-09-08 01:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(207,3875390,1,'OPT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Updates to Surgical History may not display in another deployment if Autopopulate feature is enabled ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-23 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07, SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','Y','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909 as fix to 4053059\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510887\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757749\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code fix installed on 2/21/08 E757749, I7510887.  Verfied by Darryl Gill','\"Description:  Updates made to a patient\"s surgical history at one deployment (\"\"A\"\") may be hidden if the patient has an OpTime surgical log posted  from surgery in another deployment (\"\"B\"\") and  if the Autopopulate option is enabled.  \r\nWorkflow:\r\nProvider at deployment A updates a patient\"s surgical history.\r\nThe patient has OpTime surgery at deployment B and then the log is posted.\r\nIf deployment B has enabled the Autopopulate feature, the updates made at deployment A will not display either in deployment A or B when the log is posted.  Only the update made in deployment B will display.\r\nThis is a display issue only and does not affect stored data.\r\n\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OPT - SP\"07 & SP\"08.  NCAL is not affected since the Autopopulate option is not enabled (which is the workaround).   Epic (Adam Sauder) will provide a code fix in the Jan Kpkg.  Status update - 10/29/08. \r\n','Do not enable the Autopopulate option.\r\n',NULL,'Do not enable the Autopopulate option.\r\n',NULL,'\"It is unlikely that clinicians will rely solely on the Past surgical history field for patient status. Features:  Autopopulate option enabled \r\nRegions:  Currently, no regions are impacted since they have not enabled the Autopopulate option.  NCAL and SCAL are potentially impacted if they enable Autopopulate without installing the fix. Discovered by:  Another Epic Client. Physician Representative:  Mike Krall. Epic Representative:  Adam Sauder. \"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 11:10:00','2009-04-29 02:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(208,3803831,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Questions in a user copy of a PRL-converted order set can be lost',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'PRL','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-08-29 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0911-PS-PR3711522-C75031060-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z','K111008',NULL,'2008-09-25 00:00:00','P','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'AUG08','A','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   fix standard in SP08 IU4\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758891 \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K090808\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed in production and validated. ','If a provider makes a copy of a PRL-converted order set and changes the default answer to at least one question, then closes and opens the order set, only the changed question(s) will appear in the order set copy.  The unchanged questions will be lost. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' PRL team to test, install the fix before turning on PRL. 9/5:  This fix caused other issues for SCAL, but not for NCAL. Currently in testing. 9/8/08.  9/11:  Received file 0911-PS-PR3711522-C75031060-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z, 0911-PS-PR3711522-C75031060-E757220-Spr07Nov10NS.zip.  9/15: in testing. 9/18:  Fix will be installed along with PRL (9/25).  Passed testing. 9/25:  Installed in production and validated. 9/29/08:  Original PR (3711522) incorrect.  Correct PR is 3803831. \r\n','\"Suggested workarounds include:\r\n1.  turn off the ability to create user order sets\r\n2.  flag order sets with questions with \"***\" in the comment area.  These questions then will be saved. \"\r\n',NULL,'\"Suggested workarounds include:\r\n1.  turn off the ability to create user order sets\r\n2.  flag order sets with questions with \"***\" in the comment area.  These questions then will be saved. \"\r\n',NULL,'Epic has delivered a fix, C75031041, which requires an outage.  It is assumed this fix corrects the issue, as Epic cannot replicate the issue with this fix installed.   The fix was delivered to SCAL in response to 3 test defects:  TDs 30977, 31230, and 30791.   Dhea Maloney stated that PRL in NCAL may require a special outage before or around 9/25 to install this fix.   It is unlikely the fix can be tested and included in the manifest for the 9/17 scheduled outage.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 01:24:00','2008-10-28 01:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(209,3890835,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Return key while editing PRN hides orders in Med Activity',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inpatient','I7510946,  E757785','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Mike Krall',NULL,NULL,'','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'WITS3 Install:  12/9/08','1202-AP-PR3890835-E757785-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z','K011909',NULL,'2009-01-21 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'10',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510946\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4476):  \n  SP’07 E757785 12/02/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909\nRISK RANKING:  4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Prod install targeting 1/21/09.  INSTALLED ON 01/21--CLOSED per KR.','Using the Return key while editing PRN comments in Pharmacy Order Verification may cause other medication orders to be hidden in the Medication Activity.  \r\nExample:  In Order Entry, a provider adds text to the PRN comments field for a medication and submits the order.\r\nAt Pharmacy Order Verification, the pharmacist edits the PRN comments field (free text) and uses the Return key while adding or editing text in the PRN comments field.\r\nWhen the order is processed, some medication orders do not display in the Medication Activity.\r\nThis is a display issue only; complete order information displays correctly on the MAR, and medication alerts are triggered as needed.\r\nEpic query has found 4 affected records in the last 30 days in NCAL. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' Regions should create RAs to run the query twice a week (Monday, Thursday).  Bill Yee (National Rx) will communicate to pharmacists with a reminder not to edit PRN comments field in Order Verification.  10/30: Adhoc 4476. Epic (Thomas Sharkey) is point of contact for query. 11/03: Aiming for 12/10 install, . 11/06: Rebecca will followup w/Epic on delivery date of fix. 11/10: Verify with Pharmacy (Bill Yee) on adhoc and workaround. 11/17:  Bill Yee will assess adhoc. Per BY: date for adhoc = 12/1/08, requires downtime.  We would like to wait to decide whether to install the adhoc or wait for K-pckg. \r\n11/20: The fix for this incident will be available 11/30/08. Will require an outage. It impacts orders workflows, which I believe you generally treat as full outage. In addition, some dependencies require full outage as well.\r\n12/3:  File Received.\r\n12/8:  Fix to be installed in WITS on 12/9.\r\n12/11:  Installed in WITS3 on 12/9/08.\r\n12/22:  Prod install targeting 1/21/09.','Change the profile configuration (column #7) to disable the display of PRN comments in the Medication Activity. This was rejected by the regions, due to low number of problem occurrences.   The other suggestion was for users not to edit  PRN comments during Order Verification, which is standard workflow procedure.  ',NULL,'Change the profile configuration (column #7) to disable the display of PRN comments in the Medication Activity. This was rejected by the regions, due to low number of problem occurrences.   The other suggestion was for users not to edit  PRN comments during Order Verification, which is standard workflow procedure.  ',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 02:28:00','2009-01-19 02:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(210,3895741,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Beacon Order Details Not Updated',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. George Parridy',NULL,NULL,'','SP07, SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','N','S','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confimed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510979\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4477):  \n  SP’07 E757748 12/09/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909- E757748\nRISK RANKING:  4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code installed 2/21/09 as adhoc, verified by Sheryl Balicanta E757748, I7510979, RN 161571','Order detail components may not be updated by change propagation in treatment plans.  The affected order detail components include: administration instructions, PRN reasons and comment, and question answers.  Both med and procedure orders are affected. \r\nA change propagation window appears when you make changes to the order details of a treatment plans order if the same order exists on additional treatment days.  This allows the same order details changes to be made to other instances of the same order. If a user has made changes to a medication using new weight-based dosing, changes to any of these components (administration instructions, PRN reasons and comment, and question answers) will not be propagated.  If a user has made changes to a procedure or a medication not using new weight-based dosing the changes will only fail to propagate if changes are made to different multiple response items (such as administration comments and question answers)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Kirk Ryan from Beacon team will reassess the protocols that could cause this issue to occur.   10/30: Communication was sent by Dorinda Wong to 4 Facilities w/Beacon. Adhoc 4477. 11/03: Followup w/Kirk Ryan on impact to Beacon. 11/04:  per Kirk, issue is low pri for Beacon users, can wait for Jan 09 K-package. 11/10: Confirm fix in Jan KPKG; If so - Withdraw Adhoc.\r\n','None discussed.  Still evaluating impact in NCAL\r\n',NULL,'None discussed.  Still evaluating impact in NCAL\r\n',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-28 04:39:00','2009-04-24 04:22:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(211,3906245,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Leading zero for calculated rates less than one may not show on the MAR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-31 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. George Peredy',NULL,NULL,'4483','SP07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','1104-PS-PR3906245-E757457-C75031098-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z','K111008',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K111008\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I759649 (E757457/C75031098)\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4483):  \n  SP’07 E757457 11/4/2008\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111008-E757457 & C75031098\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/29/09: Per Bill Yee, ok to close.','When a medication rate is automatically calculated based on the medication?s volume and duration, and the rate is less than one, the medication?s rate does not display a leading zero in the MAR display item for infusion rate.  Note however when selecting the medication for administration, the rate field in the medication administration form does display the rate with a leading zero.  \r\n There is only one specific medication ordering workflow which causes the error.  In Spring 2007 (DLG 109848) Epic added the ability to automatically calculate the medication?s rate based on the volume and duration.  When the rate is calculated using this functionality, the rate is stored in the order record (ORD 9035) without a leading zero which then isn?t properly handled in the MAR.\r\n ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code installed on 2/21/09 - per testing this passed on 1/30/09 RN 157577 - verify with Inpatient and close \r\nNCAL must communicate the problem and recommended workaround to the Inpatient Rx and nursing users.  Dr. Bliss has authorized an adhoc request (4483). 11/03: NCAL will followup with when this will install. 11/4:  received 1104-PS-PR3906245-E757457-C75031098-Spr07Nov10NS.tar.Z. 11/06: Reviewing desirability of adhoc vs Nov 10 KPKG install; RNs to review. 11/10: Bart to review w/BettiAnn adhoc vs. KPKG install. 11/13: Per Dhea / Andrea - Confirmed in NOV KPKG; will not pursue adhoc.  Waiting for Nov Kpkg.\r\n','Users should be instructed to verify the rate from the administration form when administering a medication. Alternatively the MAR display item for Infusion Rate could be removed from the MAR display.  The display items available are determined by either the MAR Display Items or Extended Display Items settings specified in the EpicCare System Definitions or at the Medication (ERX) record level.',NULL,'Users should be instructed to verify the rate from the administration form when administering a medication. Alternatively the MAR display item for Infusion Rate could be removed from the MAR display.  The display items available are determined by either the MAR Display Items or Extended Display Items settings specified in the EpicCare System Definitions or at the Medication (ERX) record level.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-31 04:37:00','2009-04-29 09:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(212,3905352,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,' Incorrectly rounded dose is displayed on Rx labels','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-10-31 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Michael Krall','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','K031609','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'OCT08','Y','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511368, I767458\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609-E758215\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/09:  per Cheryl Tran, fix works.  CLOSING',' If a medication is set up with a context override where:\r\n 1.)  the medication unit rounding factor for the base medication and the override context are different,\r\n2.)  the med is rounding the calculated dose, and\r\n3.)  the pharmacy label print groups are configured with specific parameters to print medication ingredients,\r\n there is a possibility that an incorrectly rounded dose is displayed on the printed label.  Epic reports there are approximately 20 affected ERX records (some meds have more than one ERX record.) \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (March-confirmed).  Workaround in place (airtight).\r\nNational Rx is implementing the workaround suggested by Epic (see above.)  Epic is working on a permanent fix.  Aiming for inclusion in the January K-package. 11/3:  Per Bill Yee, workaround in place.  Issue is resolved because of workaround being airtight.  Waiting for Kpkg. \r\n11/30: 11/13- Per Dorinda I double checked this- Macy-Kirk-and I determined when this PART issue first came to light a few weeks ago - that it did not impact Beacon because there is no rounding for the Treatment Plan drug records.  I just checked with Kirk again to validate...the erx records in Beacon do not round...and display out to the 1000\"s place (0.000). \r\nPer Kirk Ryan This doesn\"t affect our Beacon build at all.   We are not able to round at the protocol or treatment plan level.  So, the only places that rounding can occur is if the physician or pharmacist purposefully changes the dose.   It mainly affects others with WBD (pedi, etc.)','National Rx (Sylvia Fong) is changing the configuration base ERX records in National PRODNAM, and implementing an emergency RFC for testing.  Once these changes have been pushed down to the regions in production, the error will not occur.  \r\n','','National Rx (Sylvia Fong) is changing the configuration base ERX records in National PRODNAM, and implementing an emergency RFC for testing.  Once these changes have been pushed down to the regions in production, the error will not occur.  \r\n',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-10-31 04:41:00','2009-09-08 10:40:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(213,3916340,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Modified Orders may not Show as Needing to be Acknowledged under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ED, IP, Radiant, Optime, Beacon,',' I7510700','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-04 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'N/A',NULL,NULL,'','SP06 thru SP08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NOV08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510700\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757720\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/28/09: Closed PR','Modified Orders may not Show as Needing to be Acknowledged under specific circumstances\r\nOrders modified more than once may not appear in the copy of print group, 46065 - IP Orders Need Acknowledging, as needing acknowledgement.\r\nThis may occur if the copy of print group 46065:\r\ncontains the \"o\" piece in the first parameter (so that new orders grouped by order type and then by order appear) and\r\nfunctionality is used to modify an order without discontinuing and placing a new order\r\nReleases:  SP\"06 with SU E744656 installed, SP\"07 with SU E754478 installed, and SP\"08\r\nFeatures:   Copy of print group, 46065 - IP Orders Need Acknowledging Configuration',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code fix E757720 installed on 4/8/09 - per EpicRX we do not use this functionality - recommed to close NO CURRENT IMPACT- Epic (Kristie Reimer) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status. 11/10:NCAL uses print group but not the \"o piece\" functionality. Affects Inpatient,  ED, Optime, Beacon and Radiant. \r\n12/02:  Fix will be in Jan Kpkg / DLG:  I7510700. \r\nNo Current Impact.  NCAL uses print group but not the \"o piece\" functionality.  Waiting for Jan Kpkg.\r\n02/05/09 - Epic RX we do not acknowledge orders or use print groups:  46065 - IP ORDERS NEED ACKNOWLEDGEMENT','Reconfigure the print group to not use the \"o\" piece in the first parameter. ',NULL,'Reconfigure the print group to not use the \"o\" piece in the first parameter. ',NULL,'Discovered by:   Another Epic Client\r\nEpic Representative:  Kristie Reimer   608-271-9000 \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-04 03:28:00','2009-04-28 02:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(214,3936952,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'KP ONLINE posting inaccurate patient data thru wrong patient charts',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-11 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NOV08','A','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No Epic Code\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/29:  CLOSING this issue, with FYI to Joe DiMilia.  ','KP Online Issue - Patient information may be charted on incorrect patient (14 affected in NCAL, 34 throughout regions). Issue has already been resolved, but remediation has to be completed.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/13: Andre to check with Evan to see if this issue can be closed.  3/27:  If all possible remediation completed, can we close? Andre to f/u w/ Evan Felter:  has all remediation has  been completed?  Andre Mure, Michael Cobarrubia, and Jennifer Angel working together regarding remediation.  PART to distribute a spreadsheet with affected MRNs.  Issue has been resolved and only remediation is needed. 11/13:Nat\"l AMB AC and PART (Byron Harper) will meet for next steps for remediation.  11/14:  Bridge reconvened.  Epic provided options to perform remediation, but were not approved by Jansin. Bridge to reconvene Monday (11/17).\r\n12/8:  Andre to f/u to confirm, All remediation has  been complete.  \r\n12/9:  Joe DiMilia is working to remediate the last two charts. 4 of 6 remediated successfully. Current status from Byron & Joe listed in \"comment\" section.','Issue has been resolved.\r\n',NULL,'Issue has been resolved.\r\n',NULL,'Per Byron-This is the status as I understand it for NCAL.\r\nThere were originally 14 potential charts with misfiled information.  6 were confirmed.  The NCAL Bridges team was able to remediate 4 of those 6 charts.  The remaining 2 could not be immediately remediated because the remediation strategy required an editing of the original HL7 messages that came through the Interface Broker.  Messages are only retained for 30 days and those 2 messages went through the broker more than 30 days before the remediation.\r\nTo remediate the last 2 charts, NCAL would need copies of the messages sent by HMI, so that they could be reconstructed.  Those messages from HMI were not readily available in a format that our Bridges teams could use.\r\nJoe Dimiliar from the KP Online ISG group was working with HMI to obtain copies of those messages.  As of the beginning of last week, I don\"t believe they were available.  Joe would need to confirm the status of that effort.  Pending his response you may be able to 1) close the issue because remediation is complete, 2) close the issue because no further remediation is possible, 3) leave it open pending delivery of the messages from HMI and completion of the work by the Bridges team.  If HMI can deliver the messages the Bridges team should be able to complete the work rather quickly.Joe-  can you confirm where this currently stands?\r\nPER Joe DiMilia,Byron, this is an excellent summary.\r\nThe only clarification I would add is:\r\nNCAL was able to remediate 4 of the 6 charts because the messages were less than 30 days old.  This allowed them to access the original HL7 messages directly from their Regional Interface Broker.\r\nNeither the Regional Interface Broker or the National Intergration Borker (which sends receives the messages from HMI and sends them to each region) stores these messages beyond 30 days.\r\nHMI did retreive and resend the original messages for NCAL for both messages oder than 30 days, but they are in XML format.  (This is the standard format for sending PHI through a secure VPN connection over the internet.)\r\nNCAL cannot use the older messages in XML format unless we can resend them through the Integration Broker to get them translated to HL7.\r\nHere is my status report:\r\nI am actively pursuing several ideas to close this issue for these 2 messages:\r\nRun both messages through our test environment so the Integration Broker can translate them to HL7\r\nResend both message through production.\r\n#1 would require exposing PHI in testing, so we would need compliance approval and will take more time to implement (simply to set up the testing accounts to mirror the appropriate production users attributes).\r\n#2 runs the risk of creating a duplicate encounter, so we need to research and act carefully to ensure that the messages would error out, if we pursue this route.\r\nI will be working with testing environment and HMI technical contacts to explore both options.\r\nI expect to have a recommendation by end of week.  In the meantime, I welcome any other simpler (less risky) options.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-11 10:06:00','2009-05-29 11:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(215,3940553,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SP07 - Medication Reconciliation - PTA medications may not appear in Medication Activity if Sig contains line breaks',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, ED, Beacon, Rx','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-13 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Peter Dwork',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SCAL to adhoc','1205-PS-PR3940553-C75031213-E757868-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  E confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511095\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4510):  \n  SP’07 C75031213 12/05/085\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011908\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'code ifx was installed on 2/21/09 and validated successfully by Trudy David Inpatient  ','Orders may be cancelled in the new order reconciliation discharge navigator when they are intended to be signed or signed & held. If a user signs and holds an order, then edits it, and then signs and releases the order, it may be cancelled.  NCAL is currently planning to implement Medication Reconciliation in April, 2009. Sample workflow:\r\nIn the new orders reconciliation discharge navigator, sign & hold one or more (medications or procedures) discharge orders.  \r\nReturn to the discharge navigator and click the Edit link next to one of the orders signed and held in Step 1.\r\nSelect the modify button and make changes to the order.\r\nAccept the changes with a sign action.  If the order was newly entered in Step 1, it will be cancelled and will no longer appear in the discharge navigator.  (For these orders, an action of \"sign and held\" will also cause the order to be cancelled with the same effect.)  If the order was a modified or prescribed Prior to Admit (PTA) medication, or an IP medication reordered as a prescription, then the original order will appear in the discharge navigator with a status of cancelled.  (For these orders, an action of sign and hold will cause the orders to be correctly signed and held).\r\nNote:  in the new orders reconciliation discharge navigator a sign and held action is caused by selecting the \"Sign My Orders\" button in the Release Discharge Orders section.  The other button in that section \"Sign and Release All Orders\" corresponds to the sign action.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SP07.  Medication Reconciliation.  SCAL to adhoc.  Regions are not impacted until Medication Reconciliation is activated (currently scheduled for 