at section \"Sign and Release All Orders\" corresponds to the sign action.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fix bundled with other MedRec PS issue.  Per Epic, second DLG is I7511188SP07. SCAL to adhoc (did they?).  11/17:  Fix will be delivered before any regions are live on New Medication Reconciliation (11/24).  11/30:  Adhoc received and NCAL will be pursuing.  Adhoc has to be reviewed. \r\n12/3:  Per Epic (Maria Spinozzi) - There is an additional DLG required to fully fix all scenarios that could cause this patient safety issue.The DLG is I7510974. It is not yet released and Epic will keep us informed as to its status, which I will pass along to the potentially impacted regions.\r\n12/8:  Targeting Feb Install.\r\n12/9:  The second DLG that will be sent for this PSE will be I7511188.\r\nNote this is a change from the DLG listed below of I7510974. I7510974 will no longer be necessary for this PSE.*The previous ad hoc of I7511038 should not be installed in a production environment without I7511188.*\r\n3/9/09: passed testing, going in on 4/8/09.','None required as fix will be delivered before any regions are live on New Medication Reconciliation.',NULL,'None required as fix will be delivered before any regions are live on New Medication Reconciliation.',NULL,'Testing Env install targeting 12/17 ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-13 03:53:00','2009-04-29 10:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(218,3931906,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Medication orders may be unintentionally completed when Consult Notes are accepted','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-10 00:00:00','2009-09-09 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  In K031609 but to other PRs \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511049, I766851\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609-E758122 & C75031278\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/09/09: Per A. Vakil\'s 9/9/09 email fixes implemented successfully.','\"When writing a Consult Note, a user may select a consult order to associate with the note.  This list of orders can be filtered based on profile setting ?Consult Note order types? (I LPR 35171) or the system definition ORD_CONSULT mnemonic code.  If this profile setting or system definition mnemonic is not defined, the following may occur:\r\nall orders -- including medication orders -- will be available for association\r\na medication order that is associated with a Consult Note could be unintentionally completed when the note is accepted\r\nthe medication orders will display as complete on and eventually disappear from the MAR.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: Confirm with S. Ellis, A. Vakil, cc B. Mattern if ok to close.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (March-confirmed). No Current Impact.  Affects NW (only).\r\nNW only, NCAL not affected. SP\"07 - Inpatient - NW only.  11/20 --NW has installed airtight workaround. 11/30:  Waiting for Kpkg.','\"Change the system profile to ensure that order types that can include a consult are set to consult only, as per the following workarounds:\r\nTo correct the setting in the profile record, navigate to d ^L > Management Options > Profiles > Note, Letter, Transcription > Inpatient Consult and Procedure Notes screen > Consult note order types (I LPR 35171), and enter the appropriate types.\r\nEnter an invalid category value into the system definition mnemonic (eg. ?33333?).  This setting can be found via d ^L > Management Options > Edit System Definitions > Server, Interface, MF, etc. > Install Mnemonics screen > ORD_CONSULT mnemonic and code.  Check I ORD 30 to ensure that you select an invalid value.  (Note:  the LPR setting will override this setting.)\r\nEpic (Greg Hartman) will work with NW AC\"s to complete a workaround, which is airtight, by 11/10/08.\"\r\n','','\"Change the system profile to ensure that order types that can include a consult are set to consult only, as per the following workarounds:\r\nTo correct the setting in the profile record, navigate to d ^L > Management Options > Profiles > Note, Letter, Transcription > Inpatient Consult and Procedure Notes screen > Consult note order types (I LPR 35171), and enter the appropriate types.\r\nEnter an invalid category value into the system definition mnemonic (eg. ?33333?).  This setting can be found via d ^L > Management Options > Edit System Definitions > Server, Interface, MF, etc. > Install Mnemonics screen > ORD_CONSULT mnemonic and code.  Check I ORD 30 to ensure that you select an invalid value.  (Note:  the LPR setting will override this setting.)\r\nEpic (Greg Hartman) will work with NW AC\"s to complete a workaround, which is airtight, by 11/10/08.\"\r\n',NULL,'Epic (Greg Hartman) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its development by 11/18/08.  Regions are advised to implement the fix in a KPackage when available.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-17 01:43:00','2009-09-09 11:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(219,3959537,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Drug-Drug interaction alerts missing Importance during interaction checking ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-19 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','K011909','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Fixed inSP08  IU4 so wont impact KP; closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  DLG I766201  E761071\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, SP08 only, does not affect SP07, fixed in SU09.  ','\"Description:   Due to new interaction checking features which will be introduced in SP\"08, importance or override requirements for drug-drug type alerts in an interaction setting record may not be respected.  \r\nSpecifically, the following occurs during interaction checking in SP\"08:\r\nDrug-drug alerts are classified as a type of N/A instead of the importance specified in the interaction setting record (I FIS 1710), and \r\nNo override requirement (I FIS 1720) is enforced even if one was specified in the interaction setting record.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No Current Impact. SP08.  Rx, IP, AMB, Beacon, ED.  Epic (Michael Breis) will provide a code fix as part of the 011909 KPackage.  Details: DLG I766201; E761071; Outage needed. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'Discovered by:   Another Epic customer. Epic Representative:  Michael Breis    608-271-9000. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-20 08:07:00','2009-07-22 01:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(220,3953553,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Reordered medications may not display in some Medication Reconciliation print groups',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rx, ED, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-20 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4522','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0107-AP-PR3953553-E757965-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z','K011909',NULL,'2009-04-08 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confimed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511102\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4522):  \n  SP’07 E757965 1/07/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757965\nRISK RANKING:  8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/27: validated in prod; ok to close per Dhea.','Reordered medications may not display in either of the following print groups or copies used in Medication Reconciliation (a new feature in SP\"07):\r\nED Meds: Current Meds (LPG 75265)\r\nIP ORD Rec Admission Closed View (LPG 34200) ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Passed testing. Install date-4/8 as a part of K011909\r\nEpic (Maria Spinozzi) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage.  11/30:  Dhea to let us know if an adhoc is needed.  12/1 Adhoc 4522 created\r\n2/26:  Per Dhea-Passed testing. Install date-4/8 as a part of K011909.','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-20 12:39:00','2009-04-27 08:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(221,3959553,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Beacon Treatment Plans - Dosing calculations may not be updated for weight-based dosed medication orders, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-20 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'BCON','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510989\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011908-E757756\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/12: closed based on K. Reimers email noted in Next Step History below.','Dosing calculations for Beacon treatment plan weight-based dosing medications may not be updated if both of the following conditions are true:\r\nThe weight type for a weight-based dose unit is changed, and\r\nEnhanced weight-based dosing is not enabled (that is, I LSD 7620 not set to 1).  \r\nWorkflow:\r\nSelect an order-level weight-based dose unit for a weight-based dosed medication order in a treatment plan with a fixed dosing weight.\r\nSign the treatment plan medication.\r\nChange the order-level weight-based dose unit to a different weight-based dose unit based on a different weight type.  As a result, the previously signed treatment plan medication orders are no longer signed. \r\nClose the treatment plan. \r\nRe-enter the treatment plan. The medication order shows the changed dose unit, but the original dose calculation from the dose unit remains the same.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Per K. REimers email 5/12: NCAL and SCAL  were not affected by this issue because they have \"I LSD 7620 set to 1\".   In other words, they are using the new Weight Based Dosing and this issue only affects customers who are not.\r\nCode ifx E757756 was installed in NCAL PROD on 4/8/09 - verify that we have NOT enabled Weight Based dosing and if not recommend closing \r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide code fix DLG I7510989 in the 011909 KPKG.   SCAL and NCAL are not impacted since they have enabled weight based dosing with Beacon, but could be potentially impacted if they disable it.','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-20 03:24:00','2009-05-12 04:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(222,3968971,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Patient Histories may be Inaccurate.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, IntraConnect ','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-21 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,'4564','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KR requested','0109-AP-PR3968971-E758039-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,'NOV08','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511145\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4564):  \n  SP’07 E758039 1/09/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757888\nRISK RANKING:  4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'code fix was installed on 2/21/09 and validated successfully by Margaret H Lin Care Everywhere','If a patient has medical, social or surgical (doesn\"t include birth) histories done on two different instances on the same day, their sequence may not be preserved at a third (4th, 5th, etc.) instance.  When this occurs, if a user copies the most recent history to begin documentation with, what actually may appear is the next-to most recent history.  Any changes made by the user, when the history is synchronized, may not be reflected in the history. \r\nEpic has determined there are 53 affected patients in NCAL over a 4-year period.  An NCAL clinician working with an Epic TS must remediate these 53 patient charts.    ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Kelly requested adhoc 4564. Epic is working on a fix.   Epic (Robert Shimmin) will provide an update about the code fix for SP\"07 and the KPackage availability by 12/5/08.  Fix in Jan k-pckg, reqs outage.\r\n12/15:  Per Andrea, Dr. Hoberman reviewing 37 affect pt. charts.\r\n2/23/09:  code fix was installed on 2/21/09 and validated successfully by Margaret H Lin Care Everywhere\r\n2/27:  No cleanup needed (per Margaret).','Epic (Robert Shimmin) has run reports for impacted regions (NCAL and SCAL) to identify impacted patients. EPIC TS\"s will work with clinical AC\"s to review chart histories and manually resequence any histories necessary to remediate those records. \r\nUrgent Mitigation: Epic (Robert Shimmin) will run on-going reports used for remediation as a standard maintenance routine for NCAL and SCAL until a fix is available and implemented. Any additional remediation will be completed in conjunction with the regional clinical AC.',NULL,'Epic (Robert Shimmin) has run reports for impacted regions (NCAL and SCAL) to identify impacted patients. EPIC TS\"s will work with clinical AC\"s to review chart histories and manually resequence any histories necessary to remediate those records. \r\nUrgent Mitigation: Epic (Robert Shimmin) will run on-going reports used for remediation as a standard maintenance routine for NCAL and SCAL until a fix is available and implemented. Any additional remediation will be completed in conjunction with the regional clinical AC.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-21 01:49:00','2009-02-27 02:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(223,3966987,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Duplicate Workspace May cause Duplicate or Corrupt Orders under specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, Rx','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-21 00:00:00','2009-12-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'N/A','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'G',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NOV08','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Two workarounds available; confirmed in K070609\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7512039\r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP07 K070609-C75031438\r\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/15/09: Per L. Labeaud, Andre evaluating Remedy tickets for any additional issues, trends or patterns from end users affected.  Should have final update by next Pt Safety meeting.','When two workspaces for the same patient are opened in the same patient encounter, orders that are signed (procedure or medication orders) within the workspaces may result in submission of multiple duplicate or corrupted orders.  A submitted signed order will appear as if one order is placed multiple times with different order details.\r\n A physician may sign off on procedure or medication orders and not know that multiple orders are being submitted and that the orders may be duplicated or corrupted. \r\n\r\nTo be affected, the following conditions all need to apply:\r\n1.	UCW (Unified Clinical Workspace) is not turned on\r\n2.	ED and IP application modules must be licensed and in use\r\n3.	Users who access the patient while the patient is still in the ED and are allowed to place orders must have access to activities that are not allowed in the IP_ED workspace kind\r\n\r\nSample workflow:\r\n1. Open an encounter for a patient in the ED\r\n2. Write orders in the first workspace\r\n3. Open an activity that is not allowed in the IP_ED workspace kind (e.g. Inpt Rounding Navigator, IP Admission Navigator,\r\n    IP Discharge Navigator, etc.).  A second workspace is automatically opened when one of the navigators is accessed.\r\n4. Write orders in the second workspace\r\n5. Sign and submit orders on the patient\r\n\r\nSample scenario:\r\nIf a user enters a patient?s chart while the patient is admitted to the ED and selects an activity that is not allowed to run in the ?IP_ED? workspace kind, a second workspace will open in the same encounter.  If orders are entered in one workspace, they will inadvertently exist in both workspaces at the same time.  When the user signs the orders in one of the workspaces, the orders from the other workspace are signed as well, even though the additional orders are not seen in the signing workspace.  If the user then goes to the other workspace and signs those orders, which are still displayed in hyperspace and which may also contain completely different orders, a second set of duplicate but corrupt order records may be created.  Example: Multiple medication orders may display with a different medication display name than what was originally ordered (e.g. Furosemide, but with Sigs for other ordered medications (Furosemide 2.5 mg Oral, Daily, and Furosemide 20 units Subcutaneous at Bedtime [instead of Insulin], and Furosemide 25 mg Oral, BID, [instead of Metropolol], etc.)  \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'12/13/09: Per 12/8 PS meeting, Andre to see if w/a needs to be reversed/undone.\r\n12/02/09: Per A. Mure ok to close.\r\n11/11/09: A. Mure to certify.\r\n08/04/09: 6/2:  Waiting for Kpkg (July-confirmed).\r\n4/13: Per Andre w/a in place waiting for KPKG.\r\n4/6: W/A is in place per Andre but will verify IP_ED allowed work space.\r\n3/23: Andre Mure to see if workaround in place.  When is K-pckg? \r\nAndre has asked Aditi to implement workaround.  Aditi would like more info (1/19) K Reimer has provided (1/20)Andre and Ryan Lambert reviewing  work spaces to see if we are affected.;so far none are affected.Workaround? Currently no affected occurences.  Andre to f/u regarding workaround.11/21/08:  Discussion regarding implementing an approved workaround.  Epic will provide a query to check if there are any affected occurrences within the past 6 months. Epic (Kristie Reimer) will provide an update about the code fix for SP\"07 and the KPackage availability by 12/5/08.\r\n12/15:  Andre to f/u regarding workaround.','1.  Turn on UCW (Unified Clinical Workspace) or\r\n2.  IP_ED can be added as an allowed workspace kind for any activity a user would have access to for an ED patient that is also allowed in the IP_ADMISSION workspace.\r\n\r\nOption #1 is not a viable workaround for KP.  Regions may implement Workaround #2 with regional Epic TS assistance.  Epic (Kristie Reimer) provided a list of each Regions\" Activities that are not currently allowed in the IP_ED workspace kind .  Regions may include these Activites as allowedActivities in the IP_ED  workspace kind (E2N masterfile) .','','1.  Turn on UCW (Unified Clinical Workspace) or\r\n2.  IP_ED can be added as an allowed workspace kind for any activity a user would have access to for an ED patient that is also allowed in the IP_ADMISSION workspace.\r\n\r\nOption #1 is not a viable workaround for KP.  Regions may implement Workaround #2 with regional Epic TS assistance.  Epic (Kristie Reimer) provided a list of each Regions\" Activities that are not currently allowed in the IP_ED workspace kind .  Regions may include these Activites as allowedActivities in the IP_ED  workspace kind (E2N masterfile) .',NULL,'Problem Discovered by:   Another Epic Client\r\nEpic Representative / email address:  Kristie Reimer / KReimer@epicsystems.com\r\nRemediation:  None.  Currently, there are no affected orders/occurrences. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-21 02:06:00','2009-12-15 06:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(224,3970219,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3181291,'SP07 (Beacon):  Chemo meds may be edited into unintended cycles if treatment days are closed out before treatment cycles.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DLG = I7510995.','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-21 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Howard Landa',NULL,NULL,'4532','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Auth by kelly r','1211-PS-PR3970219-C75031206-E757877-Spr07Jan19NS.zip\r\n1211-PS-PR3970219-C75031206-E757877-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z','',NULL,'2009-02-21 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'BCON','N','S','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510995\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4532):  \n  SP’07 C75031206 12/11/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011908-C75031206\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'code fix was installed on 2/21/09 and validated successfully by Mark Okimoto Ambulatory','In chemotherapy, medication is administered as part of treatment cycles, and days within cycles, with treatment day close-out performed separately from cycle close-out.  In the workflow where a treatment day is closed out but not the treatment cycle, medication can go into the wrong cycle if edited into future orders.      \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic is working on a fix.  No ETA at this time. Kirk Ryan will perform the communication (see Workarounds). \r\n12/10:  4532.\r\n2/23/09:  code fix was installed on 2/21/09 and validated successfully by Mark Okimoto Ambulatory','Communicate to physicians and pharmacists:  be sure to complete treatment cycles before the next treatment day. ',NULL,'Communicate to physicians and pharmacists:  be sure to complete treatment cycles before the next treatment day. ',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-21 04:00:00','2009-02-26 06:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(225,3959542,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Filtering by Severity may cause some drug-allergy alerts not to fire','','',NULL,NULL,'IP, Rx, BEA, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-21 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','N/A','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'P',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SU09','Y','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  standard in late version of SP08 & SU09\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/18/09: Waiting for SU09. No Current Impact.  KP does not filter by severity.  KP should contact Epic if at any time in the future it decides to initiate filtering on severity.','When filtering is set using interaction setting (FIS), drug allergy records with the same name but of a different type and with inconsistent severity may cause Drug-Allergy alerts not to fire. This may occur in three separate scenarios that involve filtering by Severity, as follows:\r\nMissing drug-allergy alerts if filtering or setting importance by severity:  Allergy records of a different type with the same name could have an inconsistent severity; this may cause missing alerts if filtering via interaction setting records (FIS) has been enabled.\r\nIncorrect allergen record severity:  An issue (introduced in Spring 2008 IU4 and forward) with the drug-allergy loading code may cause an incorrect severity/signficance between a paired allergen and drug.  \r\nInadvertently filtering drug-allergy alerts for FDB via the Model System build:  This issue relates only to environments where Medi-Span information was converted into FDB.  Since only FDB has been used at Kaiser, there is no impact.\r\nFeatures:   Drug-allergy alerts; interactions filtered by Severity\r\nCurrently, KP does not filter by severity. \r\nDiscovered by:   Epic, during internal testing\r\nEpic Representative:  Michael Bries   608-271-9000  ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'No Current Impact.  KP does not filter by severity.  KP should contact Epic if at any time in the future it decides to initiate filtering on severity.\r\n12/8:  Waiting for SU09.','Epic recommends that organizations do not filter allergen alerts on severity. All regions have completed this workaround.','','Epic recommends that organizations do not filter allergen alerts on severity. All regions have completed this workaround.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-24 10:19:00','2009-09-28 03:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(226,3969580,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Discontinued meds will not display on PTA Medication Reconciliation reports for certain print groups ','','',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','I7512009/ E758670','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-25 00:00:00','2009-11-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Peter Dwork','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','Y','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confimed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512009\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’06 K070609- E758670\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/17/09: Per Y. Lassiter, certified; closing this issue.','Discontinued PTA medications will not display as Discontinued and PTA medications flagged for removal are missing any indications that they are being removed ( no flags) on certain PTA medication reconciliation reports if all of the following conditions are met:\r\nThe user?s profile is configured  to ?Drop discontinued medications immediately? (LPR item 862), and\r\nEither print group is used:\r\nLPG 49244 - RX MED RECONCILIATION PTA ADMISSION MEDS (RICH TEXT)  \r\nLPG 49245- RX MED RECONCILIATION PTA DISCHARGE MEDS (RICH TEXT)\r\nAs a result, a provider could incorrectly reorder or continue an inactive medication or order other therapies based on inaccurate information.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/11/09: Email to Y. Lassiter on 11/11 requesting certification.\r\n10/27/09: Waiting for Kpkg.  per Vikram, in July K-pckg\r\nWaiting for Kpkg - Not affected due to affected profile was a test profile, which has been deleted.\r\nEpic will provide feedback about fix.  SLG = 320003.  NCAL will review affected profile--believed to be test profile in prod environment (Andre Mure to confirm). Profile = JJCSystem, #4472000.  Per Thomas Sharkey, this is in the production environment.  it was setup in the CAM production environment.  This profile was last active in 2003 but has since been deleted.\r\n11/30:  11/26- Per Mark we do not use these print groups - we are not affected. Per Kirk Med reconcilliation does not apply to beacon as there are no \"released\" orders that cross.  The signed orders cross, but since they are not released, they are not really \"orders\" yet.  So this doesn\"t affect Beacon.\r\n12/8:  Not affected due to affected profile was a test profile, which has been deleted.  Waiting for Kpkg.','Change the look back settings to zero days in the print groups so that discontinued meds do not display on the printed reports.   \r\nEducate users that marking medications for removal will not display to the provider reviewing the printed reports. ','','Change the look back settings to zero days in the print groups so that discontinued meds do not display on the printed reports.   \r\nEducate users that marking medications for removal will not display to the provider reviewing the printed reports. ',NULL,'Affected profile in NCAL appears to be test profile. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-25 01:16:00','2009-11-17 10:40:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(227,3979615,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Med Reconciliation: Modified Signed & Held Meds in Discharge Navigator may not appear in some Print Groups',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ED, OpTime Rx','E757901-C75031225','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-25 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Dana Tom',NULL,NULL,'4530','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NW adhoc\"ed','1212-AP-PR3979615-PR3933718-E757901-C75031225-Spr07Jan19NS.zip\r\n1212-AP-PR3979615-PR3933718-E757901-C75031225-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z\r\n ','K011909',NULL,'2009-04-08 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  In K011909, dlg has different fix; C & E number are in K to different PR\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I751118\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4530):  \n  SP’07 E757784 & C75031184 12/12/08\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/27/09:Per Dhea ok to close.','In the Medication Reconciliation Discharge Navigator, if a user signs and holds a new medication, modifies it, and then releases, some print groups may not show the medication.  Database is correct, not displaying on affected print groups.\r\nAffected print groups:\r\n(Testing environment - a few copies of the printgroups are available in SCAL & NCAL)\r\n46156 - IP MEDS TAKE HOME MEDS FOR ENCOUNTER\r\n46157 - IP MED TAKE HOME MEDS WITH TRIGGER\r\n47156 - IP MEDS TAKE HOME MEDS FOR ENCOUNTER (RTF)\r\n34225 - IP ORDER REC DISCHARGE REVIEW STATUS\r\nWorkflow to reproduce the issue:\r\nIn the Medication Reconciliation Discharge Navigator, order a new medication for discharge.\r\nSign and Hold the medication.\r\nReturn to the Discharge Navigator, and modify the order (note: at this point, print group 34225 will not and should not show the medication).\r\nSign and Release the modified order.\r\nView one of the affected print groups (or a copy). \r\nThe modified order will not appear.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Installed as adhoc successfully on 4/8/09 - validated as part of release by Sherry Ellis / Fay Vafai Inpatient - recommend closing \r\nSP07, SP08, Epic (Maria Spinozzi) is working on a fix.  NCAL not affected until Med Reconciliation (Apr 09). Affected print groups received. 11/30:  NCAL pursing adhoc. \r\n12/3:  NW to adhoc and notify once requested. \r\n2/26:  Per Dhea-Passed testing. Install date-4/8 as a part of K011909','Possible to replace affected print groups with others. ',NULL,'Possible to replace affected print groups with others. ',NULL,'Affected med orders will show in Rx--this is a display issue for providers.  Most would reorder the med,  see the duplicate order alert and be confused.  Potenital if another provider does not see the med and orders a different med in lieu of the undisplayed one.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-25 02:36:00','2009-04-27 08:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(228,3979920,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,' Rx - Changes to Auto-Verified Orders Needing Pharmacist Review may not be Saved',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DLG# I7511011','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-25 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NOV08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511011\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-C75031245\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/28/09: Closed PR','With SP\"07 and SU I757634 installed, functionally was added to allow configuration of department records to send automatically verified orders (typical for ED) to pharmacists for review.  Dispensing and product fields are editable in the verify queue for automatically verified orders that need a pharmacist\"s retrospective review.  However, if a pharmacist edits any of these fields, the changes are not saved.\r\nAll regions (NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, CO, Exempla, MAS, GA, and OH) could be potentially impacted if the departments sent pharmacy orders back to verification queue for pharmacists.  Currently I DEP 48020 is set to null (I DEP 48020 controls the \"Send autoverified orders from this department to the verify queue for review functionality).  This must be set, along with I RXD 466 (\"Orders needing pharmacist review on transfer\").  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code Fix C75031245 installed in PROD on 4/8/09 - NCAL does not use this functionality, recommend CLOSE\r\nEpic (Michael Bries) will provide a code fix (DLG# I7511011) as part of a KPackage. 11/30:  No Current Impact. Functionality is not being used.  Epic (Michael Bries) will provide a code fix (DLG# I7511011) as part of a KPackage ','Functionality may be turned off so orders that were automatically verified don\"t get a retrospective review by pharmacists.\r\nAll regions (NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, CO, Exempla, MAS, GA, and OH) have the functionality turned off so as not to be currently impacted. ',NULL,'Functionality may be turned off so orders that were automatically verified don\"t get a retrospective review by pharmacists.\r\nAll regions (NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, CO, Exempla, MAS, GA, and OH) have the functionality turned off so as not to be currently impacted. ',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-26 09:48:00','2009-04-28 02:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(229,3979924,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Rx- MED LOAD - Incorrect Values in ERX Item 500 may cause Issues with Interfaces under specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-25 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','K051809','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NOV08','Y','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511144\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809 E758623\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/09: Johnette to f/up with AMB.','Medication (ERX) item 500 is a free text field used to represent all of the NDC\"s attached to a given ERX.  It is not a networked item but the values are meant to represent an NDC Record.  Some interfaces (e.g. external RX system, Pyxis) use values from this item as an external identifier for medications and allergies.  \r\nIn this issue, values in ERX500 may be incorrect due to manual entry of the wrong values, multiple changes to ND formats, soft-deleting records, or duplicating records. Some additional factors, which may cause issues with the two basic cases are listed below.  \r\nFor example, an incoming interface may accept an NDC value to represent either a medication (ERX) or an allergy (ELG) and the system will determine the medication or allergy to file with this basic logic:\r\nUse the ERX 500 index to find which ERX has the given NDC value\r\nIf looking for an ELG, then check which ELG is associated with that ERX.\r\nThe outgoing interfaces might use the reverse logic to translate an ERX or ELG into an NDC value.\r\nTo be impacted, regions must:\r\nUse an outgoing ambulatory pharmacy interface with all of the following settings - \r\nSEND_Al1=1\r\nALLERGY_CODE=2\r\nUse an outgoing ambulatory pharmacy interface or outgoing pharmacy interface with SureScripts with the setting MED_ID_HANDLING = 0 or 2, or if it is set to 3 and SECONDARY_MED_ID = 0.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: PS to notify S. Fong of 8/19 install.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).  NO CURR IMPACT\r\nEpic (Michael Bries) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage.  Epic (Michael Bries) ran reports for all regions and found a few records that are impacted.  All of these records were found to be mapped to something that was generically equivalent (e.g. Tylenol to Tylenol).  Epic (Michael Bries) will review these reports with National Pharmacy (Sylvia Fong) and communicate that no changes should be made to the impacted record (e.g. custom records mapped to a narcotic) until a fix is available.  ','See Next Step History.  ','','See Next Step History.  ',NULL,'NO CURR IMPACT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-26 09:57:00','2009-09-08 11:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(230,4003100,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NCI SP\"07 - Changes to SmartForm concept lists in the Visit Navigator section are not saved, under specific conditions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ambulatory, ED, Anesthesia, OpTime, Radiant','DLG I7511093; C75031203','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-04 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'None--NCI',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511093; C75031203\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-C75031203\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/28/09: Closed PR','Changes made to a SmartForm concept list in a Visit Navigator section will not be saved if the SmartForm is opened, closed, and reopened within the section.  This may occur if all of the following conditions are in place:\r\nA new (i.e., not \"Classic\") SmartForm is used in a Visit Navigator section;  \r\nThe SmartForm contains a concept list of tri-state controls (positive/negative controls);\r\nSP\"07 with SU C7503048 is installed.\r\nWorkflow:\r\nOpen the SmartForm from the navigator section.\r\nEdit one of the concept list values.\r\nClose the section.\r\nRe-open the section and change the concept value.\r\nClose the section.\r\nThe concept will retain the value from step 2 and not hold the value from step 4.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code C75031203 was installed in NCAL PROD on 2/21/09.  Recommend to close, due to NCAL not having this configuration. \r\nwill wait for Jan K-pckg (NCI)','  No regions are currently impacted.  According to regional Epic searches, no region uses the affected SmartForm build although some regions may have installed the affected SU. ',NULL,'  No regions are currently impacted.  According to regional Epic searches, no region uses the affected SmartForm build although some regions may have installed the affected SU. ',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-03 03:10:00','2009-04-28 02:14:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(239,4003058,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Medication and Procedure Filtered Patient System Lists may be Inaccurate under specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'Clin Doc  ','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-04 00:00:00','2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','K031609','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511263, I7511278\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809 - E758187 & E758392\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/01/09: R. Soriano verified successful install of the fix for this issue. ','Medication and procedure filtered system lists may exclude patients incorrectly for the following problems. The pharmacy workflow uses these filtered lists to identify which patients may need closer monitoring (e.g. warfarin protocol). Patients may be missing from these lists in the following 3 problem scenarios:\r\n1) Medication and procedure orders placed on pre-admitted patients are not evaluated and added to system lists when the patients are admitted.  Pre-admit med orders will be added to the system lists correctly, after they are verified by a pharmacist, which is the typical workflow. However, pre-admit procedure orders may not be added. An example of this procedure order would be a consult or system list filter for patients with particular xray procedure ordered (these procedures areusually a consult or ancillary type of procedure and are not generally clinically invasive types of procedures such as placement of a chest tube, central line, or wound debridement). If a region uses procedure orders instead of medication orders to monitor patients (ex. Warfarin Protocol), then a region may be impacted. (The value in LSD item 34804)\r\n 2) Patients with Total Parenteral Nutrition (TPN) and mixture orders might be removed from a system list incorrectly and this may occur after a system list filter is either viewed or edited. These screens are accessed from d ^L > Management Options > Edit System Definitions > Patient List. Users  must use F6 to edit a filter (see below-Edit System List Filters), although one need not change anything about the filter to be affected. A region may be affected, if a user used any of the medication related filter options. (Value in system definitions 34811, 34813, 34831). As clarification regarding this error caused by \"viewing\"- text screens in Chronicles may be entered in edit mode or view mode.  This error can occur if the screen is entered in edit mode without changes being made.  In this case the screen has been \"viewed\".  If the screen is entered in view mode, however, the error does not occur.\r\n,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,  Edit System List Filters  ,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,\r\n Filter value: DEXTROSE\r\n Medications               Therapeutic Classes       Pharmaceutical Classes   \r\n 1. 46245-DEXTROSE\r\n 2. Procedures                Order Types               Procedure Categories     \r\n Note: When the values of a filter are changed, patients with existing orders matching the filter are automatically added to system lists.  If needed, one may run \"d RebuildAdm^JCNMED1()\" from the Cache prompt to rebuild all the lists.Example:An order is placed for a TPN that has dextrose. The dextrose ERX is included in the \"DEXTROSE\" system list filter, because you want to know all patients with orders for this medication. After this order is placed, the patient appears on the patient list. Then someone on the technical team forgets what the particular dextrose system list filter contains, so they enter the record in System Definitions on the text side. Upon exiting, only the TPN ERX record is evaluated for the group \"DEXTROSE\", which it does not have, so the order and patient fall off of the system list. Instead, both the TPN ERX record and its components should be evaluated for the filter.\r\n3) Only affects version SP\"08.  Orders using med grouper items 2-6 might be removed from a system list incorrectly. As with #2 above, this happens after a system list filter is accessed on the text side. You also must edit a filter to be affected.  If you use a filter based on the ERX grouper items 2-6 (ERX items 4110 , 4120, 4130, 4140, and 4150), when you access the following screen in System Definitions (this is the 2nd screen of the Filter definitions), all orders that would otherwise match the grouper criteria, will be removed from the system list based on the filter.   Note:  Grouper items 2-6 aren\"t commonly used. Though KP is not currently impacted, we are imminently impacted due to  SP 08 implementations scheduled for 1st',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: PS to contact Rey for certification.\r\n5/6:  Tom sent email to Rey, requesting status for w/a?s 4/13: Bart to F/up with Rey.\r\n4/6: Tom S. to F/up witrh Rey S.; has the w/a been tested?2/27:  per Bart/Rey:  workaround could create potentially more problems in the system and we should wait for testing to occur2/27:  Workaround to be installed in PROD - targetting April 09.  Needs to be tested by ADT. (Per Bart).\r\nTom S. to send email to Andrea regarding status of work around; Andrea to F/U with Rey Soriano regarding status of work around.Follow-Up:  Per Epic (Cindi Batson) - sent via PART email 1/19/09, see issues 1, 2, 3 below.\r\nIssue #1:\r\nMed and procedure orders placed on pre-admitted patients are not added to system lists upon admission.  \r\nWorkaround: Create admission programming point to re-evaluate admission orders correctly.\r\nFix: DLG I7511263 ? Release date not yet scheduled.\r\nIssue #2:\r\nTPN and mixture med orders might be removed from a system list incorrectly when the filter setup screen in System Definitions is visited.\r\nWorkaround: Run the rebuild tag after accessing the filter setup screen in System Definitions to correctly re-evaluate system list filters.\r\nFix: DLG I7511278 ? Scheduled to be released in mid-February.\r\nIssue #3:\r\nOrders using med grouper items 2-6 might be removed from a system list incorrectly when the system list filter screen is accessed in System Definitions.  Only affects Spring 2008 version.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nNCAL Affected. Advices to implement workaround.  Workaround would be \"Airtight\".  Andrea has referred to Rey Soriano from clindocs. \r\nSP07 & SP08.  IP, Pharmacy, ED, Beacon, OpTime.  Epic (Cyndi Batson) will provide an update about the code fix for SP\"07 and the KPackage availability by 12/19/08.\r\n12/15:  Per Andrea, Notify R.Soriano from clindoc.  ','','','',NULL,'6/3:  per Rey S: \"The workaround #1 requires using a programming point that would automate running code that we currently have access to running manually.   The programming point requires cross suite coordination and testing with the ADT suite and at this point would not complete in time to be useful before the August 2009 fix is installed. In the meantime, we have been periodically running the rebuild code to update the system lists which we have done in the past when filters get updated.Epic\"\r\n\r\n (Cindy Batson) ran reports to determine if regions were impacted for problems #1 and #2.  The searches looked for system master files (LSD) values and found NCAL, SCAL, HI, Exempla, and NW to contain (problem #1) values in item 34804 per region and (problem #2) values in items 34811, 34813, and 34831.  Regions should review these queries and implement the workaround for item #1.  For item #2, Regions may run the utility defined below as they deem necessary.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-08 08:03:00','2009-09-01 01:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(240,4013715,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'In Basket Patient Result Messages may be Suppressed Unexpectedly under specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'',' I7511421','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-08 00:00:00','2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','K031609','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  .regions should work with Epic TS; Confirmed in 031609 \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511421, I767521\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609 E758252\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/01/09--per JDee/AMB, fix was installed 8/19, ok to close. CLOSING',' Regions that use Programming Point 52420 (Result Routing Criterion that checks to see if a patient is admitted and was designed with the intent to suppress In Basket Result Messages for admitted patients) may have patient results suppressed from their In Basket and physicians may not see anticipated results as expected. \r\nThere are two workflow variations that may be impacted by this programming point:  \r\n1. A patient is seen at an outpatient clinic and has orders placed/performed. The patient is admitted to the hospital before the results return for the outpatient orders. \r\n2. A patient is seen at an outpatient clinic and has future orders placed. The patient is admitted to the hospital near the due date of those orders so the hospital performs the orders. \r\nIn Basket Result Messages may be suppressed and the ordering/authorization provider will never see the anticipated results in their In Basket.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (March-confirmed). NCAL doesn\'t use affected programming point. Waiting for Aug install of March KPKG \r\n5/26: Johnette to f/up re KPKG.\r\n2/23:  Fix ready.  No regions have asked for adhoc \r\nEpic (Nathan DaWALT) will provide an update about the code fix for SP\"07 and the KPackage availability by 12/19/08.Epic (Nathan DaWalt), as part of the fix design, will determine the appropriate report and search criteria for impacted orders.  \r\nEpic will notify PART and the impacted region (NW) that the report is available for use.\r\n2/23: Adhoc or Kpkg? Requested status from AMB.','Epic suggests that the regions using the programming point may remove the impacted Programming Point 52420, which would change their routing schemes.\r\nEpic  (Nathan DaWalt) has discussed this with the NW Ambulatory AC (Kaile V. Riser) and at this time, the workflow supports using Programming Point 52420, as designed.  No change is anticipated.\r\n','','Epic suggests that the regions using the programming point may remove the impacted Programming Point 52420, which would change their routing schemes.\r\nEpic  (Nathan DaWalt) has discussed this with the NW Ambulatory AC (Kaile V. Riser) and at this time, the workflow supports using Programming Point 52420, as designed.  No change is anticipated.\r\n',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-08 10:32:00','2009-09-01 12:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(241,4019435,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'All Versions - ED only - Information in Visit Navigator Follow-Up section may be overwritten if two users edit or view the section ','','',NULL,NULL,'potentially AMB (unlikely) ','I7510026 (SP07) / C75031294','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-11 00:00:00','2009-09-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Alan Rogers ','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','K031609','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  SP07-I7510026  SP08 I765390\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 E757944 1/23/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609-C75031294\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/10/09: per A. Mure, fix in prod, can\'t certify.  CLOSING.  ','Description:  Edits made by one user in the Visit Navigator Follow-Up section may be overwritten if another user views or edits the section.  Specifically, \r\nthe pre-Spring 2008 Disposition and Follow-up navigator section (27040-SEC_ER_DISP) might not update for one user after a different user\"s lock is released. \r\n \r\nFor example: \r\n \r\nUser A opens and edits a patient\"s Follow-Up provider section. \r\nUser B tries to open the same patient\"s Follow-Up provider section.  The user won\"t be able to open the section because it\"s locked by User A. \r\nUser A saves/closes the patient\"s Follow-Up provider section.\r\nUser B tries again to open and edit the patient\"s Follow-Up provider section, and can, but none of user A\"s most recent changes appear.  User A\"s changes are overwritten when user B makes changes and saves the section.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (March-confirmed). Per Andre we are not affected, w/a not in place, no ad hoc.\r\n2/23/09: Waiting for March KPKG unless we get an adhoc request. Is a workaround needed?\r\n3/02: Andre will followup on workaround status.\r\n2/26:  Is a workaround needed?\r\n2/23:  Andre to re check if adhoc is needed or not.\r\nRegions to see if affected, determine if adhoc is needed.  Andre to f/u.\r\nRegions to see if affected, determine if adhoc is needed.  Epic working on a fix. \r\n12/15:  Andre to f/u if NCAL affected.\r\n12/23:  SP07 fix (I7510026) will be available 2/6/09.  ','Use print group 75147-ED Disposition Edit Trail to view all of the patient\"s disposition information and print group 75148-ED Follow-up Provider Edit Trail to view all of the patient\"s follow-up provider information.','','Use print group 75147-ED Disposition Edit Trail to view all of the patient\"s disposition information and print group 75148-ED Follow-up Provider Edit Trail to view all of the patient\"s follow-up provider information.',NULL,'Epic rep:   Austin Guentner aguentne@epicsystems.com ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-11 12:49:00','2009-09-10 10:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(243,4019636,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Diagnosis print groups may truncate information after open parenthesis',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, ED, Rx, Beacon','I17511231 / E757944','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-11 00:00:00',NULL,'2008-12-29 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Alan Rogers',NULL,NULL,'4559','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' Hawaii','0123-PS-PR4019636-E757944-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z\r\n040209-PR4019636-AH4559-SP07051809EEG.tar.Z','K011909',NULL,'2009-03-18 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:   \nNOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511231\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4559):  \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909-E757944\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/15: no response from amb re status of install; closed issue 5/15/09.  ','When displaying a diagnosis, certain diagnosis print groups may truncate information that appears after an open (left) parenthesis \"( For example,  the diagnosis  HPV (Human Papillomavirus) Vaccine would display as HPV.  \r\n This is a display issue that occurs only if a category list or type ahead display name includes an open parenthesis.  Free text entry is not affected. \r\nAffected released print groups (and copies) include:\r\n51013\r\n51024\r\n51170\r\n56213\r\n56214\r\n56507\r\n75024',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code installed in prod on 3/18/09 - E757944, I7511231 - verify with AMB and close.\r\n4/2:  second tar file received--fixes non-PS TD in orig adhoc (1/23).  Waiting for prod. confirmation (M Grange).  Code installed into NCAL CE WITS2 on 02/05/2009 and verified. Per Theresa adhoc will be in WITS on 2/5/09. 1/29: Replicated.  Theresa to install adhoc code into WITS.  ETA for fix in prod = 3/18. \r\nAndrea forwarding search results to Ryan L.  ED or AMB to own.  Regions to check print groups, apply W/A or req adhoc if affected.  Epic working on a fix.  Kieu T Trong requested fix into WITS. \r\n12/23: SP\"07 fix to be released 12/29/08.  \r\n2/23:  passed ncf - install date-3/18.','Until the fix is installed, use alternative print groups such as LPG 75168 or 75035.',NULL,'Until the fix is installed, use alternative print groups such as LPG 75168 or 75035.',NULL,'Epic rep:  Austin Guentner  aguentne@epicsystems.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-11 01:15:00','2009-05-15 11:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(244,4023507,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,' In Basket Result Message may not be Generated if Ordering Provider is not an EMR Provider',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IntraConnect','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-12 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','July 08',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:   \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758914\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108-E756394\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1/20:  per Jason Ramaker (Epic), we may close, as NCAL not affected and no fix forthcoming.  ','Interface profile variable 352-NOTIFY_EMR_PROV may prevent generation of result notification messages for an order result from an external system if the ordering provider in the OBR-16 field of the interface message is not recognized as an EMR (Electronic Medical Record ) Provider (item SER 8020=Yes). \r\n There are several identified scenarios wherein OBR-16 can reference provider records that are not designated as an EMR Provider:\r\n- The wrong ID is stored for a provider in the third-party lab or radiology systems (or the provider is entirely absent in these systems).\r\n- Multiple provider records exist for a single provider in those external systems.\r\n- User errors occur when entering the provider in those systems. \r\nIn the scenarios listed above, if the provider listed in the interface message is not an EMR provider in Epic, no result notification messages are generated for the result, for any recipients.\r\nProfile variable 352-NOTIFY_EMR_PROV can be used in Incoming Results interfaces and Incoming Transcription interfaces.  Results interfaces are always affected by this issue.  For Transcription interfaces, this issue does not apply if the interface is only used to send encounter-level transcriptions.  However, if the interface is used to send order-level transcriptions then more analysis is required - EPIC EDI representatives will work with customers to make sure that In Basket message behavior is as expected.\r\nAdditionally, the EMR provider or EpicCare Provider fields are meant to indicate whether the provider actually uses the clinical applications. In some cases, someone?s provider record could have been created in the Epic system, but regions are still using a legacy system.  This flag would ensure that they don?t have results being routed to them until they actually go-live with the Epic system.\r\n Note: This issue was previously reported in Care Concern Bulletin 11.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fix was in July K-packg; config needed as described in release note. Per PART 12/15, NCAL not using the impacted variable. The DLG I758914 (E756394) is available and the fix, I758914, was sent in the July KPackage.  Note that there is configuration required that is described in the release note.  A limited outage is required. This Special Update may be installed while most users are on the system. Results Routing may be affected, so it is recommended that this Special Update be installed when there is no user activity on them:  This means stopping the Incoming Results Interface filer and making sure that nobody is resulting orders in Enter/Edit Results, Media Manager, Procedure Notes, etc. while this is being installed.','For Results interfaces set profile variable 352-NOTIFY_EMR_PROV to null.  Note, however, that this will allow result notification messages to be sent to providers who are not EMR providers in Epic.\r\nFor Transcription interfaces Epic EDI must discuss with the customer in order to determine if any action is appropriate ? there are legitimate reasons to use this profile variable for some Transcription interfaces.',NULL,'For Results interfaces set profile variable 352-NOTIFY_EMR_PROV to null.  Note, however, that this will allow result notification messages to be sent to providers who are not EMR providers in Epic.\r\nFor Transcription interfaces Epic EDI must discuss with the customer in order to determine if any action is appropriate ? there are legitimate reasons to use this profile variable for some Transcription interfaces.',NULL,'Remediation:  Check on regional installation schedule for the July K Pkg and work with EPIC TS to configure as required. The DLG I758914 (E756394) is available and the fix, I758914, was sent in the July KPackage.  Note that there is configuration required that is described in the release note.  A limited outage is required. This Special Update may be installed while most users are on the system. Results Routing may be affected, so it is recommended that this Special Update be installed when there is no user activity on them:  This means stopping the Incoming Results Interface filer and making sure that nobody is resulting orders in Enter/Edit Results, Media Manager, Procedure Notes, etc. while this is being installed.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-12 12:28:00','2009-01-20 04:01:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(245,4031199,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'In Basket Patient Result Messages may be Suppressed Unexpectedly due to Results Notification Configuration Settings ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inpatient','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-12 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/3: Per Jansin Lee OK to close this PR.','Epic is proactively contacting all their clinical customers regarding the risks of improperly configured results notification routing. Even though the results are filed correctly to the patient chart, improper configuration or system build has the potential to cause a result notification not to be generated for all intended recipients. Although there are legitimate cases where a region may choose not to route a result notification to any provider, EPIC has identified that occasionally no notification is being sent due to improper configuration, improper use, or accidental omission of certain results routing rules or settings. \r\nBased on their recent customer experience, Epic has identified configuration areas that have a higher potential of incorrect setup or build. Over the next few days, Epic will run search utilities to check for known areas of problem configuration and formulate region specific action plans to address those areas as needed. Regional EPIC TS\"s will review the results of the searches with each region and assist each region with necessary setup changes. The configuration areas that have been identified and will be the focus in this escalation are: \r\na) Regional current build configurationvs. what Epic recommends - There may be regional build variations that should be reviewed against build recommendations suggested by EPIC.  Current regional build decisions may have valid justification but should be reviewed to determine if changes are warranted based on desired workflow or process.\r\nUser set-up configuration - EPIC queries will identify specific provider profiles that may require set-up configuration changes to enable receipt of In Basket results.\r\n\r\nc) Orders and In Basket Configuration - Specific orders and In Basket configurations that result in messages not being generated will be identified in the EPIC queries and should be reviewed.\r\nd) Pool back up set-up configuration ? Examples of this area would be: 1) a results routing scheme is improperly configured to only send results to a staff pool that has been marked inactive or doesn?t have any members, results sent through this scheme would not reach a recipient. or 2)  a clinic in a region schedules resident appointments using a generic resource for the purpose of working from one common schedule and uses results routing schemes that only send to the encounter provider, results will only be sent to the generic resource.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/13: David O. to f/up with Johnette.\r\nJohnette to check w/ Jansin if OK to close this issue. Chris (EPIC) to follow up.Jansin to resolve after discharge unsolicited orders scenario (see \"d.\" in description) Per Jansin 12/15: I have reviewed all interfaces with Epic early this week.  We are all OK except on the after discharge unsolicited orders situation where the Inbasket messages are created for the authorizing provider rather than going to the pool.  2/9:  Per Drew Davey (Epic):   Jansin?s statement is correct in that unsolicited results after discharge are routed to the authorizing provider as opposed to going to a pool (it?s not a case I?ve examined specifically yet). However, I?d argue that this doesn?t fall under the purview of this Patient Safety Issue, which dealt with setup where results weren?t getting routed *at all*.  Rather, the italicized comment below should be treated more as a side issue where results aren?t being routed to the most convenient destination. In this case, someone is still being notified of the result.\r\n \r\nJansin and I have been working through a more all-encompassing approach to results routing @ NCAL, both to deal with the PSE issues as well as additional configuration which would streamline delivery / handling of results.\r\n2/23:Johnette to check w/ Jansin if OK to close this issue. ','All regions (SCAL, NCAL, HI, NW, GA, OH, MAS, CO, and Exempla) currently have a report that they may run routinely and reroute missed inbasket messages.\r\n',NULL,'All regions (SCAL, NCAL, HI, NW, GA, OH, MAS, CO, and Exempla) currently have a report that they may run routinely and reroute missed inbasket messages.\r\n',NULL,'Impacted regions (SCAL, NCAL, HI, NW, GA, OH, MAS, CO, and Exempla) should work with their Epic TS, to re-route any result messages not generated or received, when those messages can be identified. Regions that have been routinely running reports to identify messages that require re-routing will most likely not encounter additional messages that require re-routing.\r\n\r\nUrgent Mitigation:  \r\nSteve Veats and Loretta Allen will discuss EPIC/KP regional remediation plans with potentially impacted regions (SCAL, NCAL, HI, NW, GA, OH, MAS, CO, and Exempla) at their regularly scheduled Inpatient and Ambulatory AC meetings.\r\nEpic (Jason Ramaker) has run search utilities for potentially impacted regions to check for known areas of problem configuration and set-up and is working with EPIC regional TS\"s to formulate recommendations for regional specific action plans.\r\nEach regional Epic TS will work with each of the regions (SCAL, NCAL, HI, NW, GA, OH, MAS, CO, and Exempla) to review the results of the search utilities and assist with any necessary set-up changes and implementation.\r\nAll regions will confirm to PART (Sharon Carroll) that they have completed any required changes for each of the four problem conditions in order to consider the incident closed.\r\n\r\nFrom Drew Davey (2/9/2009)\r\nJansin?s statement is correct in that unsolicited results after discharge are routed to the authorizing provider as opposed to going to a pool (it?s not a case I?ve examined specifically yet). However, I?d argue that this doesn?t fall under the purview of this Patient Safety Issue, which dealt with setup where results weren?t getting routed *at all*.  Rather, the italicized comment below should be treated more as a side issue where results aren?t being routed to the most convenient destination. In this case, someone is still being notified of the result.\r\n \r\nJansin and I have been working through a more all-encompassing approach to results routing @ NCAL, both to deal with the PSE issues as well as additional configuration which would streamline delivery / handling of results.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-12 12:33:00','2009-06-04 08:54:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(246,4041119,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Rate-based dosing units may not calculate as expected with frequencies greater than 24 hours','','',NULL,NULL,'Beacon, OPT, Rx, Discrete Sigs-AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-16 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr.  Allen Rogers','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','Y','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511831\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758597\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/09:  per Cheryl Tran, fix works.  CLOSING','Description:   A medication dose could be greater than what the ordering provider intended if the medication has both:\r\na rate-based dosage unit, and\r\na frequency that schedules doses more than every 24 hours, such as Every Monday, Wednesday, Friday                                                                 \r\nExample:\r\n10 mg/kg/day of Bactrim is ordered for a 1.1 kg pediatric patient. The frequency is Every Monday, Wednesday, Friday.  The calculated dose will be 25.6667 mg to be administered once on Monday, once on Wednesday, once on Friday, etc. The following calculation is shown in Order Entry and Verification:\r\n10 mg/kg/day x 1.1 kg = 11 mg/day over 0.4286 administrations per day (3 days of administrations/7 days in the week) = 25.6667 mg\r\nHowever, one might expect for this to calculate to 11 mg instead, which would be administered once on Monday, once on Wednesday, once on Friday, etc. \r\n10 mg/kg/day x 1.1 kg = 11 mg/day, 1 administration on each of the scheduled days = 11 mg\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: PS to f/up with B. Yee or Sylvia Fong.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed)\r\n7/7:  Andre to check if NCAL is waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed). Per Andre, Waiting for kpkg.\r\n4/13: Rebecca to see if fix will be in May KPKG.\r\nWorkaround in place (per Andre). F/u with Andre to see if waiting for Kpkg.\r\nNCAL not affected - Already installed the workaround.  Verify workaround in place. Epic (Michael Bries) will provide a code fix and inform PART of its status by 12/22/08. 12/17:  per AM, NCAL has the programming point LPP 3913, installed in the production environment.','Regions are advised to install programming point  LPP 3913: Order Validation - Check Per Day Dose Against Frequency in thier LSD level profile.   This is an airtight workaround that prevents the processing of orders with a frequency greater than 24 hours.','','Regions are advised to install programming point  LPP 3913: Order Validation - Check Per Day Dose Against Frequency in thier LSD level profile.   This is an airtight workaround that prevents the processing of orders with a frequency greater than 24 hours.',NULL,'Epic Representative:  Michael Bries / MBries@epicsystems.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-16 12:45:00','2009-09-08 10:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(247,4048276,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Remote In Basket users may not see remote InBasket messages','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-17 00:00:00','2009-08-04 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'RISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/04/09: 8/4:  per MLin, remediation completed in production, can close.  CLOSING','Epic identified approx 100 users affected in NCAL (users w/ no home deployment identified.)  This is caused by improper setting (perhaps by an AC) of item 3400 in the EMP record.  Epic says there is no good reason for a user to have no base (home) deployment.  4 types of messages affected:  results, patient med advice requests, e-refill, and e-refill follow-up. \r\nUsers who have no base deployment defined (usually due to an administrative error in which the base deployment Item 3400 is deleted, overwritten, or omitted) may not see In Basket messages or preview displays at their base deployments, depending on if and how message types are enabled for cross-deployment messaging.\r\nIf In Basket message types (e.g., results, patient medical advice requests, e-refills and e-refill follow-ups) are enabled for cross-deployment messaging, messages should be routed from the originating deployment to the provider\"s base deployment.  However, with this issue, the In Basket is correct and complete at originating deployments but the cross-deployment enabled messages are not routed to the base deployment In Basket.\r\nFor In Basket message types that are not enabled for cross-deployment messaging, messages should appear in the remote In Basket preview display, indicating work to be completed at a remote deployment.  However, with this issue, no remote In Basket preview displays appear at the user\"s base deployment.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7/10:  per MHLin, can close after 7/16 when the remediation will be completed.6/22. Per M. Lin?s 6/18 email: Screenshots taken on validation EMPs.  Pending Epic further action and feedback6/18: Helen Q. to f/up with Margaret to get update of testing\r\n6/2:  Testing in progress. This problem can be self-corrected when a new msg is generated.(per Margaret).\r\n5/6:  per Emily Jenkins, utility still being tested in KP test environ w/ MLin.  \r\n4/7:  per C Russell, MLin / Emily having testing difficulties, issue on hold. Per Chris 2/23, Emily working on next steps for RA.\r\nChris to f/up with Emily again.Chris to send email to Aaron and Emily; Tom S. to f/up too.2/2/09 per M Lin, \"We have fixed provider base deployments.  The problem can be self corrected once a new msg comes in.  Epic has not provided the a new fix yet.\" 1/5 per M. Lin:  We tested the RA  but it did not work as expected so we are waiting for the Epic update.\r\nEpic to provide RA for remediation. No code fix expected).  Aaron Greenblatt and Emily Jenkins to work with Margaret Lin. ','Provide user with a base deployment.\r\nRun RA which causes notification updates.',NULL,'Provide user with a base deployment.\r\nRun RA which causes notification updates.',NULL,'Aaron Greenblatt / agreenbl@epicsystems.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-17 02:21:00','2009-08-10 12:03:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(248,4052843,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Discharge Orders may Display Inaccurately during Medication Reconciliation',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OpTime','I7510918 (no outage required)','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-18 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Alan Rogers',NULL,NULL,'4546','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'adhoc\"ed by NW','0108-AP-PR4052843-E757931-C75031233-Spr07Jan19NS.tar.Z\r\n0108-AP-PR4052843-E757931-C75031233-Spr07Jan19NS.zip','K011909',NULL,'2009-04-08 00:00:00','N','I','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K011909\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7510918\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4546):  \n  SP’07 E757931 & C75031233 1/08/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909\nRISK RANKING:  6',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Code installed in NCAL PROD  on 4/8 as a part of K011909.  Unable to test-not applicable to our build','If you use sign and hold functionality as part of the discharge medication reconciliation workflow, and you open a prior to admission medication section at some point during your discharge medication reconciliation workflow, this may incorrectly update sign and held discharge medications orders. When this occurs, the signed and held orders may appear to be signed even though they are not released, or they may display as sign and held but you?re unable to release them. \r\n\r\nSample Workflow - Signed and Held Discharge Medications Incorrectly Marked as Signed:\r\nOpen a discharge medication reconciliation navigator and go to the review section.\r\nPrescribe an inpatient medication order as a new discharge medication.\r\nSign and hold the new prescription.\r\nRe-open the discharge medication review section.\r\nClick on the ?Sign and Release All Orders? button.  (This step is not needed if the default re-order action specified in the VCN configuration is Sign.)  Don\"t accept/sign the changes made.\r\nOpen a prior to admission medications navigator section.\r\nClose the patient?s chart, or switch to another activity.\r\nUpon reopening the patient?s chart and returning to the discharge medication review section, the medication may appear under the Signed Medications section even though they have not been released.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Not an issue currently (not using MedRec until April, and VCN setting in testing (sign & release is disabled) prevents the problem.  NW has adhoc\"ed--code should arrive 1/8/09 (per Chris R)  \r\n2/26/09: Per Dhea:  Install date-4/8 as a part of K011909.  Unable to test-not applicable to our build','1. Leave Sign and Release as \"disabled\" or add a copy of print groups that display it correctly in another section.\r\n2. Instead of using prior to admission navigator section, it would be a different report, making this functionality more difficult.',NULL,'1. Leave Sign and Release as \"disabled\" or add a copy of print groups that display it correctly in another section.\r\n2. Instead of using prior to admission navigator section, it would be a different report, making this functionality more difficult.',NULL,'Maria Spinozzi = mspinozz@epicsystems.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-18 04:14:00','2009-04-29 10:13:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(249,4054332,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'IntraConnect - Chart Synch may not Occur under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP','DLG I7511540','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-19 00:00:00',NULL,'2009-03-06 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr.  Allen Rogers',NULL,NULL,'4575','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1/16 by KR, MLin','0306-CE-PR4054332-E758276-Spr07Mar16NS.tar.Z','K031609',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'DEC08','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511540\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4575):  \n  SP’07 E758276 3/06/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609\nRISK RANKING:  5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/4:  per Wei,  For NCAL, the last run of the utility was completed on 5/1.  CLOSING. ','Description:  Depending upon workflow, data that is expected to be in a patient\"s chart may be missing because chart synch may not occur.  The data will be available in the patient\"s chart for their home instance, but not elsewhere, if viewed.\r\n\r\nIn rare circumstances, it could possibly be moderate or severe, as in medication or allergy cases.  Data may be missing, unexpectedly and perhaps unnoticed, from a patient\"s chart if viewed by a clinician in an instance that is not the patient\"s home instance.  This may impact patient care, however, the normal workflow is for a clinician to ask the patient questions or talk with the patient during the course of care.  \r\n\r\nFor inpatients, chart synch occurs after discharge, so the impact may be for ambulatory patients, however, it would be rare.\r\n\r\n NCAL & SCAL are currently impacted.\r\n\r\nFeatures:  IntraConnect Environment, Chart Synch function\r\n\r\nAffected charts:  NCAL-600/SCAL-300',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/13: per Wei Sun, installed in prod 4/8--waiting to complete final run of utility before closing. 2/23/09: Per R. Shimmon, cleanup utility approved, will be run after adhoc installed.  Chris Cordero from SCAL owns the RFC for this ad hoc, which is scheduled for delivery on March 6.  Tom to confirm with Margaret that an adhoc was requested. Per Epic (Robert Shimmin) - This issue will be fixed by DLG I7511540 in the March K-package.  If requested as an ad hoc, installation will require a downtime for the chart synchronization queues.  (NCAL and SCAL regions are considering requesting and auth\r\nAdhoc request to be decided.  Epic to run utility as remediation (only workaround). Notify Margaret regarding issue.  Epic will first run the utility and then regions to run utility after (if requested)-f/u with Margaret. ','',NULL,'',NULL,'Epic Representative:  Robert Shimmin 1-608-271-9000  \r\nAdhoc will require downtime for the chart synchronization queues.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-19 12:56:00','2009-05-04 03:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(250,4059954,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3663413,'Inpatient Medication Reconciliation - PTA medications marked Stop Taking do not discontinue on ED Discharge',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ambulatory, ED, OPTtime','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-23 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-05-26 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. George Peredy',NULL,NULL,'4557','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NW ADHOC','0202-PS-PR4059954-E758192-Spr07Mar16NS.tar.Z (Aug install)\r\n0417-PS-PR4059954-C75031367-E758523-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z (June install)\r\n0417-PS-PR4059954-C75031367-E758523-Spr07May18NS.zip','March 09 Kpckg',NULL,'2009-06-17 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Need to install fix before implementing med rec functionality if LT fix not available; multiple fixes coming, fix 1 will be server to change the print group code; fix 2 will ensure flagged meds are properly discontinued--still in process, will likely have a client component;  Confimed in K031609; I7511453 in testing\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511463/E758192, I767586, 141465 (fix 1) 149315, I767566 (fix 2) I7511453\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4557):  \n  SP’07 E758192 2/02/09 & C75031367 & E758523 4/17/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609  K051809\nRISK RANKING:  3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/30: Mar kpkg in Aug install; May kpkg in June. Mar kpkg does not affect NCAL','If the new Inpatient Medication Reconciliation Multitemplate Navigator is used in non-Inpatient workflows (such as for ED, OpTime, or Ambulatory), PTA medications marked as Stop Taking may NOT appear as Discontinued and will still appear in AVS print groups as medications the patient should continue taking.  They will also remain active for future encounters.  \r\nExample Workflow:\r\nOutpatient Medications (either patient-reported or prescriptions from previous visits) are documented in the Home Medications section (PTA medications).  \r\nA provider enters the Inpatient Discharge Medication Reconciliation tool and marks a medication as Stop Taking.\r\nThe provider signs the order, and the medication displays as Stopped Taking via the  Inpatient Discharge Medication Reconciliation tool.\r\nHowever, in the AVS print groups used in the ED, the medication appear as Continue Taking.  (If the medication was modified before it was marked as Stop Taking, it could appear in the These Medications Have Changed.) \r\nOn subsequent visits, the provider will still see the order that he or she marked as Stop Taking in the previous visit(s) via the Home Medications section. Stop Taking also appears at discharge as well via the discharge reconciliation tool.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5/27:  PROD install targeted 6/17.  Received NCF approval on 5/26.\r\n4/20: Go live with known defect 34410.\r\nAdhoc fix received 2/2/09. \r\nEpic (Brendan Krueger) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its development status by 12/29/08.  NW to ad hoc, if NW doesn\"t ad hoc then NCAL should.','Do not include Inpatient Discharge Med Rec Multitemplate Navigator tools in non-Inpatient navigators (ED, Ambulatory, etc.)\r\nFor ED, use navigator section 17805-SEC_ORDERS_ED with a navigator configuration based on Epic released record 49200 - ED Discharge Orders Section With Medication Review.',NULL,'Do not include Inpatient Discharge Med Rec Multitemplate Navigator tools in non-Inpatient navigators (ED, Ambulatory, etc.)\r\nFor ED, use navigator section 17805-SEC_ORDERS_ED with a navigator configuration based on Epic released record 49200 - ED Discharge Orders Section With Medication Review.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-23 01:32:00','2009-06-30 02:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(252,4064345,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT: MDL Medication notes may not synchronize correctly across deployments','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inpatient, ED, Pharmacy with ChartSync ','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-29 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  standard in IU7: closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I768039\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, SP08 only, does not affect SP07, fixed in SU09.  ','Starting in SP\"08 IU3, all medication problem list (MDL) records created in a remote deployment are hidden.  However, this prevents problem list-level medication notes from being synchronized correctly or made visible across deployments as expected.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-29 03:31:00','2009-07-22 01:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(253,4064347,1,'RAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Radiant, NO CURR IMPACT - Correct patient contact may not open with TWL (Technologist Work List) and Verify Orders, in a specific workflow','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-29 00:00:00','2009-08-27 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Another EPIC customer','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'RAD','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','Y','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511325\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609-C75031307\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/27/09: 8/27:  per C Burke, fix installed and verified.  Closing. ','If a clinician double-clicks on and opens the Verify Orders activity for an order from the Technologist Work List, the correct patient contact (e.g., admission or HOV encounter) may not open.  Instead, the appointment contact is opened and used for documentation.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/18/09: PS to f/up with Radiant contact C. Burke.  08/10/09: Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of the 031609 KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of its status.\r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of the 031609 KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of its status.\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, regions are advised to implement this fix when it becomes available.','No work around since no regions are currently impacted, since Epic searches showed no regions with potentially impacted patients.\r\nNW, HI, NCAL, and GA could be potentially impacted if they use the affected workflow without implementing the fix.',NULL,'No work around since no regions are currently impacted, since Epic searches showed no regions with potentially impacted patients.\r\nNW, HI, NCAL, and GA could be potentially impacted if they use the affected workflow without implementing the fix.',NULL,'Epic searches showed no regions with potentially impacted patients.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-29 04:12:00','2009-08-27 01:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(254,4064346,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURR IMPACT--Discontinued or expired medications may still display with no indication, if Print Group 48805 is used','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, Pharmacy, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-29 00:00:00','2009-09-14 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Another EPIC customer','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512218, I764746/E761763\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809- E758654\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/14/2009:  fix installed on 8/19 with May K-pckg, can\'t certify (don\'t use prnt grp), CLOSING','Due to an issue with print group 48805-IP Discharge Meds Take Home,discontinued or expired medications for a patient will continue to display, without indication that the medications have been discontinued or that they have expired.  This behavior can occur if either or both of the following two conditions are met:\r\nProfile record setting Display discontinued/expired medications for __ day(s) (I LPR 860) on the Prior to Admission list is set to any number of days but zero, in which case there is no impact., and/or\r\nA physician has marked a Prior to Admission medication as long-term; in this case, the medication does not drop off print group 48804 even when it is discontinued via Discharge Navigator. However, if the long-term medication is discontinued from theMedications Activity, it will correctly drop off the print group.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: 6/2: 8/09 INSTALL\r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix  1/5/09 Per Bart, we do not use  print group nor are there plans to use it at this time \r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status .Per Bart, we do not use  print group nor are there plans to use it at this time \r\n ','A partial workaround for SP\"07 and later is to set profile setting Drop discontinued medications immediately (I LPR 862) to Yes.  This setting will cause discontinued medications to immediately drop off of this print group, although expired medications will continue to incorrectly appear.  No region is currently impacted. According to Epic searches, no region is using the affected print group. \r\nNCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, Exempla, and CO could be potentially impacted if they implement the affected print group without installing the fix.','','A partial workaround for SP\"07 and later is to set profile setting Drop discontinued medications immediately (I LPR 862) to Yes.  This setting will cause discontinued medications to immediately drop off of this print group, although expired medications will continue to incorrectly appear.  No region is currently impacted. According to Epic searches, no region is using the affected print group. \r\nNCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, Exempla, and CO could be potentially impacted if they implement the affected print group without installing the fix.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-29 04:34:00','2009-09-14 02:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(255,4064348,1,'RAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Radiant - In Basket Message Button can cause problems','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2008-12-29 00:00:00','2009-08-27 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Another EPIC customer','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'RAD','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I7511602\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758483 & C75031358\nRISK RANKING:  9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/27/09: 8/27/2009:  per C. Burke, fix installed, verfied.  Closing.','Using the In Basket Message button (available in Study Review or the Begin/End Exam Navigator toolbars) may cause the following two problems:\r\n\r\nFor SP\"08 only: An In Basket message sent via the IB Message button may be incorrectly retracted at signing time (when the study moves to the 99-Final status). \r\nFor all releases:  In Basket messages (e.g., to report abnormal cases) sent via the IB Message button may not reach other providers as intended if those providers are not using In Basket (e.g., lack In Basket security).  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/18/09: Confirm with C. Burke if ok to close.  08/10/09: Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\nFor condition #1: SU\"09 DLG 147900 fixes the issue related to the incorrectly retracted messages at signing time. A fix for SP\"08 will be developed.\r\nFor conditon #2: Fixes for SP\"06, SP\"07, and SP\"08 will be developed.\r\n','No work around since no regions are currently impacted; Epic searches revealed that no regions have patients affected by either condition.\r\nNW, HI, NCAL, and GA could be potentially impacted if they rely on the In Basket message button to send messages and do not implement the fix.',NULL,'No work around since no regions are currently impacted; Epic searches revealed that no regions have patients affected by either condition.\r\nNW, HI, NCAL, and GA could be potentially impacted if they rely on the In Basket message button to send messages and do not implement the fix.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-12-29 04:46:00','2009-08-27 01:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(256,4078284,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'KPHC - Potential Patient Safety - Meds w/Continuous Frequency as Default and a Specific Duration calculating End Time incorrect',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pharmacy,  ED, OpTime, Beaxcon','E758317/ C75031323','',NULL,'2008-12-30 14:09:49','2008-12-30 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Another EPIC client',NULL,NULL,'4653','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SCAL created adhoc','0303-PS-PR4078284-E758317-C75031323-Spr07Mar16NS.tar.Z\r\n0303-PS-PR4078284-E758317-C75031323-Spr07Mar16NS.zip,  and more\r\n ','K031609',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3','M',NULL,'DEC08','N','S','R','B',' ','Y','S',NULL,'Clo',NULL,NULL,NULL,'M','N','Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',60,'2009-06-23 09:02:16',NULL,'End User Applications','PART KPHC','NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609; NCAl found problem with fix\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511444\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4653):  \n  SP’07 E758317/ C75031323 3/03/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609\nRISK RANKING:  4','KPHC Epic Environment','Patient Safety Issue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7/1: Per Doris Lew, validated in production; close this issue in PMO.','KPHC - Potential Patient Safety - Meds w/Continuous Frequency as Default and a Specific Duration calculating End Time incorrect. Chris from Epic reporting issue.  Per Chris, Medications with a default frequency of continuous and a specific duration will incorrectly calculate the end time using the orderded time instead of due time.  This issue affects IP, AMB and ED.  This issue was identified by another Epic customer.  Location and Contact information verified.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/2: 6/17/09 install\r\nPer Doris Lew, working with testing to close defect and get code installed in NCAL ASAP. Requires outage.PROD install targeting 6/17/09. Workaround & remediation not needed.4/8: Per TSharkey, TD34898 functioning as expected--refer to Doris Lew (KP)\r\n3/30: Per Alex testing failed waiting to hear back from EPIC (Chris Russell).TD34898. Not fixed yet.\r\n3/3/:  fix has arrived.  Workaround not in place-Andre to F/U-Remediation determined after workaround status.2/23: Workaround not in place-Andre to F/U-Remediation determined after workaround status.\r\nChris emailed PART on 2/4; fix SU is still under development.Chris will send update email; update from SCAL has not been received.1/5:  Andre Mure confirmed receiving Epic query.  Urgent Mitigation: Review Epic query to determine if any medication orders on currently admitted patients require adjustments to end date/time.\r\nQueries to be reviewed to determine if there are currently admitted patients who have orders that might require adjustments to end times.','Until the fix is installed, any of the following workarounds may be used:\r\nChange the build so that medications orders are not defaulted with a continuous frequency (not operationally feasible, however).\r\nHave end users verify that the due time is appropriate based on the start and end times for the order.  If there?s a problem, the user can deselect and reselect the appropriate frequency.  This will reset the start date/time and due time appropriately (not airtight).\r\nDo not implement the System Definitions setting option Delay on initial order scheduling.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, and Exempla will consider these workarounds and implement the second option until the ad hoc fix is available.\r\n',NULL,'Until the fix is installed, any of the following workarounds may be used:\r\nChange the build so that medications orders are not defaulted with a continuous frequency (not operationally feasible, however).\r\nHave end users verify that the due time is appropriate based on the start and end times for the order.  If there?s a problem, the user can deselect and reselect the appropriate frequency.  This will reset the start date/time and due time appropriately (not airtight).\r\nDo not implement the System Definitions setting option Delay on initial order scheduling.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, and Exempla will consider these workarounds and implement the second option until the ad hoc fix is available.\r\n',NULL,'Chris Russell sent query results to PART',NULL,'1230765161ï££D111116ï££Resolution Action:  Upgraded Application\nResolution Description:  \nCause Code 1:  Business Partner\nCause Code 2:  \nCause Description:  ï£¢',NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-01 11:20:00','2009-07-01 03:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(258,4111120,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Clarity - Reports/Extracts may be Missing Data due to Batch Audit Closing Error under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-12 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Colorado region: (Ed Kraynak, Linda F Young)',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','115-AP-PR2724897-C75031236-Spr07Jan19NS.zip   \r\n','K011909',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'JAN09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4563):  \n  SP’07 C75031236 1/15/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K011909\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/15: closed PR. No response from Amy Waldman; advised her that the issue would be closed.','This is an AMB work flow.  Clarity reporting and or extracts may be missing data due to a flagging error in closing out the audit batches program.  Extracts for CarePoint and other applications, created on a daily basis, are impacted which may impact patient safety.  Specific workflows are being identified by Epic to determine which tables are impacted.\r\nSample impacted workflows may be where a user is:\r\nIn a patient\"s workspace and linking an Encounter to an Episode\r\nAfter linking the encounter, they may continue to work in that episode (e.g. problem list)\r\nWhich may result in certain records not being flagged for extracts to Clarity, then to other applications such as Carepoint.\r\nOnce the user accesses another patient or another activity (e.g. allergies), any other data will get  correctly flagged for extract.\r\nInstallation of SU C7503131 code caused the problem.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/2: Helen sent an email to Amy Waldman to confirm resolution; Amy is OOTO until 6/8.\r\nCode fix C75031236, I7511230 was installed in prod on 4/1/09 as dependency code for E-Signature.  Verify with Clarity if Corrected. \r\n2/26: The code was installed into WITS2 as a dependency of the Orders Rec code.  At the point AMB is saying they are not impacted by this issue.  However, if the need arises for testing the code has been installed.\r\nTheresa Alexander to contact Melanie Grange and Kieu Truong to see if this was replicated.\r\nPatient Safety to forward incident to Clifford Holchuck and get status; check with Sharon and Byron to see if there is any info from EPIC. Regional Clarity leads on Data Integrity Calls will receive communication from Colorado (Ed Kraynak) and Epic (Andrea Williams) as to which tables are affected by this incident.\r\nUrgent Mitigation  \r\nRegional Clarity leads on Data Integrity Calls will receive communication from Colorado (Ed Kraynak) and Epic (Andrea Williams) as to which tables are affected by this incident.  \r\nProviders will receive a communication from CarePoint regional contacts (Tanya Bonelli/National Carepoint will assist with the communication) that data in CarePoint may be incomplete.\r\nEach potentially impacted region (NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, Exempla, CO, GA, OH, and MAS) will be able to research and mitigate any reported data from tables with errors.\r\nEpic (Andrea Williams) will provide the specific workflows that create the problem to PART and for the potentially impacted regions.\r\nFix\r\nThere is a fix currently available for SP\"07 IU3 (C75031236).\r\nImpacted regions should load the fix.\r\nImpacted regions may work with their Regional Epic TS to perform full extracts on those tables back to when each region converted to SP\"07 SU C7503131.\r\nOnce tables are refreshed, extracts in Carepoint and other applications may be created to ensure they receive the correct records. \r\nAn ad hoc code fix authorization (4563) has been requested and provided by Colorado (Ed Kraynak).\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, regions are advised to implement the fix when available.\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-12 03:18:00','2009-06-16 10:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(259,4106006,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Medications mixtures ordered in an outpatient setting may be incorrect.','','',NULL,NULL,'InPatient, AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-12 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'EPIC: Kristie Reimer','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511595\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758686\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/2009:  per Cheryl Tran, not applicable, can close.  CLOSING','Ordering a mixture in an Inpatient setting, using the Discharge Navigator for Ambulatory mixture and administration, or outpatient setting (e.g., when an Inpatient patient is discharged, or by normal Order Entry via database lookup) may lead to incomplete or inaccurate mixture prescriptions being printed, sent, or mixed. Specifically, these mixture orders would not specify dilution solutions or volume for dilutions.The Inpatient variation will only occur for mixtures to be mixed and/or administered in an Outpatient setting. \r\n\r\nBecause Ambulatory KP Pharmacies do not process mixture orders for outpatient use -- and would reject such an order as incorrect and incomplete -- this issue is not considered a patient safety risk.  Mixture orders could, however, be processed as a Back Office or Ambulatory Procedure administration, by nurses or physicians, but because the order is incomplete, it could not be mixed or administred, until clarified.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: 8/10:  fix is part of May 2009 k-package\r\nRebecca Blair will get an update on 1/28/09.\r\nWaiting for KPKG.Epic (Kristie Reimer) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its status by ... To prevent any future impact, regions are advised to implement the fix when available.\r\nHistorical Remediation:\r\nEpic (Kristie Reimer) has identified mixture orders that were ordered in an outpatient setting in the last month for each region.  Pharmacy (Kirk Ryan, Anthony E Villanueva, and Rizwan Qureshi) have reviewed these results and have determined that there were no valid prescriptions that would have been filled by Pharmacy.\r\n','Not needed, since these mixture orders, in an outpatient setting, could not be mixed or dispensed.\r\n','','Not needed, since these mixture orders, in an outpatient setting, could not be mixed or dispensed.\r\n',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-12 03:51:00','2009-09-08 10:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(261,4111680,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Interaction warnings may not display when ordering mixtures in an outpatient setting.','','',NULL,NULL,'Inpatient, Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-12 00:00:00','2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'EPIC Kristie Reimer','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'2',NULL,NULL,'JAN09','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511595\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758686\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/01/09--per JDee/AMB, fix was installed 8/19, ok to close. CLOSING','When ordering mixtures in an outpatient setting, interaction warnings may not display (Drug/Drug, Drug/Allergy, Dose Alerts) to the user. (This is somewhat related to the \"Mixtures in an outpatient setting\" issue previously escalated under SLG 335786, PART Incident #4106006, but should be considered as a separate issue).  \r\nA user may place such medication orders in the Inpatient Discharge Navigator or by normal EpicCare Order Entry via database or preference list lookup.\r\nSample Workflow Example:\r\nA patient is ordered to receive Ampicillin 2g in Sodium Chloride 0.9% 100ml in an ambulatory setting.\r\nThe user may expect to get a drug-drug interaction warning for Ampicillin and/or Penicillin.\r\nHowever, in this case, the interaction warning may not appear.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/04/09: 5/26: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).\r\n3/30: Per Rebecca currently testing SU version, then SP07 and SP08 will be tested.  Testing s/b completed 4/27.\r\nWaiting for Kpkg-fix still in development. 3/18: per Joyce Yamamoto--Amb is not impacted by this issue. 2/26: is a workaround needed?  per Johnette Dee, AMB will wait for KPKG \r\n(1/28) Andre to review - adhoc or kpkg. PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. To prevent any future impact, regions are advised to implement the fix when available.\r\n','Epic (Kristie Reimer) has provided a one line order validation programming point that can be plugged into users? profiles to warn/hard stop them any time they are ordering a mixture in an outpatient setting. This could be used to alert providers that interaction checking is not functioning and orders should be checked for allergy, dosing, or potential Drug/Drug interactions.\r\nCreate a programming point with type = 38 ? Order Validation\r\n\r\nEpic (Kristie Reimer) has performed searches and identified any mixture orders that were ordered in an outpatient setting, in the last month, for each region.  Not all of these orders would necessarily have triggered an interaction warning. A clinician may review these orders to determine if potential interactions exist.','','Epic (Kristie Reimer) has provided a one line order validation programming point that can be plugged into users? profiles to warn/hard stop them any time they are ordering a mixture in an outpatient setting. This could be used to alert providers that interaction checking is not functioning and orders should be checked for allergy, dosing, or potential Drug/Drug interactions.\r\nCreate a programming point with type = 38 ? Order Validation\r\n\r\nEpic (Kristie Reimer) has performed searches and identified any mixture orders that were ordered in an outpatient setting, in the last month, for each region.  Not all of these orders would necessarily have triggered an interaction warning. A clinician may review these orders to determine if potential interactions exist.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-12 04:19:00','2009-09-01 12:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(263,4126761,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Immunization Interaction Alerts may not Fire When Masterfile Records and Programming Point Configuration are Incomplete','','',NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, Pharmacy, OpTime, Radiant, EpicRx, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-16 00:00:00','2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JAN09','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512056\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758679\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/01/09--per JDee/AMB, fix was installed 8/19, ok to close. CLOSING','Alerts may not be working as expected and a clinician may be unaware that a patient is allergic to all or part of a vaccine, which may impact patient care.Immunization interactions aren\"t common and a clinician may check previously documented allergies, or a clinician may check with patients and document known allergies when ordering or administering an immunization.\r\nFeatures:   Immunization Interaction Alerts - Order validation programming point record 3810-Order/Allergen Check.\r\nImproperly configured immunizations may cause interaction alerts not to fire upon ordering. Although there are cases where a region may choose not to fire interaction alerts, immunizations interaction alerts will not fire if a programming point record is not set up or configuration outside the immunization record is overlooked.\r\nPrior to SP\"07, an immunization\"s interaction alerts are configured in the procedure record linked to the immunization. To see the alerts, order validation programming point record 3810-Order/Allergen Check must be set up in a user?s profile. However, this additional setup is not required for medication interaction alerts. \r\n\r\nIn SP\"07, a new immunization interaction checking feature was introduced where immunization interaction alerts could be configured by listing the immunization in the medication record for the injection. However, this step in immunization build requires configuration outside of the immunization record. If this didn\"t occur, the interaction alerts may not fire.\r\nTwo regions (SCAL & GA) have been identified as having implemented the recommended programming point.  However, additional queries of masterfile records indicate that interaction alerts may still not be firing as expected because specified items in EAP and ERX records are not populated (EAP item 10150 and ERX item 34550).  Incompletely configured EAP and ERX records may also result in interaction alerts not firing for immunizations, even in regions that have not yet implemented the recommended programming point in SP\"07.\r\nThis issue primarily affects the Ambulatory application.  Inpatient immunization orders are submitted using the ERX record which does not result in this problem.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'07/20/09: 7/20: Per S. Balicanta\'s 7/17 email, \"No we are not configuring EAP or ERX at this time because per EPIC, the alert does not fire at all without the prog. point.\"\r\n7/7: per Sandra F, the config build is \"Not completed yet\".\r\n6/19: per D. Heckel\'s 6/11 email to R. Blair: The regions will need to do config work to protect themselves from potential impact. The \"fix\" is to build out the functionality completely. All this SU does is hopefully to make that config build easier. The regions can begin build at anytime. Once they install the SU, they can use the new development to more easily complete the build\r\n6/9:Rebecca to f/up with Dustin (Epic) on 6/10 re status of configuration. \r\n5/26: per Rebecca in May KPKG; DavidO to f/up with Johnette--is data config complete?\r\n4/6: Johnette to check with Sandra re status of data config; is it complete?\r\n3/30: Tom S. to send PART email to Andrea and Adam Huffman; are we waiting for KPKG or building out code?\r\nAdam talked to Sandra Francisco; need to check w/clinicians to see if they want to build out code fix and config. Rebecca to get update from Derek and Dustin.ETA 3/13. Patient Safety will forward the incident to Jansin, copy Sandra Francisco; has EPIC tech support contacted Jansin?  1/26:  Epic AMB TS haven\'t heard from ACs at NCAL about the prog point config. Adam will f/up with his contacts re: this setup.','Potentially impacted regions will communicate to clinicians that complete interaction checking may not be occuring, particularly Pediatric Infectious Disease physicians, and should consult with clinicians and pharmacy to determine a workaround. HI and OH have developed supplemental workflows to augment interaction checking. All other regions will develop a communication to clinicians.\r\nPopulating EAP item 10150 and ERX item 34550 may be considered as a short term mitigation  \r\nAll regions have indicated that they will work with their EPIC TS to review their build configuration and complete the build of specified mastefile records.','','Potentially impacted regions will communicate to clinicians that complete interaction checking may not be occuring, particularly Pediatric Infectious Disease physicians, and should consult with clinicians and pharmacy to determine a workaround. HI and OH have developed supplemental workflows to augment interaction checking. All other regions will develop a communication to clinicians.\r\nPopulating EAP item 10150 and ERX item 34550 may be considered as a short term mitigation  \r\nAll regions have indicated that they will work with their EPIC TS to review their build configuration and complete the build of specified mastefile records.',NULL,'Epic (Derek Heckel) is developing a fix to address immunization interaction checking configuration to prompt AC\"s to complete the build of specified masterfile records and the recommended linkages.  This code fix will not automatically complete the build of records and linkages.  Recommended configuration and build changes must still be completed by AC\"s.\r\nEpic will provide an update about the code fix for SP\"07 and the KPackage availability by 1/30/09.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-19 07:55:00','2009-09-01 12:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(264,4138798,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT Printed Med Reconciliation Reports may not display leading zeroes for dose and rate values less than 1','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Thomas Sharkey)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No longer an issue for KP since only impacts SP08 and will be fixed in SU09l; therefore closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I767325\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, SP08 only, does not affect SP07, fixed in SU09.  ','Per Doris Lew pharmacy uses print group 49237. Medication reconciliation print groups 49243-Rx Med Reconciliation IP Transfer Meds (Rich Text) and 49237-Rx Med Reconciliation IP Discharge Meds (Rich Text) may not display leading zeros for dose and rate values less than one (1) in printed reports (e.g.- patient charts).  For example, 0.5 mg appears as .5 mg, which may be confusing for a user and result in 5 mg being entered with an order instead of .5 mg.\r\n\r\nThese print groups are contained in Epic \"canned\" reports: 49304 and 49306 but are also included in NCAL and SCAL Clinical Downtime Reports and may be included in other Inpatient regional reports.  Inclusion of a leading \"0\" for medication dosages with values less than 1 is a Joint Commission on Accreditation of Healthcare Organizations (JCAHO) requirement. \r\n\r\nThis issue was originally reported by EPIC as affecting all releases from SU\"05 through SP\"08.  The original clinical assessment was Severe, Rare, and Broad.  Subsequent investigation by EPIC revealed that this issue only affects SP\"08.  This revision in affected releases was reported by EPIC at the time when regions (NCAL, SCAL, HI, Exempla, and NW) were contacted, based on the original assessment and the understanding that our current SP\"07 release was affected.  Revision of the clinical assessment occured during discussion of this incident with the Regional PART teams.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Tom Sharkey) will provide an update about the code fix for SP\"08 and the KPackage availability by 1/30/09.PART Communications (Sharon Carroll) will communicate code fix and KPackage delivery, to the impacted regions (NCAL, SCAL, NW, Exempla, and HI).\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings and distributed monthly to all PART regional teams.   \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. ','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 10:42:00','2009-07-22 01:49:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(265,4140398,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Custom Alert Rules may not be recognized as being Custom','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'indirectly: Inpatient, Ambulatory, Beacon, ED, and OpTime module','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Michael Bries)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Not an issue for us.  Only impacts SP08; standard in SU09; closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I767215\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, affects SP08, fixed in SU09',' In Sp\"08, it may be possible for either of the following two things to occur:\r\nDose checking, pregnancy, or lactation RXR records that have previously been customized may be overwritten by the medication load of records from the medication vendor.  When this occurs, alerts are still triggered correctly according to vendor data.  However, there may be customized alerts, which may be triggered for additional conditions that aren\"t covered by the vendor data.  In this case, these extra customized alerts may not be triggered as expected.\r\nMore than one custom dose checking custom pregnancy or custom lactation RXR record of the same type may be created with the same external identifier.  In this case, only the custom record with the lower .1 will be used in the system, so any conditions specified in the RXR record with the higher .1 may not be triggered (unless they also happen to be in the RXR record with the lower .1).\r\n\r\nBoth issues can occur only if a custom RXR rule has more than one contact marked as custom (RXR item 70 is set to Yes).  If a custom rule in which only one contact is marked exists as custom, the problem can\"t happen until another contact is marked as custom as well.\r\n\r\nIn SP\"08, RXR records can be any of the following types:\r\nDose Check\r\nDuplicate Therapy Check\r\nPregnancy Alerts Check\r\nLactation Alerts Check\r\nPrecautions Check (only Medi-Span, so N/A)\r\nDrug-Disease Check\r\nAge/Gender Check\r\n\r\nOnly Dose Check, Pregnancy alerts, Lactation alerts, and Precautions may have custom contacts that are impacted by this incident.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix (I767215) as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status. PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. \r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-22 09:02:00','2009-07-22 01:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(266,4140430,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Dose Rounding Warning may not fire in Verification for Mixtures','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Michael Bries)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511686\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758543\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/2009:  per Cheryl Tran, not applicable, can close.  CLOSING','If using the before verification programming point record 84710 - Ord Val Before Verify - Check for Dose Warnings (or a copy of it) in Pharmacy System Definitions, the warning may not appear for mixture components that have been rounded by more than 10% (regardless of whether the programming point record is configured as a hard stop).  The warning appears for the overall ordered dose if the overall dose (as opposed to mixture components) has been rounded by more than 10%. \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: 8/10:  fix in May 2009 K-package\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. \r\n','','','',NULL,'No regions are currently impacted, as the programming point is not being used.  However, any regions that are considering implementing the affected functionality could be potentially impacted in the future.   ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-22 09:13:00','2009-09-08 10:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(267,4140450,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Orders without Phase of Care specified may be discontinued on transfer','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'IP, ED, OpTime, and Beacon','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Michael Bries)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No longer an issue for KP since only impacts SP08 and will be fixed in SU09; closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I768445\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED--affects SP08 only, fixed in SU09 ','Programming point record 34711 - IP Auto DC at Transfer by Dept may be copied and configured to automatically discontinue specific orders during transfer.  In SP\"08, a new optional parameter was added to this programming point record to enable the Phase of Care (e.g. pre-op, post-op) to be used as one of the inputs of the programming point record logic.  If this option is used, orders without Phases of Care specified may be discontinued.\r\n\r\nIn the programming point record configuration, the phases of care variable (%PocC) contains two pieces of data delimited by a caret: a list of phases of care IDs, and a flag to indicate if the order should be included or excluded if it has one of the phases of care specified.\r\n\r\nFor example, if the copy of programming point record 34711 is configured as follows:\r\n	s %frq=1--1-, %EAP=100500, %PoC=\" 10;50;60^2\" d TrfrAct^JORDTRFR\r\nThe first caret-delimited piece of the %PoC indicates that the phases of care IDs of interest are 10, 50, and 60.  The second piece (the value 2) indicates that this parameter is being used as an exclusion list -i.e., any order that has one of the Phases of Care specified will not be discontinued during the transfer.\r\n\r\nThis issue occurs when the second caret-delimited piece of the %PoC variable isn\"t set to 2, which indicates that any order with one of the specified phases of care IDs will be discontinued during transfer.  When configured in this manner, in addition to discontinuing orders with the specified Phases of Care, it also discontinues all orders that don\"t have a Phase of Care specified.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Michael Bries) will provide a code fix  as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available.','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-22 09:25:00','2009-07-22 01:45:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(268,4140420,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - A printed MAR may display current orders as future orders','','',NULL,NULL,'IP and ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Michael Bries)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511339\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809- E758609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/2009:  per Cheryl Tran, not applicable, can close.  CLOSING','A printed MAR (Medication Administration Report) may use print group 45119-IP PRINTED MAR2 (Rich Text) or a copy of this print group to display information in two shifts per day.  If the print group is configured for two shifts per day, current orders may display as future orders during the second shift.  When the orders are marked as future orders, a message stating \"Future Med-Do not Administer\" may appear.  This occurs for orders that don\"t have a due time during the second shift.  This doesn\"t affect orders for the first shift.\r\n\r\nThree statements describing the parameter configuration for print group 45119-IP PRINTED MAR2 (Rich Text) or its copy must be true for the incident to occur:\r\n\r\nParameter 3, which controls how many days the MAR will display, is set to 1.\r\nParameter 7, which determines how the shifts will be displayed, is set to either 1 or 3, and the department for the patient being viewed is configured to have two shifts. This means that either there are two shifts listed in the department record in item DEP 24001 or that item is blank and there are two shifts listed in System Definitions in item LSD 34550.\r\nParameter 24, which controls the message displayed on the MAR for future medications, is set to 3.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: fix in May 2009 K-package\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. ','','','',NULL,'No regions are currently impacted, as none are configured with two shifts per day.  However, any regions (NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, and HI) that are considering implementing the affected functionality could be potentially impacted in the future. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-22 09:33:00','2009-09-08 10:45:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(269,4140388,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - NoteWriter Annotated Images may not display correctly','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, IP, Anesthesia, and OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-21 00:00:00','2009-09-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Danielle Dyer)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I768348, I7512051\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-C75031374\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/10/2009:  per A. Mure, fix in prod, can\'t certify.  CLOSING','When the same annotated image appears in both the Physical Exam SmartBlock AND a custom SmartForm in NoteWriter, annotations entered in one location can shift position or disappear altogether when viewing the image from the other location.  The annotations may appear to be lost or be associated with the incorrect part of the image.\r\n\r\nAn Epic query of KP environments indicates that no regions are currently using the same image in both a Physical Exam SmartBlock AND a custom SmartForm in NoteWriter. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: 8/10:  fix in May 2009 K-package\r\nRemove custom SmartForms or remove the images from the affected SmartForms.  Instruct all users to perform all annotation in the Physical Exam SmartBlock  .Epic (Danielle Dyer) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. ','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-22 09:43:00','2009-09-10 10:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(270,4154344,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Beacon  - Dosing calculations of order-specific dosing weight will not propagate, in specific workflow','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-26 00:00:00','2009-09-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Kristie Reimer)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'BCON','N','S','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511600\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809 -E758447\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/17/2009:  per Dorina Wong / Evelyn: fix certified, OK to close.  CLOSING','With enhanced weight-based dosing enabled, dosing calculations of order-specific dosing weight will not propagate with weight or BSA (body surface area) values in Beacon treatment plans if the following uncommon workflow is used:\r\nOpen a Beacon treatment plan with at least two occurrences of the same weight-based dosed medication (medication order A and medication order B).\r\nWith medication order A, select a dosing weight type of \"order specific\" and enter a value (Cyclophosphamide with an \"Order-specific\" BSA of 2 m2).  \r\nDo not propagate these dosing options to medication B on the pop-up window that appears. \r\nWith medication order B, select a different dosing weight type such as Treatment Plan, Actual, Ideal, or Adjusted (Cyclophosphamide withActualselected as the weight type which has a BSA of 1.82 m2).  \r\nAgain, do not propagate these options to medication A on the pop-up window that appears.\r\nReturn to medication order A and change the weight value to Order-specific.  \r\nPropagate the change to medication order B on the pop-up window that appears.	\r\nMedication order B will have the weight value from medication order A but will still have the original dosing weight type from step 3.  (Cyclophosphamide which has a BSA of 2.1 m2 but with Actual still selected as the weight type).  \r\nThe  BSA of 2.1 is propagated from the first Cyclophosphamide to the second Cyclophosphamide order, but the weight type of Actual is still selected.\r\nIf the user signs medication order B, the weight value in the summary sentence will be saved \r\n     (Actual).  If the user leaves the treatment plan without signing and then reopens the treatment\r\n     plan, medication order B will have the original weight value and weight type prior to change\r\n     propagation (Cyclophosphamide with Actual selected as the weight type which has a BSA of\r\n    1.82 m2). ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/14/09: T. Stewart sent detail to D. Wong on 9/11; D. Wong will have testing done.  08/18/09: Confirm with K. Ryan if ok to close.\r\n08/10/09: 8/10:  fix in May 2009 K-package\r\nPer Kirk Ryan, adhoc not needed.  Waiting for 05/09 K-pckg.  An ad hoc code fix was not deemed necessary by Beacon AC Kirk Ryan.\r\nEpic (Kristie Reimer) ran searches at NCAL to find any affected OTP records which have not been released.  No affected records were found.\r\n2/23:  workaround needed? checking with kirk.\r\n','Manually update orders with order-specific weight values instead of using change propagation.  \r\n','','Manually update orders with order-specific weight values instead of using change propagation.  \r\n',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-27 11:29:00','2009-09-17 10:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(271,4157810,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Unexpected default values might appear for Outpatient medications in user Order Sets','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, OpTime  ','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-27 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'N/A','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SIGS','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511576 \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809 -E758482\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/09: per Sherry Ellis + Doris Lew--don\'t use discreet sigs, can close.  CLOSING','With user-customized versions of Order Sets, user-specified values for default frequency or default dose for outpatient medications may not be respected.  As a result, the following may occur:\r\nWhen the custom Order Set is opened, orders not selected may appear with the user-specified defaults ;\r\nWhen the user selects a medication, the configured ERX-level defaults for frequency and/or dose information is used instead of what the user specified.\r\n\r\nThe problem occurs if all of the following conditions are in place:\r\nProtocol-based (PRL) Order Sets and Discrete Sigs are turned on.\r\nThe order is for an outpatient medication. \r\nThe medication (ERX) record is configured with a specified outpatient default frequency or an outpatient default dose.\r\nThe Allow Non-Discrete Sigs field is set to Yes in the medication record.\r\nThe base Order Set does not have a frequency or dose specified. \r\nThe user override Order Set has a frequency or dose that differs from the medication record defaults. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: Confirm with B. Yee if ok to close.\r\n08/10/09: fix in May 2009 K-packg.  No Current Impact--Discrete Sigs  \r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent future impact, regions are advised to implement the fix when it becomes available. ','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-27 03:33:00','2009-09-08 03:17:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(272,4165296,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'No Current Impact - Pharmacy - Table mixtures (using tablets or caplets) may use dispense rounding factors to calculate a higher dose than expected','','',NULL,NULL,'IP','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-29 00:00:00','2009-09-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Lara Ebert)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511811\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758630\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/08/2009:  per Cheryl Tran, not applicable, can close.  CLOSING','A component\'s dispense rounding factor is used when calculating the dose for a mixture component.  The administration rounding factor is used for simple meds (a medication that is just one medication). If mixtures are created on the fly, using tablets or caplets (or other solid state) mixtures (this issue does NOT involve solution mixtures), the calculation may result in a nurse administering more medication than intended. \r\n \r\nFor example:\r\nA user may create a mixture record for PREMPRO, which contains 0.625 mg of estrogen, and 2.5 mg of medroxyPROGESTERone, per dose. \r\nEach component is configured the following way:  \r\nestrogen >> 0.625 mg = 1 tab, the admin rounding factor is 0.5 tab, and the dispense rounding factor is 1 tab.\r\nmedroxyPROGESTERone >> 10 mg = 1 tab, the admin rounding factor is 0.25 tab, and the dispense rounding factor is 1 tab.\r\nWhen the mixture is ordered, the order dose for each component is 0.625 mg and 2.5 mg respectively. However, in Order Entry, the calculated dose for the medroxyPROGESTERone is 10 mg instead of 2.5 mg. The system would dispense 1 tab of medroxyPROGESTERone instead of a 1/4 tab.\r\n\r\nWhile the ordered dose for each component would be correct, the MAR might indicate that both tabs should be administered.  \r\n\r\nThe provider may not be aware that the 10 mg should be cut into quarters to administer 2.5 mg instead of 10 mg.\r\n\r\nKP National Pharmacy confirms that regions do not create tablet or capsule mixture records or \"on the fly\" mixtures using capsules or tablets.  An EPIC query confirmed that no such mixtures exist in KP Production environments.  This issue can also occur if ERX capsule or tablet mixtures are built, or if IMS (Intelligent Medication Selection) is enabled.  KP does not have any of these type ERX records and IMS is not currently enabled. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: fix in May 2009 K-package\r\nEpic (Lara Ebert) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record fix information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this fix when it becomes available. \r\n','Don\'t create ERX mixture records using caplets or tablets. If they are built, the dispense rounding factor should be equal to or less than the administration rounding factor. \r\nDon\'t create \"on the fly\" mixtures using tablets or capsules.','','Don\'t create ERX mixture records using caplets or tablets. If they are built, the dispense rounding factor should be equal to or less than the administration rounding factor. \r\nDon\'t create \"on the fly\" mixtures using tablets or capsules.',NULL,'No current impact as none of the potentially impacted regions (NW, HI, NCAL, SCAL, and Exempla) create mixtures using Tablets or Caplets (not solutions) \"on the fly\" and there are no such ERX mixture records in KP Production environments.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-01-29 02:09:00','2009-09-08 10:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(273,4169692,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3516524,'IP Medications ordered from PRL Smart Sets or Preference Lists may be incorrectly marked as completed','','',NULL,NULL,'ClinCon, ED, Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-02 00:00:00','2009-09-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'EPIC','',NULL,'4705','','','','','','adhoc is for fix, in Mar kpkg','0414-PS-PR4169692-E758371-Spr07Mar16NS.tar.Z\r\n0310-NCAL-Spr07SLG347505.txt (this is prg pt w/a)','K031609','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'7',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','N','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511654\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4705):  \n  SP’07 E758371 4/14/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609-E758371\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/22/09: Per Doris Lew this issue can be closed;NCAL was never affected b/c there were no OTLs w/ the affected config.','With LGQ-based Smart Sets that have been converted to PRL (protocol-based structure), Inpatient medication orders that are placed from a Smart Set or a preference list, and are ordered as \"until discontinued,\" may instead appear as completed on the MAR as soon as they are ordered.    This occurs if the medication order meets all of the following conditions:\r\nInpatient ordering mode\r\n* Number of doses (I OTL 7210) = 0 \r\nFrequency has a type of PRN, Specified, or Non-specified\r\nNo default count or count type is specified at any level (OTL, EFQ, ERX)\r\n\r\nOnly medications with order frequencies of PRN (as needed) or scheduled doses are affected.  Medication orders with order frequencies of \"1 time\" or \"continuous\" are not affected.\r\n\r\n* The error occurs when the OTL 7210 item is set to 0.  It is probable that this setting is inadvertently changing during the PRL conversion itself, even though it has not been set to 0 during configuration. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/22/09: Per S. Ellis, Pharmacy should certify; Helen sent email to D. Lew on 9/22.\r\n09/15/09: Follow up email to S. Ellis on 9/15.\r\n08/18/09: Confirm with S. Ellis ok to close; cc B. Mattern.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (March-confirmed).\r\n6/9:  March kpkg, Aug \'09 install. Waiting for KPKG, willl not use adhoc.\r\n4/13: Tom S. to send email to Andrea; Andrea will then f/up with Aditi or Sherry Ellis. Pt Safety to forward adhoc to P. Lesperance and Chris Russell.\r\n4/6: Programming point will not be installed; waiting for adhoc.\r\n4/2:  Adhoc ?4705? requested.  Instructions for w/a received from Adam Huffman on 3/6. \r\n2/23: Dhea will check with Adam re: ETA for work around.Adam Huffman working with Epic (Kristie) regarding workaround\r\nEpic (Peter Lesperance) will  provide a code fix and notify PART by 2/13/09 of its status.\r\nPART Communications (Chris Okon) will notify impacted regions of the fix status.\r\n2/17:  Adam Huffman working with Epic (Kristie) regarding workaround\r\n4/2:  Per Dhea, adhoc needed.  Adhoc \'4705\' requested.','Regional Epic technical services representatives will:\r\nRun a utility to identify affected records;\r\nCreate an After Defaultingprogramming point that should identify templates with OTL item 7210 set to 0 and remove it.\r\nEPIC recommends pairing these workarounds and incorporating them as steps in the PRL conversion process.\r\n','','Regional Epic technical services representatives will:\r\nRun a utility to identify affected records;\r\nCreate an After Defaultingprogramming point that should identify templates with OTL item 7210 set to 0 and remove it.\r\nEPIC recommends pairing these workarounds and incorporating them as steps in the PRL conversion process.\r\n',NULL,'Epic Representative:  Peter Lesperance\r\nPhysician Representative:  Scott Adelman',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-02 04:29:00','2009-09-22 03:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(274,4177492,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Beacon  - Modified Beacon treatment plan orders may appear with inconsistent weight values','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-03 00:00:00','2009-09-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','','','','','','waiting for K pckg','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'BCON','Y','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511732\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758573\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/17/2009:  per Dorina Wong / Evelyn: fix certified, OK to close.  CLOSING','With enchanced weight-based dosing enabled (LSD 7620 = Yes), modified Beacon treatment plan orders may display inconsistent dosing weight or BSA values. The problem occurs with the following workflow:\r\nRelease a weight or BSA based dosed medication order from a Beacon treatment plan.\r\nModify the released medication from either the medications activity, order review, or an active orders navigator section.\r\nOpen the Order Composer and change the weight type.\r\nClose and then reopen the order composer.  The weight type buttons, summary sentence weight type caption, and dose calculation change to the non-Treatment Plan (TP) weight type values.  The weight value selected is different from the weight value in the summary sentence and dose calculation.\r\n\r\nThis is a display issue only; actual calculations are not affected.\r\nNote: SP\'08 SU - I767050/C7600641 distinguishes weight type buttons for treatment plan weights from \"TP\".  Without the special update installed, these buttons would appear the same as the non-treatment plan weight buttons and may not be detected by the user, although the weight value would still appear changed.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/14/09: T. Stewart sent detail to D. Wong on 9/11; D. Wong will have testing done.  08/18/09: Confirm with K. Ryan if ok to close.\r\n08/10/09: fix in May 2009 K-package\r\nEpic (Liz Nickels) will provide a fix and notify PART of its status by 2/23/09.  An ad hoc code fix was not requested, per NCAL (Kirk Ryan).','Do not modify treatment plan orders.  Instead, discontinue released orders, enter a new medicaton order from the treatment plan, and release the new order. \r\nPer Kirk Ryan, NCAL will implement the workaround until the fix is installed.','','Do not modify treatment plan orders.  Instead, discontinue released orders, enter a new medicaton order from the treatment plan, and release the new order. \r\nPer Kirk Ryan, NCAL will implement the workaround until the fix is installed.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-03 01:38:00','2009-09-17 10:28:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(276,4187411,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient - New Medication Reconciliaton feature  - Pharmacy changes to a medication during verification may not take effect',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rx','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-05 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'4614','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0216-AP-PR4187411-E758208-C75031304-Spr07Mar16NS.tar.Z\r\n0216-AP-PR4187411-E758208-C75031304-Spr07Mar16NS.zip','K031609',NULL,'2009-04-08 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  SP07 I7510974; SP08  I766660 (E761467/C7600490)\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4614):  \n  SP’07 C75031304 & E758208 2/16/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Adhoc Code installed into NCAL PROD on 4/8/09 and validated. (E758208, C75031304, DLG I7510974) ','Changes that a pharmacist makes to a medication during verification may not be saved if at the same time another user has opened a Medication Reconciliation Navigator with a Review Prior to Admission section for the patient.  The problem occurs as long as the Med Rec Navigator is open, even if no activity occurs.  In addition, the pharmacist and the other user are not aware of the other\'s actions.  The affected fields are Product, Dose, Route, Frequency, Start Date, or End Date.\r\nMost medication changes made at pharmacy verification are should not prevent the patient from receiving the correct medication. \r\nFeatures:  New Medication Reconciliation functionality.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Adhoc created #4614.\r\nPer Dhea, adhoc is needed.InPatient is the owner.\r\nDiscuss whether NCAL will pursue an adhoc or wait for Kpkg.  \r\n3/23:  passed CAB, ready for install 4/8','Close the Navigator when not in use (not airtight)',NULL,'Close the Navigator when not in use (not airtight)',NULL,'Epic (Maria Spinozzi) will provide a SP\'07 code fix (I7510974) and notify PART by 2/20/09.\r\nAn ad hoc code fix was tentatively authorized by NW (Nick Socotch).\r\nDiscovered by:  Another Epic customer.\r\nEpic Representative:  Maria Spinozzi\r\nPhysician Representative:  Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-05 02:03:00','2009-04-24 03:26:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(281,4161333,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3385384,'PRL Smart Group Order may result in inaccurate \"Duplicate Order Pop-Up Error Message\" under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-05 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'SCAL (Tony Ahankoob)',NULL,NULL,'4630','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' cancelled','CHG000003385384 = RFC','Build Fix Only',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','Y','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'STANDARD IN RELEASE:  SUM09',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Build Fix only. Adhoc 4630 cancelled per Dhea.  No fix forthcoming.   Per Epic (KReimer), NCAL is not affected.','A \"Duplicate Order Pop-Up Error Message\" may occur upon loading of the order set (defaulting identical orders, e.g. nursing order - within a SmartGroup) if two conditions are active:\r\n1 - Ad hoc package (E757611/4508) for defects TD30624 and TD33511 was installed\r\nand\r\n2 - Have one or more of the following Inpatient duplicate intervals set to anything other than ?-1?: \r\nEAP 10120, EDP 10395, DEP 17225, or LSD 1661\r\n\r\nIf a user replies to the error message\'s resulting question \"Continue placing order?\" with a response of ?No?, the order doesn\'t get submitted and doesn\'t show on the patient\'s chart.\r\n\r\nOrders within a SmartGroup (OSQ) may share a generic EAP record with a custom display name. If in a SmartGroup for such orders, a user creates a User Version OrderSet and defaults the two or more orders with the identical EAP record, the \"pop- up\" will also occur in the base orderset if two or more orders are defaulted OR the user selects two or more orders, then the system displays a \"Duplicate Order Pop-Up Error Message\" and asks the question \"Continue placing order?\",  even though three unique tasks or \"orders\" are being placed by the user, the system is comparing the EAP IDs not the individual order details. If the user replies \'yes\', all orders will go through.  If the user replies \'no\', the order mentioned in the pop-up doesn\'t get submitted (the other order that shares the EAP will still be submitted) and doesn\'t show on the patient chart.   ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'There will not be a code fix, forthcoming.\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record this information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings and distributed monthly to all PART regional teams.   \r\nTo prevent any future impact, it would be proactive for all regions to implement this recommended fix . \r\nEpic (Kristie Reimer) recommends that impacted and potentially impacted regions implement the fix, which is to change or keep the appropriate configuration, since the OrderSet activity is correctly respecting the configuration.\r\n2/24:  NCAL does not meet condition 2.  Epic recommends that EAP 10120, EDP 10395, and DEP 17225 be set to null and LSD 1661 be set to ?-1?.  NCAL has the recommended setup and is therefore not affected.','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-05 02:21:00','2009-02-26 05:24:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(282,4188701,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Beacon - Copying and pasting discontinued treatment plan orders can result in unexpected End Date/Time','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-06 00:00:00','2009-09-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr.  Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'BCON','N','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511877\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809- E758666\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/17/2009:  per Dorina Wong / Evelyn: fix certified, OK to close.  CLOSING','End dates and times in Beacon treatment plans may display with unexpected values if the treatment plan order is copied and pasted after being released and then discontinued or completed.  This issue occurs only with PRN medications and is evident in two workflows:\r\n\r\nWorkflow 1\r\nSign and release a treatment plan order that has a PRN frequency and no end date (until discontinued) or specified duration.\r\nDiscontinue the order.\r\nCopy and paste the discontinued order to a future day or cycle in the treatment plan.\r\nOpen the Order Composer for the order. \r\nThe order will appear with an end date of ?S.?  Note: \"S\" means \"now\" and may be a valid value in other circumstances.\r\nThe error will be evident on day 1 of the treatment plan.\r\n\r\nWorkflow 2\r\nSign and release a treatment plan order that has a PRN frequency and no end date (until discontinued), and a specified number of doses.\r\nDocument administrations for the total amount of doses.  This will complete the order.\r\nCopy and paste the completed order to a future day or cycle in the treatment plan.\r\nOpen the Order Composer for the order.  \r\nThe copy will appear with a five-digit DTE number (internal date) as the end date.  If the order is released, the order will have no end date (until discontinued).\r\nThe error will be evident on the MAR.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/14/09: T. Stewart sent detail to D. Wong on 9/11; D. Wong will have testing done.  08/18/09: Confirm w/ K. Ryan ok to close.\r\n08/10/09: fix in May 2009 K-package\r\n5/8:  per Dorinda, No remediation is needed (affected orders were PRN)  4/1:  KR@Epic:  to rerun search, tell PART / Tom if recs remediated.  If not, Tom will forward to NCAL Beacon (Sheryl Balicanta):   2/6: Per Kirk Ryan, adhoc not requested.  F/U regarding remediation/workaround completion.\r\n2/27:  Lori Ridley or Loretta Allen - Waiting for response regarding remediation/workaround completion. PART to f/u with epic.','Review the end date and time before signing and releasing treatment plan orders.  \r\nIf the end date and time is incorrect, unselect and reselect the frequency to reset the end date and time.','','Review the end date and time before signing and releasing treatment plan orders.  \r\nIf the end date and time is incorrect, unselect and reselect the frequency to reset the end date and time.',NULL,'Features:  Treatment plans\r\nEpic (Kristie Reimer) ran regional searches and discoverd two affected records in NCAL.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-06 01:19:00','2009-09-17 10:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(298,4209504,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Last Reference Range for results may be Incorrect','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB, ED, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-13 00:00:00','2009-11-24 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Weisenthal ','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511834, I768289\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 C75031370 \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/24/09: Per B. Shepardson ok to close; not able to test in prod.','In the Results Review activity, an incorrect reference range may display when using the Ref Range button.  Pressing this button will display a row with the Latest Range for each result, however, if: \r\n1) There is more than one component record sharing the same common name\r\n2) Results for both components are displaying in the row\r\n3) The reference range has been changed from a previously configured reference range, \r\nan incorrect display of the Latest Rangemay occur. The reference range for an earlier component will be shown rather than the latest.  \r\nThe correct reference range for each result will still be displayed with that result, in the result detail pop up.  It may also be viewed in the status bar when hovering the mouse over the result.  The condensed and latest data views will also show the correct reference range. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/02/09: Per Y. Lassiter\'s 11/2 email, not yet tested in prod.\r\n10/20/09: Per Y. Lassiter, no update.\r\n10/06/09: Per Y. Lassister, still working on certifying install.\r\n09/29/09: Per Y. Lassiter\'s 9/29 email she is working on getting certification; scenario is difficult to set up.\r\n09/22/09: Yolanda to f/up.\r\n09/22/09: Per Bart\'s 9/15 email, T. Pratt followed up with Kristie Fowler of Epic; any update?\r\n09/15/09: Bart to f/up w/ A. Hoffman, T Pratt today.\r\n08/18/09: A. Thorup to f/up with A. Hoffman and Trevor Pratt.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed). No workaround needed. Per Bart Shepardson 2/20/09 no action required per Dr. Hoberman; known chronic problem, doesn\'t affect patient safety.\r\nSpecial Updates will be created to fix this issue.  Until the Special Update is installed, users may use the suggested workarounds listed above.\r\nEpic (Greg Hartman) and KP HealthConnect ACs and physicians recommend that impacted and potentially impacted regions implement workaround #1 listed above.\r\nRegions should confirm with PART which workaround they have implemented \r\nIf workaround #1 is selected, installation of a code fix is not required.  However, if in the future a region would like to use the reference range button, the fix should be implemented.  Epic will include the fix in an IU for SP\'08.\r\n2/26:  Suggested workaround is not acceptable-only workaround acceptable is clinician\'s knowledge (trust).\r\n','Disable the reference range button to NOT display (recommended airtight workaround)\r\nEach region may remove the Ref Range button by performing these steps:\r\n	A)  Duplicate E2U record 17471 into a record outside of the Epic release range (100,000+).\r\n	B)  Edit the duplicate record, and make the following changes:\r\na.	In the \"Overrides menu descriptor:\" field, enter \"MR_TB_RESULTS_REVIEW\".\r\nb.	Page-down to the \"Menu Information\" screen.  Remove the \"MR_IT_RR_SHOW_REF\" entry from the list.\r\n2. Verify the correct reference range for a result by double clicking on the cell for each result\r\n3. Hovering the mouse over each result and viewing the reference range in the status bar\r\n4. Display the reference range for each result in the cell with the result. This can be done by setting the ?Allow multiples lines?? flag toYes in the Lab Result section of System Definitions, and then in Results Review clicking the Options button and checking the ?Show reference range per value? box .','','Disable the reference range button to NOT display (recommended airtight workaround)\r\nEach region may remove the Ref Range button by performing these steps:\r\n	A)  Duplicate E2U record 17471 into a record outside of the Epic release range (100,000+).\r\n	B)  Edit the duplicate record, and make the following changes:\r\na.	In the \"Overrides menu descriptor:\" field, enter \"MR_TB_RESULTS_REVIEW\".\r\nb.	Page-down to the \"Menu Information\" screen.  Remove the \"MR_IT_RR_SHOW_REF\" entry from the list.\r\n2. Verify the correct reference range for a result by double clicking on the cell for each result\r\n3. Hovering the mouse over each result and viewing the reference range in the status bar\r\n4. Display the reference range for each result in the cell with the result. This can be done by setting the ?Allow multiples lines?? flag toYes in the Lab Result section of System Definitions, and then in Results Review clicking the Options button and checking the ?Show reference range per value? box .',NULL,'If workaround #1 is selected, installation of a code fix is not required.  However, if in the future a region would like to use the reference range button, the fix should be implemented.  Epic will include the fix in an IU for SP\'08.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-13 01:26:00','2009-11-24 09:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(299,4221374,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Blood Pressure Percentile value in SmartLinks may be miscalculated, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AMB, IP','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-17 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr.  Benjamin Broder',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','K072108',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'10',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','A','L','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I758495/E755931\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K072108\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No Current Impact.  GA affected only.  Fix received in K072108 and already installed by NCAL.','Features:  Best practice alerts, Cache v 5.2.3 or below\r\nDiscovered by:  Another Epic customer\r\nEpic Representative:  Derek Heckel\r\nBlood pressure percentile itself is not a value that would influence a provider\'s patient care decision. \r\n Potential Problem Description:  The value for blood pressure percentilemay be calculated incorrectly in certain Smart Links (201 and 202) if both of the following conditions are true:\r\nCache version 5.2.3 or below is used (a problem with the Cache Z-Power function is the root of the problem);\r\nThe affected patients are age 10 or under\r\n\r\nAs a result, the incorrect blood pressure percentile calculation may trigger misleading and inaccurate Best Practice Alerts.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No Current Impact.  GA affected only.  Fix received in K072108 and already installed by NCAL.','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-17 03:28:00','2009-02-17 03:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(300,4102327,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Modified PTA Med may appear as New Med on Discharge Report. Clinically Not Patient Safety','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-01-13 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Liz Nickels)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','0520-PS-PR4102327-E758740-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z','K070609','','2009-06-17 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'0',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  orig fix (E758740) pulled from Kpackage; fixed by E758976 NCAL and SCAL also need E759362-E759193 & C75031523\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512217\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4574 & 4874):  \n  SP’07 E758740 5/20/09 E759362-E759193 & C75031523 9/11/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/06/09: Per R. Blair, fix will be in Nov K-pckg. Will NCAL install adhoc/TD before 2010?','When using the new medication reconciliation tools, replacing a PTA medication (using new Replace functionality, which links the PTA med to the replacement med) at admission, and then later modifying the original PTA medication at discharge, causes the modified medication to display in the START taking section of the PTMEDDISCHARGE SmartLink and Patient Friendly Take Home Meds print group (LPG 46165). The PTA medication should appear in the CONTINUE these medications which have CHANGED section.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n1.  Admit patient with PTA Meds\r\n2.  Replace a PTA med with a new Inpt order (Replace Acetaminophen 1 tab BID with Losartan)\r\n3.  On discharge, reorder the Acetaminophen but change the order (Acetaminophen 2 tabs BID)\r\n4.  The Smartlink will state that the patient should Start the medication, rather than Continue the\r\n      medication with Changes.  \r\nper 2/18/09 PART email:\r\nThe issue has now been expanded to include a similar scenario which may occur when an alternative alert is used:\r\nIf an alternative alert is triggered and accepted when re-ordering the PTA medication for the inpatient stay, and then the inpatient medication is prescribed at discharge, the new prescription appears under the \'Continue these medications which have CHANGED\' section.  Instead it should appear under the \'START taking these medications\' section, and the original PTA medication should be displayed in the \'STOP taking these prior medications\' section.\r\n\r\nThe second scenario still only occurs with the new med rec tools as in the first, so there is still No Current Impact. \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'6/30: code backed out; this issue is associated with 4581633.\r\n6/1:  Received NCF Approval. PROD install targeting 6/17/09.\r\n5/20:  File received.  Notified Dhea.\r\n4/27/09: Per Dhea waiting for code fix end of May.\r\n3/9/09: NW requested adhoc; PART will update on 3/10.\r\nNW (Nick Socotch) may request and authorize an ad hoc and will confirm via email to PART, along with the 4 digit ad hoc number. If NW doesn\'t request an adhoc, PART Communications (Sharon Carroll) will follow-up with NCAL (Tho mas W. Stewart) and SCAL (Kimberly Nida) to see if they are interested in an ad hoc.\r\nFixes are currently in progress for the affected versions (SP\'07 and SP\'08).  \r\nEpic (Liz Nickels) will provide confirmation and information about the KPackage availability by 1/23/09.\r\nPART Communications (Sharon Carroll) will communicate code fix and KPackage delivery, to the impacted and potentially impacted regions (NCAL, SCAL, NW, Exempla, and HI).','Prior to a Special Update being released, regions may temporarily remove the Replace button from their affected navigator configuration (VCN) records and ask the providers to submit the Inpatient replacement medication as a new inpatient order.','','Prior to a Special Update being released, regions may temporarily remove the Replace button from their affected navigator configuration (VCN) records and ask the providers to submit the Inpatient replacement medication as a new inpatient order.',NULL,'This issue was not added to PMO when it was received via email on 1/13/09 because it is \"clinically not patient safety\".  Thereafter it was decided to add it to PMO when an update for this issue was received on 2/18/09.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-18 01:58:00','2009-10-26 02:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(301,4225303,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT SP ?08 only. Modified Med Rec orders may revert to original order information after Activity switching','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ambulatory, Optime, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-19 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No longer an issue for KP since only impacts SP08 and will be fixed in SU09; closed out\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I767566\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED--affects SP08 only, fixed in SU09','In an Orders navigator section configured for medication review, modifications made to an outpatient medication may revert to the original order information if the user switches activities before signing.  Upon returning to the Orders navigator, the user--unaware that the changes were not made as intended--may proceed to sign orders, including the one that should have been modified. \r\n\r\nExample Workflow:\r\nA user documents outpatient medications in the Home Medications section. These medications are either patient reported or prescriptions from previous visits.\r\nA clinician enters a Visit Navigator with an Orders section configured for medication review, such as an Orders section with configuration record 49200-ED Discharge Orders Section with Medication or a duplicate.\r\nThe clinician orders a medication.\r\nHe or she clicks the Modify button for an outpatient medication and edits the order details.\r\nThe clinician switches activities then returns to the navigator. \r\nThe information for the modified order reverts to what was prior to modification.\r\nThe clinician signs displayed orders, but the one marked for modfication is not changed as intended.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Brendan Krueger) will provide a code fix and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) by 3/3/09 of its development status and KPackage.','',NULL,'',NULL,'Epic Representative:  Brendan Krueger  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-19 01:46:00','2009-07-22 01:43:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(302,4225320,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT -  Printing episode reports containing print group LPG 82000 for multiple patients may display incorrect patient data','','',NULL,NULL,'InPatient, Beacon','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-19 00:00:00','2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  SP07 DLG I7511673 and SP08 DLG I767929\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758683\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/01/09--per JDee/AMB, fix was installed 8/19, ok to close. CLOSING','Printing episode reports for more than one patient may cause other print groups to print information from the first patient\'s episode for all subsequent patients.  This occurs if the episode report contains print groups that display episode-level information, in particular 82000-OB Results Console (HTML) or a copy.\r\n\r\nPrinting episode reports for more than one patient simultaneously can be done through the Patient Lists\r\nactivity or batch printing.\r\n\r\nExample workflow in Patient Lists activity:\r\nOpen a patient list containing several patients with current pregnancy episodes. Make sure that test patients have episode information entered, such as pregnancy dating information.\r\nOn the Patient Lists toolbar, click Patient Report.\r\nUnder the Reports window, select a report that contains a results console print group and print that report for the patients.\r\nOn the printed reports, episode information from the first patient on the patient list carries over to the reports for subsequent patients.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).  No Current Impact-Affected print group not being used.\r\nEpic (Danielle Dyer) will provide code fixes (SP?07 DLG I7511673 and SP?08 DLG I767929) as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status by 3/3/09.\r\n3/3:  Waiting for Kpkg-No Current Impact-Affected print group not being used.','','','',NULL,'Discovered by Epic (Danielle Dyer) during testing\r\nPotentially impacted areas: SP\'07 with Special Update package E753336 installed; SP\'08\r\nFeatures:   Reports; Print group LPG 82000\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-20 09:21:00','2009-09-01 12:13:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(303,4225328,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4225328,'NO CURRENT IMPACT  but imminent- Order Entry - User can remove pended orders locked by another user ','','',NULL,NULL,'Beacon, Radiant,Ambulatory','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-19 00:00:00','2009-11-11 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'4685','','','','','','created by NCAL','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  NCAL cancelled ad hoc auth # 4685; confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511946 \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609-C75031418\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/11/09: Per M. Wilson 11/1 ok to close.','If two users are in a patient?s outpatient encounter, it is possible for one user to remove one or more pended orders and the other user to sign them. There is no indication to the second user that the order(s) are actually canceled. This issue occurs when one of the Orders navigator sections intended to be used in an Inpatient context is used in an Ambulatory context.\r\n\r\nOther Epic applications (e.g., Inpatient, ED) that place orders in an Inpatient context should not be affected because in an Inpatient workspace pended orders are not shared across ordering sessions and do not appear in the navigator.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/11/09: Helen sent email to M. Wilson 11/11; ok to close? \r\n10/20/09: Per M. Wilson 10/20, Case Req will be implemented post SU\'09. July kpkg, Nov install.\r\n10/20/09: Helen sent email on 10/20 to Michael Wilson to get status of Case Request.\r\n08/11/09: Per Dhea Case REquest still on hold; probably won\'t be installed until SU\'09 \r\n5/26: Waiting for Kpkg (July).  Withdrawing adhoc - per Dhea, Case Request is on hold indefinitley. \r\n6/2:  Waiting for Kpkg.  Withdrawing adhoc (per Dhea).\r\nThis issue is a show stopper for Case Request.\r\n5/12:  per Michael Bries, in July k-packg.  No adhoc requested.\r\n3/23: Rebecca to talk with Dustin this week. Targeting May release, no outage required.\r\n3/16: Adhoc 4685 request. Once \"Case Request\" goes live in early May suites will be affected..Verifying this a NCI. 3/9/09: No Beacon impact; waiting for response from Radiant.Checking with Johnette.  Fix/Kpkg status by 3/3/09. No regions are currently impacted.  An Epic check of the acking (Rebecca Blair) of the status by 3/3/09.configuration at each region confirms there is no current impact.  In addition, regional workflows do not use Inpatient Order navigators in an Ambulatory context.  \r\nNCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, Exempla, CO, MAS, GA, and OH could be potentially impacted if.they begin to use Inpatient Order Navigator sections in Ambulatory settings without installing the fix, although this possibility is very low.\r\n3/4:  Verifying this a NCI. Checking with Johnette. ','','','',NULL,'Discovered by Epic (Danielle Dyer) during testing.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-20 09:40:00','2009-11-11 02:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(304,4233157,1,'OPT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'OpTime Barcoding  - Vendor Zimmer?s barcode format discrepancy may lead to incomplete product records','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','I7511965','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-20 00:00:00','2009-08-21 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr.  Benjamin Broder','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','May09','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','Y','M','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  comfirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511965\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758490\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/21/09: 8/21/09:  cerified by Kim Starks--CLOSING ISSUE',' Changes to the proprietary barcode format used by the vendor Zimmer have affected how Epic software parses barcode information of scanned Zimmer implant products. Zimmer\'s changes to their barcode format were not communicated to Epic in time for them to create and apply updated code.  As a result, key scanned information for Zimmer implant products such as lot number and expiration date was not recorded correctly via scanning, making it difficult if not impossible to trace implants in the event of a product recall.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/18/09: Confirm with K. Metzger and K. Starks if ok to close. Does w/a need to be undone?\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).  Workaround in place.\r\n6/1:  Waiting for Kpkg.  Workaround in place (per Kirk)\r\n3/25: Per Adam S, fix ready 4/1.  \r\n3/25: SU E758490.  Workaround in place (per Kirk). Fix is a programming point-no ETA.  Epic to search for affected records.Bridge to reconvene on Monday at 10am.  Affected functionality already disabled as a workaround (per Kirk). Epic to search for affected records.\r\n3/2: Fix is a programming point-no ETA. ','Epic (Adam Sauder) will provide NCAL and SCAL with a programming point that will enable correct reading of Zimmer barcode scans by 2/24/09.\r\nTo mitigate further impact to records, NCAL (Kirk Metzger) temporarily disabled the barcoding processing by setting the LSW setting set to NO.  This is a client configuration change that was done on individual workstations at affected facilities.  Scanning of barcoding will not be possible and all implant information will be entered manually.\r\nSCAL (Kimberly Nida and Pat Jones) continued their clinical practice of validating the accuracy of all scanned data, especially for questionable scans, and will also manually enter data when scanned data is inaccurate.',NULL,'Epic (Adam Sauder) will provide NCAL and SCAL with a programming point that will enable correct reading of Zimmer barcode scans by 2/24/09.\r\nTo mitigate further impact to records, NCAL (Kirk Metzger) temporarily disabled the barcoding processing by setting the LSW setting set to NO.  This is a client configuration change that was done on individual workstations at affected facilities.  Scanning of barcoding will not be possible and all implant information will be entered manually.\r\nSCAL (Kimberly Nida and Pat Jones) continued their clinical practice of validating the accuracy of all scanned data, especially for questionable scans, and will also manually enter data when scanned data is inaccurate.',NULL,'NCAL (Kirk Metzger) and SCAL (Kimberly Nida) will implement the workaround until the fix is installed and will continue to validate the data before filing.  \r\nNCAL and SCAL will manually correct inaccurate scanned data.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-20 04:08:00','2009-08-31 09:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(305,4241917,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Beacon - Treatment Day may be Deleted after Modifying Properties','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-24 00:00:00','2009-09-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Weisenthal ','',NULL,'4661','','','','','','SCAL to adhoc','0309-PS-PR4241917-E758408-C75031337-Spr07Mar16NS.tar.Z\r\n0309-PS-PR4241917-E758408-C75031337-Spr07Mar16NS.zip','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','Y','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K031609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511140\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4661):  \n  SP’07 E758408/C75031337 3/09/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K031609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/17/2009:  per Dorina Wong / Evelyn: fix certified, OK to close.  CLOSING','Under a specific workflow, a treatment day may be unexpectedly deleted from a Beacon treatment Plan by a user, when modifying the treatment plan by cutting and pasting a treatment day and modifying treatment plan properties.\r\n\r\nExample Workflow:\r\n1.   Copy and paste a treatment day.\r\n2.	Open the order composer for an order in the original day that was copied and change the value of  any of the order composer items.\r\n3.	Instead of clicking Accept, click the Properties button to open the treatment plan properties.\r\n4.	Change a setting on the Dosing tab and click Accept.\r\n5.	The change propagation window will appear.  With either radio button selected, click Accept.\r\n6.	After clicking Accept, the two days will appear identical, but with a status of Cancelled.\r\n7.	Close the treatment plan and re-enter.  The original copied day is deleted.\r\n\r\nAn inadvertently deleted treatment day in a treatment plan may impact patient care. A patient may not receive an intended (e.g. chemo) treatment.  ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/14/09: T. Stewart sent detail to D. Wong on 9/11; D. Wong will have testing done.  08/18/09: Confirm with K. Ryan ok to close.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (March-confirmed). NCAL will not implement adhoc. \r\n3/10  per Dorinda Wong: This is not urgent and can wait for the March kpkg.  \r\nAdhoc-4661.  Workaround = correct workflow. Kirk Ryan already sent out a communication to NCAL users and trainers and SCAL trainers. Fix status update-3/6.2/24/09:  SCAL to adhoc.  Kirk already sent out a communication to NCAL users and trainers and SCAL trainers. Workaround = correct workflow. Epic (Liz Nickels) will provide a status update about the fix and KPackage by 3/6/09.','Until a fix is available, users should click Accept to save changes in the Order Composer before clicking the treatment plan properties.\r\nPer Dorinda Wong 3/10: that is the normal and usual workflow that is taught and practiced.  ','','Until a fix is available, users should click Accept to save changes in the Order Composer before clicking the treatment plan properties.\r\nPer Dorinda Wong 3/10: that is the normal and usual workflow that is taught and practiced.  ',NULL,'Epic (Liz Nickels) reports that there is no search available for potentially affected treatment plans for the NCAL region. Epic Representative:  Liz Nickels 1-608-271-9000. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-24 12:41:00','2009-09-17 10:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(306,4245688,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Patient Allergy Alert may not Fire if a specific medication is ordered under specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB, IP, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-25 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Michael Bries)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','0427-AP-PR4245688-E758536-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'0',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  one fix installed by pharmacy--invisible to regions-partial fix confirmed in K051809; \nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511975, I7512814\nAD HOC AVAILABLE (AUTH # 4742):  \n  SP’07 E758536 4/27/09  E759143 8/15/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809 & K091409\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/18: allergy search results received from Epic (sent to SFong / BYee)','Due to changes Epic made to the FDB Allergen load to address the previous patient safety issue in PART Incident # 3577341 (SLG 290791), in conjunction with actions FDB took in their allergen data, it is possible that a patient may have an allergen documented that won?t fire an allergy alert if a specific medication is ordered.\r\n\r\nThis issue occurs because of 2 problems with how EPIC addresses FDB medication records.  Medication records can be \"marked\" by FDB as \"Unassociated\", \"Split\", or \"Replacement\". \r\n\r\n1) Unassociated Records ? According to FDB, any real medications should not be marked as ?Unassociated.?  Unassociated medications are normally items such as shampoo, supplies, etc.  However, Epic has found real FDB medication records marked as ?Unassociated?.  Epic assumes that FDB meant to mark them as \"Replacement\" or \"Split\". \r\n\r\nWith the changes Epic made in SP\'07: I759326 - E757940, I759822 - E756905 and SP\'08: I765903 - E760749, when an allergen gets updated in an FDB load, Epic code will remove the medications from drug type allergen records that are marked as ?Unassociated? because the meds are no longer associated with the record. As a result that medication won?t fire against the allergen with which it was previously associated.\r\n\r\nIn this case, Epic can identify the allergen that is a problem. However, Epic can\'t identify which medications used to be associated with the allergen so that data can?t be provided.\r\n\r\n2) Replaced Records ? Sometimes FDB marks medications as ?Replaced? or ?Split?. This means that a medication record is being replaced by one or other medication records.\r\n\r\nWith the changes we made in SP\'07: I759326 - E757940, I759822 - E756905 and SP\'08: I765903 - E760749, when an allergen gets updated in an FDB load, Epic code removes the meds from drug type allergen records that are marked as replaced, since the meds are no longer associated with the replaced record. Since Epic code currently isn\'t looking at the replacement file, Epic code will remove the medications from the allergen and not add back the medications that are the replacement. Thus a similar Problem 2 will arise, as in Problem 1, where a patient has an allergen documented and an allergy alert won\'t fire for a specific med.\r\n \r\nIn this case, Epic can identify the allergen that is a problem and provide a replacement suggestion of which allergens the region should be using instead. Epic can also tell if a patient is currently allergic to one of the meds on their profile where the alert didn?t fire. \r\n\r\nThe numbers of affected patient charts identified by region with affected ELG records and active medication orders are:   SCAL: 67, NCAL: 43,  CO: 3, NW: 12, HI: 0, MAS: 0, OH: 0, GA: 5\r\n\r\nNote:  Until special updates are developed and installed, regions may continue to have affected allergens identified on this search, after each FDB load occurs. FDB is working to correct their data to insure all clinically relevant changes are in the replacement file. However, until Epic has the SU\'s developed, more affected records may be introduced by the FDB load.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/02/09: per Syliva Fong, Rx meeting again with FDB in late Sept; will get a better idea of the eta.  FDB fix not expected in Sept.; earliest would be Oct/Nov.  09/01/09: per Sylvia Fong, the work around needs to continue in place until FDB puts in the final piece.  Leaving open as PS until this is complete.   7/14:  Technically, the issue is fixed; however, KP does not have a way to clean up (replace) old/bad allergens with good allergens.  Each region is now forced to manually fix patient records each time FDB updates the ELG (allergen) master file.   \r\n7/14:  per BYee, each region still needs to continue to work with their own Epic TS to run reports on affected patient allergy profiles; NCAL had 0 patients, SCAL had 7.7/7: May K pckg (and fix) installed into NATLNAM on 6/27.  Checking w. Bill Yee if OK to close. 5/29/09:  per BYee The fix is delivered, tested and in the May K package.  This will be installed into NATLNAM on 6/27/09.  Unfortunately, this fix will actually worsen our allergen clean up problem.  3/25:  per Mohamed I Umarji, another round of cleanup completed.  3/9/09: no adhoc; waiting for KPKG.Fix status-3/6.Per Cheryl Tran 3/2:  Rx did not find any issues that needed consultation with a physician. Most consisted of topicals and birth control pills. Either those meds have been discontinued on the outpatient basis, switched to something else, or the patient has not picked up a refill in quite some time.  Rx does not need a physician for NCAL.  Per B. Yee:  Our pharmacists will manually review these charts and then if needed, work with a regional physician (identified by PART rotation) to determine if any remediation is needed. ','Same as Urgent Mitigation','','Same as Urgent Mitigation',NULL,'Epic Representative:  Michael Bries 1-608-271-9000  \r\nPhysician Representative: Peter Dwork  303-360-1550',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-25 11:38:00','2009-09-18 10:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(307,4250957,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Results may be missing in certain Print Groups, SmartTexts, SmartPhrases, Reports, and SmartLinks for non-sequential visits','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-27 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Alan Rogers ','',NULL,'4675','','','','','','by NW','0619-AP-PR4250957-E758888-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z\r\n0619-AP-PR4250957-E758888-Spr07Jul06NS-Notes.zip\r\n0731-AP-PR4250957-E759118-Spr07Sep14NS.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'G',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'FEB09','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  I7512081/E758888 delivered 6/19/09 only partial fix: confirmed first fix in K070609; second fix (E7591187) on 7/31/09\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7512081 & I7512392\r\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4675):  \r\n  SP07 E758888 6/19/09 & E759118 7/31/09\r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP07 K070609 & K091409\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/02/09: Still waiting for 2nd fix in Sept kpkg, 2/2010 install.','With non-sequential visits, certain Print Groups and SmartLinks that are configured to display most recent results may have results data missing or show results for prior visits. This issue occurs when visits are not performed in the same sequence that the visit?s contacts are created.  Although the problem is more likely to occur with non-sequential HOV visits, it can also happen in certain Ambulatory situations.\r\nExample 1: Non-sequential visits in HOV (IP) settings\r\nOn 2/13/09, a patient is scheduled for an appointment on 4/19/09.\r\nOn 2/16/09, the patient has an interim encounter (e.g., lab tests, consultation, or any other encounter) and a new contact is opened.\r\nOn 2/19/09, data from 2/16/09 does not show up in print groups or Smartlinks designed to show last value, although the data does appear in the patient chart.\r\nIP Potentially Affected SmartLinks\r\nHHS ID - Mnemonic - Code -  Affected Configuration Parameters	\r\n62 LASTLABV  lastLbV2^LUPPDB16 N/A-always affected.\r\nThis SmartLink attempts to find all prior visits in the specified time range, and may miss visits created out of order.\r\n70 LASTVIST	 lastVis2^LUPPDB16	N/A-always affected\r\nThis SmartLink will always find the last visit that was created, which may not be the last visit performed.\r\n127 THISVISIT  thisVis^LUPPDB52	Affected if thisvis= \"\", or thisvis=2\r\n128 LASTPROC  lastProc^LUPPDB52  Affected if thisvis= \"\", or thisvis=2\r\n133  GETLABS  getlabs^LUPPDB16	N/A-always affected\r\nThis SmartLink attempts to find all prior visits in the specified time range, and may miss visits created out of order.\r\nIP - Potentially Affected Print Groups\r\nLPG ID - Name - Code - Affected Configuration Parameters\r\n1262 C_0445 TB Status  TBStat^LYCHAPG2  N/A-always affected\r\n52022	Orders: Standard Orders Based on Order Types (HTML)	orders^LYUMDPG1	Affected unless 15th parameter (eptdat) is used. When this parameter is set, only results for orders placed on that encounter are considered.\r\n1121	LAB: ABNORMAL RESULTS	abnTests^LARCS04	N/A-always affected\r\n1412	LABS: LAST 6 MONTHS (TYPE 1)	LabRslts^LARCS18A	Affected unless 3rd parameter (ndays) is set to 1.  When this parameter is set to one, order results for orders placed on that encounter are considered.\r\n1450	LAB: LAST 6 MONTHS (ORD_LAB)  LabRslts^LARCS18A  Affected unless 3rd parameter (ndays) is set to 1.  When this parameter is set to one, order results for orders placed on that encounter are considered.\r\n\r\nExample 2: Non-sequential visits in Ambulatory settings\r\nA patient schedules a visit with his/her PCP for the afternoon of 2/21/09. \r\nLater in the day, the patient schedules another visit with a specialist for the morning of 2/21/09.  \r\nOn 2/21, the patient has some lab worked performed during the morning visit with the specialist.  \r\nDuring the afternoon visit with the PCP, the clinician uses one of the affected SmartLinks to view results from this and prior visits. \r\nSince the morning visit on 2/21/09 was created after the afternoon visit, the results from the 2/21 morning visit will not be displayed by the SmartLink. \r\nAmbulatory - Potentially Affected SmartLinks\r\nHHS ID - Mnemonic - Code - Affected Configuration Parameters\r\n62  LASTLABV  lastLbV2^LUPPDB16	N/A-always affected\r\nThis SmartLink attempts to find all prior visits in the specified time range, and may miss visits created out of order.\r\n127 THISVISIT  thisVis^LUPPDB52	Affected if thisvis= \"\".\r\n128  LASTPROC  lastProc^LUPPDB52	Affected if thisvis= \"\"\r\nAmbulatory - Potentially Affected Print Groups\r\nLPG ID - Name - Code - Affected Configuration Parameters\r\n1121  LAB: ABNORMAL RESULTS	abnTests^LARCS04	N/A-always affected\r\n1412	LABS: LAST 6 MONTHS (TYPE 1)	LabRslts^LARCS18A	Affected unless 3rd parameter (ndays) is set to 1.  When this parameter is set to one, order results for orders placed on that encounter are considered.\r\n1450	LAB: LAST 6 MONTHS (ORD_LAB) LabRslts^LARCS18A	Affected unless 3rd parameter (ndays) is set to 1.  When this parameter is set to one, order result',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/11/09: A. Mure to certify.\r\n10/20/09: Per R. Blair all files received.  Nov install.\r\n08/11/09: Per Andre ignoring ad hocs waiting for KPKGs.\r\n07/31/09: another adhoc file received\r\n6/16: Waiting for Kpkg (July).  W/a, remediation mitigation not needed (Per Andre)  5/26: Work around will be done per Andre; will f/up with more info today.\r\n5/20: Andre checking with Isacc Santos regarding workaround, mitigation, and remediation status.\r\nNW has adhoc?ed\r\nAndre/Bart to f/u regarding workaround/mitigation status. Regions will review search results and work with their TS to determine regional impact and severity and alternative Print Groups, Reports, and SmartLinks. Regions will review search results and work with their TS to determine regional impact and severity and alternative Print Groups, Reports, and SmartLinks.\r\n3/4:  f/u regarding workaround/mitigation status.','Epic (Maria Spinoza) ran a query that revealed affected print groups, SmartLinks, SmartText, Reports, and user-created Smart Phrases in all regions. These reports were sent to all regions.\r\nEpic (Maria Spinoza) will re-run SmartText and SmartPhrase searches to capture User, to facilitate mitigation.\r\n','','Epic (Maria Spinoza) ran a query that revealed affected print groups, SmartLinks, SmartText, Reports, and user-created Smart Phrases in all regions. These reports were sent to all regions.\r\nEpic (Maria Spinoza) will re-run SmartText and SmartPhrase searches to capture User, to facilitate mitigation.\r\n',NULL,'Epic (Maria Spinozzi) has no details for a fix.  No fix planned for SP07.  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-27 12:48:00','2009-12-02 10:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(308,4253552,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3412081,'New Medication Reconciliation - Modified PTA Med may not get Discontinued as Expected under specific circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inpatient, Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-02-27 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Weisenthal',NULL,NULL,'4650','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NCAL','0319-PS-PR4253552-C75031344-E758412-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z\r\n0319-PS-PR4253552-C75031344-E758412-Spr07May18NS.zip','N/A',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:    will also fix 4290378; Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511626\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4650):  \n  SP’07 E758412 & C75031344 3/19/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/24/09:  Code installed as adhoc on 4/8/09 - 0319-PS-PR4253552-C75031344-E758412-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z, validated as part of the Release by Sherry Ellis / Fay Vafai','In the new Discharge Medication Reconciliation Navigator, it is possible to modify a prior to admission (PTA) medication in such a way that it may not cancel the original medication. This will result in the patient having two active orders for the same medication: the original PTA medication and the modified medication. The affected workflow involves signing and holding a modified PTA med order in one med rec session and subsequently modifying and signing the same PTA med order in another med rec session. \r\n \r\nThe affected workflow is as follows:\r\n1.  Open the medication reconciliation from the discharge navigator\r\n2.	Go to the Reconcile Medications for Discharge tab\r\n3.	Click ?Modify? next to one of the home medications and change one of the order properties\r\n4.	Accept the order and move to the Review and Sign step of med rec\r\n5.	Click ?Sign & Hold? next to the newly-modified discharge order and finish the med rec process\r\n6.	Open the discharge med rec navigator a second time\r\n7.	Click the ?Edit? hyperlink next to the home medication that you modified previously\r\n8.	Change a property of the of the order, accept your changes, and move to Review and Sign\r\n9.	Click ?Sign? next to your modified order and complete the med rec process\r\n10. Go to the Patient Summary activity and view the Discharge Summary Report. In the ?Home Medications? print group, you will see that there are two instances of the order you modified.\r\n\r\nSmartLinks that pull discharge medication data and Print Groups and Reports that display this data will also be affected.  EPIC released Smartlink- PT Med Discharge, and EPIC released Print Groups- Home Med (48810) and Take Home Med (46516) may display incorrect data (both orders) until the fix is installed.  Regions should review these items and determine any mitigating actions that should be taken until the fix is installed.\r\nA PTA medication that is modified may unexpectedly not be discontinued.  This may result in two orders that may be confusing to Clinicians and Discharge Pharmacists, which may impact patient care.\r\n\r\nFeatures:  New Medication Reconciliation functionality, and Reports, Print Groups, and Smart Text including SmartLinks for Notes that pull discharge medication data',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3/16: Attempting to fix with a build.3/9/09: fix is in testing for SU ?09; after testing SP07 and 08 will be retrofitted. Still researching work around. Adhoc authorized - 4650.  No ETA on fix arrival. Epic status update-3/6/092/27: Epic (Peter Lesperance) will provide a status update about the fix and KPackage by 3/6/09.\r\nAdhoc authorized - 4650.  No ETA on fix arrival.\r\n3/31: Per Kelly will be installed 4/8.  3/30: Per Dhea going to CAB today.','Special updates will be developed to fix this issue. As a workaround until the fix is installed, users may cancel and place new ?After Discharge? orders, rather than editing signed and held ?After Discharge? orders.  Imminently impacted regions (e.g. NW, NCAL, and SCAL) will implement the workaround and assess their implementation schedules if the fix is not available.',NULL,'Special updates will be developed to fix this issue. As a workaround until the fix is installed, users may cancel and place new ?After Discharge? orders, rather than editing signed and held ?After Discharge? orders.  Imminently impacted regions (e.g. NW, NCAL, and SCAL) will implement the workaround and assess their implementation schedules if the fix is not available.',NULL,'Discovered by:  Another Epic Client',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-02-27 03:25:00','2009-04-29 10:19:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(309,4272797,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'A Multiple-Occurrence Frequency may Unexpectedly default to an Occurrence Count of One in User Created Order Sets under specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'ED','I7511980, E758780','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-06 00:00:00','2009-09-09 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Peter Lesperance)','',NULL,'4689','','','','','','SCAL to adhoc','0324-PS-PR4272797-E758461-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z (order validation programming point)\r\n0526-AP-TD35444-E758780-C75031424-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z\r\n0526-AP-TD35444-E758780-C75031424-Spr07Jul06NS.zip\r\n0728-PS-PR4272797-E758871-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'MAR09','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Programming pt ST fix (I7511990) delivered, add AD hoc coming for LT fix; regions working on putting ST programming pt in. as of July 1, KP national testing\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  (1)  I7511990, (2) I7511980 (E758780 & C75031424) (3) I7512006\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4689 & 4760):  \n  SP’07 E758461 3/24/09 E758780  & C75031424  5/26/09 & E758871 7/28/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809 & K070609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/09/09: Per D. Lew successful implementation for med orders; per S. Ellis, scenario causing issue for procedure orders occurs too infrequently to test.  ','When creating user order sets a user may override an order template\'s frequency. After the PRL conversion has been completed, if a user creates a user order set and changes an order frequency from a \"when\" type frequency ( \"when\" type = once or one time dose) to a multiple occurrence frequency (BID, TID, QID, etc.), in one or more of the orders, the composer displays additional fields that allow users to specify the number of occurrences. If the user doesn\'t specify either a number of occurrences or number of doses to be administered the order template record will be saved with 1 occurrence (1 dose or 1 time). As a result, the user may incorrectly assume that when submitting the order, that has been changed in the order set, the order will be placed as Until Specified (administered or performed indefinitely until the order is changed or discontinued).  This issue applies to both procedure and medication orders that include a \"when\" type frequency. Additionally, for medication orders, if the number of occurences is not changed and is saved as 1 occurance, the order status on the MAR will change to Completed, once a dose is administered and documented on the MAR.\r\nExample Workflow\r\n1.Open a patient hospital encounter and go to the Order Set activity (Action > Order Set)\r\n2.Select an order set that has at least one order with a \"once\" or other \"when\"-type frequency in it.\r\n3.Go to \"Manage User Order Sets\" and create a new user order set.\r\n4.Override one of the one-time orders and change the frequency to any scheduled or non-scheduled type frequency (PRN, daily, Q4H, etc.).\r\n5.Do notchange the number of doses/occurrences or the type of count (hours, days). Notice that it appears blank in the user order set editor, implying ?until specified? or ?until discontinued.?\r\n6.Accept the changes to the order and the user order set.\r\n7.Look at the resulting order in the order set. If the frequency is in the summary sentence, it will display \"1 dose\" or \"1 occurrence.\" In the order composer, the dose/occurrence fields will display 1 dose/occurrence.\r\n8.If the order is placed, it will have a dose/occurrence count of one.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: Confirm with S. Ellis ok to close; cc Britt Mattern.\r\n08/10/09: adhoc fix is in manifest for 8/19.\r\n08/04: testing in progress--involves a number of packages  07/28/09: 6/18: still targeting Aug release.6/2:  WITS3 replication in progress.  PROD install targeting 8/19 release. (per Dhea)\r\n5/18:  per BYee, we have installed the interim LPP in NCAL, we will stop reviewing these orders on a daily basis.   final fix currently in Spring \'07 Epic Testing (per Peter Lesperence) \r\n4/10:  Adhoc installed in WITS2 on 4/9.\r\n3/24: tar file for order validation programming point received.\r\n4/1:  per Epic (PL):  The short-term fix is the order validation programming point that can be used to warn users if they are placing orders that match the patient safety issue.\r\nThis new order validation programming point is in a new routine and will not require a downtime to install.\r\nThis fix was authorized as ad hoc  4689 and was delivered to KP on 3/24/09.\r\nSCAL and NCAL are working on implementing the short-term fix.\r\nThe long-term fix is in testing for SU\'09. \r\nNext, it be retrofitted back to SP\'08 and SP\'07.\r\nEpic will provide another status update to PART by 4/3/09\r\n.3/23: in NCAL one provider had one order set affected and is being remediated. \r\n3/18: still waiting to get adhoc # from SCAL 3/11 Bridge Call: Kimberly to check with providers to see if utility is needed or if working with affected providers would work better. Per 3/11 PART email, same adhoc can be used for the two separate code deliveries. \r\n3/11 Bridge: Per Andrea, NCAL does not need utility.  Can existing adhoc be used for the programming point or does another need to be requested?  Peter and or Dustin will check on. \r\nPer 3/10/ PART email: Epic (Peter Lesperance) is currently developing an order validation programming point that will alert users when they place an order that is scheduled for only one dose/occurrence, but the frequency is not a \"when\" type frequency. \r\n3/9/09: S. Ellis and B. Yee received queries and will review; clincon is the owner.A special update is in process to fix this issue.  Until the Special Update is installed, users may use the suggested workaround. Epic (Peter Lesperance) will provide a status update about the fix and KPackage by 3/13/09.\r\nSCAL (Kimberly Nida) will request and authorize an ad hoc code fix and provide the ad hoc number to PART and Epic (Peter Lesperance) when it is available.','Until these have been installed, users should be advised to closely review any user order sets they create to ensure they have the expected defaults.\r\nImpacted regions (NCAL and SCAL) plan to communicate and implement the workaround.  \r\nUrgent Mitigation:  \r\nImpacted regions (NCAL/Tom Stewart and SCAL/Kimberly Nida) will distribute the Epic queries to designated Pharmacists and Clinicians to review and potentially remediate currently active patient orders.\r\nEpic (Peter Lesperance) will work with Regional Epic TS to set the query up to run in production, on a daily basis, for each impacted region.\r\nEpic will send the results to the designated regional rep (NCAL/Dhea Maloney & Bill Yee, SCAL/xxx) until a fix is available.\r\nImpacted regions may review the queries and develop communication/action plans as needed to mitigate impact to patient care.\r\nNW (Malinda Fleege) will review this incident within the region to determine an option prior to their PRL conversion to minimize impact.','','Until these have been installed, users should be advised to closely review any user order sets they create to ensure they have the expected defaults.\r\nImpacted regions (NCAL and SCAL) plan to communicate and implement the workaround.  \r\nUrgent Mitigation:  \r\nImpacted regions (NCAL/Tom Stewart and SCAL/Kimberly Nida) will distribute the Epic queries to designated Pharmacists and Clinicians to review and potentially remediate currently active patient orders.\r\nEpic (Peter Lesperance) will work with Regional Epic TS to set the query up to run in production, on a daily basis, for each impacted region.\r\nEpic will send the results to the designated regional rep (NCAL/Dhea Maloney & Bill Yee, SCAL/xxx) until a fix is available.\r\nImpacted regions may review the queries and develop communication/action plans as needed to mitigate impact to patient care.\r\nNW (Malinda Fleege) will review this incident within the region to determine an option prior to their PRL conversion to minimize impact.',NULL,'Epic Representative:  Peter Lesperance 1-608-271-9000  \r\nPhysician Representative: Mike Krall  503-813-3255, C: 503-780-8456',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-06 10:53:00','2009-09-09 02:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(310,4286941,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Default orders from a Best Practice Alert follow-up order navigator may appear in Ordering section of another navigator','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, OpTime, Beacon, Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-12 00:00:00','2009-09-09 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAR09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512004\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-C75031393\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/09/09: Per A. Vakil\'s 9/9/09 email fix implemented successfully.','If the BestPractice Alert follow-up order navigator is included in a system profile, any follow-up orders in the BestPractice Alerts section that are selected by default and then manually deselected by a user might still appear in the ordering section of  a separate navigator.  As a result, the user might then miss and unintentionally sign these unwanted orders, especially when several follow-up orders are placed. \r\n\r\nThis issue occurs in any workflow if all of the following conditions are in place:\r\n\r\nSP\'07\r\nSpecial Update E755634 is installed\r\nA BestPractice Alert follow-up order navigator is configured in the profile\r\nThe triggered BestPractice Alert has one or more suggested follow-up orders that are selected by default, i.e., orders not been previously acted upon. \r\nThe user selects an acknowledge reason in the BestPractice Alerts section.\r\n\r\nSP\'08\r\nA BestPractice Alert follow-up order navigator is configured in the profile\r\nThe triggered BestPractice Alert has one or more suggested follow-up orders that are selected by default. In SP\'08,  follow-up orders are selected by default if they are configured in the BestPractice Alert with a selection frequency of Manually Once, Manually Selected or with no frequency defined.\r\nThe user selects an acknowledge reason in the BestPractice Alerts section.\r\n\r\nThis issue also occurs when multiple BestPractice Alerts appear in the BestPractice Alerts navigator section. If follow-up orders are placed for one BestPractice Alert, all follow-up orders suggested for the additional BestPractice Alerts that were selected by default will appear and be selected automatically in an ordering navigator section in a separate follow-up order navigator, regardless of whether the user previously deselected the orders. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: Notify A. Vakil and S. Ellis of 8/19 install.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).\r\n5/26: PS to f/up with Rey.\r\n4/6/09: Aditi confirmed NCI; waiting for Rey?s confirmation.\r\n3/16: Dhea sent email to EPIC; has not heard back yet. Rey and Aditi verifying whether NCAL is affected or not.Dhea to f/u to verify NCAL is not affected.Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\n3/12/09:  Per Kelly, E755634 is installed in NCAL.  Dhea to f/u to verify NCAL is not affected.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-12 08:08:00','2009-09-09 11:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(311,4290378,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT, but IMMINENT IMPACT. Inpatient - New Med Rec functionality - Inpatient medications may be wrongly discontinued prior to discharge, in specific workflow',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-12 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'George Peredy',NULL,NULL,'4650','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','0319-PS-PR4253552-C75031344-E758412-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z\r\n0319-PS-PR4253552-C75031344-E758412-Spr07May18NS.zip','N/A',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:   will also fix 4253552; Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511626\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4650):  \n  SP’07 E758412 & C75031344 3/19/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/24/09:  Code installed as adhoc on 4/8/09 - 0319-PS-PR4253552-C75031344-E758412-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z, validated as part of the Release by Sherry Ellis / Fay Vafai','An inpatient medication may be erroneously discontinued prior to patient discharge if both of the following two conditions are in place:\r\n\r\nThe \"Stop Taking on Release\" system definition is set to Yes, and\r\nThe following workflow occurs:\r\nAn inpatient medication is ordered at admission or during the hospital stay\r\nIn the discharge naviagtor, the same medication is prescribed in advance for outpatient discharge.\r\nAt Review, the provider signs and holds the outpatient medication. \r\nThe same or another provider returns to discharge navigator, selects Edit, and discontinues the medication.\r\nAt Review, the provider signs the discontinued medication.\r\n In Medication Activity, the inpatient medication is discontinued unexpectedly.\r\n ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3/18/09: Fix for 4253552 will resolve 4290378 as well.AdHoc status by 3/13 (Epic to research if new adhoc has to be authorized or fix will be included with a pending adhoc). Workaround is not acceptable and will not be implemented.3/12/09:  MedRec will not go live on 4/21 if this issue is not resolved (per Dr. Hoberman, recommended by Epic). Epic (Maria Spinozzi) will provide an ad hoc code fix and notify by 3/13/09 if this fix can be included in another pending ad hoc fix. AdHoc status by 3/13 (Epic to research if new adhoc has to be authorized or fix will be included with a pending adhoc).  Workaround is not acceptable and will not be implemented.\r\n3/31: Per Kelly, will be installed 4/8. 3/30: Per Dhea going to CAB today.\r\n','A possible workaround is to remove the EDIT hyperlink; however, it is not recommended by Epic. \r\n',NULL,'A possible workaround is to remove the EDIT hyperlink; however, it is not recommended by Epic. \r\n',NULL,'If Medication Reconciliation and ordering of Discharge medications are completed at a time that is significantly (e.g. several hours or days) before actual patient discharge, an Inpatient medication could be unexpectedly discontinued and medications might not be administered and potentially impact patient care.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,79,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-12 11:07:00','2009-04-24 04:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(312,4286937,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - SP08 - Order Entry - Linked orders may be signed but are not displayed in Order Entry, under specific conditions','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ED, Inpatient, Ambulatory, Pharmacy, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-12 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','N/A','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No longer an issue for KP since only impacts SP08 and will be fixed in SU09; closed out\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, affects SP08, fixed in SU09',' In certain circumstances, linked medication orders can still be signed even though they do not appear in Order Entry. This issue occurs if both of the following conditions are true:\r\nNavigator section 17805-SEC_ORDERS_ED or a duplicate is used\r\nThat navigator section is configured to use either the Active Orders subsection or the Review Active Orders subsection.\r\nFeatures:   Order Entry; Navigators; linked orders\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Waiting for Kpkg.  No Current Impact.  SP08 only.','',NULL,'',NULL,'Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing\r\nPhysician Representative:  N/A (no current impact incident)\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-12 05:12:00','2009-07-22 01:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(313,4306259,1,'OPT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NCI --Patient surgical information may be incorrect if a case and a standalone log are created at the same time by two different users','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-17 00:00:00','2009-08-21 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. George Peredy','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MAR09','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512022\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758583\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/21/09: 8/21/09:  cerified by Kim Starks--CLOSING ISSUE','If a case is created by one user while at the same time a standalone log is created by a different user, the case and the standalone log could share the same ID.  Because the system assumes that any case and log that share the same ID are related to the same patient and surgery, incorrect patient surgical information may appear wherever patient data is viewed.\r\nExamples:\r\nIn Chart Review, the information of the patient associated with the case may be mixed with that of the patient associated with the standalone log, and vice-versa.   \r\nWhen a user attempts to create a new log from a case, the stand-alone log opens. If the user does not carefully review the log information, he or she could easily misinterpret or overwrite the displayed information.\r\nIncorrect patient and surgery information may display on application reports such as the Status Log when report columns are configured to retrieve information from logs related to the standalone case log.\r\nFor this issue to occur, OpTime Location Security point 18 must be assigned in the system profile to allow the creation of standalone logs.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/18/09: Notify K. Starks of 8/19 install.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).\r\n3/26: per Darryl Gill: We do not have this security point enabled (OpTime Location Security point 18)\r\n3/23: Tom S. to send PART email to Darryl Gill to verify status of security point.NCAL to verify if Optime security pt is present--if not, no problem.  Epic (Adam Sauder) will provide a code fix (DLG I7512022) and inform PART by 3/24/09 of its development.','Maintain current config, if security pt not present.  ',NULL,'Maintain current config, if security pt not present.  ',NULL,'Problem requires a certain Optime security pt to be added.  Epic says that security pt is not present in any region.  NCAL to verify.  Epic rep = Adam Sauder',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-17 02:01:00','2009-08-31 09:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(314,4306280,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Soft-deleted medications and procedures may not appear in order panels or PRL-based SmartSets and Order Sets ','','',NULL,NULL,'','I7511981 (E758739) ','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. George Peredy','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'G',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'MAR09','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511981\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609-E758739\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/23/09: Per Bart, 11/23, testing still in process.','A soft-deleted medication or procedure record included in an order may cause that order to not display in Hyperspace for order confirmation nor to be submitted in either:\r\nOrder panels, or\r\nPRL-based SmartSets or Order Sets (LGQ-based sets are not affected)\r\nThis issue occurs whether the order is selected by default or not in Order Sets and Smart Sets. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/16/09: Per Bart\'s 11/16/ email, testing s/b complete by end of week.\r\n11/11/09: Email to B. Shepardson 11/11 requesting certification of install.\r\n09/01/09: Waiting for Kpkg (July) Nov \'09 install.\r\n5/12:  per Michael Bries, in July k-packg.  No adhoc requested.\r\n3/26:  Per Britt, Mark Knoblauch has replaced the 2 affected EAPS.  3/23:  Per Minh Nguyen: The only ERX on the regional order set affected was from an old Smartgroup.  The new version does not contain the affected ERX.  I went ahead and retired the old version.  Orders team to review Epic list of order/smart sets, panels.  3/18:  New Epic query sent to Bart, Trevor PrattEpic (Michael Bries) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its status by 3/24/09\r\nAdhoc needed?  SCAL will not adhoc. ','Review content of regional reports provided by Epic (Michael Bries) on 3/17/09 and replace or delete affected ERX and/or EAP records in orders contained in SmartSets, Order Sets, SmartGroups or Order Panels','','Review content of regional reports provided by Epic (Michael Bries) on 3/17/09 and replace or delete affected ERX and/or EAP records in orders contained in SmartSets, Order Sets, SmartGroups or Order Panels',NULL,'Epic (M. Bries) to run 2nd query from lead system, provide to PART/ regions. 3/18: received. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-17 02:25:00','2009-11-23 03:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(315,4314093,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3480254,'IntraConnect - ChartSync - Orders attached to cancelled admissions may not be synchronized','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-20 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Michael Krall','',NULL,'4691','','','','','','','0518-CE-PR4314093-E758549-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z\r\n0602-NCAL-Spr07SLG367733.txt','N/A','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'R',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'MAR09','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K070609\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7512033\r\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4691):  \r\n  SP?07 E758549 5/18/09\r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP?07 K070609-E758549\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/17/09:  per M. Lin, the most recent PSUP testing has completed under RFC 4309773.  Production RFC 3903455 (tentatively scheduled for 1/12 - 1/14).','Orders attached to cancelled admissions may not be synchronized. When admissions are cancelled, most medication orders will be pended, with no risk of being acted upon. No medication orders will remain active for attached orders. Procedure order results that have been performed and resulted prior to the cancelled admission, will not be synchronized and can be viewed only in the deployment where they were resulted. In addition, procedures that haven\'t been acted on could remain active.\r\nFor example:\r\nA patient is admitted in an outpatient or ED setting\r\nA provider wants to hospitalize the patient (or, the patient is inadvertently admitted in ADT).\r\nThe provider writes a medication and/or procedure order to be carried out prior to hospital admission.\r\nThe hospital admission is cancelled.\r\nOrdered medications are pended and are no longer processed, but procedures remain active and could be carried out and resulted.\r\nAfter ChartSync, the remote deployment does not display procedure results for the patient.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'12/17: The most recent PSUP testing has completed under RFC CHG000004309773.  Production RFC CHG000003903455 (tentatively scheduled for 1/12 - 1/14).\r\n10/26/09: Email to M. Lin on 10/26 requesting update.\r\n10/06/09: Per M. Lin\'s 10/6 email: EPIC does not have a timeline for when the subscript errors will be fixed; they will provide an update when a more concrete timeline is known.\r\n10/06/09: Helen Q. sent an email on 10/6 to Margaret Lin requesting an update.\r\n09/23/09: Per M. Lin\'s 9/23 email, testing was not successful; will need to do another round of testing.\r\n09/22/09: Per M. Lin, testing is in process and s/b complete this week; thereafter s/b moved into prod.\r\n09/15/09: email to M. Lin on 9/15 requesting update on remediation\r\n08/31/09: Per M. Lin\'s 8/18 email , fix did go in; however, not all records are remediated yet due to the PSUPNBM issue. \r\n08/18/09: PS to f/up with M Lin re testing on 8/17.\r\n08/11/09: Per M. Lin\'s 8/11 email, \"Epic has updated the code and we will do PSUP testing starting next Monday (RFC CHG000003933064).\"\r\n08/04/09: per M. Lin\'s 7/31 update in Remedy, remediation could not be completed b/c some records could not be accessed.\r\n07/23/09: PROD RFC for the remediation. CHG000003875499 per MLin\r\n6/17:  fix installed in prod.  Per M Lin (7/1/09)--remediation phase 1 tested successfully, phase 2 in prog pending Epic availability.  6/2:  PROD install targeting 6/17 install.  Search and Cleanup code received.\r\n6/2:  Search and Cleanup code received.\r\n5/26:  PROD install targeting 6/17 install.  Remediation will take place after code fix installed.\r\n5/20:  AdHoc received. Targeting 6/17 install.  Margaret checking w/Epic regarding remediation, mitigation and workaround.5/6:  per Emily Jenkins, adhoc on sched for 5/14; utility still in development @Epic, no date  yet.3/23:Emily to provide update on utility 4/23.  AdHoc requested.\r\nEpic to develop utility re-synch affected records (status 4/15). Wei to f/u if an AdHoc needed.Epic (Emily Jenkins) will develop a search and cleanup utility to identify and resynch affected records on an ongoing basis.Epic will provide a code fix and notify PART by 4/15/09 of its development (advised to install the fix when available). Wei to f/u if an AdHoc needed.\r\n3/23:  AdHoc needed (per Wei). AdHoc auth created/RFC created.\r\n\r\n','NCAL and SCAL will work with their with local TS to schedule and run the cleanup utility when available, until the fix is installed.','','NCAL and SCAL will work with their with local TS to schedule and run the cleanup utility when available, until the fix is installed.',NULL,'Features:  ChartSync\r\nDiscovered by:  Epic\r\nEpic Representative:  Emily Jenkins, Robert Shimmin\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-20 04:22:00','2009-12-17 10:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(316,4315446,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3480873,'SnapShot Activity, Current Meds in Chart Review, and History in Medications Activity-  Discontinued Chronic Long-term medications may Inconsistently Display as Active Medications ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-20 00:00:00','2009-07-29 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Michael Krall','',NULL,'4692','','','','','','Auth by David Campen','0528-AP-PR4110478-E758767-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z = utility for LT fix\r\n0624-AP-PR4315446-E758854-Spr07Jul06NS-Rel.doc \r\n0624-AP-PR4315446-E758854-Spr07Jul06NS-Docs.doc \r\n0624-AP-PR4315446-E758854-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'MAR09','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','Y','Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  PPT delivered to NCAL as ST fix. Utility for LT fix delivered on 5/28/09 (I7512167).  Regions who use this, wont necessarily need second SU (I7512169) Confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512167, I7512169 \nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4777 & 4692):  \n  SP’07 E758767 5/26/09 & E758854 6/24/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609 -E758854\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/29/09: Closing this PR; see J. Yamamoto\'s 7/28 email text in Next Step History below.','If the Chronicpushpin icon is used to designate medications as long term, those medications, if discontinued, may still appear as Active in in the SnapShot Activity, Current Meds in the Chart Review Activity, and History in the Medications Activity, indicated by the red Chronic Meds/PushPin icon.\r\n\r\nThe MDL conversion must be completed to be affected by this issue. NCAL, NW, MAS, and CO are the only regions to have completed the conversion, however, other regions may be imminently affected once the conversion is complete in their region.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7/28: \"We have successfully removed all long-term medication flags from existing records utilizing the MDL cleanup utility Epic provided. We also removed functionality to prevent users from flagging any new medication orders as long-term. These actions resolve existing and future concerns regarding long-term med flags. We were able to proceed ahead of schedule and completed the MDL cleanup on 7/8/09.\"\r\n7/7:  Check w/Joyce on 7/25 if push pin has been removed.\r\n6/16:per Kelly R. target install is 6/25; process will take 17-18 days to complete push pin removal.  Next update w/b 6/23.\r\n6/3:update from Joyce Yamamoto: On 6/2 Epic delivered the MDL utility to remove the long term push pins.6/3: update continuation: The MDL utility was installed in WITS2 on 6/2 and ready to start testing; ETA is tentatively scheduled for 7/15 release.\r\n5/19: Package ID for the utility is E758767.  This utility is still scheduled to be delivered on or before 5/29.  Utility req by Dr. Hoberman\r\n3/30:Per Joyce Y, AMB will remove the long-term push pin from all meds marked as long-term.\r\n3/23/27:  Epic responses received 3/26:bridge call w/ Andrea, BYee, Epic, Joyce Yamamoto:  Epic has concerns w/ removing pushpin functionality.  Utility will take a long time, require extensive testing.  3/23: Adhoc auth?ed by NCAL (David Campen) #4692, shell RFC created  ','1. Remove the SnapShot Activity\r\n2. Implement an HTML report (new functionality in displaying SnapShot data) and remove or do not use print groups that display medication information in the report.\r\nIf option 2 if selected for NCAL, NCAL would have to move to HTML first.\r\n',NULL,'1. Remove the SnapShot Activity\r\n2. Implement an HTML report (new functionality in displaying SnapShot data) and remove or do not use print groups that display medication information in the report.\r\nIf option 2 if selected for NCAL, NCAL would have to move to HTML first.\r\n',NULL,'The fix addresses both the HTML & Non-HTML SnapShot activities and clearly indicates in those activities if there are any medications listed that are currently discontinued.  \r\nIt is most likely that this will happen when a medication was marked long-term in the application but then discontinued by the interface without removing the long-term flag.  However, based on profile settings, it is possible for discontinued medications to stay on a patient?s medication list for a period of time after being discontinued to account for the fact that a patient could take a medication before coming in to the office at which time the physician instructs the patient to cease taking the medication ? in this event, the medication may still be active in the patient?s body for a period of time.  \r\nWith this fix, any medications that fit this criteria and display in the SnapShot will clearly indicate that they have been discontinued.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-20 06:04:00','2009-07-29 10:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(317,4324217,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient, Beacon, OpTime, ED - Medication alerts for records with Ca, Fe, Mg, or Zn may not fire or fire inappropriate alerts for patients. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Beacon, OpTime, ED, Inpatient','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-24 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'no Epic fix forthcoming','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'MAR09','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Collaborative build fix;  data will be corrected in 4/16/09 FDB load & should be in prod by 4/29/09\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/2: per PART/Sylvia Fong, prod incremental load completed 4/29, FDB corrected ERX recs.  Closing. ','Because of inconsistent dose checking information in ERX records provided to KP by FDB, medications containing the elements Calcium, Iron, Magnesium, or Zinc, (e.g.. Calcium Carbonate, Calcium Gluconate, Calcium Lactate, Magnesium Sulfate, Magnesium Gluconate) may  not trigger consistent dosing alerts.  For example, FDB dosing alert information that has been inconsistently based on elemental Ca, elemental Ca+base, or other base element records or a combination of both may or may not trigger alerts for specific medication orders.  As a result, those orders may contain incorrect dosages that could contribute to potential Pediatric or Adult overdosing.\r\nTo be impacted, dosing alerts must be enabled as follows: 1) The LSD system record programming point 7740 (dosing rule) is set to use FDB, and 2) the FIS master file filter is set to accept alerts. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3/27: National Pharmacy (Sylvia Fong) has received confirmation from FDB that the data will be corrected in the 4/16/09 incremental load.  If no change in load schedule to PRODNAM, then it should be in production by 4/28.  FDB must develop ways to address correcting these inconsistencies in the ERX records that they provide. FDB has proposed blanking out all records until they decide on how to correct the issue. This is not supported by KP. Sylvia Fong has provided a proposed communication for the regional providers.  Sylvia will distribute for NCAL.  ','National Pharmacy (Sylvia Fong) will issue a communication to regional pharmacists regarding this issue.  Regional Pharmacies will use this communication to notify physicians that dosing alerts for medications containing Ca, Fe, Mg, Zn are not firing. Until a fix is available, physicians should be aware of these inconsistencies and exercise professional medical judgment in ordering these medications.  NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, and Exempla will apply the workaround.\r\nNational Pharmacy (Sylvia Fong) will work with KP Clinical Content to identify inconsistent dose information in affected FDB ERX records and modify those records to ensure consistent dosage checking and alert firing.',NULL,'National Pharmacy (Sylvia Fong) will issue a communication to regional pharmacists regarding this issue.  Regional Pharmacies will use this communication to notify physicians that dosing alerts for medications containing Ca, Fe, Mg, Zn are not firing. Until a fix is available, physicians should be aware of these inconsistencies and exercise professional medical judgment in ordering these medications.  NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, and Exempla will apply the workaround.\r\nNational Pharmacy (Sylvia Fong) will work with KP Clinical Content to identify inconsistent dose information in affected FDB ERX records and modify those records to ensure consistent dosage checking and alert firing.',NULL,'While the problem manifests in ordering these medications, this is not an EPIC code issue. The problem does not require an EPIC fix. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-24 01:44:00','2009-06-02 02:05:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(319,4327835,1,'OPT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SP?08 only - Radiant and OpTime - Orders and Clinical Documentation do not appear in the Unified Clinical Workspace after relinking a log ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Radiant','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-26 00:00:00','2009-07-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'SPR08','A','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No longer an issue for KP since only impacts SP08 and will be fixed in SU09; therefore closed out.\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I768870\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/22/09: CLOSED, SP08 only, does not affect SP07, fixed in SU09.  ',' When a user opens a patient?s log, programming point record 48185-Relink Log and Move Orders checks for either of the following situations:\r\n\r\nThe case date is the current date and the patient has been admitted for the case.\r\nThe patient has been admitted to the ED on the current date or the day prior.\r\n\r\nIf either condition is true, the programming point record unlinks the log from the pre-admission contact and links it to the current admission or ED visit. When this occurs in the Unified Clinical Workspace (UCW), the UCW is not updated to recognize that the log is now linked to the admission. \r\n\r\nAs a result, any ordering or clinical documentation that occurs in the currently open encounter directly after linking is attached to the pre-admission contact that?s no longer linked to the log. When the chart or log is reopened at a later time, the UCW retrieves information from the current admission, and any orders that were placed and attached to the pre-admission contact do not appear.  In addition, if related encounter functionality is not set up, clinical documentation such as flowsheet data and notes may fail to appear in the UCW.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No Current Impact.  SP08 only.  Epic (Adam Sauder) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage.\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,'Discovered by:   Epic, during internal testing\r\nEpic Representative:  Adam Sauder   608-271-9000  \r\nFeatures:   Unified Clinical Workspace, Clinical Documentation, Orders, logs\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-26 01:40:00','2009-07-22 01:40:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(320,4338372,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'IMMINENT-New Medication Reconciliation functionality - Medications may not be saved to patient chart if Accept, Pend, or Cancel button is used in certain navigators and workflows',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inpatient, Pharmacy, ED, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-03-30 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Howard Landa',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'9',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','Y','M','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Fix in progress; most likely July Kpackage; I7511927 had to be removed, but was added back after fixed by I7512376: Confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511927\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609-C75031412\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/27: Per Dhea ok to close.','If the new navigator sections Review Prior to Admission Medications and/or Home Medications are configured to display the buttons Accept, Pend, and/or Cancel, these buttons may not function as expected and could cause user-entered medications to not be saved, in certain workflows. The Pend and Cancel buttons behave differently depending on what value is set in the visit navigator configuration item Keep navigator open when closing Reconciliation Wizard (VCN 35280). This item was introduced in special updates I7511053 (SP\'07) and I767666 (SP\'08).\r\n \r\nFor example, in the following workflow the use of the Accept button will cause medications entered by a user to not be saved to the patient\'s chart:\r\nOpen the Review Prior to Admission Medications or Home Medications navigator section.\r\nModify or add new medications.\r\nPress the Accept button. Nothing appears to change.\r\nModify or add other medications.\r\nMark medications as reviewed or leave the section. The second set of changes made after the Accept button was pressed will not be saved.\r\n \r\nBehaviors triggered by how the Keep navigator open when closing Reconciliation Wizard (VCN 35280)is configured are:\r\nIf set to Yes: the Pend and Cancel buttons display the same behavior as the Accept button, described above.\r\nIf set to No (default) or left empty: clicking the Pend or Cancel button will cause the navigator to close. Any new medications or changes to medications that were not marked as reviewed will not be saved to the patient\'s chart.  This behavior will also occur if the special update is not installed.\r\nAdditions or changes to PTA or Home medications made in the medication reconciliation process may not be saved.  However, most providers usually use Order Entry, Order Set or their preference list to modify medications.  \r\n ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Workaround in place (per Aditi).  4/2 Per Dhea: adhoc NOT needed.3/30/09:  Epic (Greg Hartman) will provide a code fix (which automates the same actions as the workaround by preventing configuration to set these items to Yes)-status by 4/13/09.\r\nPART bridge on 3/31 to discuss issue.\r\n3/31:  Workaround in place (per Aditi). Dhea to f/u and find out if adhoc needed.\r\n4/2 Per Dhea: adhoc NOT needed.','Configure the visit navigator configuration (VCN) records for Review Prior to Admission Medication and Home Medications sections to not display the Accept, Pend or Cancel buttons. \r\nNW has already configured this functionality as part of their build for their Med Rec go live, so they have the workaround already implemented.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, and HI will work with their regional TS\'s to correct the affected configurations before going live with Medication Reconciliation.\r\nThis is an airtight workaround.',NULL,'Configure the visit navigator configuration (VCN) records for Review Prior to Admission Medication and Home Medications sections to not display the Accept, Pend or Cancel buttons. \r\nNW has already configured this functionality as part of their build for their Med Rec go live, so they have the workaround already implemented.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, and HI will work with their regional TS\'s to correct the affected configurations before going live with Medication Reconciliation.\r\nThis is an airtight workaround.',NULL,'Features:  New Med Rec functionality; navigator sections Review Prior to Admission Medications and/or Home Medications configured to show Accept, Pend, and/or Cancel buttons; Special Updates I7511053 (SP\'07) and I767666 (SP\'08) installed\r\nImplement the workaround to remove the Accept, Pend, and Cancel buttons from the Review Prior to Admission Medications and/or Home Medications navigator sections. \r\nThe steps for configuration of the workaround are:\r\nSet the Show Accept item to No\r\nSet the Show Pend item to No\r\nSet the Show Cancel item to No      \r\n\r\nDiscovered by:  Epic, during testing\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-03-30 08:07:00','2009-04-27 08:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(321,4363293,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Duplicate alerts for medication or procedure orders may not fire in Discharge Navigator, in certain circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'Pharmacy, ED, Beacon, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-03 00:00:00','2009-09-09 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'EPIC','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','L','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','Y','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511966, I7511968\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758418, E758673\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/09/09: Per A. Vakil\'s 09/09/09 email, fix implemented successsfully.','Duplicate alerts may not fire as expected if a patient, at discharge, is given a prescription for two medications and/or orders for two procedures.  This can happen in the following workflow:\r\nA patient with an active PTA (prior to admission) prescription is admitted to the hospital.\r\nThe PTA prescription is suspended and then reordered and recorded as an inpatient medication to maintain continuity of care.\r\nThe inpatient order now has a new ORD record while the PTA order remains suspended.\r\nOn discharge, the provider can choose to a) resume or discontinue the suspended outpatient order, or b) prescribe or discontinue the inpatient order as a new outpatient order.\r\nIf both options a and b are chosen, the patient will have two active outpatient orders for the same medication or procedure.  In this case, the two orders are linked together as part of a reorder chain.\r\nDuplicate medication or procedure alerts will not fire as expected.\r\n\r\nIf the reordering functionality is not used to place separate orders, duplicate alerts will fire as expected.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/18/09: PS to f/up with S. Ellis, A. Vakil, cc Brit Mattern, Stan X. Deutsch.\r\n08/04/09: Waiting for Kpkg (May-confirmed).\r\n5/26: waiting for KPKG per Andre.\r\n4/13:  per Bart, NCAL has w/a in place, 2 clinicians reviewing every medication discharge orders. Per Bart procedures not a concern.  We are covered. \r\nEpic (Michael Bries) will inform PART by 4/8/09 if there were any previous instances that required remediation.Epic (Michael Bries) will provide a standard fix in SU\'09.\r\nEpic will provide a pre-SU\'09 code fix only if there is sufficient customer demand.\r\nNo ad hoc was requested.\r\nEpic (Michael Bries) will inform PART by 4/30/09 if a pre-SU\'09 code fix will be planned, based on customer response.','Ensure that duplicate orders are not fulfilled for patients at discharge.  NCAL, SCAL, NW, Exempla, and CO have already implemented this workaround.\r\nEpic (Michael Bries) will include, in the May 2009 KPackage, a programming point that will enable duplicate alerts to fire.','','Ensure that duplicate orders are not fulfilled for patients at discharge.  NCAL, SCAL, NW, Exempla, and CO have already implemented this workaround.\r\nEpic (Michael Bries) will include, in the May 2009 KPackage, a programming point that will enable duplicate alerts to fire.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-06 11:23:00','2009-09-09 11:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(322,4349281,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Chart Review - Cerner CoPath free text data does not display correctly in hyperspace Synoptic reports',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Amb','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-07 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'NCAL',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','M','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  CDR problem fixed at national level to the ability possible- did not require an Epic code fix\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/24:  per Bill Pshea, fixes installed on 6/16/09.  Closing this issue. ','Free text data exported from the Cerner CoPath application to KP HealthConnect as BLOBs (binary large objects) does not display correctly in Hyperspace for Synoptic Pathology reports.  Specifically, the report information is inconsistently wrapped, making it difficult for providers to interpret and use the reports in Hyperspace.\r\n\r\nThe problem is caused by the 78-character line length limit of the CDR (Central Data Repository) which receives data from Cerner as discrete elements.  This line length restriction is unalterable and limits the formatting options of other reports including the Synoptic report, which displays correctly in Cerner but needs more than 78 characters/line to display correctly in Hyperspace.  \r\n\r\nTo be impacted, a region must:\r\nbe using or plan to use Synoptic Pathology reports and \r\nbe connected to the CDR.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/28:  We have completed the modification and testing of the 72 SYNOPTIC reports in the CoPath pre-production system.  Today I will gather the test results and present them to Dr. Metcalf for review.  Assuming that he deems the testing successful, then we will make the same changes in the training system and create an RFC to make these same changes in the production system.\r\n4/8:  per Bill Pshea:  short term solution = chng line length, still evaluating. Possible long term solution:  add tab for path. repts. Patient risk considered low. \r\nNCAL (Dr. John Metcalf and Bill Pshea)  will work with the  Division of Research and with OR Analytic groups to determine when enhancements may be applied to the CDR which would allow greater line length limits.  They may also pursue the alternative of implementing a separate interface for the CDR with the CoPath application.\r\n4/8:  per Bill Pshai:  short term solution = chng line length, still evaluating. Possible long term solution:  add tab for path. repts. Patient risk considered low. ','Ensure that a 78-character line length is standard for all Copath, CDR, and KPHC data exports and reports. Revision of the character line length has resolved the issue for some Synoptic reports (there are over 70) but is still problemmatic in a few reports.  This change, however, has greatly improved the display in KP HealthConnect hyperspace reports.',NULL,'Ensure that a 78-character line length is standard for all Copath, CDR, and KPHC data exports and reports. Revision of the character line length has resolved the issue for some Synoptic reports (there are over 70) but is still problemmatic in a few reports.  This change, however, has greatly improved the display in KP HealthConnect hyperspace reports.',NULL,'This is not an EPIC issue.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-07 02:02:00','2009-06-24 02:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(323,1234567,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1234567,'Brief Description - Test 123','Short Status - Test 123',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Prelude, ADT','','',NULL,NULL,'1952-04-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-05-10 00:00:00',NULL,'fixed by ','epic rep',NULL,'adhoc','','impact ','justify','email activities','init call duration','adhoc comments','files received','kpackage','ets status','2010-04-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'R',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'NOV07','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'part status',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'04/29/09: Move to live, roll out to regions.','Description - Test 123',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Next Step History - Test 123','Work-Around - Test 123',NULL,'Work-Around - Test 123',NULL,'Comments - Test 123',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-10 02:34:00','2009-08-28 03:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(324,4385665,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3595464,'ChartSync - Prior patient history information may not display in remote deployment, under specific conditions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'OpTime, IntraConnect (ChartSync) ','I7512170','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-10 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Andy Wiesenthal',NULL,NULL,'4746','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' ','0529-AP-PR4385665-E758704-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z\r\n0529-AP-PR4385665-E758704-Spr07Jul06NS-Notes.zip','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  SCAL auth ad hoc; Confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512170\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4746):  \n  SP’07 E758704 5/29/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/30: per Kelly R. installed on 6/25 and validated in prod by Herminio Mercado. ',' Previous patient History information may not display when viewed in a remote deployment if all of the following conditions are true:\r\n1. ChartSync is used.\r\n2. Patient history information is viewed in a remote deployment in a report that uses a History-related print group. (The home deployment is unaffected. The History activity does display the information correctly in the remote deployment)\r\n3. SU I7511145/E758039 has been installed. \r\n4. Patient history was not updated since the installation of the SU.\r\n\r\nSpecifically, if a patient\'s history was updated before the above mentioned SU was installed, that history update will either:\r\nNot display, if there was only one pre-SU installation History contact, or\r\nDisplay only the contact from the second most recent day the history was updated, if there were two or more pre-SU installation History contacts. \r\nFor example, if the patient has a contact on 1/4/09 and on 3/1/09, the report will display only the information from the 1/4/09 contact.  If the patient had a history contact on 1/4/09 and multiple history contacts on 3/1/09, the print group will still display the 1/4/09 information.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/9: per Teresa in testing. adhoc received will go in out of cycle.\r\nNCAL AMB decided to not install workaround/waiting for AdHoc.  Expected delivery date 5/28. Outage requirements unknown.\r\n4/29:  per JAngel. AMB wants adhoc. Created adhoc 4746. 4/17:  F/u with AMB & OPT.  More info needed for them to decide what to happen. Epic (Dan Rooney) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its development status by 4/20/09.\r\n4/20:  AMB researching workaround since fix will be delivered in May.\r\n5/6:  NCAL AMB decided to not install the workaround and wait for Epic to deliver the fix.\r\n5/15:  Pkg # E758704, outage requirements unknown. status update 5/21.','Three workaround options are available:\r\nRefer to the History Activity and not history reports for correct information.\r\nRemove affected print group(s) from the history report.  Epic (Dan Rooney) is searching for affected print groups in use and will notify PART, NCAL, and SCAL of query results by 4/13/09.\r\nUsing Patient Highlights functionality, add a new programming point to the LPP record; this will trigger a pop-up warning, if the patient chart is affected, to notify a user that correct History information might not display correctly in reports and that for correct History information, the History activity should be used .\r\nEpic (Dan Rooney) provided  NCAL and SCAL with the programming point 4/10/09.\r\nNCAL (Wei Sun) and SCAL (Linda Gaspard) will implement the programming point by 4/11/09',NULL,'Three workaround options are available:\r\nRefer to the History Activity and not history reports for correct information.\r\nRemove affected print group(s) from the history report.  Epic (Dan Rooney) is searching for affected print groups in use and will notify PART, NCAL, and SCAL of query results by 4/13/09.\r\nUsing Patient Highlights functionality, add a new programming point to the LPP record; this will trigger a pop-up warning, if the patient chart is affected, to notify a user that correct History information might not display correctly in reports and that for correct History information, the History activity should be used .\r\nEpic (Dan Rooney) provided  NCAL and SCAL with the programming point 4/10/09.\r\nNCAL (Wei Sun) and SCAL (Linda Gaspard) will implement the programming point by 4/11/09',NULL,'Discovered by:  Another Epic customer\r\nEpic Representative:  Daniel Rooney \r\nNote:  The usual workflow for physicians writing Consults is to copy and paste History information from reports into their Note.  Until a fix is installed, consulting physicians may consider inserting a SmartLink into their Note to access the correct History information in the History activity.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-10 02:44:00','2009-06-30 01:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(325,4386272,1,'RAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Radiant - Information from multiple linked orders may display incorrectly if a specifically configured Smartlink is used  ','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-13 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Weisenthal','',NULL,'','','','','','','','4/17: Issue Notification PDF file received from EPIC.','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'G',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'RAD','N','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512195\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K071619-E758877\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/10/09: NCI for NCAL--fix in July 09 k-packg','Information from multiple linked orders in Radiant may display incorrectly in notes or reports that use SmartLink RISFRMTLINK (1120001).  For example, some detail information (Date, Diagnosis, etc.) from a Radiology result report of an Abdominal Imaging Procedure may appear in the chest Imaging report for the same patient.  ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'GA only.  Epic (Michael Yandl) will provide a code fix and notify PART by 4/24/09 of its development status.  PART Communications (Chris Okon) will then notify GA and potentially impacted regions.\r\nNo ad hoc was requested.\r\nTo prevent impact, regions are advised to install the code fix when available.','Either of the following two workarounds are suggested:\r\n1. Create a custom override format SmartLink set up with the correct order ID variables for the, or\r\n2. Ensure that the third parameter of the SmartLink is set to 1 wherever the SmartLink is used in Radiant. \r\nGA (Angel Cobiella) will review the workaround options and confirm if the workflow for Linked Orders is standard in GA. He will then communicate the workflow to physicians and work with the GA Epic TS to build the custom SmartLink (workaround #1).\r\n4/21:  Epic (Mike Yandl) has provided the following workaround details to override the RISFRMTLINK SmartLink:   \r\nIn Hyperspace, access the SmartLink Editor and create a new SmartLink.\r\nIn the Override SmartLink field, enter RISFRMTLINK or the name of a SmartLink that uses the code smrtLnk^RISLPP8. Indicate that you want to pull data from the SmartLink you are overriding.\r\nOn the SmartLink tab, change the SmartLink code field to:  s tOrd=%ord d smrtLnk^RISLPP8 s %ord=tOrd\r\nClick Accept.\r\nEpic will still provide Special Updates at a later date, and we will inform you of code development status as we receive it.  HI and NW have already applied workaround #1.\r\n','','Either of the following two workarounds are suggested:\r\n1. Create a custom override format SmartLink set up with the correct order ID variables for the, or\r\n2. Ensure that the third parameter of the SmartLink is set to 1 wherever the SmartLink is used in Radiant. \r\nGA (Angel Cobiella) will review the workaround options and confirm if the workflow for Linked Orders is standard in GA. He will then communicate the workflow to physicians and work with the GA Epic TS to build the custom SmartLink (workaround #1).\r\n4/21:  Epic (Mike Yandl) has provided the following workaround details to override the RISFRMTLINK SmartLink:   \r\nIn Hyperspace, access the SmartLink Editor and create a new SmartLink.\r\nIn the Override SmartLink field, enter RISFRMTLINK or the name of a SmartLink that uses the code smrtLnk^RISLPP8. Indicate that you want to pull data from the SmartLink you are overriding.\r\nOn the SmartLink tab, change the SmartLink code field to:  s tOrd=%ord d smrtLnk^RISLPP8 s %ord=tOrd\r\nClick Accept.\r\nEpic will still provide Special Updates at a later date, and we will inform you of code development status as we receive it.  HI and NW have already applied workaround #1.\r\n',NULL,'NCAL is not currently impacted since they do not use the affected SmartLink and the affected SmartLink configuration, but could be potentially impacted if they do so.\r\n4/17: Issue Notification PDF file received from EPIC.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-13 12:17:00','2009-10-27 09:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(326,4392262,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Clinical Admin - Updates by ICD-9 Code Diagnosis Utility may cause ICD-9 code drift in LQH records with subsequent inaccurate Patient Medical History documentation','','',NULL,NULL,'InPatient, ED, OpTime, Beacon','DLG I7512240, package E758695','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-16 00:00:00','2009-09-30 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','K051809','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'5',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y','N','N','Y','N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Utility available as of 5/06/09; Confirmed in K051809\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512240\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809- E758695.\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/30/09: Closing this issue; per M. Caparas 9/29 email, \"NCAL build is not affected by this issue\".','5/1 PART email: ICD-9 drift could also occur for HMT and LGL records; if the regions want to switch over to the grouper build framework for these records as well, EPIC has developed searches for these master files as well.\r\nUpdates by the ICD-9 Code Diagnosis Update Utility may result in ICD-9 code drift in LQH records.  As a result, LQH records in the History Visit Navigator section may contain updated EDG records such that, when LQH questions are used for documenting Medical History, incorrect or inaccurate history data may be associated with an incorrect diagnosis and incorrect information may display in History Print Groups in reports.\r\n\r\nSpecifically, when the ICD-9 Update Utility runs, the update utility will add to the LQH record all EDG records with an ICD-9 code that matches that of any of the EDG records that are already a part of the LQH record. EDG diagnosis records in an LQH (as well as LGL and HMT) record may incorrectly or unintentionally be added to the LQH record.  \r\n\r\nBecause the ICD-9 code assigned to non-reference diagnosis records can change over time, it is possible that the list of ICD-9 codes for diagnosis records may \"drift\" over time. These EDG records may then manifest an \"ICD 9 drift\", when routine update and propagation of new or different EDG records by the CMT team occurs (generally on a yearly basis). Subsequent documentation using questions in the LQH record may then file to an inappropriate diagnosis and be displayed in History Print Groups which could indicate that a patient has a condition that they do not have.\r\n \r\nFor example: an LQH record that was originally built using a BPH (Benign Prostatic Hypertrophy) diagnosis record, as the Affirmative Diagnosis (item 430 in the LQH record),  may be updated to include a Subphrenic Abscess After Surgery diagnosis (EDG) record.  Documentation using questions for a diagnosis of BPH may now be associated with a diagnosis of Subphrenic Abscess After Surgery.\r\n\r\nNote:  EDG records, identified in EPIC queries as having the ICD-9 drift, generally demonstrated only a slight variation, which is usually from more general to more specific, within the correct \"EDG Family\".  In this case,  grossly inaccurate History information would not occur .  \r\n\r\nThere are, however, some examples of drift in the queries that are questionable and require further analysis.  For example, further analysis has shown that the BPH to Subphrenic Abscess association noted above may have been due to builder error rather than ICD-9 drift.  However, EPIC is recommending to all customers to migrate to the use of VCG groups rather than discrete diagnoses in the Affirmative Diagnosis field of the LQH record.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/29/09: AMB checking if utility needs to be run. Following up with Vicky Santiago (AC) and Drew at EPIC.\r\n09/22/09: Johnette/Marian to f/up with Romulus Tendencia.  Per Chris at Epic, fix was installed. 09/15/09: Johnette is researching status.\r\n08/11/09: 6/30: update request re utility has been sent to Sandra Francisco; no response yet.\r\n6/9: Johnette to check w/Jennifer Angel to see if utility will be run. \r\n5/18:  Johnette to check if NCAL wants to run utility.\r\n4/27: Rebecca/ Chris to follow up with EPIC re long/short term fixes.  Per Dan Rooney: The utility to build VCG groupers should be ready week of May 4.EPIC will supply a utility that will update the build of all regional LQH records to use groupers instead of Affirmative Diagnosis records\r\nEPIC, in conjunction with API and regional teams, will coordinate the initial run of the utility.  EPIC will provide the utility queries of regional LQH records and compiled VCG groups to designated regional representatives.  Tom S. provided Johnette Dee and Jennifer Angel as the NCAL contacts. Epic will provide the utility and notify PART by 4/30 of the utility build status.  The KP CMT team will workd with the regional reps to determine how the new \"LQH Update Utility\" may be integrated into an on going LQH maint process.\r\nLong Term Fix: EPIC will supply a code fix that will disable the ICD-9 Code Update Utility in a future SU.  EPIC will provide a status update by 4/23/09.\r\n5/1 PART email:The SU to disable the ICD-9 update utility is complete for SP08;the SP07 version s/b ready in late May.','Urgent Mitigation:\r\nImplement the workaround.\r\nDo not use the ICD-9 Diagnosis Code Update utility.  (Although this w/a is not doable since it is not currently known who or what initiates the Update utility).\r\nFor ICD-9 code designation in LQH records, change the build of LQH records to use VCG groups.  This can be done manually if regions desire, if they feel that they have LQH records with questionable diagnoses attached, but EPIC recommends the use of a new utility under development to automate this process\r\n','','Urgent Mitigation:\r\nImplement the workaround.\r\nDo not use the ICD-9 Diagnosis Code Update utility.  (Although this w/a is not doable since it is not currently known who or what initiates the Update utility).\r\nFor ICD-9 code designation in LQH records, change the build of LQH records to use VCG groups.  This can be done manually if regions desire, if they feel that they have LQH records with questionable diagnoses attached, but EPIC recommends the use of a new utility under development to automate this process\r\n',NULL,'EPIC reps: Nathan Eckberg, Daniel Rooney\r\nAlthough NCAL is not currently affected, all regions contain LQH records that could be affected as subsequent ICD-9 updates occur.  Therefore all regions need to do remediation and complete the fix.\r\n4/27: Epic searches have been updated to give a clearer picture of what records should be addressed and are being run for each region\r\nThe utility to build VCG groupers should be ready early next week. Running it will be a 3 stage process:\r\nRun the utility for a desired subset of LQH records. This will generate import files for groupers that contain the ICD-9 codes from the EDG records linked to a given LQH.\r\nReview the import files, and use the ones you want to create VCG groupers.\r\nRun the final piece of the utility to attach the VCG groupers to the LQH records.\r\nSUs to disable the problematic ICD-9 update utility are in progress. The SP\'07 version should be available in late May (no confirmed date).\r\nEpic will check in with PART by end of day 4/28 on the status of the grouper utility.\r\n ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-16 01:34:00','2009-09-30 08:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(329,4405935,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Unseen orders can still be signed, under specific conditions','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, Pharmacy, OpTime, Beacon','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Michael Krall','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'G',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','M','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I7512209\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609 - C75031444\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/11/09: Email to D. Lew 11/11 requesting approval to close.','Orders that are placed from a navigator order section but not seen by an end user can still be signed.  This can occur if all of the following conditions are met:\r\nOrder panel is ordered from a navigator order section\r\nAt least one of the constituent orders in the order panel triggers an alternative alert\r\nAn alternative order is selected which triggers a BPA with at least one single order suggestion\r\nUser accepts one of the orders from the BPA.  \r\nAs a result, the alternative order that the user selected is not visible in the navigator order section. If the ordering session is signed, the invisible alternative order is also signed.\r\n\r\nThe problem does not occur in any of these cases:\r\nBPAs are not used with single order suggestions\r\nThere are no order panels with constituent orders that trigger alternatives\r\nOrders are placed from order entry.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/01/09: July kpkg, Nov \'09 install\r\n5/26: Chris will inquire about running search again. Andre to ensure that affected build will not be implemented before fix is installed.\r\n4/27: NCAL not affected at this time. Per Chris still in dev, no due date as of now.\r\nEpic (Greg Hartman) will provide a code fix and notify PART by 4/24/09 its status.\r\nEpic searches indicated that the NW was the only region identified that had the linkages necessary for this issue to occur.  NW (Bonnie Olds) will work with NW Physician (Michael Krall) to complete any changes based on the recommended workaround as appropriate for the region.','Epic (Greg Hartman) suggested the following workarounds:\r\nTemporarily suspend the use of BPAs with single order suggestions. BPA concepts can be rebuilt using OrderSets with a single order.\r\nReplace any medications or procedures in panels that trigger alternatives with the actual alternative record.\r\nVerify that any BPAs with single order suggestions do not trigger based on medications or procedures which are suggested in alternative alerts.\r\nEpic searches indicated that the NW was the only region identified that had the linkages necessary for this issue to occur.  NW (Bonnie Olds) will work with NW Physician (Michael Krall) to complete any changes based on the recommended workaround as appropriate for the region.','','Epic (Greg Hartman) suggested the following workarounds:\r\nTemporarily suspend the use of BPAs with single order suggestions. BPA concepts can be rebuilt using OrderSets with a single order.\r\nReplace any medications or procedures in panels that trigger alternatives with the actual alternative record.\r\nVerify that any BPAs with single order suggestions do not trigger based on medications or procedures which are suggested in alternative alerts.\r\nEpic searches indicated that the NW was the only region identified that had the linkages necessary for this issue to occur.  NW (Bonnie Olds) will work with NW Physician (Michael Krall) to complete any changes based on the recommended workaround as appropriate for the region.',NULL,'EPIC contact:Greg Hartman, GHartman@epicsystems.com, (608) 271-9000',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-17 11:00:00','2009-11-11 03:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(330,4406544,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Orders May Not Be Scheduled as Intended With Frequency Changes in User Overrides','','',NULL,NULL,'Pharmacy, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-17 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'Andy Weisenthal','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'G',NULL,'2',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  In K070609, but not as addressing this incident (does address 4406504) \r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7511980\r\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4760):  \r\n  SP?07 E758780, C75031424 5/26/09 & E758871 7/28/09\r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP?07 K070609-E758780 & C75031424\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/21/09: Per Aditi\'s 12/14 email, she was not involved with the config.  Sent F/up email to Andre.','An inpatient order may not be scheduled as intended if all of the following conditions are true:\r\nThe order has been saved to a preference list or SmartGroup with either a When, Continuous, or Non-Specified type frequency as well as a default start time;\r\nThe user changes the frequency to a Specified type in a user level override without changing the default start time;\r\nThe default start time is in the future at the time the order is placed.  \r\n\r\nThe first dose or occurrence will be scheduled for the next scheduled time after the default start time rather than having a dose or occurrence scheduled at the default start time.\r\n \r\nThis issue affects inpatient medications (SU\'05 and later) and procedures (SP\'08 only) placed from user overrides of Composer-based Preference Lists, Protocol-based Order Sets and LGQ/OTL-based Order Sets.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'12/13/09: Helen sent email 12/13 to A. Vakil to confirm config after install was completed.\r\n11/11/09: A. Mure to certify.\r\n10/27/09: Andre to confirm plan for config with Aditi.\r\n10/20/09: 6/16: config will be done after install (Nov) per Andre. \r\n5/11: Per Andre search results reviewed, no action required. Will wait for KPKG, fixed by configuration.\r\n4/27: T. Stewart forwarded search results to Andre and Bart.Epic (Kristie Reimer) will provide a code fix and notify PART by 4/24/09 of its status.\r\nAn ad hoc code fix was not requested.\r\nHI, NW, NCAL, SCAL, Exempla will install the code fix in a Kpackage when available. \r\nA search has been created to find affected orders, and was sent to PART.','Urgent Mitigation:  \r\nImplement the workaround based on search results\r\n\r\nWorkaround:  \r\nChange the frequency of the user level override in the editor and then perform either of the following workarounds:\r\nSelecting the \"As Scheduled\" option to clear out any unintended offset start dates and times, or \r\nRe-enter the start time to cause the order to schedule as expected with the first dose/occurrence at the start time.\r\nHI, NW, NCAL, SCAL, and Exempla will work with Physicians and/or Regional build teams to correct the affected ordering tools with the appropriate workaround.\r\n','','Urgent Mitigation:  \r\nImplement the workaround based on search results\r\n\r\nWorkaround:  \r\nChange the frequency of the user level override in the editor and then perform either of the following workarounds:\r\nSelecting the \"As Scheduled\" option to clear out any unintended offset start dates and times, or \r\nRe-enter the start time to cause the order to schedule as expected with the first dose/occurrence at the start time.\r\nHI, NW, NCAL, SCAL, and Exempla will work with Physicians and/or Regional build teams to correct the affected ordering tools with the appropriate workaround.\r\n',NULL,'Kristie Reimer kreimer@epicsystems.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-17 11:16:00','2009-12-21 10:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(331,4405776,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3563782,'Unauthorized users can discontinue medications in Medication Reconciliation Workflow','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB Rx, IP, all reg','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Michael Krall','',NULL,'4734','','','','','','','0701-AP-PR4405776-E758961-C75031470-Spr07Sep14NS.tar.Z\r\n0701-AP-PR4405776-E758961-C75031470-Spr07Sep14NS.zip\r\n0701-AP-PR4405776-E758961-C75031470-Spr07Sep14NS-Notes.zip','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','A','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Not much of a workaround for ambulatory; most likely a utility component to the SU & will need manual analysis; Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512362\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4734 (NCAL)):  \n  SP’07 E758961 & C75031470 7/01/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/06/09: per Y. Lassiter NCAL not affected (per Aditi).  No ad hoc, will install with Sept Kpkg. ',' An unauthorized user can discontinue medication orders in one of the following three Medication Reconciliation related workflows: \r\n\r\n1.  An unauthorized user may submit a medication order for physician review, to be approved and signed for submittal.  Since the order is already Active, a pop-up window appears that indicates that the medication order for that medication is already Active. The pop-up window allows the  unauthorized user to discontinue the medication in KPHC.  The medication is discontinued in HealthConnect but not discontinued in NCAL\'s PIMS Pharmacy medication system.\r\n2.  An unauthorized user right-clicks in the Medication Activity which brings up a pop-up action window that allows the user to discontinue a medication.  The medication is discontinued in HealthConnect but not discontinued in NCAL\'s PIMS Pharmacy medication system.\r\n3.  An unauthorized user may enter the Medication Activity and click the Reorder/Change button.  This pends the order for the provider, who may then approve and sign the order although the old prescription is now discontinued.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/24/09: Per Y. Lassiter\'s 9/24 email: AMB will own this Ad Hoc\r\n09/15/09: Johnette & Yolanda to follow up if waiting for Kpkg or pursue an Adhoc.\r\n08/05/09: Per S. Balicante\'s 8/5 email \"Apparently the \'escalation flag\' is an EPIC internal lingo to notify TS from other regions of the importance of a particular issue\". \r\n8/4: Per Johnette, J. Yamamoto is working with pharmacy. \r\n08/04/09: waiting for July 09 k-packg/Nov install--at least AMB affected. \r\n7/8:  per JDee / SBalicanta:  escalation flag has not been installed.  Waiting for Sept K-pckg 6/30: Johnette to f/up with Joyce re status of escalation flag. Per Chris (Epic) kpckg delivery date s/b 9/14.  \r\n6/17: per Joyce Y., the new security point directly applies to Amb and Inpatient and indirectly impacts Pharmacy.\r\n5/19:  per Joyce Y, AMB wants the escalation flag, will contact Ryan. Checking w/Joyce regarding status.\r\n6/9:  per Ryan H:  (The ad hoc fix (#4734), which will include a security point to allow discontinuing medications, is targeted for a 7/01/09 delivery. A utility component will be included in order to add the security point to existing security classes. Affected regions will then need to manually determine which security classes should not have this security point available and remove it as necessary.\r\nThe fix is expected to be in the 070609 KPackage; this date will be confirmed by the time the ad hoc is delivered. A full outage will be required to install the fix.)\r\n\r\nUpdate per S. Balicante\'s 7/8 email:\r\nThe recent data received from Pharmacy is that the problem is mostly from Inpatient nurses.  The adhoc will not help them.  Inpatient will work with Pharmacy to identify nursing workflows surrounding d/c meds.\r\nIn Amb, we have removed the d/c button from Meds activity a while back.  It did not completely resolve the issue, but it did help reduce errors in PIMS.\r\nWe will have to coordinate this adhoc with Security, prior to installing and testing.\r\nFinally, we will wait for this in the September Kpkg so that other testing in progress is not disrupted, and to take advantage of kpkg regression.\r\n\r\n AMB wants the escalation flag, will contact Ryan.  R Habbley\'s 5/7 email: \r\nDue to the size of the project, there are two more levels of approval that are required before we can start looking at a delivery timeline; in the event that approval is not granted at either of those levels, I have drafted an escalation flag and that can be put into place as soon as necessary.\r\n4/27:  PART to get update from Ryan Habbley--when can we expect adhoc?\r\nAdHoc - 4734.  Epic (Ryan Habbley) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its development status by 4/24/09.','Workaround = Urgent Mitigation:  \r\nEnforce policy that practitioners should not carry out actions beyond their clinical scope of practice.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, Exempla, CO, MAS, OH, and GA will enforce scope of practice limitations.','','Workaround = Urgent Mitigation:  \r\nEnforce policy that practitioners should not carry out actions beyond their clinical scope of practice.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, Exempla, CO, MAS, OH, and GA will enforce scope of practice limitations.',NULL,'Epic contact - Ryan Habbley / rhabbley@epicsystems.com\r\nFeatures: Medication Activity, Discontinuing medications \r\nProbable Clinical Severity: Probable Moderate, Possible Severe\r\nPer Ryan Habbley\'s email dated 5/8/09:\r\nIn regards to your question about the true discontinuing user, the system uses the information of whoever clicked on the button.  So, if a nurse or MA clicks the reorder button in the medications activity or pends a new order in Order Entry and chooses to discontinue the existing order, even though the existing order may not be discontinued until the new order is signed, the nurse or MA is recorded as the discontinuing user.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-20 07:49:00','2009-10-06 02:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(332,4404533,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Incorrect Insulin Order in Department and Personal Preference Lists',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-20 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Andy Weisenthal',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','M','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No code fix required; regional data fix only\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/28:  Closed, per Iris Young','Due to user error during the build process in NCAL only, an incorrect display name for an insulin medication order appeared in an Ambulatory APC (Adult Primary Care) Preference List that may have been copied to Physicians\' Personal Preference Lists.  The display name -- Insulin NPH 100 units/ml injection, 10 units qhs (at night) or ud (use as directed), inject 30 units @ bedtime or as directed -- had contradictory dosages. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4/28:  per Iris:  \"Yes, the Orders Preference List has been fixed.  The correction was done on 4/16 by the Ambulatory Build team.  It was not a Epic code issue, but simply a human error. There is also no additional correction that\'s required at this time. \"\r\nEpic (Adam Buckingham) ran searches in NCAL production for the last six months and found that some patients had active affected orders.  However, even the higher dosage of 30 units is appropriate for many of those patients. The queries indicated that only one Physician had saved the order to a personal Preference List.  NCAL immediately contacted that physician who removed or corrected that order. NCAL Pharmacy (Iris Young) reviewed the query with other Pharmacists and Physicians to determine if orders were incorrect and if any require a change or reevaluation.  ','No workaround is available or needed. \r\nUrgent Mitigation:  \r\nNCAL discovered this issue on 4/16/09 and immediately remediated the order in the APC Departmental Preference List. ',NULL,'No workaround is available or needed. \r\nUrgent Mitigation:  \r\nNCAL discovered this issue on 4/16/09 and immediately remediated the order in the APC Departmental Preference List. ',NULL,'Epic Representative: Adam Buckingham',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-21 09:03:00','2009-04-28 09:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(333,4412230,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Results routing schemes might share compiled routine names','','',NULL,NULL,'Amb, ED, Optime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-20 00:00:00','2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Scott Adelman','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'6',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Regional Data fix\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/01/09: closing; config fix only, no code fix. Per CRussell, DDavies will check with Jansin about clean-up. ','Prior to SP\'06, results routing schemes (LRS) that were duplicated may incorrectly have the same routine names (I LRS 30).  As a result, some results messages may have been misrouted without reaching the intended recipient.   Although this problem was fixed in SP\'07, a few records still shared the same name, most likely because they were rarely used or not used at all.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Waiting for Kpkg.  NCAL not affected.  Colorado/Exempla affected.\r\nEpic (Amy Bowers) will perform the fix.\r\nCO (Michael DuPont) will review this fix with Exempla and coordinate carrying out the fix.\r\n5/18:  NCAL not affected.','No workaround is needed.','','No workaround is needed.',NULL,'EPIC rep: Amy E Bowers',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-21 09:35:00','2009-09-02 09:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(334,4394478,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'No Current Impact: Abnormal Results Not Flagged in Flowsheet Rows.','','',NULL,NULL,'Inpatient, ED, MyChart','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'P',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28/09: 6/2: Epic has determined that the fix for this incident will not be done before SP\'08 or SU\'09.  ','Review flowsheet rows built using flowsheet part 2025-Transplant Result Common Name (Use Pt. Thresholds) do not indicate when a result is abnormal--that is, they are not flagged by yellow highlighting and the letter A at the result value.  Without these indicators, clinical users might not notice that certain results are abnormal.  The issue occurs whether or not the abnormal value is outside of the patient-specific thresholds or the default reference ranges. In addition, reports that rely on this flowsheet may also fail to indicated abnormal results. \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Danielle Dyer) ran a search to confirm that no regions have the affected configuration.  Regions are strongly advised not to use the affected config until SU09 goes in.  ','','','',NULL,'Epic Representatives:  Danielle Dyer, Dustin Foster',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-23 08:57:00','2009-09-28 03:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(335,4420433,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Print Group Might Not Display Correct Allergy and Medication Information. No regions are currently using the affected functionality','','',NULL,NULL,'Reports, Chart Review, print groups that cal routine UPArep^LYRC','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-22 00:00:00','2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7511997\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809-E758624\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/18/09: Close after 8/19 install.','Allergy and medication information do not appear correctly in print groups that call the routine UPArep^LYRCCF05. For example, the print group displays \"No Known Allergies\" and a verification date even if the patient has a documented and verified allergy.  \r\n\r\nIf a patient is admitted, only medications ordered during the admission appear. For example, outpatient medications that have been suspended do not appear. If no medications have been ordered during the admission, the print group displays \"Patient has no current medications,\" regardless of whether the patient has any outpatient prescriptions. \r\n\r\nThe routine UPArep^LYRCCF05 was released in SP\'07 but was not included in any Epic standard print groups. The routine would need to be deliberately added to new or modified print groups.  ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: fix in May 2009 K-package\r\nEpic (Jason Ramaker) ran a search to confirm that no regions have the affected configuration','','','',NULL,'Epic Representative:  Jason Ramaker',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-23 09:55:00','2009-09-01 08:10:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(336,4425382,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Ambulatory - AVS or clinical summary may not print correctly, in certain conditions','','',NULL,NULL,'','There are two required DLGs for the fix: I7512274 & I7512326  ','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-24 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. George Parridy','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7512274 & I7512326\r\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \r\n  SP?07 fix expected on 7/15/09\r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP?07  K091409- E759039 & E758993\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/29/09: Waiting for Sept. Kpkg.  NCAL not affected, no adhoc needed (per Joyce).',' Server-side printed reports of an AVS (After Visit Summary) or a clinical summary may not wrap correctly at page breaks, depending on how the print groups are formatted and how much information needs to be displayed. Specifically, if print groups or copies do not follow a style sheet, it is possible for the line at a page break to wrap incorrectly and not align with appropriate columns.  The information itself is unaffected, but how it is displayed could cause confusion.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/11/09: Helen to f/up with Johnette.\r\n7/7: per R Habbley, SU will be available on Wed 7/15/09. Full outage required.\r\n6/30: Per William Yu, NCAL only uses 2 of the affected print groups and only affects the print group if we don?t use the style sheet and if this is a server side printing.6/9: Johnette to F/up with Jennifer Angel.\r\n5/26: Johnette to forward query results. AMB to review query results. Checking w/Johnette regarding status update.\r\n5/1:  per Epic (R. Habbley):  use of stylesheets with IE6 should be acceptable.  4/24/09:  Query results received. AMB to review query results.  Epic to send query results. f/u with AMB after results received.\r\n5/18: Johnette to forward query results. AMB to review query results.','Epic (Ryan Habbley) will send search results of affected print groups. The results will also include a list of affected print groups.\r\nTo prevent the problem, regions may enable style sheets for affected reports, print groups and copies.\r\nIf a print group cannot be used with a style sheet, Epic (Ryan Habbley) will provide a manual adjustment to the specified line length.  For example, certain style sheets can be enabled only if IE version 7 is used;  however, this version of Internet Explorer is not yet supported at Kaiser.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, HI, Exempla, CO, GA, OH, MAS are advised to review their respective search results and either utilize a style sheet or change the line length parameters in the print group.','remediate.','Epic (Ryan Habbley) will send search results of affected print groups. The results will also include a list of affected print groups.\r\nTo prevent the problem, regions may enable style sheets for affected reports, print groups and copies.\r\nIf a print group cannot be used with a style sheet, Epic (Ryan Habbley) will provide a manual adjustment to the specified line length.  For example, certain style sheets can be enabled only if IE version 7 is used;  however, this version of Internet Explorer is not yet supported at Kaiser.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, HI, Exempla, CO, GA, OH, MAS are advised to review their respective search results and either utilize a style sheet or change the line length parameters in the print group.',NULL,'Regions:  NCAL, SCAL, HI, Exempla, CO, GA, OH, MAS are currently impacted.  NW could be potentially impacted.\r\nApplications:   Ambulatory\r\nReleases:  SP\'06-SP\'08\r\nFeatures:  Print groups used in AVS or clinical summary reports; style sheets\r\nRegions:  NCAL, SCAL, HI, Exempla, CO, GA, OH, MAS are currently impacted.  NW could be potentially impacted.\r\nDiscovered by:  Epic during testing\r\nEpic Representative:  Ryan Habbley',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-24 12:49:00','2010-06-14 12:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(337,4442406,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'User Version Order Sets may display incorrect Frequency','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-04-29 00:00:00','2009-09-22 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder','',NULL,'','','','','','','SCAL to adhoc','0526-AP-TD35444-E758780-C75031424-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z\r\n0526-AP-TD35444-E758780-C75031424-Spr07Jul06NS.zip','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'3',NULL,NULL,'APR09','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K070609\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4760):  \n  SP’07 E758780 & C75031424 5/26/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/22/09: Per S. Ellis and D. Lew, ok to close, certification completed.','In different sessions, within the User OS build, when multiple orders (from within the same smartgroup or other smartgroups) are defaulted with a Frequency Starting ?Tomorrow?; the specific time recorded in previous settings is overwritten with ?0000? without informing the user.\r\n\r\nThe problem occurs in the following workflow:\r\nPull up any Order Set.\r\nClick ?Create User Order Set?\r\nIdentify an order and set it to Starting ?Tomorrow? and designate a time.  Default the order.\r\nNote summary sentence.\r\nAccept and view User OrderSet in patient chart.\r\nThe order should appear appropriately.\r\nClick on ?Edit User Order Set.?\r\nSelect another order in the same OSQ/section or an entirely different one.\r\nSet that order to Starting ?Tomorrow? and designate a same or different time than the original order. Default the order.\r\nCompare the two summary sentences; they should read as you configured them.\r\nAccept the changes and return to the patient chart.\r\nNote that the first order?s execution time has been changed to midnight (0000), but the second order is configured correctly.\r\nIf you continue to edit the Order Set and change other orders following the same steps, only the latest edits will retain the correct time and all previous orders will default to midnight (0000)\r\n\r\nPer PART email dated 5/11, per K Reimer an additional scenario will affect existing default start time: \r\n1. You have an existing default start time (in either a Base Order Set or a User Order Set) that is earlier than the current time, and \r\n2. you create a User Order Set or edit your existing User Order Set.  ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/15/09: Follow up email sent to S. Ellis on 9/15.\r\n08/18/09: PS to f/up with S. Ellis re certification.\r\n08/11/09: adhoc files received May 26.  Per A. Thorup w/a not needed.\r\n08/04/09: targeting 8/19 for fix.  Fix also fixes 4709807.\r\n6/30: per Dhea, adhoc recvd in May; s/b in Aug release. Sherry Ellis to ask Dr. H is communication is needed6/9: files received; will be in Aug ?09 release. Tom S. to f/up with Sherry.\r\n5/26: Andrea to f/up with Sherry re w/a and any required education.  Checking w/Andrea regarding status update.\r\n5/11: Per PART email, K Reimer provided an additional scenario that will affect default start time; it is documented in the description section below. \r\n5/6:  per KReimer, Epic is unable to develop searches to identify affected User OrderSets.  The workaround discussed last week is still the recommended workaround. NCAL will prob need communication to users.  Sherry J Ellis to own.  Andre to check w/ Dr. Hoberman / Bettianne','5/12:  simplified w/a: \r\nUntil a fix is available, users should review the start time before signing orders.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, and NW will perform the workaround and also develop and send an appropriate communication to providers.','','5/12:  simplified w/a: \r\nUntil a fix is available, users should review the start time before signing orders.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, and NW will perform the workaround and also develop and send an appropriate communication to providers.',NULL,'Discovered by SCAL.  Kristie Reimer from Epic',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-04-29 04:07:00','2009-09-22 10:42:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(338,4446731,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Drug-Allergen interaction alerts may not appear for deleted FDB medications, under specific conditions','','',NULL,NULL,'Inpatient. Rx, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-05-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'N/A','',NULL,'','','','','','','','0427-AP-PR4245688-E758536-Spr07May18NS.tar.Z\r\n1106-AP-PR4446731-E759403-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z (adhoc 5023)','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  12-15-09\r\nNOTES:  Two fixes; first one same fix as PR 4245688; Confirmed in K051809, second fix  (utility SU) available; Confirm with Pharm in mid-Dec\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n   I7511975 / E758536 & I7512814\r\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4742 & 5023):  \r\n  SP?07 E758536 4/27/09 & E759403 11/6/09 \r\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \r\n  SP?07 K051809 & K111609\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/21/09: R. Blair sent a f/up email to S. Fong on 12/16.','Drug-allergen alerts may not appear for medications marked as deleted by First DataBank (FDB).  This occurs if all of the following conditions are true:  \r\n\r\nMedications and allergens are loaded from FDB.\r\nIn EMR System Definitions, the Create meds that are deleted by vendor field (I LSD 4201) is set to No or is left blank;\r\nIn EMR System Definitions, the Include medical supplies as allergens field (I LSD 4410) is set to Yes.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/06/09: Ad hoc 5023 was added 10/28 per C. Tran\'s request.\r\n10/23/09: Per S. Fong FDB fix s/b mid Dec.; B. Yee has assigned someone to f/up on ad hoc.\r\n10/20/09: R. Blair to f/up with S. Fong; adhoc or kpkg for 2nd fix?\r\n5/4: Waiting for Kpkg.  Fixed in the May pkg along with 4245688.\r\nNo Current Impact--see comments','Epic (Dustin Foster) has already provided a code fix which is shared with PART Incident 4245688:  DLG- I7511975 / E758536; ad hoc #4742; in May 2009 KPackage; no outage needed. will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.','','Epic (Dustin Foster) has already provided a code fix which is shared with PART Incident 4245688:  DLG- I7511975 / E758536; ad hoc #4742; in May 2009 KPackage; no outage needed. will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.',NULL,'Epic (Michael Bries) ran a search for all regions and determined that none had the affected configuration.\r\nThis incident is related to PART Incident 4245688 and shares the same code fix.  NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, MAS, GA, OH, CO, Exempla could be potentially impacted if they modify the configuration to be affected without having installed the fix.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-01 11:59:00','2009-12-21 10:04:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(339,4449426,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT  - Ambulatory  - Default immunization dose can override ordered medication dose, in certain circumstances',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-05-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SIGS','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No plans to use discrete sigs in near future so no current impact\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6/30: will close this issue; Johnette will notify if it needs to be re opened.','A modified medication dose may not be reflected in the Immunizations/Injections activity if all of the following conditions are in place:\r\n\r\nA procedure (EAP) that is linked to an immunization (LIM) record along with a corresponding medication (ERX) record is ordered.\r\nThe dose of the ERX is manually modified.\r\nInpatient workflows only: the Immunization / Injection activity is used to administer the medication. NOTE: Administration via the MAR is not impacted.\r\nAmbulatory workflows only: discrete sigs are used.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Since the issue is corrected in build, Epic (Dustin Foster) is not planning a code fix','Fix:  \r\nSince the issue is corrected in build, Epic (Dustin Foster) is not planning a code fix\r\nOnce discrete sigs are used, regions are advised to correct the immunizations and injections build in either of the following ways:\r\nCreate a procedure record and link to an immunizations record. Using this configuration, the clinician orders only the procedure. \r\nCreate a procedure record for the administration and do not link it to an immunization. Using this configuration, the clinician orders both the procedure for the administration and the corresponding medication.',NULL,'Fix:  \r\nSince the issue is corrected in build, Epic (Dustin Foster) is not planning a code fix\r\nOnce discrete sigs are used, regions are advised to correct the immunizations and injections build in either of the following ways:\r\nCreate a procedure record and link to an immunizations record. Using this configuration, the clinician orders only the procedure. \r\nCreate a procedure record for the administration and do not link it to an immunization. Using this configuration, the clinician orders both the procedure for the administration and the corresponding medication.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-01 06:18:00','2009-06-30 02:07:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(340,4466699,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'KPHC Potential Patient Safety Issue- Affiliate Link','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,'2009-05-07 11:15:40','2009-05-07 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Wiesenthal','',NULL,'4829','','','','','','GA asked for adhoc','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'0',NULL,'0','M',NULL,'NCI','N','S','P','B',' ','Y','S',NULL,'Clo',NULL,NULL,NULL,'M','N','N','Y','N','Y','Y','Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',60,'2009-07-13 11:10:28',NULL,'Infrastructure Software','PART KPHC','NOTES:  Confirmed Client package in K091409; Problem with fix, per Renee Walton (11/24) only successfully installed in MAS and SCAL\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512099\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4829):  \n  SP’07 C75031468 7/02/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409\n','KPHC Environment','Patient Safety issue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: R. Blair will f/up with Dustin @ Epic to see if server pkg has been received.','KPHC Potential Patient Safety Issue- Affiliate Link Displays Incorrect Patient Information',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NCAL not affected (doesn\'t use AffiliateLink)\r\nTrack until fix received in kpackage and installed in prod','As soon as possible, communicate to affiliate providers that they should not open more than one patient chart at a time.\r\nThree options are recommended to communicate with affiliate providers, and regions should use as many as are feasible.\r\n1.  Display a system broadcast message when Affiliate Link users first log on. This message must be no more than 220 characters. The recommended text is:\r\nWARNING!\r\nTo prevent a potential patient safety issue, do not open more than one chart on the same computer at the same time.\r\nSee {REGIONAL CHOICE e.g. home page, In the News} for details.\r\n2.  Display the following Urgent Message on the home page, in the \"In the News\" section, or other commonly viewed page used by your region.\r\n3.  If InBasket functionality is enabled, include the following Urgent Message in an email sent to affiliate providers. \r\nURGENT MESSAGE TO ALL AFFILIATE PROVIDERS \r\nWe were recently alerted to a potential software issue that may cause patient charts to display incorrectly in certain situations.\r\nIf two patient charts are open at the same time, the header and patient information may not match.  \r\nPlease open only one chart at a time on the same computer and be sure to close it before opening a second chart.  \r\nWe are working with our vendors to correct this issue. Once we have remedied the situation, we will notify you immediately. \r\nThank you.','','As soon as possible, communicate to affiliate providers that they should not open more than one patient chart at a time.\r\nThree options are recommended to communicate with affiliate providers, and regions should use as many as are feasible.\r\n1.  Display a system broadcast message when Affiliate Link users first log on. This message must be no more than 220 characters. The recommended text is:\r\nWARNING!\r\nTo prevent a potential patient safety issue, do not open more than one chart on the same computer at the same time.\r\nSee {REGIONAL CHOICE e.g. home page, In the News} for details.\r\n2.  Display the following Urgent Message on the home page, in the \"In the News\" section, or other commonly viewed page used by your region.\r\n3.  If InBasket functionality is enabled, include the following Urgent Message in an email sent to affiliate providers. \r\nURGENT MESSAGE TO ALL AFFILIATE PROVIDERS \r\nWe were recently alerted to a potential software issue that may cause patient charts to display incorrectly in certain situations.\r\nIf two patient charts are open at the same time, the header and patient information may not match.  \r\nPlease open only one chart at a time on the same computer and be sure to close it before opening a second chart.  \r\nWe are working with our vendors to correct this issue. Once we have remedied the situation, we will notify you immediately. \r\nThank you.',NULL,'NCAL not impacted, does not use AffiliateLink',NULL,'1241811506ï££D111116ï££Resolution Action:  Upgraded Application\nResolution Description:  \nCause Code 1:  Business Partner\nCause Code 2:  \nCause Description:  ï£¢',NULL,60,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-08 12:56:00','2009-10-20 02:15:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(341,4470890,1,'RX',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SP?07 - Inpatient - Order Entry/New Med Rec functionality - Orders created in Order Entry and then modified, signed and held in a non-med rec navigator may remain active when the modified order is released from a New Med Rec navigator','','',NULL,NULL,'MedRec, IP, Rx, opt','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-05-08 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Michael Krall','',NULL,'','','','','','','SCAL to adhoc','','N/A','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','Y','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  SCAL decided didnt need ad hoc; Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512373\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409- C75031507\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28/09: Sept KPKG, 2/2010 install','An original order may not be discontinued if all three of the following are true:\r\nthe order was created using Order Entry and then signed\r\nthe order was modified and signed and held in a non-med rec navigator (e.g. rounding navigator)\r\nthe order was then released in a New Med Rec navigator\r\nTo reproduce:\r\nPlace an inpatient order in Order Entry.  Sign.\r\nIn a non-med-rec navigator (like a rounding navigator), modify the order.  Sign and Hold the modification.\r\nIn a med rec navigator, go to the New Orders Section and click on the \"Select and Release Pended/Held Orders? link.\r\nSelect the order (do not release). This will pull the order into the navigator.\r\nGo to the Review and Summary section and Sign the order.\r\nIn order view, the original order is shown as still active along with the new signed order just signed. The original order should have been discontinued. In addition, no duplicate alert will fire.\r\nFeatures:  Order Entry/New Med Rec functionality',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Waiting for Kpkg.  Per Aditi Vakil?s email, \"NCAL is not affected by this since we don?t have the \"Select and Release Pended Orders\" link in the new Orders Rec navigators.\r\n6/17: update continuation from Aditi; adhoc not needed, KPKG ok.\r\n5/11: Andre/Andrea to check with Bettianne/Dr. Hoberman re work around options. per Chris restricted to med orders.\r\nWorkaround in place.  Check if adhoc is wanted (scal to adhoc). No affected orders were found in any region.\r\nEpic will provide a fix and notify PART by 5/15/09 of its status.\r\n','Report results from Epic (Maria Spinozzi) revealed no currently impacted records for NW, NCAL, and SCAL.\r\nEither or both of the following two workarounds are recommended:\r\nDisable the \"Select and Release Pended Orders\" button \r\nComplete all steps in one navigator (do not move from med rec to non med rec).\r\n','','Report results from Epic (Maria Spinozzi) revealed no currently impacted records for NW, NCAL, and SCAL.\r\nEither or both of the following two workarounds are recommended:\r\nDisable the \"Select and Release Pended Orders\" button \r\nComplete all steps in one navigator (do not move from med rec to non med rec).\r\n',NULL,'NW, NCAL, and SCAL are impacted since they all have the functionality and/or configuration that cause the issue. However, no affected orders were currently found in production.\r\nEpic Representative:  Maria Spinozzi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-08 01:48:00','2009-09-28 03:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(342,4482098,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Beacon - Medication orders that are modified, pended, and held may not appear correctly in treatment plan ','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB, Inpatient','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-05-13 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'BCON','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512388\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759056\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28/09: Sept KPKG, 2/2010 install',' If a clinician modifies a treatment plan order after it has been released, and then pends or signs and holds the order, the modified order does not appear correctly in the treatment plan.  To be impacted, a region must allow clinicians to modify a signed facility-administered medication without discontinuing the original order.  \r\nSpecifically, this issue does not occur if the Allowed Medication Modifications field in EMR System Definitions, which controls this feature, is blank.  NOTE: Beacon treatment plans and simple treatment plans are impacted: \r\nThe issue may occur in either of the following two workflows:\r\n1. The order appears in the treatment plan with the modifications and a note that the order reflects post-release modifications. However, the modifications have not been finalized and should not appear in the treatment plan until the pended order is signed or the held order is released.\r\n2. If the clinician removes the modifications, the original order appears in the treatment plan and the modifications are appropriately removed. However, the order appears as an unreleased order instead of a released order. A clinician can release the order again, which could result in the medication being administered twice to the patient if the clinician or other clinicians do not notice that two orders appear in the MAR for the same medication.\r\nExample:\r\n1. A patient arrives at the oncology infusion center for his/her chemotherapy infusion appointment.\r\n2. The nurse releases the patient?s treatment plan orders, including an order for a 10 mg Decadron injection.\r\n3. Later, the oncologist decides to change the dose of the Decadron. He accesses the Medications activity, selects the Decadron order, and clicks Modify.\r\n4. After clicking modify, Order Entry automatically opens, and the order appears. The oncologist changes the dose to 20 mg and pends the order.\r\n5. In the treatment plan, the order appears with the modifications, even though the modifications have not been signed.\r\n6. The oncologist then decides to remove the modifications for the Decadron injection. He or she opens Order Entry and clicks the Remove button next to the pended order.\r\n7. The order now appears as unreleased in the treatment plan. This is inaccurate, as the order was released previously (in step two). \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'5/13:  forwarded PART email to Sheryl Balicanta, Dorinda Wong, Kirk Ryan','NCI--no W/A needed','','NCI--no W/A needed',NULL,'Epic (Kristie Reimer)  reviewed the system configuration in all regions live on Beacon and has determined that no region has the configuration necessary to be affected.  However, NCAL, SCAL, NW, CO, GA, and MAS could be potentially impacted if they use Beacon with the affected features without installing the fix.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-13 11:16:00','2009-09-28 03:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(343,4482067,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - IMS substitution in Refill workflows may lead to incorrect dosing','','',NULL,NULL,'all others','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-05-13 00:00:00','2009-11-23 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'NCI','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512280\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609-E758798\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/24/09: Per V. Santiago, ok to close, NCAL not affected.','Intelligent medication selection (IMS) is a process by which EpicCare selects the most appropriate medication strength to order, based on the dose. For example, upon ordering, IMS may change a medication?s sig from ?two 10 mg pills daily? to ?one 20 mg tablet daily.?  When IMS is implemented, IMS will be active for refilled prescriptions as well as those placed at discharge\r\nIMS and refilled prescriptions\r\nIf dose changes in refills of existing medications are not adequately communicated, a  patient might not realize that the strength has changed and continue to take two tablets of a prior strength when the correct sig is now one tablet daily.  \r\nExample: \r\nA patient requests a refill of a prescription for Lipitor (80 mg total/day taken in two 40mg tablets).\r\nThe provider refills the order for a daily dose of two 40 mg tablets to be taken once a day, as before.\r\nIMS will replace the two 40 mg tablets with one 80 mg tablet to be taken once a day, as designed. \r\nHowever, if the patient is used to taking two tablets and continues to do so without realizing that the per-tablet strength is higher, patient care could be impacted.\r\nIMS and discharge workflows\r\nIn hospital discharge workflows, a physician may order a medication and then modify its dose before patient discharge and medication dispensation. Any modified medications are identified as changed in the patient?s discharge report, and the patient should be counseled about the changes before leaving the hospital. However, if a PTA medication order is modified at discharge, the patient might not realize that the strength has changed and continue to take two tablets of a prior strength when the correct sig is now one tablet daily.\r\nIn discharge workflows, IMS functions as follows: \r\nIMS substitution can occur when a prior-to-admission medication is ordered upon admission. If IMS substitutes a product with a different strength upon admission, the new product might be prescribed upon discharge. \r\nIMS substitution can also occur when a prior-to-admission medication is reordered or modified upon discharge or when a new drug is ordered during the admission and ordered as a prescription upon discharge. \r\nIMS does not occur when a prior-to-admission medication is simply resumed, because a new order is not placed in this situation. \r\nExample: \r\nOn discharge a prescription for Lipitor (40 mg total/day taken in two 20mg tablets) is modified to 80 mg total/day taken in two 40 mg tablets\r\nThe provider submits the order for a daily dose of 80 mg total/day taken in two 40 mg tablets to be taken once a day.\r\nIMS will replace the two 40 mg tablets with one 80 mg tablet to be taken once a day, as currently designed. \r\nHowever, if the patient is used to taking two tablets and continues to do so without realizing that the per-tablet strength is higher, patient care could be impacted.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/28/09: July KPKG, 11/09 install.\r\n5/13:  forward PART email to Johnette (AMB), BYee (Rx)','NCI','','NCI',NULL,' IMS has not currently been implemented in any KP region but may be implemented after installation of the SU\'09 release. Once National Pharmacy enables IMS, however, all regions could be potentially impacted (NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, GA, CO, Exempla, MAS, OH) .',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-05-13 01:50:00','2009-11-24 12:07:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(345,4533814,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'MAS only - Medication Replacer utility may incorrectly replace medications in Order Template records','','',NULL,NULL,'Ambulatory, Pharmacy, ED, Beacon, OpTime, Radiant','I7512302/E758701','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-01 00:00:00','2009-11-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Andy Wiesenthal','',NULL,'','SP07','','','','','not requested','','July 09','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV07','N','S','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K070609\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512302/E758701\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609-E758701\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/10/09: OK to close per A. Mure.','If the Medication Replacer utility is used to replace a medication on a Preference List or OrderSet, the utility may incorrectly replace the medication in an order template (OTL) record without changing the display name.  As a result, Preference Lists and/or Order Sets (which are comprised of order template records) may not display the correct name for the medication.  \r\nRoot Cause: The logic in the Medication Replacer utility is incorrect.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'10/27/09: 6/16: Waiting for Kpkg (July). \r\n6/3: Per Bart Shepardson, no plans to use this utility.\r\n6/1: Verify that NCAL has no plans to use Medication Replacer utility before fix is installed. ','Clean up affected OTL records. (MAS only)\r\nUntil the fix is installed, do not use the Medication Replacer utility.','','Clean up affected OTL records. (MAS only)\r\nUntil the fix is installed, do not use the Medication Replacer utility.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-01 04:26:00','2009-11-10 11:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(346,4540081,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Inpatient -New orders may be filed to encounter for discontinued medication order if certain print groups are used ','','',NULL,NULL,'Rx, ED, Optime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-03 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'EPIC (Dustin Foster)','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512503\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-C75031480\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28/09: Sept Kpkg, 2/2010 install','A newly placed order may be filed to a previous encounter -- instead of the current encounter -- in the following workflow:\r\nA clinician opens a patient?s chart, to a prior encounter, and discontinues a medication order from a reportwhich uses print group (or copies of) 34225-IP Ord Rec Discharge Review Status, 46155-IP Med PTA for Encounter, or 34220-IP Take Home Meds, that is configured to display the Discontinue hyperlink and the order is discontinued using that hyperlink;\r\nThe clinician then opens Order Entry or an Orders navigator section and places one or more additional orders.\r\n\r\nThe additional orders are not filed on the current encounter but rather on the prior encounter from which the medication was discontinued.  Possible consequences are medications not being dispensed or labs not being performed.  \r\n\r\nRoot Cause: A hyperlink in Print Groups not functioning as expected.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NCI, as no regions are currently using the affected functionality.','','','',NULL,'No regions are currently impacted, according to searches done by Epic (Thomas Sharkey).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-03 04:36:00','2009-09-28 03:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(347,4427301,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3728369,'Order Entry - Transfer orders released from Pended Held form may be lost','','',NULL,NULL,'OPT, ED','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-09 00:00:00','2009-11-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Hoberman','',NULL,'4788','','','','','','','0622-AP-PR4427301-E758946-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z\r\n0622-AP-PR4427301-E758946-Spr07Jul06NS-Notes.zip','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUN09','A','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K070609\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4788):  \n  SP’07 E758946 6/22/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/17/09: Per Y. Lassiter, certified; closing this issue.','Transfer orders may be lost if selected from a Pended Held form that does not specify a pending reason.  This can occur in the following workflow:\r\nOpen a Transfer Navigator.\r\nReorder a PTA medication.\r\nFrom the Pended Held form, select the Signed and Held Orders group. The orders appear selectable.\r\nSelect the orders.  \r\nThe orders will be pulled into Order Entry and can be removed and lost.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/11/09: Email to Y. Lassiter on 11/11 requesting certification.\r\n10/27/09: Per Yolanda TD162 testing is complete; will be in Nov install \r\n10/06/09: the fix for the issue has been installed, the TD is in test s/b part of Nov install.\r\n08/11/09: Per Dhea\'s 8/5 email, \"We are still waiting for a code fix for TD162 and the code for 4427301 is on hold until that fix arrives.\"\r\n07/21/09: Testing Passed; TD162 defect was opened. Express Test Plan was approved by Rosalba.\r\n6/30:per Dhea, testing is in process; target install is Aug or before.\r\n6/23: File received.  WITS install on Thursday 6/25. Fix will not require an outage.  Andre to check w/Dr. Hoberman about sending a communication (workaround = communication).\r\n6/23: File received.  WITS install on Thursday 6/25. Code being reviewed by multiple teams.\r\n6/9/09:  AdHoc 4788 - Epic provide status of fix by 6/16. Fix will not require an outage.  Andre to check w/Dr. Hoberman about sending a communication (workaround = communication). ','Communication only.\r\nDo not select orders that do not have a pending reason. \r\nRelease all transfer orders from the Transfer Navigator and not the Pended Held form.\r\n\r\n','','Communication only.\r\nDo not select orders that do not have a pending reason. \r\nRelease all transfer orders from the Transfer Navigator and not the Pended Held form.\r\n\r\n',NULL,'Regions:  NCAL, SCAL, and NW are currently impacted.  HI may be potentially impacted in the future when it implements Med Rec. Exempla is not impacted as it has no plans to implement the medication reconciliation functionality.\r\nDiscovered by:  NCAL in production',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-09 02:49:00','2009-11-17 10:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(348,4561764,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'ED only - PTA meds may not display for ED contact if certain Inpatient print group or Smart Link is used','','',NULL,NULL,'Inpatient','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder','',NULL,'4793','','','','','','NCAL to adhoc','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUN09','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409; E758976 is fixed by installing auth 4874 E759362-E7549193-C75031523--should install fix prior to Sept Kpackage\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512585\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4803 & 4874):  \n  SP’07 E758976 7/20/09 & E759362-E759193 & C75031523 9/11/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/06/09: Per R. Blair, adhoc will be in Nov Kpkg.','If a specific Inpatient print group and/or a specific Inpatient Smart Link is used to record prior to admission medications (e.g., meds recorded in an office visit or via Home Med) in an ED encounter, the medications may display incorrectly or not at all in the patient medication list.\r\n\r\nAffected:\r\nInpatient print group 46165 - IP PATIENT TAKE-HOME (DISCHARGE) MEDICATIONS (or copies)\r\nInpatient SmartLink 340 ? PTMEDDISCHARGE (or copies)\r\n\r\nIn an ED encounter with SP\'07, the affected print group and Smart Link will display differently depending on whether or not SU E758740 is installed:\r\nIf SU is not installed and the medication is modified, the medication incorrectly appears in the START taking section of the print group and SmartLink instead of the CONTINUE taking  these medications which have CHANGED section.\r\nIf SU is installed, the medication does not appear in the print group or SmartLink at all.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'6/30: per Andre, appears ED not affected;communication not required.\r\n6/10:  Andre to check for prnt group, SmartLinks in ED, arrange for communications\r\nEpic (Sara Rem) will provide a code fix and inform PART by 6/17/09 of its development status; PART Communications (Chris Okon) will then notify potentially impacted regions.\r\nNCAL will authorize an ad hoc code fix.\r\nRegions are advised to install the fix when available to avoid potential impact.','Do not use Inpatient print groups or Smart Links in ED contacts.  \r\nUse Smartlink 75260  ED PT MEDS and print group 75260 ED Meds: AVS Med Reconciliation Rich Text (or copies) in place of the affected Print Group and Smartlink.','','Do not use Inpatient print groups or Smart Links in ED contacts.  \r\nUse Smartlink 75260  ED PT MEDS and print group 75260 ED Meds: AVS Med Reconciliation Rich Text (or copies) in place of the affected Print Group and Smartlink.',NULL,'Epic rep:  Sarah.  SREM@epicsystems.com',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-10 04:36:00','2009-10-06 02:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(349,4558141,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Order Entry - Cancelling an Order Modification can discontinue an active order without warning, in specific configurations','','',NULL,NULL,' Ambulatory, ED, Beacon, OpTime, Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-11 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'not assessed, NCI','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512470\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759076 & C75031500\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28/09: Sept KPKG, 2/2010 install',' Modifying and then cancelling an order from the Order Review activity, Medications activity, or certain print groups can result in the immediate dicontinuation of the original order without warning.  This may happen if certain conditions are in place, as shown below:\r\n\r\nFor Inpatient Procedure OR Medication Orders\r\nSP\'06, SP\'07, or SP\'08\r\nModified from the Order Review activity or the Medications Activity AND \r\nConfigured as follows:\r\nIP Procedure Orders (configuration 1 OR 2):\r\nConfiguration 1\r\nUser\'s active profile settings Show discontinue form (I LPR 945) = No AND \r\nEMR System Definitions setting Reason for discontinued orders requirement (I LSD 4132) = None  OR\r\nConfiguration 2\r\nUser\'s active profile settings Show discontinue form (I LPR 945) = No AND \r\nEMR System Definitions setting Reason for discontinued orders requirement (I LSD 4132) = Required, Recommended, or left blank, AND \r\nUser?s active profile has a value specified for the setting Default discontinuation reason (I LPR 947).  When the Confirm Action window is configured not to appear, the system uses the value specified as the discontinue reason to meet the requirement.\r\nIP Medication Orders (configuration 1 OR 2):\r\nConfiguration 1\r\nUser\'s active profile settings Show discontinue form (I LPR 945) = No AND\r\nEMR System Definitions setting Reason for discontinued orders requirement (I LSD 4134) = None AND \r\nEMR System Definitions setting Allowed Medication Modifications (I LSD 25000) contain no entries\r\nConfiguration 2\r\nUser\'s active profile settings Show discontinue form (I LPR 945) = No AND \r\nEMR System Definitions setting Reason for discontinued orders requirement (I LSD 4134) = Required, Recommended, or left blank, AND \r\nUser?s active profile has a value specified for the setting Default discontinuation reason for inpatient (I LPR 946), AND \r\nEMR System Definitions setting Allowed Medication Modifications (I LSD 25000) contains no entries.\r\n\r\nAmbulatory Medication Orders Only\r\nSP\'07 only\r\nIf modified from a copy of the print group 34220-IP Take Home Meds (Rich Text) AND either of the following two system configurations described below is used:\r\nConfiguration 1\r\nCopy of print group 34220 has the eighth parameter = 1, AND \r\nUser?s active profile has Show discontinue form (I LPR 945) = No, AND \r\nEMR System Definitions Inpatient discontinue reason requirement (I LSD 4134) = None.\r\nConfiguration 1\r\nCopy of print group 34220 has the eighth parameter = 1, AND \r\nUser?s active profile has Show discontinue form (I LPR 945) = NO, AND \r\nEMR System Definitions Inpatient discontinue reason requirement (I LSD 4134) = Required, Recommended, or left blank AND \r\nUser?s active profile has a value specified for the setting Default discontinuation reason for inpatient (I LPR 946).',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/25/09: 6/11:  Waiting for K-package ','Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent future impact, regions are advised to implement the fix when available. \r\n','','Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage and inform PART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) of the status.\r\nPART Tracking (Rebecca Blair) will record information in the PART tracking report that is shared with potentially impacted regions during regular regional tracking meetings, and distributed to all PART regional teams monthly. \r\nTo prevent future impact, regions are advised to implement the fix when available. \r\n',NULL,'No regions are currently impacted, since Epic searches found that  no region is using the affected configuration.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-11 03:51:00','2009-09-28 03:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(350,4567154,1,'RAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Radiant - Results values may not display in certain HTML patient labs table  ','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-12 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Michael Krall','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUN09','N','L','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  SU09 and SP08 complete, SP07 Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512581\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409 - E759220\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: 6/16: waiting for Sept. KPKG','Lab values may not display in the Results column of  HTML table GDI52006 or copies. The data values are stored correctly and can be viewed in all other areas that display lab results.\r\n\r\nRoot Cause: System search for values stops at first table, although valid values may be stored in second table.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Mike Yandl) will provide a code fix and notify PART by 6/26/09 of its development status; NCAL not currently affected.\r\nNW and GA are impacted since an Epic search revealed that they are the only regions to have copies of the affected table. \r\n','Do not use GDI 52006 or copies to display HTML lab results.  Instead, display relevant lab info by using GDI 52480 or copies.','','Do not use GDI 52006 or copies to display HTML lab results.  Instead, display relevant lab info by using GDI 52480 or copies.',NULL,'NW and GA are impacted since an Epic search revealed that they are the only regions to have copies of the affected table. \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-15 10:18:00','2009-10-20 10:08:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(351,4581633,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3760699,'Medication Reconciliation -  Discharge SmartLink and print group may display incorrect information if I7512217/E758740 is installed','','',NULL,NULL,'','I7512585','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-18 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Drs. Scott Adelman, Hoberman, Wiesenthal','',NULL,'4803','','','','','','','0720-AP-PR4581633-E758976-Spr07Sep14NS.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'MedRec','N','S','F','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409; E758976 is fixed by installing auth 4874 E759362-E7549193-C75031523--should install fix prior to Sept Kpackage\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512585\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4803 & 4874):  \n  SP’07 E758976 7/20/09 & E759362-E759193 & C75031523 9/11/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/06/09: Per R. Blair, ad hoc will be in Nov install.','Discharge instructions may be incorrect and confusing to patients due to a problem introduced by ad hoc code fix I7512217/E758740 (also in the 070609 KPackage).  \r\n\r\nThis issue affects both the old and new medication reconciliation functionalities as follows: \r\nFacilities using old med rec: When print group 46165 or SmartLink PTMEDDISCHARGE is used, inpatient medications appear on the list of discharge meds. No inpatient medications should appear on this list. \r\nFacilities using new med rec:  When print group 46165 or SmartLink PTMEDDISCHARGE is used, outpatient procedures appear on the list of discharge meds. No procedures should appear on this list.  If displaying the unreviewed meds, inpatient medications will also appear on the list of discharge medications. Inpatient medications should not appear on this list.\r\n\r\nRoot Cause: Retrofitting SP\'08 medication reconciliation functionality to SP\'07.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/11/09: Per Dhea, adhoc 4803 on hold b/c of defect; adhoc 4874 (target release is 11/09) needs to be installed before 4803 can be implemented.\r\n9/22/09: See update from K. Regan in the comments section below\r\n08/04:  adhoc on hold, per Dhea request 07/20/09: received adhoc files, see below for filename. \r\nAffected code backed out on 6/17.  Awaiting further info regarding fix from Chris (Epic).  Adhoc 4803. NCAL (Kelly Ragan) removed the affected ad hoc fix on 6/17/09.\r\nPer Kelly Ragan: Summary - NCAL would like epic to re-evaluate the following adhoc 4574 - Patient   Safety 0520-PS-PR4102327-E758740-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z - -   and deliver a new fix that addresses both PR4102327 and the new one.....4581633.','Regions that have not yet installed this package should wait until a fix is delivered. \r\nEpic TSs will work with all potentially impacted regions to ensure that the affected code is not installed.\r\nNCAL (Kelly Ragan) removed the affected ad hoc fix on 6/17/09.\r\nEpic (Maria Spinozzi) will remove the affected code from the 070609 KPackage.\r\n','','Regions that have not yet installed this package should wait until a fix is delivered. \r\nEpic TSs will work with all potentially impacted regions to ensure that the affected code is not installed.\r\nNCAL (Kelly Ragan) removed the affected ad hoc fix on 6/17/09.\r\nEpic (Maria Spinozzi) will remove the affected code from the 070609 KPackage.\r\n',NULL,'Per K. Ragan\'s 9/22/09 email:\r\nPer my understanding, this adhoc corrects the following:\r\nTD	NC162\r\nPR	4432708\r\nPR	4432731\r\nPR	4675674\r\n\r\nIn addition, per Epic TS Maria Spinozzi - Code 0720-AP-PR4581633-E758976-Spr07Sep14NS.tar.Z, is fixed by installing Ad hoc 4874: 0911-AP-TDNC162-E759362-E759193-C75031523-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z\r\n\r\nThis fix 0911-AP-TDNC162-E759362-E759193-C75031523-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z  needs to be installed with or prior to the Sept Kpackage.  \r\n\r\nThis code is targeted for 11/7/07 for NCAL PROD install. \r\n\r\nAny code that contains [E758976/I7512585], should not be installed without 0911-AP-TDNC162-E759362-E759193-C75031523-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-18 03:55:00','2009-10-27 11:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(352,4567569,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Order Entry - Orders could be discontinued unintentionally when released at patient transfer, in certain circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'Rx, ED, OpTime, ADT','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-16 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Michael Krall','',NULL,'','','','','','','','0616-AP-PR4351571-E758781-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z\r\n0616-AP-PR4351571-E758781-Spr07Jul06NS-Notes.zip (6/24 email for PR4351571)','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUN09','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y','N','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  NW not sure if auth ad hoc;  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512598\nAD HOC AVAILABLE:  \n  SP’07 fix available 7/20\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759021\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: Waiting for Sept Kpkg.  No Current Impact.','(1) Potential Problem Description:  Orders may be unintentionally discontinued when a patient is transferred from one unit to another.  This can happen if:\r\nan auto-discontinue programming point is used, AND \r\nthe transfer event which triggers the auto-DC programming point occurs just prior to the release of the signed-and-held transfer orders. \r\nThis issue would most likely happen with long-stay patients who have many orders.\r\n\r\nWorkflow:\r\nBefore the patient is transferred, orders that meet the criteria configured in the programming point for auto-discontinue are signed and held. \r\nThe patient is transferred in the system, triggering the programming point to auto-discontinue active orders that meet the criteria configured in the programming point.  (NOTE: Departments can specifiy the units where this programming point will fire.) \r\nA user releases the signed and held orders before the programming point has finished running, which increases the chance for those orders to be discontinued as well.\r\nRoot Cause:Race condition with auto-discontinue of orders.\r\nFeatures:  Order Entry; Auto-discontinue programming point (copy of 34711) for IP Transfer LSD 34122',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NCAL is not impacted since they do not use the auto-discontinue programming point. \r\n','Remove the Auto-discontinue programming point from LSD 34122 and discontinue orders manually. \r\nDo not physically transfer the patient until the transfer is initiated.  This should allow the programming point to finish running (at least 5-10 minutes) before the orders are released. \r\nSCAL and NW are advised to work with their Epic TS to implement the appropriate workaround.\r\nSCAL (Kim Nida) and NW (Tammy Dee Shaw) will review conditions for impact with their internal teams and notify PART of action plans.','','Remove the Auto-discontinue programming point from LSD 34122 and discontinue orders manually. \r\nDo not physically transfer the patient until the transfer is initiated.  This should allow the programming point to finish running (at least 5-10 minutes) before the orders are released. \r\nSCAL and NW are advised to work with their Epic TS to implement the appropriate workaround.\r\nSCAL (Kim Nida) and NW (Tammy Dee Shaw) will review conditions for impact with their internal teams and notify PART of action plans.',NULL,'Regions:  SCAL and NW are impacted.  HI is potentially impacted.  NCAL and Exempla/CO are not impacted. \r\nSCAL and NW are impacted since they have enabled the affected programming point and may have affected workflows.\r\nAlthough HI has the affected programming point, it is only potentially impacted since it does not use affected workflows.\r\nNCAL and Exempla/CO are not impacted since they do not use the auto-discontinue programming point. \r\nEpic Representative:  Tim Williams and Peter Lesperance',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,140,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-23 11:18:00','2009-10-20 10:10:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(353,4598242,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Notewriter HPI template intermittently fails to automatically generate text in the note','','',NULL,NULL,'ASAP','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-24 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'4894','','','','','','req\'d by SCAL','0827-PS-PR4598242-C75031522-E759189-Spr07Sep14NS.tar.Z\r\n0827-PS-PR4598242-C75031522-E759189-Spr07Sep14NS.zip','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUN09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Propagation planned for 6/26 and 7/01/09; coll build complete as of 7/01/09; Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512738\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4894):  \n  SP’07 EC75031522 & E759189 8/27/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409 - E759189 & C75031522\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: Per Andre, propagation is complete; Sept kpkg, 2/2010 install.','In Notewriter, text is automatically generated when clicking on various buttons in the HPI, ROS and PE tabs. In a specific but rare workflow, the text for the content documented on the HPI tab (either using QuickForms or SmartForms) is not generated in the note.  The frequency is observed to be intermittent and inconsistent.   \r\n\r\nRoot Cause:CMT Naming Convention-   KP HLX records contain an underscore in the naming convention.  The identified impacted HLX records that contain an underscore \"_\" character (i.e.KPCUI#12111_BOL) cause the Epic logic to read incorrectly  and misinterpret \"where\" the text is to display in the note.  CMT will address the naming convention and will propagate new HLX records to remediate the issue.\r\nEpic will develop code to fix the logic so that  HLX records that contain the underscore\"_\" characters in the item 40, in future records, are not misinterpreted.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/25/09: Waiting for Sept kpkg. Email to Andre on 9/29: do we need to do another propagation?\r\n07/22/09: Per Brenden Krueger (EPIC) long term fix is coming; the SU will prevent creation or import of HPI concepts with underscores in the CUI ID.  \r\n07/21/09: Per Andre, w/a complete; Rebecca to f/up with EPIC (Brenden) re additional fix to be completed.\r\n6/30: per Andre, testing of w/a (HLX propagation of records) is in process now; no adhoc required.  Helen to send email to R. Mekho re adhoc.\r\nEpic (Brandon Krueger) will update PART on a projected code fix delivery date, next Wednesday, 7/1/09.\r\nSee Urgent Mitigation and work around below.  ','Urgent Mitigation:  \r\nA communication was sent to ED physicians instructing them to-  \"Until further notice, take care as ED notes are created using Notewriter, specifically when using \"HPI tab.  If this issue is observed, while reviewing a note in the \"Note tab\", click back onto the \"HPI tab\" to reinitiate the text generation.  Then, click back onto the \"Note tab\" to review the note. This will cause the Epic logic to be re-triggered and to display the text correctly. Please review notes to ensure the text reflects correct documentation. Using free-text directly, instead of clicking the buttons on the \"HPI tab\", may minimize the impact.\"\r\n\r\nWorkaround:  \r\nAn HLX propagation of records that do not contain the underscore \"_\" character in the naming convention (item 40) is scheduled for this Friday, 6/26, with final propagation into regional Production environments on Wednesday, 7/1/09.  These dates have been agreed upon by Inter-regional ED ACs to allow for regional testing and updating regional production profiles/settings to minimize disruption to Notewriter functionality   ','','Urgent Mitigation:  \r\nA communication was sent to ED physicians instructing them to-  \"Until further notice, take care as ED notes are created using Notewriter, specifically when using \"HPI tab.  If this issue is observed, while reviewing a note in the \"Note tab\", click back onto the \"HPI tab\" to reinitiate the text generation.  Then, click back onto the \"Note tab\" to review the note. This will cause the Epic logic to be re-triggered and to display the text correctly. Please review notes to ensure the text reflects correct documentation. Using free-text directly, instead of clicking the buttons on the \"HPI tab\", may minimize the impact.\"\r\n\r\nWorkaround:  \r\nAn HLX propagation of records that do not contain the underscore \"_\" character in the naming convention (item 40) is scheduled for this Friday, 6/26, with final propagation into regional Production environments on Wednesday, 7/1/09.  These dates have been agreed upon by Inter-regional ED ACs to allow for regional testing and updating regional production profiles/settings to minimize disruption to Notewriter functionality   ',NULL,'7/14:  Epic (Brendan Krueger and Robyn Pingel) ran queries to determine if patient charts had been potentially affected by text generation failure.  Only SCAL and HI have identified charts that require remediation.  A reconvene of the patient safety call was held on 07/12/09 with to coordinate remediation steps and action plans with SCAL and HI. SCAL and HI plan to manually review the potentially affected charts to determine if remediation steps are required.  If it is determined that remediation is necessary, the following steps are outlined for both Ambulatory and ED workflows that use the HPI template in NoteWriter.\r\nDocuments outlining these steps, along with associated screenshots, were sent to the affected regions to insure correct chart remediation.\r\n\r\nAmbulatory: Steps for Remediation\r\n\r\n1. Enter an Ambulatory patient?s chart either through the Patient Care menu or from Schedule (double click on completed appointment).\r\n2. Edit the note in NoteWriter.\r\n3. Open NoteWriter HPI.\r\n4. Confirm your findings on the form. The HPI text regenerates to match findings. Note that associated symptoms may appear twice. Accept the note.\r\n5. The Addendum files with the restored HPI text. Both the original and the addendum have the original encounter date.  The addendum will have the current time as the filed time.\r\n\r\nED: Steps for Remediation\r\n\r\n1. Enter an ED patient?s chart.\r\n2. Go to the Notes activity.  Select the affected note and click Addendum (or Edit Note).\r\n3. The NoteWriter HPI tab opens by default. Confirm findings on the form. The HPI text regenerates to match findings. Note that associated symptoms may appear twice as in the example below. Accept the note.\r\n4. The Addendum files with the restored HPI text. The addendum has the original note time as well as the current time as the filed time. \r\n5. Click on the icon on the left to compare both versions of the note.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-06-25 11:03:00','2009-10-20 02:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(354,4617049,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - OTL - Incorrect order names may appear in preference lists, Order Sets, and SmartSets, in specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'Pharmacy, Amb, ED, OpTime, Radiant','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512631\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759089\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28/09: Sept KPKG, 2/2010 install','Medication and/or procedure order names may display incorrectly in protocol-based Order Sets, protocol-based SmartSets, or preference lists if the same order template record (OTL) is referenced in multiple SmartGroups (OSQ) records or in multiple preference lists (LPF records).  \r\n\r\nThe problem occurs if SmartGroup order template records are duplicated in Chronicles text instead of with the Save As feature in the SmartGroup Editor in Hyperspace. \r\n\r\nThis issue does not occur when:\r\nSmartGroups are duplicated in Hyperspace (the recommended method), or\r\nPreference lists are duplicated in Chronicles.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/25/09: Waiting for Sept kpkg.\r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 01:58:00','2009-09-28 03:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(355,4620204,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SP?07 Inpatient  - Non-discharge orders can appear in and be discontinued from print group LPG 34225','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','SP?07 with code fix E758604 installed (in 051909 Kpackage)','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','L','R','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512739\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759155\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/25/09: Waiting for the Sept kpkg','Non-discharge orders can appear as discharge orders and can be discontinued if all of the following conditions are in place:\r\nPrint group 34225 ? IP ORD REC DISCHARGE REVIEW STATUS or a copy is used\r\nSU E758604 is installed \r\nthe New Medication Reconciliation functionality is implemented.  ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/11/09: Per D. Maloney\'s 8/10 email, \"We do not show the discontinue hyperlink in our copies of LPG 34225 so we are not impacted by this issue.\"\r\n8/10:  email reminder sent to Dhea--are we affected after 8/19, is W/A in place?\r\n08/04:  NCI for NCAL.  \r\n07/31/09: per Chris R, Server package E758604 was installed on 7/16, but NCAL print groups are still unaffected as they do not show the discontinue hyperlink.\r\n07/21/09: Chris (EPIC) will check to see if NCAL is affected after the install of KPKG.7/7:  per Dhea, We have confirmed with our TS that we are not impacted by this issue as we do not show the discontinue hyperlink in our copies of LPG 34225.\r\nNCI--no impact until E758604 installed (in 051909 Kpackage) Epic (Liz Nickels) will provide a code fix and notify PART by  07/15/09 of its development status.','Configure Print Group 34225 to not show actionable hyperlinks. The print group will still display the inpatient order that could be misleading, but it would not be actionable from this print group.  Once the user navigated to the discharge navigator to take action, it would be more apparent that the discharge order was discontinued.\r\nConsider using print group 45093 or 46165 as alternatives to this print group.\r\n','','Configure Print Group 34225 to not show actionable hyperlinks. The print group will still display the inpatient order that could be misleading, but it would not be actionable from this print group.  Once the user navigated to the discharge navigator to take action, it would be more apparent that the discharge order was discontinued.\r\nConsider using print group 45093 or 46165 as alternatives to this print group.\r\n',NULL,'No regions have the affected code installed. (051909 KPKG)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 02:39:00','2009-09-28 03:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(356,4615669,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'MAS only - KP Online and My Chart  - Member-generated messages to providers may fail transmission ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 00:00:00','2009-08-04 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','SP09 with 051809 KPackage installed','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JULY09','N','L','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Epic modified Mychart server which will resolve problem for remainder of regions\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/04/09: 8/4:  Kelly confirmed, config installed 7/22 successfully.  Can\'t certify (MAS only).  CLOSING',' Messages sent by members using MyChart online may not reach the intended receiver if the SP\'07 051809 KPackage has been installed.  This KPackage includes a new client-based MyChart function for session security.  Specifically, an authentication token is recorded at member session initiation, and if the token is invalidated by a mismatch during the session, the MyChart transaction will not complete.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7/8: per Kelly,  config to correct this issue will be in ALL PROD environments on 7/22/09Regions planning to install 051909 are advised to have their Regional API and MyChart AC?s work with the regional Epic TS to ensure that MyChart is configured correctly during testing and load of the 051909 to Testing and Production environments.  7/2:  see PART updates in \"Comments\".  Regions planning to install 051909 are advised to have their Regional API and MyChart AC\'s work with the regional Epic TS to ensure that MyChart is configured correctly during testing and load of the 051909 to Testing and Production environments.','Ensure that the MYCHART.ini configuration setting is set to disable checking for token validation. \r\nMAS has completed the workaround.\r\nRegions planning to install 051909 are advised to have their Regional API and MyChart AC\'s work with the regional Epic TS to ensure that MyChart is configured correctly during testing and load of the 051909 to Testing and Production environments.\r\nFix:  Since completing the workaround corrects the problem, a code fix is not needed.\r\n  \r\n',NULL,'Ensure that the MYCHART.ini configuration setting is set to disable checking for token validation. \r\nMAS has completed the workaround.\r\nRegions planning to install 051909 are advised to have their Regional API and MyChart AC\'s work with the regional Epic TS to ensure that MyChart is configured correctly during testing and load of the 051909 to Testing and Production environments.\r\nFix:  Since completing the workaround corrects the problem, a code fix is not needed.\r\n  \r\n',NULL,'Update from PART 7/2:  During scheduled kp.org outages on 7/12 (SCAL) and 7/22 (all other regions except MAS), the NATL ISG team will modify the MYCHART.ini file with: FILTERCSRF=False\r\n2. The updated MYCHART.ini file will be pushed by the Natl KP SI team to all regional MyChart IIS web servers (except MAS which was remediated on 6/30)\r\n3. The MyChart IIS web servers will be recycled.\r\nThese steps will insure that default configuration settings are accurate for the load of the May K pkg in each region, based on regional schedules for that load.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 02:44:00','2009-08-04 04:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(358,4617034,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Dates may be incorrect in medication prescription reports, under specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, Optime, Pharmacy','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512401\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759062\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/28/09: Sept KPKG, 2/2010 install','Dates for all but the first order in a medication prescription report may be incorrect if  both of the following conditions are true:\r\nSP\'07 SU E758514 (originally included in the July 09 KPackage) is installed.  This SU includes SmartLink 6942-RxOrdDateFormat.\r\nSmartLink 6942-RxOrdDateFormat or a copy is used.\r\nThe third parameter of this SmartLink is set to null (\"\").  ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 03:58:00','2009-09-28 03:57:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(359,4617071,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - ChartSync - Updates may be lost if patient records are rehomed in standalone mode','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NCI','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512681\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E758985\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/25/09: Waiting for Sept kpkg',' If ChartSync updates a file out of order at the same time someone starts rehoming a patient record in standalone mode, the earlier update can get lost. This problem does not happen when patient records are rehomed as part of patient merges since the merge already triggers full GetRecords at the remote deployments.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Brandon Podoll) will provide a  SP\'07 code fix as part of a KPackage','','','',NULL,'No regions are currently impacted since KP currently rehomes patient records as part of patient merges. However, NCAL and SCAL (the only two regions using ChartSync) could be potentially impacted if they start performing standalone rehomes before they upgrade to SU\'09 or prior to installation of the fix.\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-01 04:02:00','2009-09-28 03:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(361,4628153,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,' Inpatient  - Automatically discontinued orders may be inadvertently reactivated and signed','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-07 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y','Y','N','N','N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409 ; impacts thru SU09\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512799\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-C75031505\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'08/25/09: Reconfirmed waiting for Sept kpkg.','Using an uncommon workflow, physicians may inadvertently reactivate and sign orders that were automatically discontinued and later reordered and cancelled.\r\n\r\nFor this issue to occur, both of the following configuration settings must be in place:\r\nProgramming point 34711 - IP AUTO DC AT TRANSFER BY DEPT must be set in System Definitions as an ADT Action Programming Point in the field Transfer (I LSD 34122).  This sets specified orders to auto-discontinue upon transfer, to and/or from designated units identified in the configuration.\r\nNavigator order sections must be configured to display orders that were automatically discontinued at transfer by the programming point by setting SHOW ORDERS DISCONTINUED AT TRANSFER to Yes in the navigator configuration (I VCN 34105=1). \r\n\r\nProvider Workflow\r\nFrom a Navigator, access an order that was auto-discontinued on transfer, and reorder it. \r\nLeave the Navigator by going to a different section such as Problem List or View a Report.\r\nReturn to the Orders section.  Close the Orders section or go to another section.  The reactivated orders will display.\r\nUsing the Red X, remove or cancel the orders that were reordered.\r\nUsing the hyperlink, return to the Orders section.\r\n\r\nThe cancelled or removed orders will be reactivated when the Orders section is reopened.  If the provider adds ands signs a new order, the reactived orders previously cancelled or removed will also be signed.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'07/21/09:Sept KPKG\r\nEpic (Peter Lesperance) will provide a code fix and update PART by 7/17/09 with development status.','If affected by issue (NCAL currently is NOT): \r\nDisable the navigator configuration by setting SHOW ORDER DISCONTINUED AT TRANSFER to NO.  \r\nUse the Order Review activity to review orders discontinued at transfer.','','If affected by issue (NCAL currently is NOT): \r\nDisable the navigator configuration by setting SHOW ORDER DISCONTINUED AT TRANSFER to NO.  \r\nUse the Order Review activity to review orders discontinued at transfer.',NULL,'SCAL, NW, and HI are currently impacted since they have the affected configurations, according to an Epic search.  NCAL and Exempla are potentially impacted if they implement the affected configuration..',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-07 12:41:00','2009-10-13 11:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(362,4642158,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Choosing A Medication Panel From An Alternative Alert During Reorder Will Not Discontinue the Original Medication','','',NULL,NULL,'all regions except OH','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Alan Rogers ','',NULL,'4870','','','','','','','0921-PS-PR4642158-C75031555-E759333-Spr07Nov16NS.zip\r\n0921-PS-PR4642158-C75031555-E759333-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z\r\n0921-PS-PR4642158-C75031555-E759333-Spr07Nov16NS-EPICWEB.zip\r\n0921-PS-PR4642158-C75031555-E759333-Spr07Nov16NS-HOMEHEALTH.zip','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','Y','N','Y','Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  testing uncovered addl problems; client and server fix with outage expected\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512788\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4870):  \n  SP’07 E759333 & C75031555 9/21/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609-E759333 & C75031555\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/07/09: per J. Yamamoto\'s 10/7 email, will wait for the Nov K Pkg.','Original medications may not be automatically discontinued when reordered and signed if a clinician instead chooses to order the medication panel that is presented in an alternative alert for the medication. As a result, duplicate medications could potentially be dispensed or administered to the patient.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/21/09: 9/21:  fix files received.  WITS?\r\n07/29/09: See content of J. Yamamoto\'s 7/29 email in Next Step History below. \r\n7/29: Remove problematic alternative med alerts:\r\nWe coordinated with NCAL Pharmacy Database team to pull all alternative med alerts containing panels. Dr.Bornstein approved this yesterday. Communication to the users was sent by the New Features Team. Twenty-two alternative alerts containing the panels were removed by the Pharmacy Database team last night.\r\n\r\nRemediate existing duplicate med orders:\r\nPharmacy is currently researching the active duplicate med orders to decide which orders should be discontinued. They will be contacting the authorizing providers who placed the orders.\r\n07/21/09: Helen to f/up with Joyce re status of w/a. Sept or Nov kpkg?\r\n7/22: From N DaW: server fix only, affected code is involved in order creation, so a downtime to prevent users from creating orders during the installation is recommended.  07/20/09: Per Byron Harper\'s email, the fix s/b available for delivery by 9/1.\r\n7/16: Per Joyce Y. no action will be taken until EPIC specifies what the fix is.  Joyce is also analyzing the list from EPIC to determine impact.\r\nTom to forward query to AMB.  Workaround needed?\r\nEpic running queries to determine affected orders (Nathan DaWalt). Epic TS to communicate with regional contacts. ','Regions should evaluate the possible workarounds and the queries provided by Epic to determine if action is necessary and if so, which workaround is appropriate for their region.  Workarounds will most likely vary by region\r\n1.Communicate to providers that reorders should be checked to determine that the correctly intended orders are being signed and submitted. An existing Ambulatory medication may be duplicated or duplicate therapies may be initiated by selecting a medication panel.\r\n2. Remove medication panels from Alternative Alerts.  Epic will provide queries of built panels by region and currently affected orders.  Regions are urged to review these queries to determine if, in fact, Alerts with panels are firing and if panels are selected during reorder of single medications.\r\n3. Insert SmartText into the Alert record to notify providers that selecting a medication panel from an Alternative Alert may result in duplicate medication or duplicate therapy orders.\r\nHistorical Remediation:   \r\nDuring routine Ambulatory encounters, physicians should verify, validate, and correct current medications in the Medications list as part of the routine Medication Reconciliation process with the member.','','Regions should evaluate the possible workarounds and the queries provided by Epic to determine if action is necessary and if so, which workaround is appropriate for their region.  Workarounds will most likely vary by region\r\n1.Communicate to providers that reorders should be checked to determine that the correctly intended orders are being signed and submitted. An existing Ambulatory medication may be duplicated or duplicate therapies may be initiated by selecting a medication panel.\r\n2. Remove medication panels from Alternative Alerts.  Epic will provide queries of built panels by region and currently affected orders.  Regions are urged to review these queries to determine if, in fact, Alerts with panels are firing and if panels are selected during reorder of single medications.\r\n3. Insert SmartText into the Alert record to notify providers that selecting a medication panel from an Alternative Alert may result in duplicate medication or duplicate therapy orders.\r\nHistorical Remediation:   \r\nDuring routine Ambulatory encounters, physicians should verify, validate, and correct current medications in the Medications list as part of the routine Medication Reconciliation process with the member.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-10 02:57:00','2009-10-21 11:23:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(363,4634938,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'MAS only-  AffiliateLink  - Progress Notes and Patient Instructions may not appear in Patient Charts when using AffiliateLink to view patient information','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-10 00:00:00','2009-07-21 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Dr. Allan Rogers','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JULY09','N','L','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No Epic code needed\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/21/09: closing; NCAL not impacted, not EPIC related','After implementation of the May K pkg, MAS reported that Progress Notes and Patient Instructions were not appearing in Patient Charts when using AffiliateLink to view patient information, as of 07/02/09.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7/14: No Epic code fix is  needed, since the problem is not due to Epic code.\r\nNo Epic code fix is  needed, since the problem is not due to Epic code.\r\nSCAL, GA. CO. and OH are advised to ensure correct configuration of servers using .NET 2.0. before implementing the 051809 KPackage.','After consultation and testing, Epic (Tracy Kolstad) determined that the root cause was not related to Epic code.  MAS Regional IIS servers were then audited to determine if they were utilizing the correct .NET 2.0 software.  Servers were reconfigured to insure correct utilization of .NET 2.0 software and recycled.  Progress Notes and Patient Instructions displayed correctly after these actions were taken.',NULL,'After consultation and testing, Epic (Tracy Kolstad) determined that the root cause was not related to Epic code.  MAS Regional IIS servers were then audited to determine if they were utilizing the correct .NET 2.0 software.  Servers were reconfigured to insure correct utilization of .NET 2.0 software and recycled.  Progress Notes and Patient Instructions displayed correctly after these actions were taken.',NULL,'Not sure if technician error or error with May K-package. Other regions loading the May K package could be potentially impacted.  Care should be taken to insure that server settings are correct for AffiliateLink functionality  \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-10 03:19:00','2009-07-23 01:59:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(364,4637430,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'MAS, Physician In Basket functionality disabled by load of May K pkg','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-10 00:00:00','2009-09-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Allan Rogers','',NULL,'4837','','','','','','','0710-AP-PR4628007-C75031449-E758449-Spr07Jul06NS.zip\r\n0710-AP-PR4628007-C75031449-E758449-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C','NA','N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','M','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512538\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4837):  \n  SP’07 E758449  & C75031449 7/10/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/01/09--per JDee/AMB, fix was installed 8/19, ok to close. CLOSING','Due to a problem with code introduced in the 051809 KPackage (specifically DLG I758970), Ambulatory Physician InBasket (IB) functionality related to message forwarding has been impacteded. Specifically, Visit Date (EOW 121) is not carried forward when IB messages are forwarded, causing encounter-related IB columns to be blank and preventing some actions such as: creating Result Notes, Quick Notes, and using the Encounter button, as well as, Buttons for completeing responsibiltiy messages, such as \"Reviewed\", or \"Sign\". \"Forward\" and \"Reply\" continue to \"work\" and send the information, however, the receiving physician still can\'t act on the message for the same reasons.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/10/09: adhoc fix is in manifest for 8/19.\r\n08/04:  testing completed--next step CAB and install   07/21/09: Per Alex installed last night and in testing now.  7/14:  per Alex S, replication successful, reqstd adhoc files loaded into WITS, sched for 7/17.\r\nFile Received.  Replication required by 7/14 and request WITS3 install needed ASAP','Notification will be sent by MAS (Allan Roglers) to MAS physicians to inform them about defective InBasket functionality  \r\nAdditionally, PART will work with Epic (Jason Ramaker) to develop a communication to alert regions about potential patient safety issues that MAS has identified in the May K package\r\nPART incident 4615669- Secure messaging in MyChart has been linked to the May K package.\r\nA potential problem with viewing or Progress Notes in Affiliate Link has been identified\r\nThis current issue with InBasket msgs - \r\n','','Notification will be sent by MAS (Allan Roglers) to MAS physicians to inform them about defective InBasket functionality  \r\nAdditionally, PART will work with Epic (Jason Ramaker) to develop a communication to alert regions about potential patient safety issues that MAS has identified in the May K package\r\nPART incident 4615669- Secure messaging in MyChart has been linked to the May K package.\r\nA potential problem with viewing or Progress Notes in Affiliate Link has been identified\r\nThis current issue with InBasket msgs - \r\n',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-10 03:52:00','2009-09-01 12:28:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(365,4636578,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - OpTime  - Surgical procedures may appear duplicated in Past Surgical History Activity when using the .PSH SmartPhrase','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','C',NULL,'N',NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JULY09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'07/20/09: This issue has been determined to not be a potentional patient safety issue. Closing PR.','As of 4/8/09, surgical procedures (EAP) should auto-populate in the Past Surgical History Activity when a surgical log is posted, in NCAL and SCAL.  A user may also manually enter other historical surgical procedures.  When using the .PSH Smart Phrase, procedures documented manually in the History activity will appear twice in .PSH, since .PSH will pull from both the History and the posted log.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'After consultation with Epic (Ben Sherman), NCAL surgeon (Dr. Maggie Mentakis), NCAL OpTime AC (Matt Kosta), Natl Clinical AC (Sumi Hawk), and Natl OpTime AC (Cathy Huntley), it was determined that the application and functionality were working as designed.  Duplication of previously documented surgical procedures using the .PSH SmartPhrase does not pose a patient safety risk. ','',NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-10 03:57:00','2009-07-20 09:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(366,4655216,1,'RAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Radiant - Accession numbers may be incorrectly assigned to scheduled orders','','',NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-14 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'N/A','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'RAD','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512820\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609- E759349\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: Nov kpkg, 2/2010 install.','A unique accession number may be incorrectly assigned to each occurrence in a multiple-occurrence order if all of the following are true:\r\nThe order uses a frequency that is defined for imaging order types as informational only. \r\nThe order is the second occurrence of a multiple occurrence order. \r\nSP\'07 with SU E757258 is installed.\r\n\r\nAs a result, users cannot search for the order by its accession number, and images may be linked to the wrong occurrence of an order.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/25/09: Update from EPIC expected on 9/8/09\r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage.\r\nNW, NCAL, HI, and GA could be potentially impacted if they change their build to include the affected frequency configuration.\r\n','','','',NULL,'No current impact, as no regions are currently using the affected frequency build for imaging order types.\r\nSearches in the regions live on Radiant (NW, NCAL, HI, and GA) reveal that NO affected frequencies exist.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-14 03:31:00','2009-11-25 10:37:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(367,4662940,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient - Order information may be missing in print groups that use Additional Information programming points','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, Rx, OpTime','','',NULL,NULL,'2009-07-17 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Allan Rogers','',NULL,'4851','','','','','','Andre M reqd','0813-PS-PR4662940-E759162-Spr07Sep14NS.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00','N','N','O','NA','N',NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','M','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512422\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4851):  \n  SP’07 E759162 8/13/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/24/09: Sept KPKG. Per Y. Lassiter\'s 9/24 email: per Ryan Lambert there is no need to test this print group as we are not using it nor do we intend to.','If an Additional Information programming point is added to a native HTML order print group in a Rich Text report, the report may not display all applicable orders.  As a result, the user may not be aware of active orders not shown in the report. The information that does display depends on the function of the programming point used.  This issue is unpredictable and occurs when RTF data is entered into HTML order print groups that are used in RTF reports.\r\n\r\nThe following Additional Information programming points (or copies) may be problematic:\r\n \r\nID		LPP Name											Executable Code\r\n34022		IP CHILD ORDER STATUS									$$ordStatus^JORDUTL1\r\n34047		IP CHILD ORDER STATUS (DOC SCI)							$$ordStatus^JORDUTL3\r\n34049		IP ORDER ADDITIONAL INFORMATION WITH MULTIPLE ALLOWED ITEMS	$$CStatus^JYCCFPP1\r\n34202		IP CHILD ORDER STATUS									$$CStatus^JYGHSPG1\r\n34708		IP - SIG WEIGHT ADDITIONAL INFO LPP						$$%WeightChangeCmplxCell^HUWEIGHT2\r\n46010		IP ORDER INFORMATION - PRN REASONS						$$PRNrea^JYUTPP3\r\n46011		IP ORDER INFORMATION - ADMIN INSTRUCTIONS					$$ADMIN^JYUTPP3\r\n84300		RX ADDN INFO - MED INTERACTION							$$InteractInfo^RXMEDPG\r\n\r\nOrder information is viewable in other areas, including the MAR which also includes a flag that indicates if a medication has not been acknowledged before administration.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/22/09: Y. Lassiter to f/up with Ryan Lambert re testing of affected print group 30646015.\r\n09/15/09: Alex to follow up with Aditi if replication has occured.  BIO testing will occur once replicated.\r\n08/25/09: Andre has requested an RFC to move adhoc into test CHG000003983655.\r\n08/04/09: Per C. Russell fix still under development; next update will be 8/6.\r\n07/20/09: Andre M has req adhoc #4851.\r\nEpic (Chris Russell) will provide a code fix and notify PART by 7/22/09 of its development status.','Regions may choose to perform either of these two workarounds:\r\nRemove affected programming points from print groups.\r\nSeparate Rich Text from HTML print groups; put HTML print groups into a new HTML report until the fix is available.','','Regions may choose to perform either of these two workarounds:\r\nRemove affected programming points from print groups.\r\nSeparate Rich Text from HTML print groups; put HTML print groups into a new HTML report until the fix is available.',NULL,'CHG000003862783  (shell RFC for prod, owner = Kelly) ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-17 01:01:00','2009-09-29 03:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(368,4664389,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'MAS only  - Progress notes may be converted to telephone encounter type, in certain circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-21 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','John Zook',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','L','N','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  No code fix coming\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/15/09: NCAL is not currently affected; per Christina Reski OB conversion s/b completed in Jan/Feb 2010.','Plain text progress notes will not be converted to rich text progress notes if all of the following conditions are true:\r\nOB encounters are linked in a pregnancy episode\r\nThe episode is closed.\r\nClinical notes have been converted from plain text to RTF (Rich Text Format), i.e., HLV to HNO.\r\nAs a result, plain text progress notes would not be visible at any place of the application to the end user.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'10/06/09: Marian C. is following up.\r\n09/29/09: AMB to follow-up when NCAL will run OB note conversion.\r\n07/21/09:  Epic and NCAL to work together during OB note conversion \r\nno code fix from Epic expected--NCAL could be impacted when we run OB note conversion. TS at Epic will work with KP with OB conversion, Epic will have batch utility ready for remediation.   ','Close and resolve old affected episodes with batch job.\r\nMAS (Mustafa Karaca) will run a batch job to close affected episodes.\r\nEpic (John Zook) has developed clean up routines to be followed in sequence after the batch job:\r\nConvert plain text notes to HNO (utility tbd by EOD 7/21/09)\r\nConvert incorrect telephone encounter notes to progress notes (utility completed 7/20/09)\r\nRemove duplicate records (utility tbd later this week).','','Close and resolve old affected episodes with batch job.\r\nMAS (Mustafa Karaca) will run a batch job to close affected episodes.\r\nEpic (John Zook) has developed clean up routines to be followed in sequence after the batch job:\r\nConvert plain text notes to HNO (utility tbd by EOD 7/21/09)\r\nConvert incorrect telephone encounter notes to progress notes (utility completed 7/20/09)\r\nRemove duplicate records (utility tbd later this week).',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-21 12:36:00','2009-11-25 10:39:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(369,4672423,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NCAL only  - Not all results returned when using line-indexed related group items in Reporting Workbench ','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-21 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Maria Spinozzi   ',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','L','R','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Epic determined later that SCAL also impacted; Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512794\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759092\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: Sept kpkg, 2/2010 install.','With Reporting Workbench, results may be missing if all of the following conditions are in place:\r\nThe report searches a line-indexed item as one of the columns in a related group criterion;\r\nThe column contains multiple values to search;\r\nThe report template uses the Ad Hoc engine;\r\nThe Ad Hoc engine uses the line index to generate its list of records to search. \r\n\r\nRecords only appear in the results if the first value checked for the record meets the search criterion. \r\n\r\nTo reproduce:\r\nAdd a new Health Maintenance Topic criterion to a copy of the Find Patients ? Generic Criteria template.  \r\nThe Health Maintenance Topic criterion should search EPT-18640 and EPT- 18642. Create the two items as columns in a related group. \r\nCreate a report from a copy of the Find Patients - Generic Criteria template that includes the Health Maintenance Topic criterion. \r\nSet the patient base to All Patients. \r\n*Add search values to the Health Maintenance Topic criterion. Make sure that there is more than one topic that matches your test patient records, but that the status does not match for all topics. \r\nRun the search.\r\nRemove the first line of the search expressions in the report. \r\nRun the search again.\r\nNote that different records are found. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'08/12/09: Per A. Thorup\'s 8/6 email, \"Bill Yee said there were other reports available to pharmacists that provided the same information.\" \r\nPer A. Thorup\'s 8/6 email, affected reports are pharmacy reports.\r\n07/29/09: PS will forward PART email to Johnette for her review.\r\nEpic (Maria Spinozzi) is developing SP\'07 code fix E759092 and will notify PART of its progress by 7/27/09. Reports affected are IVENT-Fremont, IVENT-Reasons, IVENT-Interventions. ','','','Use Chronicles and/or Clarity reports to retrieve the same data.',NULL,'NCAL is currently impacted, since Epic (Maria Spinozzi) searches revealed three reports from different NCAL deployments. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-21 12:45:00','2009-10-20 10:36:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(370,4665688,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient  - Volume information may be missing from soft-deleted flowsheet rows in the Intake/Output Activity','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-21 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Kristie (Reimer) Fowler-- kreimer@epicsystems.com',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','September 2009','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512887\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759248\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/21/09: Per A. Thorup w/a is in place.  Sept KPKG.','If a flowsheet row is soft-deleted,  the Intake/Output activity will not load or display the row. Consequently, the portion of I/O calculated from the visible I/O rows will not include the soft-deleted row.  However, the volume information from the soft-deleted row will be included in the portion of I/O totals that are calculated from the information stored on the server.  \r\n\r\nThe overall impact is that when soft-deleting I/O flowsheet rows, the totals displayed in the Intake/Output activity will not be accurate until approximately 24 hours after the row has been soft-deleted. \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'07/21/09: NCI at this time, as long as regions follow protocol.  \r\nWill not ask for adhoc as long as protocol is working (see Workaround below).  Epic working on fix. ','Maintain standard KP clinical practice to delay soft-deletion of flowsheet rows for two weeks.   This practice reduces the chance of the problem occurring but is not airtight.','','Maintain standard KP clinical practice to delay soft-deletion of flowsheet rows for two weeks.   This practice reduces the chance of the problem occurring but is not airtight.',NULL,'DLG# I7512887 / Package # E759248',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-21 01:21:00','2009-10-21 03:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(371,4685254,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3881100,'Functionality that Displays Last Lab Component May Not Display Values for Same Components Filed at the Same Instant','','',NULL,NULL,'all clinical apps + Affiliate Link',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-24 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Denise Bowen dbowen@epicsystems.com',NULL,'4855',NULL,'','','','4 hrs (TS + DO)','also:  4908, 4909, 4910, 4911','0903-PS-PR4685254-E759318-Spr07Sep14NS.tar.Z (adhoc 4855)\r\n0914-PS-PR4685254-E759359-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z (adhoc 4908)\r\n0916-PS-PR4685254-C75031560-E759380-E759377-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z\r\n0916-PS-PR4685254-C75031560-E759380-E759377-Spr07Nov16NS.zip\r\n','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  I7512897-E759318 Del,          I7512900-E759377 Del,             I7512918-E759359 Del,                   I7512919-E759410 & C75031560 Del,                 I7512946 -E759380 Del; E759318 is broken; GA rquesting ad hoc for (E7700799)\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n   I7512897,  I7512900, I7512918. I7512919, I7512946, I7701847 for SU09\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4855, 4909,4908: (orig inclu 4910 & 4911 too)):  \n  SP’07 E759318 9/03/09; E759359 9/14; C75031560, E759377, E759410 & E759380 9/16\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/27/09: Tar file for adhoc 4909 rec. 10/27.','This issue affects regions that use functionality to display the last value for a result component. If multiple result values are filed to a particular result component at the same instant, then only one of the values appears as the last lab component value in the affected functionality. Other simultaneously filing components will not display. Results may be viewed correctly using the Results Review activity, however.\r\n\r\nThis issue can occur for results filed by the results interface or manually entered in the Enter/Edit Results activity. For example, if this issue occurs for culture results being filed from a results interface, a clinician could assume that there is only one organism when there are actually multiple organisms growing in this culture. \r\n\r\nThis issue also affects the following:\r\nLast Lab SmartLinks or Smart Texts with Last Lab SmartLinks embedded\r\nInBasket results functionality\r\nPrint Groups or print group copies configured to display Last Lab results.\r\nProgramming point LPP 18813 ? Lab Test Report for Meds  Like LPP 18814, this programming point is also used in OCC records with the Report display item to display result information in the Order Composer.\r\nThe Results Review activity affected if the following views are used:\r\nLatest Results View\r\nCondensed View\r\nExamples of lab tests that contain components that could be affected are Urine Cultures or a CBC.  In these examples, a Urine Culture or a CBC are considered components which have multiple values (organisms or Hgb, Hct, WBC, etc) posting to that component.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/16/2009: more fix files arrived\r\nPer Y. Lassiter\'s 9/24 email: IP will own this ad hoc.\r\n09/14/2009:  see comments for curr status re: outstanding DLGs.   08/20/09: 8/20:  per Rosalba / Sherry Ellis / Aditi, NCAL will not implement a workaround.   08/11/09: 8/11: new W/As for consideration provided by Epic in pdf doc--forwarded to Sherry Ellis.  Sherry would like to receive 7 DLGs (fixes) incrementally in Sept.   08/04/09: Epic has identified new areas of affected functionality--see comments.  Updated reports run by EPIC were sent to A. Thorup and A. Vakil on 8/4. 7/29:  per Drew Davey:  NCAL affected build = 308200005-NCO_RESULTS_REPORT:_HEM_ONC_LABS_(NATIVE_HTML7/29:  per Drew Davey--\"In response to the question of whether or not NCAL is affected due to the pull forward functionality, they indeed are. The ORD results which I shared with my regional contact (Jansin Lee; CC?d) all exhibit the issue of multiple result components filing to the same result contact for the same order at the same instant\"\r\n7/24:  Epic running queries to determine print groups affected--results expected week of 7/27. 07/24/09: Must send communication to inform providers how to view components.  Regions must determine. ','Communication to providers--regions must determine how best to view components','','Communicate to both KP and Affiliated non-KP providers to look in Results Review, when possible, for correct lab results if it appears that some lab data may not be displaying or documenting.\r\nNational AffiliateLink AC (Jenna Ingelson) will coordinate with National KPHC Communications (Ravi Poorsini) to craft a single communication to the Affiliated providers, and will work with Regional AffiliateLink AC\'s to post the communication in AffiliateLink, as appropriate for each affected region.\r\nCommunicate that SmartLinks may be affected and that documentation should be checked for accuracy.\r\nEpic (Denise Bowen) will send a list of affected builds containing affected SmartLinks and print groups to PART and to each region by 7/28/09.\r\nSmartLink section of the build search has been fine-tuned to better detect SmartLink HHS 918 - ROUNDING REPORT COMPONENT BASED RESULTS (RRRESULTS) and LPGs that use this SmartLink or copies. \r\nLABRSLT SmartLink (HHS 220) is now affected and will be detected in the build search. \r\nAdditional affected print groups included in revised build search:\r\nLPG 53070 - LAST LAB RESULTS (RICH TEXT)\r\n52068-IB Results: Consolidated Results with Historical Values (Rich Text)\r\n52608-IB Results\r\nNW, NCAL, SCAL, HI, Co/Exempla, MAS, OH, and GA will review region-specific information and work with their physician leads to determine appropriate communications and plans of action for their region.\r\nRegions may work with their Epic TS\'s to obtain report results.\r\nISG (Alice Ducey) was notified of potential impact to the AffiliateLink web application.\r\nResults Review Workaround \r\nAffected views can be disabled if listed in the profile setting ?Results Review views to hide? (LPR item 34099 ? Profiles> Lab, Result > Page down 4 times).\r\nExtended Views are not affected and should still be used in the workaround.\r\nAdditional Workarounds as of 8/11/09\r\nEpic (Denise Bowen, Jason Ramaker) has provided additional workarounds which you may consider usig until the SU fixes are available and installed in your region.\r\n\r\nUse Extended View to View Lab Results\r\nSince the Extended View of the Results Review activity is not affected, instruct clinicians to use the Extended View to view lab results. To ensure that only Extended View can be accessed, configure the clinicians\' profiles as follows:\r\nIn Clinical Administration, select Management Options > Profiles (LPR).\r\nOpen your profile and select Lab, Result.\r\nOn the Results Review screen, enter Latest Results View and Condensed View in the Results Review views to hide field.\r\nShow all existing values for a result component in Hyperspace\r\nConfigure the following affected areas of Hyperspace so that they display all of the existing values for a result component. This configuration ensures that all of the values appear when multiple values are filed at the same instant. \r\nUtilize mnemonics:  SmartLinks 13, 55, 56, 61, 63, 168, and 169 each can use a mnemonic to display all values for a result component. The mnemonic must be added in the in the following format: [<result component basename>:*. For example, if you want to display all values for a WBC component and you are using SmartLink 61, your SmartLink should appear as such: .LASTLAB[WBC:*. You can also use a comma-delimited list to specify multiple result components in the mnemonic. For example, [WBC:*,RBC:*. This mnemonic can be added to the SmartLink on-the-fly, or it can be added when the SmartLink is used in another SmartTool, such as a SmartText or SmartPhrase. \r\nUtilize print groups: Print groups 55629 and 15023 each have a parameter that can be set so that the print group displays all values for a result component. Specify a result component in the first parameter of print group 55629 or the second parameter of print group 15023 in the following format: <result component basename>:*. For example, WBC:*. You can use a comma-delimited list to specify multiple result components in the parameter. For example, WBC:*,RBC:*.\r\nConfigure pro',NULL,' 09/14:  Update on DLG arrivals per Denise Bowan:\r\n     DLG I7512946 ? 9/15/09\r\n         E759380\r\n         Ad hoc 4911 ? expected delivery: 9/16/09\r\n     DLG I7512900 ? 9/16/09\r\n         E759377\r\n         Ad hoc 4909 ? expected delivery: 9/16/09\r\n     DLG I7512919 ? 9/16/09\r\n         E759353, C75031560\r\n         Ad hoc 4910\r\n         Still in Pend QA, will attempt to include in 9/16/09 delivery if released in time\r\n 8/4:  Epic nows say these additional areas of functionality are affected:\r\nLABRSLT SmartLink (HHS 220) is now identified as affected \r\nSmartLink HHS 918 - ROUNDING REPORT COMPONENT BASED RESULTS (RRRESULTS) and LPGs that use this SmartLink or copies.  \r\nAdditional affected print groups included in revised build search:\r\nLPG 53070 - LAST LAB RESULTS (RICH TEXT)\r\n  52068-IB Results: Consolidated Results with Historical Values (Rich Text)\r\n  526008-IB Results\r\nProgramming point LPP 18813 ? Lab Test Report for Meds also affected.  Like LPP 18814, this programming point is also used in OCC records with the Report display item to display result information in the Order Composer.\r\nThe Results Review activity is affected if the following views are used:\r\nLatest Results View\r\nCondensed View\r\nResults Review Workaround \r\nAffected views can be disabled if listed in the profile setting ?Results Review views to hide? (LPR item 34099 ? Profiles> Lab, Result > Page down 4 times).\r\nExtended Views are not affected and should still be used in the workaround.\r\n\r\n\r\nrisk assessment by Dr. George Peredy  Some puzzlement over why this wasn\'t noticed previously.  As reported by Epic, orders affected for NCAL = 83 in last 4 months.  Other regions had much higher order # (e.g., CO 14K in last 3 mo, 11K of which were EKG).\r\nSLG 415286 \r\nSP\'07 SUs (DLGs create thus far):\r\no   DLG I7512903\r\no   DLG I7512897\r\no   DLG I7512900 ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-24 01:04:00','2009-11-03 11:30:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(372,4696694,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - SP\'07 -  Information entered in a SmartForm navigator section may not be saved if a read-only SmartForm section opens in the same navigator','','',NULL,NULL,'OpTime, Anesthesia, Inpatient, ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-29 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Jason Ramaker',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'JUL09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512857\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-C75031528\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: Sept kpkg, 2/2010 install','Data entered in a SmartForm navigator section or SmartSection may not be saved when another SmartForm in read-only mode loads in the navigator.   This issue does not affect Classic SmartForms.\r\n\r\nTo recreate:\r\nOpen a navigator and enter information in a SmartForm section or SmartSection (Section A).\r\nScroll to a read-only SmartForm section (Section B), which causes Section B to load.\r\nExit the navigator.\r\nThe information that the clinician entered in Section A is not saved.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/04/09: Epic (Jason Ramaker) will provide code fix SP\'07 - I7512857 as part of a KPackage','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-07-29 02:38:00','2009-10-20 10:45:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(373,4709807,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient - NCAL, SCAL impacted - Unit pairs in OTL order templates could become mismatched, in certain circumstances ','','',NULL,NULL,'ClinCon',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-03 00:00:00','2009-09-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Peter Lesperance',NULL,'4760',NULL,'','','','1 hour TS & HQ','adhoc fixed PR 4272797, and this ','0728-PS-PR4272797-E758871-Spr07Jul06NS.tar.Z    Requires outage ','July 09 K-pkg ','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'C','NA',NULL,NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'AUG09','N','S','N','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7512006/E75887\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4760):  \n  SP’07 E758871\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K070609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/22/09: Per Doris Lew, ok to close.',' Two unit pairs-- specifically, dose/dose units (ERX records) and occurrence/occurrence type units (ERX and/or EAP records) -- in OTL order templates for orders in user created PRL Order Sets could become mismatched if both of the following conditions are true:\r\nA user overrides one item of the pair but not the other (e.g., overrides the dose but not dose unit), and\r\nA change is subsequently made to the underlying ERX or EAP record and propagated by National Pharmacy.\r\n\r\nSample workflow:\r\nA medication is configured to default 2 mg as the dose.\r\nA base PRL order set is created using the medication with no default specified for the dose or dose unit.\r\nA user creates a version of this PRL order set and changes the dose but not the dose unit. The dose unit defaults to the ERX default, but it is not saved in the OTL record because it is not changed.  (The problem does not occur if both parts of a unit are changed.)\r\nNational Pharmacy makes a change to the ERX record to specify a new default dose and/or dose unit.\r\nWhen the user who created the user order set places a customized version of the order, the dose will come from the user\'s OTL but the dose unit will come from the ERX record.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/22/09: Per S. Ellis Pharmacy should certify; Helen sent email to D. Lew on 9/22.\r\n09/15/09: F/up email sent to S. Ellis on 9/15.\r\n08/18/09: PS to F/up with S. Ellis (Order Sets), cc B. Mattern.\r\n08/11/09: Per Andre, two more queries for remediation will be run before install of fix and one thereafter.\r\n08/10/09: 8/10:  adhoc fix is in manifest for 8/19.\r\n08/04/09: 8/4:  per Dr. H, \"The docs need to be contacted to fix or we need to wipe out the favorites with the errors.\" Andre to confirm who will do this.   08/03/09: 8/3:  query file (potentially affected order sets) received from Epic, forwarded to Dhea, Sherry Ellis, Andre.    fix received 7/28, moved into WITS on 7/29. Fix for PR4272797 also corrects 4709807.','','','',NULL,'fixed in July K-package and in adhoc file received for PR 4272797 (adhoc 4760), received 7/28.  \r\nWill require remediation after fix is installed.\r\nAiming to install fix 8/19\r\nUPDATE 8/6/09: Potentially additional impact\r\nTo date, KP National Pharmacy (Dorcia E Hart) has reviewed this issue and offers the following response:\r\nNational Pharmacy reviewed the initial search results for affected user OTL order templates and Order Sets for NCAL and SCAL on 8/4/09 to confirm if dose/unit and occurrence/type have been changed. \r\nTwo ERX\'s were found to be potentially affected, but it was determined that they have not been changed in dose/unit and occurrence/type\r\n69517 Lactated Ringers only has one orderable unit which is ml      	  \r\n60420 Fat Emulsion has three orderable units which are ml, mg, g/kg/24hr --the default is 100 ml and has not been changed.\r\nThis indicates that the current impact on Order Templates is minimal because the frequency of changes to ERX records is low.  \r\nMedications are reviewed weekly, but they are changed infrequently.\r\nA  list of upcoming propagation of ERX changes can be provided on request.\r\nEpic (Peter Lesperance) has provided new information about this incident which may or may not further affect your region.  \r\nThe PART Team has reviewed this information with National Pharmacy (Dorcia Hart) and a National Clinical Content AC (Kindra Walker).  \r\nAlthough NW was not immediately impacted with the initial notification , this update indicates that there may now be some exposure for the NW, in addition to  potential additional impact for NCAL and SCAL.  \r\nIn NCAL, SCAL, and NW, we have confirmed that a Pharmacy Clinical Content team is responsible for creating and/or modifying medication orders in the Medication section of Base Order Sets.  Dorcia Hart is forwarding this information with the attached search results to those teams for their analysis and response. \r\nPlease check with your regional Pharmacy Clinical Content team (who modify orders in Base Order Sets) after they have analyzed the additional information to determine if there is further impact or any need for remediation of Base Order Sets or User OrderSets.\r\nNew Information from Epic (Peter Lesperance):\r\nEpic has discovered another scenario that can cause the same issue reported in PR 4709807. The issue reported to PART involved changes to the ERX record subsequent to a user creating a user order set involving that ERX. The new scenario involves changes made to the base order set subsequent to a user creating a user order set.\r\nNew Scenario:\r\nA base order set is created with or without defaults for the two affected item pairs (dose/unit and occurrence/type). For example, a base order set is created with an Aspirin order with a dose/unit of 81 mg.\r\nA user creates an override for this base order set and changes one item in an item pair, but not the other. For example, the user changes the Aspirin dose to 160 mg. This will be compiled correctly initially.\r\nAn administrator modifies the base order set and changes the dose/unit to 1 Tab for the Aspirin order. This triggers a recompile of affected user order sets. Because the user order set in this scenario changed the dose but not the unit, the new compiled OTL will take the dose from the user order set (160) but take the unit from the base order set (Tab), resulting in an incorrect dose of 160 Tab.\r\nUpdated OTL search results that identify Order Sets impacted by this newly identified scenario are attached to this email. These results include the user order sets that might be affected by changes to base order sets. \r\nPlease note that there are results for NW and each deployment in NCAL and SCAL. You or the Pharmacy teams may contact regional Epic TS (Chris for NCAL, Shoba for NW, or Peter Lesperance for SCAL) to assist in explaing and analyzing the results.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-03 11:24:00','2009-09-22 03:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(374,4732768,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Patient data might not appear in last column of Inpatient Rounding Report if data spans multiple pages','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, Beacon',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-11 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'AUG09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513022\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609-E759413\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: Nov kpkg, 2/2010 install','Data may not appear in the last column of the Inpatient Rounding Report (LRP 45760-Inpatient Rounding Report Rich Text, or copies) if:\r\ndata in the last column spans multiple pages and  \r\nthe print group in the Inpatient Rounding Report has been configured to allow data in the last column to span multiple pages.\r\n\r\nA physician might not realize that data is missing from the report when this issue occurs and might make a decision based on incomplete data.\r\n\r\nThe released version of the Inpatient Rounding Report is not affected because the last column displays only the label Notes, which does not span multiple pages.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/22/09: Per Aditi\'s 9/22 email, affected print group has been installed; will be revisited in a couple of months.\r\n09/22/09: Helen to f/up with Aditi; will print group with w/a still be implemented before the fix is available?\r\n08/19/09: per Aditi:  waiting for fix, probably will implement prntgrp w/ w/a (LRP 45760 ? Inpatient Rounding Report)\r\n08/18/09: Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage\r\nNo regions are currently impacted, since an Epic search revealed that no region is using the affected report.','Per Epic\'s official notification:\r\nWork with your Epic representative to determine if your Inpatient Rounding Report displays data that spans multiple pages in the last column.\r\nTo prevent this issue, configure the print group in your Inpatient Rounding Report so that you are not using a SmartLink or a programming point record to display dynamic data in the last column of the report. Instead, configure the last column to display static data, such as a label. By displaying static data in the last column, you can ensure that the data does not span multiple pages. For example, the released version of the Inpatient Rounding Report displays the label Notes: so physicians can write notes in the column.\r\nAlternately, if your Inpatient Rounding Report uses three or fewer columns, you can configure the print group to include an empty column as the last column. To do this, specify an additional column with a width of 1% for your print group. Then adjust the widths of the other columns so that the total for the widths does not exceed 100%.','','Per Dustin Foster\'s 8/12 email: \"In the Resolution section notice (of the official notification document from EPIC) that it describes how to configure the print group in a manner to prevent the issue.  This isn\'t in a section titled \"Workaround\" but this is definitely a workaround if they need to use the print group.\"',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-11 03:49:00','2009-10-23 11:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(375,4752153,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Future or standing orders may display incorrectly after patient record merge/unmerge','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-18 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Betsy Radtke  ',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'AUG09','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Confirmed in K091409\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513033\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K091409-E759291\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/27/09: See Comments section for feedback from D. Arterberry; ok to wait for Sept kpkg. ','Potential Problem Description:   Future or standing orders may display incorrectly in the Open Orders activity after two patient charts are merged and then unmerged.  The following example illustrates this issue:\r\nPlace a standing or future order for patient A.  This order will appear in the Open Orders activity for that patient.\r\nMerge patient A\'s chart with patient B\'s chart.  The standing order for the merged patient (patient A)  will still appear in Open Orders.\r\nUnmerge the patient charts into records A and B.\r\nOpen patient record A, then open the Open Orders activity.\r\nThe original standing order for patient A appears in Open Orders for patient B but not patient A.\r\nHowever, the original standing order for patient A appears correctly in Chart Review and other areas of patient A\'s chart.\r\nIf the standing order is released from patient B\'s Open Orders, the resulting child order will file into patient A\'s record.\r\nThis issue only affects standing orders originally placed for the source patient (patient A) before the merge .',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'10/26/09: F/up email to D. Arterberry on 10/26.\r\n10/13/09: F/up email to D. Arterberry 9/23.\r\n09/23/09: Per E. Felter, Diane Arterberry is the contact for this issue.  Helen sent f/up email to Diane on 9/23.\r\n09/22/09: Helen to f/up with E. Felter; ok to wait for fix, don\'t need adhoc?\r\n08/25/09: Helen forwarded PART email to E. Felter and Hung Mele on 8/18.\r\n08/18/09: No charts in NCAL identified as affected','','','Inform HIM they should look for standing / future orders if they merge charts',NULL,'Affects HIM / Chart Reconciliation\r\nRisk assessment:  Dr. Andy Weisenthal\r\nUtility available to fix affected charts\r\nPer D. Arterberry\'s 10/27 email: \"I rechecked with Epic and Ncal has not had this problem.  The risk to Ncal is still very slow as it would take the combination of having future or standing orders as well as the records having to undergo a merge and unmerge.   Since there have not been any occurrences I would think that it\'s OK to wait until the code is installed as part of the k pkg and an Ad Hoc is not needed.\"\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-18 12:36:00','2009-10-27 10:29:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(376,4763882,1,'ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'ChartSync -  Chart locking may occur if certain patient data is corrupted ','','',NULL,NULL,'Ambulatory, IntraConnect',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-24 00:00:00','2009-10-21 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Robyn Pingle',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'C','NA',NULL,NULL,'Z',NULL,'4',NULL,NULL,'AUG09','N','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  with config change Kpackage fix performed as planned\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K051809\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/21/09: Per Y. Lassiter, fix is working in prod; closing this issue.','After the implementation of SP\'07 in NCAL and SCAL in 2008, incidents of intermittent chart locking began to occur that caused delays in the admission of some patients to the ED.  Specifically, non-clinical data was not being synced for some patients who had documented visits in a remote instance.  \r\n\r\nUntil the fix was delivered in the May 2009 KPackage, NCAL and SCAL worked with Epic to manually correct the errors as they occurred.  However, the problem persisted after the fix was installed, and the previous manual workarounds no longer worked. In addition, the problem was also evident in Ambulatory as well as ED.\r\n\r\nEpic (Robyn Pingel) identified data in specific patient records that had been corrupted, and once these records were corrected the code fix performed as intended.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'10/13/09: Per C. Russell, code for clean up installed successfully; email to Yolanda 10/13 for certification.\r\n09/22/09: Per Yolanda, in process; waiting for approval before installed in prod.\r\n09/01/09: per CRussell, RA 1683 was sent on 8/26 and has been approved.  The code for the cleanup was FTPed yesterday and is under review.  Whenever the code is approved, Robyn will be able to perform the cleanup.\r\n08/25/09: Epic (Robyn Pingel) will search for other affected records and run a cleanup utility. C. Russell will F/up re status of other affected records.\r\nEpic (Robyn Pingel) manually corrected the affected patient records.\r\nThis issue requires only a data fix.\r\nThe code fix for this issue was delivered in the May 2009 KPackage.\r\n','','','Once record cleanup is complete, the affected patient records will be correct and the installed fix should prevent further occurrences of the problem.\r\nA workaround is not needed.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-25 01:42:00','2009-10-21 03:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(378,4772039,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Inpatient - Orders could be sent without authorizing provider','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pharmacy, ED, OpTime, Beacon',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-28 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Dustin Foster',NULL,'',NULL,'','','15 minutes','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'AUG09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513072 I7701880\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609 -E759483 & C75031587\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage','Orders can be sent without an authorizing provider if users:\r\nhave their profile configuration setting Require Auth Prov? (I LPR 893) item set to No (the default is Yes)\r\nsign orders without completing the Providers form\r\n\r\nIn addition, the likelihood of the problem occuring may increase if either of the following two conditions is true:\r\nThe Using Default Provider? (I LPR 8315) item is set to No in the user?s profile. \r\nThe Using Default Provider? item is set to Yes, but the default provider is not configured to be an authorizing provider.\r\n\r\nAs a result, providers may not be notified of results for orders that were placed without an authorizing provider.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Jason Ramaker) ran a search that showed no regions with the affected configuration.  However, NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW and Exempla could be potentially impacted if they changed their current configurations without installing the fix.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-28 12:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(379,4772052,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - IP, IP Pharmacy - Dispense amount may change if Inpatient orders are modified in Verify Orders Activity','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pharmacy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-28 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Dustin Foster',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'AUG09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513015, I7701713\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609-E759367\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage','The dispense amount for a medication may be calculated using an Ambulatory rounding value in an Inpatient setting if the following conditions are in place:\r\nSP\'07 with SU E754067 is installed.\r\nDiscrete sigs feature is implemented. \r\nThe pharmacist modifies the medication in the Verify Orders activity. \r\nThe medication record is configured to have different administration rounding factors for Inpatient and Ambulatory medication orders.  \r\n\r\nThe dispense amount is NOT affected in the following situations:\r\nMixture medications, because the dispense amount is calculated differently. \r\nIf  the medication is modified in an in activity other than Verify Orders (such as a physician modifying the medication in the Rounding Navigator).\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No regions are currently impacted, as an Epic search revealed that no region had the affected build.  In addition, discrete sigs are not used at this time.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-08-28 04:07:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(380,4790560,1,'OPT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - SP\'08 and after - Patient Headers using surgical case or log programming point records may display incorrect or no information ','','',NULL,NULL,'Radiant',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-02 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Adam Sauder',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NCI',NULL,NULL,'P',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  Regional Data fix; no code coming\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/29/09: Per K. Starks, Darryl Gill and she will ensure that this is addressed from an OpTime/Anesthesia perspective.','Patient Headers may display information outside of the surgical or invasive record (new in SP\'08).  Incorrect or no information may display if the header configuration  contains programming point records that retrieve information from the Surgical Cases (ORC) or Surgical Logs (ORL) master files , which store patients\' surgical or invasive records in cases and logs.\r\n\r\nFor case or log information to be available outside of the surgical or invasive record, the viewing clinician must follow these steps:\r\nOpen the patient?s case or log.\r\nBe within the workspace that contains the open case or log in order to access any non-surgical or non-invasive information (such as the patient?s hospital chart). If a different workspace is used to do this step, the programming point cannot retrieve correct information to display in the header.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/29/09: Helen Q. sent f/up email to M. Wilson requesting confirmation of receipt of email and that he will ensure config install.\r\n09/08/09: Helen Q. forwarded PART email to Michael Wilson, cc\'d Kim Starks.\r\n09/02/09: Must implement config described in Workaround before going to SU09\r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) is not planning a code fix for this incident. Implementing an Epic recommended configuration will avert the problem.','Use the following configuration before implementing SU\'09 in production:\r\nIn Clinical Administration, go to the Patient Workspace Settings screen (Management Options > Profiles (LPR) > Activity, Workspace, In Basket). \r\nIn the Patient header field beneath the Programming Points heading at the top of the screen, enter a patient header that contains no case or log programming point records.\r\nBeneath the Encounter Type Specific Patient Header Overrides heading, enter Surgery in the Encounter Type column and enter your OpTime header in the Patient Header column.','','',NULL,'NCI--doesn\'t affect until SP08 and later\r\nNCAL could be potentially impacted if we use OpTime with SU\'09.\r\nFound in Epic testing.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-02 04:36:00','2009-09-29 03:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(381,4809076,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Result note In Basket messages are not sent if comment field is blank','','',NULL,NULL,'InPatient (minimally?), ED, OpTime, Radiant, Beacon',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-10 00:00:00','2009-09-22 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Dan Bailey',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','30 minutes; T. Stewart and H. Quihuiz','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'C','NA',NULL,NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SEP09','N','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'STANDARD IN RELEASE:  SUM09',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'09/22/09: Consensus is to close; NCAL not afffected.','A Result Note In Basket message that is forwarded to another user may not reach the intended recipient(s) if the following conditions are in place:\r\nThe Result Notes form is launched by the Result Notes In Basket command button (R HIC 110). \r\nThe sender does not enter any comments.\r\nNo default text is specified in the Text to Use for Empty Result Notes (I LPR 39) item in the EpicCare Profile.    \r\n\r\nThe Result Notes activity launched by the Result Notes - Activity In Basket command button (R HIC 160) is not affected by this issue. This feature was introduced in SP\'07 as a replacement for the Result Notes In Basket command button.  With this feature it is important to select at least one order to ensure that the result note is filed to the medical record.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'09/10/09: 9/10:  per Johnette, NCAL is not affected (using LPR 39 for default text) \r\nT. Stewart to forward PART notification to J. Dee; setting of I LPR 39 needs to be checked.  No code fix is planned.  Query results inconclusive.','Historical Remediation/Urgent Mitigation:\r\nNot possible.\r\nWorkaround:  \r\nSpecify a value in the Text to Use for Empty Result Notes (I LPR 39) item of the system level EpicCare Profile record and all other fixed Profile records.\r\nTransition to the Result Notes - Activity In Basket command button (standard in SU\'09).\r\nHow is each region configured? ','Not Possible','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-10 01:04:00','2009-09-22 11:38:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(382,4820311,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient - Order values in PRL-based user order sets may not be saved correctly, in certain circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-15 00:00:00','2009-11-11 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Peter Lesperance',NULL,'4928',NULL,'','','','30 minutes H. Quihuiz','Tony Ahankoob SCAL will request','0918-PS-PR4820311-E759409-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z\r\n0921-PS-PR4820311-E759406-Spr07Nov16.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'C','NA',NULL,NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SEP09','N','M','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  no outage for utility; fix requires outage; standard in SU09 IU2\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513146 (utility) & I7513147 I7702102, I7702110\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 4928):  \n  SP’07 E759409 9/18/09 E759406 9/21/09\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/11/09: OK to close per Y. Lassiter\'s 11/11 email.','This issue occurs if SU I7511980 (in 070609 KPkg) has been installed.  User-specified values in PRL-based User Order Sets may be replaced by information from the associated source medication (ERX) or procedure (EAP) records.  The next time the User Order Set is opened, default order values will appear instead of what the user specified. The base order information is not affected.\r\n\r\nTwo situations can trigger this issue:\r\nA user creates a User Order Set and specifies a PRN reason without modifying another frequency group item (Frequency, Start Date, Start Time, End Date, End Time, PRN comments) inherited from the base Order Set.\r\nUser Order Set defaults may be changed if the User Order Set was created before installing SU I7511980 and recompiled after installation. This occurs if:   \r\nthe clean-up utility specified in PR 4709807 has not been completed and\r\nan administrator modifies the corresponding base Order Set \r\n\r\n*The two logical groups of items are that are impacted by this change are:\r\n Dose Group\r\nDose\r\nDose unit\r\n Frequency Group\r\nFrequency\r\nCount/Occurrences\r\nCount/Occurrence type\r\nPRN reasons\r\nPRN comment\r\nStart date\r\nStart time\r\nEnd date\r\nEnd time\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/11/09: Email sent to Y. Lassiter on 11/11 requesting certification.\r\n10/06/09: per Yolanda s/b part of Nov install\r\n09/22/09: S. Ellis moving the utility and fix into WITS.\r\n09/21, 09/18:  fix files received.  WITS? \r\n09/16/09: Clean up utility s/b avail 9/28; update on code fix will be provided on 9/21. The cleanup utility should be run after the affected SU is installed.  EPIC provided search results to S. Ellis and B. Yee.','If a user changes a PRN reason, he/she must also modify an additional frequency group item so that correct recompilation is triggered.\r\nRun the cleanup utility from Epic (Peter Lesperance) that will delete affected User Order Sets and alert end users of the deletion.  This utility will be released as SP\'07 SU I7513146.','Epic (Peter Lesperance) provided results of a search for affected User Order Sets in SCAL and NCAL to Inpatient Pharmacy (Bill Yee), SCAL (Tony Ahankoob), and NCAL (Sherry Ellis), and will continue to do so until the fix is implemented in those regions.\r\nPer Sherry Ellis\'s 10/22 email remediation is on going.\r\n','',NULL,'Per Bill Yee, NCAL will want the adhoc. \r\nRe w/a: Per Sherry Ellis\'s 10/22 email, \"No communication was sent due to the low number of user order sets impacted.  Dr. Hoberman\'s decision was to reach out to the individual\'s impacted and remediate through local Site support.\" ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-15 03:12:00','2009-11-11 04:18:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(383,4833564,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'ChartSync - NCAL, SCAL only - Complete history information not saved with user override','','',NULL,NULL,'IntraConnect (chart sync)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-18 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Robert Shimmin rshimmin@epicsystems.com',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SEP09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  fix is installable during a chart sync queue stoppage and doesnt require full outage\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513197, I7702260\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609-E759549\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/28/09: Per M. Lin\'s 10/27 email, 5 Id\'d charts will be remediated in prod on 10/29.',' In an Ambulatory encounter, a physician may choose to use ChartSync Override functionality when viewing the patient chart.  A prompt notifies the physician that only incomplete data may load. If a provider invokes this functionality and incomplete patient history data is loaded, complete patient history information may not be saved for future encounters, even in the home deployment. Only the data from the most recent encounter is saved.  \r\n\r\nFor example:\r\nA patient\'s history indicates that a previous episode of chicken pox is documented. \r\nIn a current encounter at another deployment, a provider chooses to override the complete loading of patient information using ChartSync and documents a diagnosis of  pneumonia for that patient.\r\nIf the provider uses the Override functionality, the chicken pox diagnosis is not pulled forward to the current encounter. \r\nWhen the provider saves documentation for the current encounter, in future encounters the pneumonia diagnosis will appear but not the one for chicken pox.\r\n\r\nThis issue has been known since 2004 and only impacts the history activity and certain navigators.  The audit trail is intact. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'10/26/09: Per M. Lin\'s 10/26 email PSUP testing has been completed for the clean up code. \r\n10/26:Per R. Shimmin\'s 10/26 email, additional clean ups will be needed if more occurrances are found.\r\n10/09/09: Per R. Shimmin\'s 10/9 email to M. Lin, code is available to remediate NCAL charts. \r\n10/07/09: Helen Q. left a VMX for R. Shimmin re status of restoring patient integrity.\r\n09/18/09: Epic (Robert Shimmin) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its development status by 9/25/09.\r\n9/18: Epic (Robert Shimmin) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its development status by 9/25/09.','Only workaround is to communicate to users:  avoid using the user override function to invoke chart sync. ','SLG #438049','Only nine charts were impacted within the last 12 months (even split between NCAL/SCAL).\r\nEpic is exploring the process to restore patient chart integrity via Chart Merge functionality.\r\nNCAL and SCAL TS\'s will assist regions with implementing this process.',NULL,'Risk accessment by Dr. Allen Rogers.\r\nPhysicians are more likely to base clinical decisions on the problem list and not the patient history.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-09-18 12:52:00','2009-10-28 02:17:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(384,4880445,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Reporting Workbench searches with mixed-case criteria may have incomplete results','','',NULL,NULL,'OpTime, Radiant, InPatient',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-05 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Adam Sauder',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'OCT09','N','S','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  DLG I7513246\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609-E759500\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/13/09: Andrea to f/up w/M. Flagg; per R. Blair, fix is in Nov kpkg (E759500).','Reports generated from Reporting Workbench might not return all records if mixed-case or all lowercase text appears in any free-text data fields or is used as a search index.  This is especially critical in the event of recalls if searches are performed on Implant Model, Serial, or Lot Numbers fields or the Immunization Lot Number field. \r\n\r\nFor example, if abc-123 is entered as the lot number value, a search on abc-123 will return no results.   If the lot number value is ABC-123, only a search on ABC-123 will return results; lowercase abc-123 or mixed-case AbC-123 will have no results. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Andrea is following up w/Marc Flagg re use of Workbench reports\r\nSU\'09 will include the fix which will automatically convert new and historical implant and immunization data to uppercase. Epic searches revealed the presence of records with mixed-case implant or immunization information however, per Marian (AMB) NCAL is only using WB reports for Anticoag, Radiant and Gyn (bar coding) so NCAL should not be affected.','Until the fix is installed, do not use Reporting Workbench to generate reports on implant or immunization information.\r\nIf a recall report is necessary, work with the regional Epic TS to create and run the report in Clarity.','','',NULL,'Physician Representative:Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-06 02:17:00','2009-10-13 03:25:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(385,4891070,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - In Basket messages may be sent to inactive users, in specific circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'InPatient, ED, OpTime, Radiant, Beacon, Anesthesia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-09 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Jason Ramaker',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'OCT09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I770459, I7513255\nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K111609-E759574 & C75031606\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/20/09: Per V. Santiago, NCAL does not use the affected buttons.','In Basket messages may be sent to inactive users (e.g., the Status (I EMP 50) item = 2) and thus never read if either of the following two In Basket buttons is used to forward the message:\r\n2047-Forward Encounter/Done \r\n2048-Forward Authorizing/Done\r\n\r\nThe buttons can be used in other message type definitions such as Transcription, Inpatient Transcription, and Result Notes. Using these buttons for those message types would also result in In Basket messages being routed to inactive users.\r\n\r\nThe message will be marked as Done and removed from the sending user?s In Basket with no indication that it was sent to an inactive user.  ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'10/13/09: Epic (Jason Ramaker) will supply code fix I7700459 in a SU\'09 release IU.\r\nNCAL does not use the specified buttons but could be potentially impacted if they choose to do so for results forwarding.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-09 11:56:00','2009-10-20 01:17:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(386,4892902,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Results Review activity may not display all results for users granted access with Inpatient security points, in certain circumstances ','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB, Nurse Triage, ED, OpTime, Pharmacy, Beacon, Affiliate Link',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-09 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Tim Williams',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'OCT09','N','L','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  12/02/09 (TW)\r\nNOTES:  entering Epic QA\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7513318, I7702673\r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED:  \r\n  SP07 K012510\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/15/09: Per L. Labeaud: Extremely minimal impact .  Only 6 end users affected who do not use results review.  No need for workaround at this time.','An incident similar to this--#2934489--was initially escalated in November 2007. In this related incident, a user\'s Inpatient security classification that authorizes him/her to view all results in Results Review could be be overwritten by an additional EpicCare departmental security classification. As a result, the user cannot view all results in the Results Review activity as expected.  \r\n\r\nThis issue occurs if  all of the following conditions are true:\r\nThe provider has both Inpatient and Ambulatory department-level security classifications;\r\nThe provider\'s Inpatient security classification includes Inpatient Security points 4-Results Review, 7-Chart Review or 12-Orders Review;  \r\nThe provider\'s Ambulatory department-level security classification contains security points that override the Inpatient security classification at the department level;\r\n The provider\'s Ambulatory security classification does not contain at least one of the following EpicCare security points for the department: \r\n16 - Chart Review\r\n94 - Order Review\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'12/13/09: Per V. Santiago\'s 12/10 email, AMB not affected; Andre forwarded query to M. Flagg for his review.\r\n12/02/09: Andre to f/up.\r\n10/13/09: Andre to f/up.\r\n10/09/09: Epic (Tim Williams) will provide SP\'07 code fix E754123 and notify PART of its development by 10/16/09.\r\nThe EPIC query of potentially affected provider security records was forwarded to A. Mure and Andrea Thorup.','Add security point 16-Chart Review or 94-Order Review as appropriate to an affected user\'s default security classification and to any security classifications that are specified as department-level overrides for the user. ','','',NULL,'Physician Representative:Andy Wiesenthal',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-09 01:20:00','2009-12-15 05:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(387,4903553,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Result values with non-numeric characters may display as truncated ','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB, Pharmacy, Beacon, OpTime, ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-14 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'OCT09','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7513349 I7702771\r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED:  \r\n  SP?07 K012509 -E759624 \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/15/09: Per L. Labeaud:Extremely minimal impact. No need for workaround at this time.','Result component values that include non-numeric data may be truncated if the display field is formatted only for numeric values.  This may occur if the source results data has been formatted in any of the following ways:\r\nAs a ratio. (e.g., for titre). For example, when a result is 1:99, 1 appears in the flowsheet row. \r\nAs a range (e;g; a value in a reference range). For example, when a result is 10-99, 10 appears in the flowsheet row. \r\nAs a string. For example, when a result is ?more than 8,? 0 appears in the flowsheet row.\r\nUsing < or >. For example, when a result is <100, 0 appears in the flowsheet row.\r\nUsing a comma as a group or decimal separator (e.g., with European currency). For example, when a result is 1,000, 1 appears in the flowsheet row. \r\n \r\nThis is a display issue only with fields that are expecting numeric data.  Actual ORD data is not impacted, although different places that reference the ORD value are constrained by what they can display. \r\n\r\nThe following six issues are impacted:\r\nNumeric flowsheet rows that extract and display result values might show truncated values.  \r\nGraphing activities that include result values might show truncated values.  All of the following graphic activities are affected:  Results Review;  Documentation Flowsheets;  Accordion Report; and  Outpatient Synopsis Activity.\r\nReporting Workbench queries for patients with specified Last Result values might return inappropriate patient records.\r\nCensus Field (PAF) columns that display result values might show truncated values.\r\nBest Practice Advisories (BPA) that check result values might not be created. If the following programming points (LPP) are used to check the result value for a specified result component, the calculation might fail if the programming point finds non-numeric result values: \r\nR LPP 10010, DECREASE\r\nR LPP 10020, VALUE IS OUTSIDE OF NORMAL RANGE (USE MOST RECENT RESULT)\r\nR LPP 10025, ABOVE BY (USE MOST RECENT RESULT)\r\nR LPP 10030, BELOW BY (USE MOST RECENT RESULT)\r\nR LPP 10035, DEVIATE BY\r\nR LPP 10040, INCREASE\r\nR LPP 10041, PERCENT INCREASE\r\nR LPP 10043, PERCENT INCREASE (COMPARE WITH OLDEST ORDER IN LOOKBACK WINDOW)\r\nR LPP 10045, CHANGE\r\n \r\nSmartLink records that use Result Values in a calculation might use truncated result values and display inaccurate calculations.  Three Epic-released SmartLinks are affected:  \r\nR HHS 56002, PEAK HEART RATE\r\nR HHS 56003, PEAK EFFORT\r\nR HHS 56005, PEAK BLOOD PRESSURE',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'12/13/09: Per 12/8 PS meeting, consensus is that affected BPAs need to be reviewed; R. Blair forwarded BPAs to Lyle and Andre.\r\n10/23/09: Per Byron Harper\'s 10/23 email, see comments re affected areas.\r\n10/20/09: Per A. Thorup still researching to determine impact.  Helen forwarded PART email and query to Michael Wilson (OpTime).\r\n10/15/09: Epic (Maria Spinozzi) will provide a fix for each scenario  and notify PART of its development status by 10/23/09\r\nPART notification was forwarded to K.Ryan, D. Wong, S. Ellis, V. Santiago.\r\nPART forwarded an EPIC query to be reviewed by each region to determine impact. A. Thorup will discuss w/ Bettianne and Dr. Hoberman.  ','Regions should alert their clinicians who may be impacted by specific query items (e.g., flowsheets, BPA\'s, etc).','NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, Exempla, CO, MAS, OH, and GA will review their regional query results to determine how they are impacted and take action they deem appropriate.\r\nIf an impacted item is part of the National Build, regions should work with the appropriate National AC for remediation (Flowsheets - Mary Seggerman; BPA - Fiona Po).\r\n','',NULL,'Flowsheets:  No Regions Impacted. Flowsheets are not affected in 2007.\r\nSmartlinks- No Regions Impacted. Only Cardiant is affected.\r\nNCAL: Affected BPAs\r\nNCAL\'s lab system (RILIS) sends all of their results as a padded string. \"    0.94\" instead of 0.94 \r\nAll results coming from RILIS in this form are affected by this issue. NCAL ACs have been alerted to this and are evaluating the affected BPAs.\r\n ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-15 07:39:00','2009-12-15 05:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(388,4909920,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT (IMMINENT IMPACT for GA only) - SU\'09 IU1 - In Basket report might not display multiple results, in certain circumstances','','',NULL,NULL,'InPatient, ED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-16 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  SU09 IU2 I7702403/E7701048\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix in SU\'09 IU2 (DLG I7702403/E7701048)','If an In Basket message has two or more unreviewed results, only one result may display for each message.  This occurs if all of the following conditions are true:\r\nAny of the following print groups (or copies) are used in In Basket reports:\r\n52060-Results: Consolidated Results Compact (Rich Text), \r\n52061-Results: Consolidated Results with Historical Values (Rich Text)\r\n52068-IB Results: Consolidated Results with Historical Values (Rich Text) \r\nThe report that contains the print group does not have a stylesheet applied. \r\nOne of the affected print groups (or copies) is configured to show report link icons (i.e., the nineteenth parameter of the print group is set to 1). ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'No regions are currently impacted since they have not yet installed SU\'09.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-19 09:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(389,4909910,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - MyChart - Discontinued medications may continue to appear in Medication Lists  ','','',NULL,NULL,'MyChart, Lucy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-16 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'OCT09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513245 I7702392\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED:  \n  SP’07 K012510 -E759505\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/21/09: See feedback from MyChart Tech Services in Next Step History.','A medication that has been discontinued could still display in a member\'s MyChart if the setting to specify the number of days after an end date is not set to zero or null. In addition, instead of indicating that the medication has been discontinued, the word \"Expired\" appears which may confuse the member into thinking that he or she should still take the medication.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Per MyChart Tech Services (via Vickie Santiago): \"An SU for Spring 2007 has been released which should be delivered in the November K-package which will make sure that even if you change this field the issue  will not occur.\"\r\n10/20/09: V. Santiago is confirming no impact on MyChart; per Andrea she thinks we don\'t use \"Lucy\".\r\nEpic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix in SU\'09 IU2\r\nNo regions are currently impacted, since all have the affected configuration set to zero or null.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-19 09:29:00','2009-10-26 09:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(390,4919341,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SP 07 Inpatient Regions-Page Breaks May Cause Misaligned Medication Information in After Visit Summary Reports','','',NULL,NULL,'ED (ASAP), Inpatient Pharmacy (WILLOW), OpTime',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-20 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Chris Russell',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'OCT09','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7513330, I7702706\r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED:  \r\n  SP07 K012510-E759631\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/02/09: Per Andre, no impact; waiting for Jan kpkg, 5/2010.','Misaligned medication information (medication name and dosing instructions) may appear at page breaks in After Visit Summary Reports using Print Group  46165 (IP Take-Home Discharge Medications), and potentially other print groups, if the following formatting combinations occur.\r\n\r\n The text in the medication name column is bold-face type.\r\n The medication in question appears at the bottom of the page, such that the first line of the details column (the column that contains the dose instructions) falls on the last available line to be printed.\r\n\r\nWhen these conditions are true, the text of the medication name may not start on the same line as the dose instructions.  Instead, the instructions will fall to the 2nd page, leaving only the dose information in the details column on the first page.\r\n\r\nPrint Groups 53012 and 56511 (both confirmed in use by Hawaii) and 56500 (confirmed in use by the NW) may possibly be affected.  They both use tables and Bold text in printing medication orders in AVS reports.\r\n\r\nThe Hyperspace display of the After Visit Summary is unaffected. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/2: Per Sylvia Fong: none of the print groups are in use for Willow..\r\n10/27/09: Andre to contact Isaac Santos re impact on ED, IP; Helen sent email to S. Fong re impact on IP Rx (Willow). 10/27: Per Chris (EPIC) no ETA, in development. Appears NCAL is not affected.\r\n10/21/09: A. Mure is reviewing the issue.\r\nPer M. Wilson\'s 10/21 email OpTime is not using the AVS.\r\nPART notification sent to Michael J. Wilson (OpTime) on 10/21.','Clinicians printing the After Visit Summary are recommended to review the printed page to ensure that instructions starting at the end of a page are clear.  \r\nIn addition, a link can be added to the After Visit Summary report which, when clicked, will allow the report to be sent to the printer using the Epic Print Service (EPS), as opposed to the default Windows Printing Service.  Reports printed with EPS will always place a page break where a new row in the medication table begins, rather than splitting a single row across pages. Print Group 46665 (IP Print Report from Hyperlink) is not affected and can be used in place of Print Group  46165 (IP Take-Home Discharge Medications) or other print groups that may be affected.  \r\nIf  SU E758740 (includes LPG 46165), which was delivered as an ad hoc on May 20th has been loaded by a Region, the boldface for most medication names will be removed (so frequency of occurence of this problem is minimized), except in cases where the same medication name appears in more than one order. If the medication name appears in more than one order, this probelm can still occur.  (E758740 was originally scheduled for the July KPackage but pulled at the last minute due to a problem.  It was fixed by E758976, which is in the September K-Package.) Loading E758740 reduces the risk of this issue occuring, however, it does not completely correct the issue and is not considered a fix. ','','All regions using print groups in their AVS reports should review those reports to determine if this issue occurs.',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-21 09:47:00','2009-12-02 10:44:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(391,4928423,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SP 07 NCAL and SCAL  - Released Chart Synched Orders may revert to Signed and Held Status','','',NULL,NULL,'EpicCare Inpatient, Care Everywhere',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-22 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Robert Shimmin',NULL,'5007',NULL,'','','','','NCAL','1117-PS-PR4928423-E759600-Spr07Jan25NS.tar.Z\r\n1117-PS-PR4928423-E759600-Spr07Jan25NS-Notes.zip','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'OCT09','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7513341\r\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 5007):  \r\n  SP07 E759600 11/17/09\r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED:  \r\n  SP07 K012510-E759600\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/02/09: Testing s/b complete 12/1; planned for prod 12/16.','When a member is admitted to a facility in a non-Home Deployment and orders are written, Signed and Held, and then Released, the parent orders may inadvertently revert to a status of Signed and Held when data is automatically synched between deployments in Care Everywhere.  This issue occurs when the following criteria are met:\r\n\r\n1. A region has loaded SU E758549 (delivered as an ad hoc and in the July K package)\r\n2. A member is admitted to a facility in a non-Home Deployment\r\n3. One or more providers opens the chart and keeps the chart open from when orders are Signed and\r\n    Held, through admission, and until after the orders are Released \r\n4. A Race condition occurs while the data is being filed',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/25/09: Per T. Alexander 11/24, code was installed in WITS3 on 11/24 and verified.\r\n11/23/09: Per T. Alexander\'s 11/23 email, change request has been submitted to install to WITS3 on 11/24.\r\n10/28/09: Per A. Huffman\'s 10/28 email, using the error reports as a w/a is not doable.\r\n10/27/09: Helen sent an email to M. Lin re error reports; will they be used as a w/a?\r\n10/22/09: Epic (Robert Shimmin) will provide an ad hoc fix which will also be included in the January 2010 K package.','Providers should close patient charts after Signing and Holding orders or before a member is admitted and the orders are Released\r\nNCAL and SCAL have existing Error Reports written that will generate an error message when a \"fail to release\" action occurs','','',NULL,'Dr. Ben Broder',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-22 02:06:00','2009-12-21 09:50:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(392,4932537,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Summary Reports Might Contain Inaccurate Medication Lists','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, (ASAP), Orders, InPatient Pharmacy (Willow), OpTime',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-23 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Dustin Foster',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7702568\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/26/09: Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage or Interim Update, SP08 and SUM09','A clinician can print a summary report, such as a Discharge Summary or After Visit Summary, to provide a patient with instructions related to medications the patient should continue taking after leaving the hospital.\r\n \r\nWhen a clinician modifies the patient\'s medications and prints the summary report, the changes to the medications might not appear in the report. In Hyperspace, however, the medications appear in the report as expected. after a report has been printed,  As a result, the patient might have an inaccurate list of medications, and the clinician might not realize that the medications are incorrect in the patient?s printed version of the report.\r\n\r\nThis issue occurs when using a summary report that contains one of the records listed below, or a duplicate, and the record is configured as described below. When the records are configured as described below, the print group or SmartLink displays the medications that were listed as the patient?s current medications as of the time the patient was discharged or the time the After Visit Summary was printed: \r\n\r\nSmartLink 340-PtMedDischarge. The seventeenth parameter is set to the default value of null (\"\"). \r\n\r\nPrint group 46165-IP Patient Take-Home Discharge Medication Information. The nineteenth parameter is set to the default value of null. \r\n\r\nPrint group 48805-IP Discharge Meds Take Home. The twelfth parameter is set to the default value of null. \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-26 08:30:00','2009-10-26 08:35:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(393,4932548,1,'RAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Measurements and SmartForm Data Not Copied to All Linked Orders','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-23 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Mike Yandl',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  standard in IU3\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7701868\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Epic (Mike Yandl) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage or IU','If a radiological study is configured to show measurements or use a SmartForm that is associated with a generic finding result context, the reading physician might not see all the measurement or SmartForm data entered in other linked orders, if multiple orders are linked to a single study. The measurement and SmartForm data entered for the orders is saved, but it does not appear in the study review palette for other orders. \r\n \r\n In addition, when users view the reading physician?s report in Chart Review and other locations, for one of the linked orders, the measurement and SmartForm data for all the linked orders does not appear.  A reading physician could base his findings on incomplete information, and users viewing the reading physician?s report would not see the complete results for the study. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-26 08:34:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(394,4932558,1,'RAD',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - Measurements for Imaging Orders Can Be Unintentionally Overwritten','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-23 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  standard in IU2\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7701790\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'10/26/09: Epic (Mike Yandl) will provide a code fix as part of a KPackage or IU','If a user enters measurement information for imaging orders using the Enter/Edit Results activity (or if measurement information is populated by an interface) and multiple values for the same measurement are populated on the same imaging order, it is possible for measurements to be unintentionally overwritten in the Measurements section of the Technologist Navigator or tabs that support measurements in a study review palette.    \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-26 08:39:00','2009-10-27 11:32:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(395,4948741,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Results Review may not display all results if certain configuration settings are used ','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-30 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Peter Lesperance',NULL,'5033',NULL,'','','','','req\'d by Rosalba  ','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'OCT09','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  12/07/09 (PL)\r\nNOTES:   2009 version in testing; then 2008 & 2007 work begins. regions need to make adjustments until the SU is available\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7513318, I7513318 \r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/15/09: Per L. Labeaud: Extremely minimal impact .  Only 6 end users affected who do not use results review.  No need for workaround at this time.','Results could be filtered unexpectedly from Results Review if certain user, security, and profile configuration settings are in place.  Three configuration areas have been identified:\r\nProfile ? Chart Review Excluded Encounter Types \r\nRestricted Patient Access (as with \"break the glass\")\r\nSecurity Class Overrides \r\n\r\nDetails: \r\nProfile ? Chart Review Excluded Encounter Types.  Intended to filter lab orders placed in specific encounter types from the Chart Review tabs and Review Flowsheets, the For Labs Tab & Flowsheets profile setting setting also filters the orders from Results Review.\r\nRestricted Patient Access (\"break the glass\").  Restricted patient?s results can be filtered for a user if any of the following configuration scenarios are in place: \r\nAllow Restricted Access = No or blank, and no departmental restricted access overrides are used.  No results will appear for the user with access to Results Review.\r\nAllow Restricted Access = No or blank, and restricted access overrides are configured by department to grant access.  A user with access to Results Review only sees results for orders placed in encounters from departments that have given that user restricted access. \r\nAllow Restricted Access = Yes, and restricted access overrides are configured by department to restrict access.  A user with access to Results Review can only sees results for orders placed in encounters from departments that have not blocked access for the user.\r\nSecurity Class Overrides.  Results can be filtered from Results Review if all of the following three security class overrides by department or unit are used. \r\nThe user is assigned a department security class override for a specified department or unit\r\nThe updated security class does not include security to view results.\r\nOrders are placed for the patient in the specified department or unit. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'12/13/09: T. Stewart requested that EPIC run queries b/c they had not been run previously;sent to Lyle and Andrea.  Lyle forwarded to Rosalba and M. Flagg.\r\n11/3:  Rosalba has requested adhoc: #5033 created. \r\n11/17:  Epic (Peter Lesperance) has informed us of the following change:  Due to feedback from various customers, Epic will not be removing the restrictions on displaying results in Results Review for the ?exclude encounter types? listed in the profile (filter #1 of the three noted in the original patient safety escalation):\r\nProfile ? Chart Review Excluded Encounter Types.  Intended to filter lab orders placed in specific encounter types from the Chart Review tabs and Review Flowsheets, the For Labs Tab & Flowsheets profile setting setting also filters the orders from Results Review. \r\nEpic will instead be enhancing the Results Review help text to discuss this restriction. \r\nOnly NW and OH were using this setting in any profiles.\r\nThe 2010 fix is still underway and a timeline for SUs has not been established.  Epic will provide another update on 11/23/09\r\n10/30: A. Thorup will discuss w/Dr. Hoberman\r\nRegional TS can run needed queries.','Adjust security classes used for department overrides so that they contain the appropriate security points to view results.\r\nRemove the encounter type exclusions from the For Labs Tab & Flowsheets profile setting.\r\nReview user settings for access to restricted patients to determine the impact based on regional configuration.','Epic (Peter Lesperance) ran search queries to identify:\r\nProfiles with excluded encounter types specified in the For Labs Tab & Flowsheets setting.\r\nUser records with access to Results Review and either restricted access or security override configurations that might filter results.\r\nRegions are advised to work with their Epic TS to review and analyze these searches.','',NULL,'Restricted Patient Access impacts NCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, CO, Exempla, OH, MAS and GA,  depending on how restricted patients are handled.\r\nSecurity Class Overrides impacts NW, NCAL, SCAL, HI, GA, and MAS.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-30 02:35:00','2009-12-15 05:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(396,4947952,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SP\'07 - NW only - Results routed with redirection may not reach any recipients, in certain circumstances ','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-30 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','S','P','L',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  11/30/09 ( PL) \nNOTES:  Fix will be in SP07 Kpackage and also available in SU09 IU3; also most likely in Jan Kpackage; wo; server only fix requring a downtime\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7702926, I7513379\nAD HOC EXPECTED (AUTH # 5033):  \nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/01/09: Epic (Nathan DaWalt) will provide a code fix before the release of SU\'09 IU3. ','A result message sent through routing redirection may not reach any intended recipients if all three of the following conditions are true:\r\nA future or standing order is placed within an inpatient encounter or HOV encounter but released and resulted within a separate encounter.  This can occur if the order is placed as either: \r\nAn after visit order (such as from an HOV encounter), or.\r\nA discharge order (such as from an inpatient encounter).\r\nThe matching line of the In Basket Recipients section of the results routing scheme associated with the resulted order is set up as follows:\r\nAuth. Provider? (I LRS 160) = No.\r\nAdditional Recipient Programming Point (I LRS 180) is set to one of the following programming point records:\r\n1052-CHILD ORDER\'S PARENT ORDER ROUTING SCHEME RECIPIENTS\r\n1053-REFLEX ORDER\'S ORIGINATING ORDER ROUTING SCHEME RECIPIENTS\r\n1057-GRANDCHILD ORDER\'S ORIGINAL OUTPATIENT ORDER ROUTING SCHEME RECIPIENTS \r\nThe matching line of the In Basket Recipients section of results routing scheme associated with the original future or standing order (for child or grandchild orders) or the original order (for reflex orders) is set up as follows:\r\nAuth. Provider? = No.\r\nA programming point is listed in Additional Recipient Programming Point but cannot determine a results message recipient for the original order.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/3/09:  As an FYI, note (info) has been forwarded to Beacon.\r\nThis fix is not scheduled to be in the November 2009 KPackage.','Ensure that results routing schemes that specify routing redirection include an authorizing provider (i.e., set Auth. Provider? to Yes).  \r\n','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-02 09:18:00','2009-11-03 11:07:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(397,4959990,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Performing an unmerge can result in various issues related to Contact Mover ','','',NULL,NULL,'all',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-03 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Brandon Podoll',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  11-11-09\nNOTES:  Some Sus coming; impacts thru SU09 IU2\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513375 I7702875\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED:  \n  SP’07 K012509\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/13/09: Per E. Felton and D.Arterberry emails no inaccurate patient records exist, no remediation needed.  If the unmnerge process is needed the w/a would be done to ensure pat data is correct.','The Contact Mover functionality is invoked during the unmerge process and can also be used in standalone mode.  Although KP does not use Contact Mover in standalone mode, it unmerges records as needed and is thus is affected by Contact Mover. \r\n\r\nEpic has identified fourteen different issues related to Contact Mover and possibly the unmerge functionality.  All are issues that relate to whether the right information reaches the correct unmerged, separated records. The issues are:\r\n1. Allergies Remain on the Source Patient Record and Are Not Moved to Target Patient Record. This can impact allergies added while the patient records were merged.\r\n2. Problem List Problems Remain on the Source Patient Record and Are Not Moved to Target Patient Record. This can impact Problem List items added while the patient records were merged.\r\n3. Immunizations Remain on the Source Patient Record and Are Not Moved to Target Patient Record. This can impact immunization items added while the patient records were merged.\r\n4. Overlay Resolution Report Doesn?t Indicate That Outpatient Medication and Procedure Orders Are Discontinued When Moved to the Target Patient Record.  The Source patient would need to have the medication or procedure order prior to the merge. The records would then need to be unmerged.  It is important to review the medications on both the Source record and Target record. as well as checking the Overlay Review Report.\r\n5. Outpatient Prescriptions for Source Patient Record Might Be Incorrectly Discontinued During Contact Move. The Source patient would need to have the medication or procedure order prior to the merge. The records would then need to be unmerged.  It is important to review the medications on both the Source record and Target record. as well as checking the Overlay Review Report.\r\n6. Actions Taken for the Source Patient Based on In Basket Messages Are Not Voided When the Contact Is Moved The In Basket message would have to have been on the Source patient prior to the merge.  The action on this message would need to have occurred post-merge.  When the unmerge occurs, it is important to check the In Basket message and data in the both the Target and Source record to determine if a problem occurred.\r\n7. Incorrect Order Information Appears in Treatment Plans. The treatment plan would need to exist on the Source record prior to the merge.  The associated orders would need to be released while the records were merged.  After unmerging, check the Source record to see if orders are still released when this treatment plan is moved back to the restored record.\r\n8. Changes Made to a Treatment Plan Remain on the Source Patient Record and Are Not Moved to the Target Patient Record. The treatment plan would need to exist on the Source record prior to the merge.  Changes would need to be made while the records were merged.  After unmerging, it is important to check both the Source and Target records to see which record has the changed info in the treatment plan.  \r\n9. Mammography Letters Can Be Sent to the Wrong Patient. This may occur if the letter was sent while records were merged.\r\n10. Mammography Recommendations Resolved for Wrong Patient.  This may occur if the documentation occurred on an encounter from the Source patient after the records were merged.  After unmerge, it is important to check data in both Target and Source records.\r\n11. Documented Implants Remain on the Source Patient Record and Are Not Moved to the Target Patient Record.  For this to occur, the documentation would need to be on the encounter from the original Source patient.  Documentation would need to have occurred after the merge.  Both Target and Source records should be checked after the unmerge.\r\n12. Anticoagulation Information Remains on the Source Patient Record and Is Not Moved to the Target Patient Record. The anticoagulation information would need to be on the Source record prior to the merge. Documentation would need to occur on this encounter pos',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/10/09: Per D. Arterberry queries are still being reviewed, s/b be done by the end of week;she will work w all regions once she can provide clarification on data.\r\n11/03/09: Diane Arterberry to review with regional Identity ACs\r\nEpic (Branden Podoll) will provide special updates only for the following items from the issues list:\r\nIssue #4: SP\'08 and SU\'09 fixes are planned to add information about the discontinued orders to the Overlay Resolution report. \r\nIssues #6 and Issues #9-14: Fixes planned for SP\'07-SU\'09.\r\nAn ad hoc code fix was not requested.','From the beginning of Epic implementation, KP has promoted the practice of an unmerge review policy. The process is to review both the Target and Source Records after the unmerge to ensure that each record has the correct data (allergies, immunizations, encounters, appointments, PCP, etc).    \r\nThe current worklow is:\r\nAfter the unmerge, review the Overlay Detection Report.\r\nEnsure that all items are accounted for on the \"restored\" target and \"restored\" source records after the unmerge.  \r\nAny items listed on the \"pre-unmerged\" record (i.e., items added while records were merged) should be manually added back to the correct patient record.\r\nAll regions (NCAL, SCAL, NW,  HI, CO/Exempla, MAS, GA, and OH) continuie to implement the workaround.\r\nRegions may refer to the above list of issues for more information on specific workaround suggestions, and take action as they see necessary.','Epic (Brandon Podoll) is running searches to determine if regions have currently affected records, and will send search results to Identify AC Diane Arterberry who will review and then forward to appropriate regions.\r\nRegions should work with their Epic TS to review and interpret the searches for degree of potential impact.\r\n','',NULL,'Risk assessment by Dr. Andy Weisenthal\r\nDiscovered by Epic',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-03 03:58:00','2009-11-13 01:52:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(398,4961781,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - IntraConnect - Chart Synchronization might not synchronize some linked records','','',NULL,NULL,'IntraConnect',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-05 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Robert Shimmin',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','Jan 2010 K-pckg','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  11/23/09 (RS)\nNOTES:  SU09 fix expected in Dec, SP07 fix Jan 15--both in Jan Kpackage or IU\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \n  SP07 I7513375 SU09  I7702875\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/9:  per R. Shimmin, SP\'07 SU I7513375 will be available January 15, 2010.','Chart synchronization might not synchronize linked records or their updates for a patient. As a result, a patient\'s record could have incomplete information and possibly linked records from another patient.  This issue may occur unpredictably.\r\n\r\nExample scenario:\r\nD = Deployment\r\nPatient 1 is homed at D-A and has an order. Both the patient and order records exist at D-B and D-C. \r\nAt D-B, the order for Patient 1 is updated and the update is sent to the patient\'s home deployment (D-A).  \r\nAs an update for an unrelated patient (Patient 2) is sent from D-B to D-A, the order for Patient 1 is incorrectly associated with Patient 2.  \r\nDuring the synchronization process, the chart synchronization audit unlinks Patient 1 and his order record at D-A.  Note: The order is not actually linked to Patient 2 in Chronicles, so Patient 2?s record will not be affected. The incorrect association instead affects how chart synchronization handles the data for Patient 1. \r\nD-C requests Patient 1?s chart from its home, D-A. Because the order record has been unintentionally unlinked in step 3 above, Patient 1?s chart might synchronize to D-C without the order record. A clinician at D-C would not have the latest update made to the order for Patient 1, although the update would remain in the order at D-A.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'11/5/09: Epic (Robert Shimmin) will deliver the SP\'07 code fix  I7513375 by 11/17/09.   NCAL and SCAL are the only regions using ChartSync. \r\nAn Epic search noted no affected records in NCAL and SCAL for SP\'07, although there could be potential impact if the SP\'07 fix I7513375 is not installed.','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-05 04:16:00','2009-11-09 02:56:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(399,4968169,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SP\'07 only - Data may not be saved with Copy Forward in navigator Doc Flowsheets','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-06 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Kristie Fowler',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','M','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  12/04/09 (KF)\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7513407\r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/15/09: See L. Labeaud\'s comments in next step history dated 12/15.',' If the Copy Forward functionality is enabled for Navigator Flowsheet sections, data copied from one column to another may not be saved.  This occurs if all of the following conditions are true:\r\n\r\nSP\'07 is installed with SU C7503521/DLG I754084 (May 2008 KPackage).\r\n\"Allow Copy Forward\" is set to Yes in the configuration record (item VCN 34705) for the Navigator section; if this setting is left blank, the LSD setting (LSD 34920) to allow copying must be set to yes.  Without this, the green hyperlink for copying will not appear in the navigator.\r\nIndividual Flowsheet rows in the template must be set to Allow Copy Forward.\r\nThe copy TO column has data.   The issue does not occur if the column is blank.\r\nWhen copying data from one column to another, the user:\r\nDoes not overwrite the column when prompted\r\nCloses the section without selecting the File button.\r\n\r\nAs a result, the copied data is not saved.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'12/15: Per Lyle, polled Mary Seggerman, National AC who stated may have impact for IP Pharmacy for Copy Forward was set to NO for NCAL. Bill Yee (Pharmacy lead) agreed.  We are evaluating just turning off sections and rows based on EPIC suggested workaround.  Rey Soriano, AC lead has been forwarded the querie and will be determining ability to turn off sections as suggested.\r\n12/13/09: Sent f/up email and query to suite reps on 12/1; reviewed query in 12/8 PS meeting.  Per Vickie S. AMB not affected.\r\n12/13/09: IP/ED still need to determine impact.\r\nPer PARTs 12/7 notification, fix has been added to the 1/25/2010 kpkg.\r\n11/06/09: Forwarded PART email and query to suite reps.\r\nPer Y. Lassiter, NCAL did implement SU in May kpkg that is one of the conditions of this issue.','Until the fix is installed, set the Copy Forward function to No in the Flowsheet configuration record for the affected sections. \r\nFor sections that do not have a configuration record, one may be created and attached, and the Copy Forward setting set to No.\r\nNCAL, NW, CO, MAS, and OH will review their search results and determine their plan of action for the workaround.  HI, SCAL, Exempla, and GA are advised to do the same.\r\n','Because of the time-based nature of this issue, it is not possible to determine past attempts to copy columns.\r\nEpic (Kristie Fowler) ran searches to determine which regions have affected builds and will give results to PART on 11/6/09, who will then forward to regions.\r\n','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-06 01:54:00','2009-12-21 02:20:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(400,4978963,1,'OTH',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'MyChart - Discontinued medications show as current for one day past End Date','','',NULL,NULL,'Mychart',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-10 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','1120-PS-PR4978963-E759635-Spr07Jan25NS.tar.Z\r\n1120-PS-PR4978963-E7701419-Sum09IU3NS.tar.Z','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','M','F','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  SP07 I7513387/E759635;  SU09 I7702970/E7701419\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 5049):  \n  SP’07 E759635 11/20/09\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED:  \n  SP’07 K012509\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/10:  per D. Yeap, \"NCAL is not affected by this as we do not display discontinued med. Also, we do not turn on the Wallet Card feature either. We are good with this.\"','Discontinued medications may display as current in MyChart until the day after the End Date.  \r\nSpecifically:\r\nOn MyChart Medications and Health Summary pages, any discontinued long-term medications will be displayed until the day after the prescription end date.\r\nIin the Wallet Card feature, discontinued medications, regardless of long-term status, will appear as current medications until the day after the end date. If the patient clicks on the Load From My Clinic button on the Wallet Card page, his downloaded list of current medications will include any discontinued medications with an end date in the future.\r\n \r\nThis issue pertains only to the patient\'s display and does not apply to AffiliateLink nor the MyChart prescription refill functionality.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Epic (Jacob Boehr) will provide a code fix and notify PART by 11/12/09 of its development status.  The fix is scheduled to be delivered the week of 11/16/09.','Epic has not proposed a workaround at this time.\r\nNCAL (Andy Wiesenthal) suggested suspending the printing of wallet cards until the fix is installed.','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-10 02:22:00','2009-11-20 02:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(401,4999577,1,'OPT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - OpTime - Implant documentation might be deleted when logs based on changes to procedures or preference cards are automatically updated','','',NULL,NULL,'Radiant',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-18 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Adam Sauder',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7703229\r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/22/09: NCAL, SCAL, HI, NW, CO, and GA could be potentially impacted if they have the affected configuration without the fix when they upgrade to SU\'09.','Existing implant documentation could be deleted during automatic log updating if the system is configured to automatically update existing logs to reflect changes made to an associated procedure or preference card record.\r\n \r\nSpecifically, this occurs when all of the listed system or location definitions settings are set as follows:  \r\nThe Case Update on Procedure Edit field contains any value except No Update.  (On Settings 4 form.)\r\nThe Log Update on Procedure Edit field is set to Copy from case.  (On Settings 4 form.)\r\nThe Auto-populate Implant Table? field is set to either At log creation and pick list creation or At log creation only.  (On Settings 3 form.)\r\n \r\nIf implant documentation is deleted from the log, the patient?s surgical record no longer lists the implants that were documented during surgery.  If a deleted implant is recalled, it is then impossible to use the system to identify the patient as being affected.   \r\n\r\nThis issue should not occur if either of the following fields contain programming point record 48754-OR/Inv Case Update Check (Log Exists Day of Case):\r\nThe Case Update Check Programming Point field or \r\nThe Log Update Check Programming Point field ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'No regions are currently impacted since SUM 09 has not been loaded. ','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-18 03:43:00','2009-12-22 10:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(402,4983346,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'NO CURRENT IMPACT - SP\'07 only - Print Group 47255 does not display Signed and Held orders ready to be released from general navigators and clinician order entry ','','',NULL,NULL,'OpTime, ED, Pharmacy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-19 00:00:00','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','Tim Williams',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','1120-PS-PR4983346-E759619-Spr07Nov16NS.tar.Z\r\n1120-PS-PR4983346-E759619-Spr07Nov16NS-Notes.zip','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'DLG NUMBER(S):  \n  I7513358 SU759619\nAD HOC DELIVERED (AUTH # 5058):  \nKPACKAGE DELIVERED:  \n  SP’07 K1116090-E759619\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/23/09: NCAL does use affected configuration; fix will be in Nov 2009 kpkg.','Signed and Held orders may not appear in print group 47255 Order: Pended Orders (or a copy) if both of the following conditions are true:\r\nSP\'07 is installed with SU E759427\r\nPrint group 47255 (or a copy) is configured to show signed and held orders that can be released only from general navigators and activities (parameter eight is set to 2). \r\n\r\nAs a result, clinicians might conclude that there are no signed and held orders available to be released from general navigators and activities when in fact such orders exist. \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-19 01:31:00','2009-11-23 02:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(403,5006315,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient - SP\'07 - CMED SmartLink displays all medications as current from the both current day and other encounters ','','',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-19 00:00:00','2009-11-24 00:00:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'C','NA',NULL,NULL,'Z',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'NOTES:  in 2010 release a new CMED Smartlink; but config change considered final fix\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'11/24/09: Confirm with Aditi Vakil if ok to close. per Aditi ok to close','All medications from the current day as well as from other encounters could display under the header \"Current Hospital Medications\" if theCMED SmartLink (or a copy) is used with parameters are set as follows:\r\nParameter 1-curr is set to 1 to display current medications as of the current date, and \r\nParameter 7-mode is set to 2 to display Inpatient medications, and \r\nParameter 9-header is not set, and \r\nParameter 14-MARtab is not set according to the workaround below. \r\nThe remaining parameters do not impact this issue.  \r\n\r\nSample Workflow:\r\nAn admitted patient has several orders placed by the attending physician. \r\nThe patient is discharged and then readmitted the same day or transferred to another facility. \r\nAn attending physician places new orders. \r\nThe attending physician starts a note and uses the hospital\'s version of the CMED SmartLink while documenting additional information. \r\nIf the Inpatient application has the configuration to automatically discontinue medications four hours after discharge, and it has only been two hours since the patient was discharged or transferred, the SmartLink pulls in medications from both of today\'s admissions. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NCAL was initially impacted but is no longer since they have corrected their configuration per the workaround.  No code fixes are currently scheduled for current Epic releases.\r\nRegions should implement the workaround as a configuration fix.  \r\nEpic is designing a new CMED SmartLink for their 2010 release.','','In the copy of CMED, set parameter 14-MARtab equal to \"4^ID\" where the ID is a TAB record ID for a MAR tab with the following setup:  \r\n On the first screen, give the tab a display name, set the type to \"GUI,\" and set Active to \"No.\" \r\n On the second screen, set the left column of the Active Group line \"Include\" and the right column of the same line to \"Active.\" \r\nAlternatively, set parameter 9-header to better describe the list of medications the SmartLink retrieves, such as \"All hospital medications for today\". \r\nCreate  a copy of programming point 34320 ? IP GENERIC CONTACT INFO, to be used to sort the confirmed admissions to the top of the contact selection window.\r\nCreate a copy of order validation programming point 34997 ? IP ORDER VALIDATION - CHECK FOR ROOM & BED, which will prevent users from signing orders in a contact where the patient has no room and bed. NCAL has identified issues in testing with implementing this programming point.  Epic (Chris Russell) will provide an update on 11/17 regarding the implementation of the programming point. \r\nStop the practice of assigning beds before admission, if facilities in your region engage in that practice.\r\nIf regions have two separate SmartLink for CMED and HOSPMEDS, the HOSPMEDS SmartLink should be rectified the same way.','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-20 02:15:00','2009-11-24 01:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(404,5004134,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Inpatient Flowsheets - Intake and Output rows may display incorrect data','','',NULL,NULL,'ED, OpTime',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-19 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Chris Russell',NULL,'5069',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','L','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  12/04/09 (CR)\r\nNOTES:   National developed and propagated the corrected build; SU10 in testing by 12/4\r\nDLG NUMBER(S):  \r\n  I7513477\r\nAD HOC EXPECTED (AUTH # 5069):  \r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/15/09: See L. Labeaud\'s comments in next step dated 12/15.','Intake/Output data added to a row in the default I/O template could display in an attached LDA group row instead of in the original row.  Users looking at the I/O row outside the default I/O template will not see the I/O data.  If they then attempt to redocument the data somewhere other than the default I/O template, it will calculate twice in the default Intake and Output Activity, leading to an incorrect I/O total.\r\n\r\nFor this issue to occur, all of the following factors must be in place:\r\n Lines, Drains, and Airways group(s) with a duplicable Intake and Output row, as part of the LDA group, are in use.\r\nThere are non-duplicable I/O rows in another template, separate from the default I/O template. These separate I/O rows are not listed in the default I/O template.\r\nThere are workflows where an LDA group, which was started on a previous or concurrent encounter, may be attached to an I/O flowsheet for a currently admitted patient. \r\n\r\nThe following workflow will reproduce this issue:\r\n \r\nA currently admitted patient has an LDA attached in a flowsheet for a currently admitted patient, which was inserted in a different encounter.  (An LDA may be added from a previous encounter if the encounters are related, or by simply picking the existing LDA when adding it to the template.)\r\nDocument a value in the I/O row contained in the LDA group in Flowsheet A.  Note: This row should be duplicable, meaning that copies of it can be made (although no copies are made in this scenario).\r\nProceed to a separate template, Flowsheet B, that contains I/O rows. This template is not the default I/O template itself, but a separate template designed to group several I/O rows of similar type together for convenience.\r\nDocument on one of these I/O rows.  Note: The row in this separate template should not be listed as part of the default I/O template itself, and should be a non-duplicable row (meaning that it cannot be copied).  The data on this row must be entered immediately after the LDA documentation in step 2.\r\nGo to the default I/O template, Flowsheet C, and notice that the row you just documented on has been added to the I/O template.  \r\nIn this same row, file some additional data in the row.\r\nNotice that the data has disappeared from the row where you attempted to file it.  The data instead appears in the LDA group where values were documented in step 2.\r\nProceed to the Documentation Flowsheet template from step 3.  The data you filed is not there.\r\nAt this point, the clinician is not seeing the correct I/O totals for the patient. If the clinician attempts to redocument the data in a template other than the I/O template, the value will be calculated twice in the Intake and Output activity and will show up twice in the default I/O template itself.  To reproduce this, redocument the value that is missing in step 7 in the same Time column .\r\nReturn to the default I/O template, and notice the data is now listed in both places.\r\nIn the I/O Activity, the data is now being counted twice.\r\n\r\nIn this scenario it is possible to produce I/O totals that are significantly different than the true I/O for the patient.  \r\nNOTE: More than one row may be affected at one time.  If additional rows are documented on in Step 2, they may also behave in this way.\r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'PER ANDREA T. I get a daily update and we have had no further issues. We are looking at a long term fix of automatically DCing LDAs on discharge but aren\'t going to discuss it again until 1/4/10.  Requesting that EPIC TS go to Weekly reports.\r\n12/13/09: per Lyle at 12/8 PS meeting, appears impact is minimal;no remediation as of now, Chris will run query 1 more week and Lyle will check with Andrea re how long review process will be. \r\n12/02/09: Per L. Labeaud, still in discussion; impact appears to be for pediatrics.\r\n11/24/09: Per A. Thorup, remediatiation changes have not been released, TBD.  Per C. Russell ETA for fix s/b available week of 12/1.\r\n11/23: Bettianne requested daily status from Epic.  One pat in SCL is affected by this issue.  Andrea has consulted w/ Rey Soriano re the affected patient b/c the activity is bizarre.\r\nEpic (Chris Russell) will provide a code fix and notify PART by 11/23/09 of the development status.\r\nAn ad hoc authorization is needed.','','I/O Flowsheet groups and rows that are not part of the I/O template itself may be added in a \"Start Removed\" state to the I/O template.  Adding them natively to the I/O template will prevent this issue from occurring.  Adding them in a \"Start Removed\" state will keep them from appearing in the template unless they are manually added by the user, or documented on.\r\nKPHC National AC (Mary Seggerman) will review queries provided by Epic (Chris Russell) to determine which rows should be added to default template 103, which is used by NCAL, SCAL, HI, and the NW regions.  These changes will be propagated to the affected regions today, 11/19/09.\r\nChanges to affected Exempla I/O templates will be assessed today by Exempla in the CO instance.  Exempla ACs (Leslie Jagoda and Tina Richardson) will determine if affected rows will be added to Exempla\'s default I/O template or whether Exempla will work to educate nurses to avoid adding LDA groups to templates.\r\nA consistent communication will be sent to the affected regions, in conjunction with the propagation, to alert nurses that they may see flowsheet rows on the default I/O template which have not previously been there.  Based on new functionality in  SP\'07, where flowsheet rows from one template may populate the default I/O template when values are entered on the non-default I/O template, nurses have previously noted that new rows may appear on the default template.  This has not frequently occured in NICU, PICU, and PEDS units so communication will focus on those areas, in addition to Adult units.\r\nOnce the changes have been propagated, the Interregional Nursing Governance Group will further review the impact on these changes. ','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-20 02:35:00','2009-12-15 06:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(405,5024077,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Batch template 34100 can cause header for first patient to repeat for subsequent patients','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB, ED, Rx',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-25 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Shoba Selvarajan',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'NOV09','N','S','R','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','Y','Y',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EPIC CODE STATUS DUE:  12/11/09 (SS)\r\nNOTES:  regions checked the reports and NCAL/SCAL were impacted\r\nKPACKAGE EXPECTED',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/15/09: Per L. Labeaud not an issue for NCAL at this time. ','In specific reports using batch template (E1A) 34100, the header information for the first patient in a patient list may repeat for subsequent patients in a patient list. This occurs  if both of the following conditions are true:\r\nBatch template record (E1A) 34100 is set up to print a report for each patient on a patient list.\r\nThe report contains a header print group that contains patient information such as patient\'s name, MRN, etc.\r\n\r\nFor example, the header print group on the second and all subsequent pages of a report, configured to use patient lists, may contain the name and MRN of the first patient on the list. If a page for the second patient or other patients on the patient list contains allergies or medication information for that patient, it may appear that the patient information for the second and consecutive patient names in a patient list could be associated with the first name on the list.    \r\nPrinting is server side.\r\nAt Kaiser, examples of printing using the batch template that meet these criteria could be patient letters (though currently Patient Lists are not implemented in Ambulatory implementations within KP) or MARs for Phase 1 or Phase 2 hospitals in current Inpatient implementations. \r\n\r\nUPDATE 12/10/09\r\nEpic (Shoba Selvarajan ) has informed us that there are now two variations of this incident that have been identified.  The first, is the original PART issue that was reported and discussed and it has no impact on any region. The second variation impacts only  NCAL, SCAL and CO. \r\n\r\nNO REGION IMPACTED BY THIS ISSUE: Issue #1 variation (QAN 840546)  ? Repeating header due to specific print groups\r\nWhen a batch job using template 34100 or 34500 generates certain reports, the header or footer for the first patient can repeat on every page.  As described below, this is dangerous because users might incorrectly think that clinical information from the body of a page corresponds to the patient identified in the header.  Reports containing print groups 54058, 54024, or 54014 (or copies thereof) in the body of the report that also uses a running header or footer print group (ie a print group that appears at the top or bottom of each printed page) will cause this issue.\r\nWorkaround: Do either of the following:\r\nRemove the running header from your report and replace it with a similar body print group OR \r\nReplace one of the affected body print groups with a similar print group. Affected body print groups are listed below along with some suggested replacements:\r\nLPG 54024 (affected) is similar to LPG 54088 (not affected)\r\nLPG 54014 (affected) is similar to LPG 54099 (not affected)\r\nLPG 54058 (affected) is somewhat similar to LPG 54011 (not affected) and/or LPG 54089 (not affected)\r\n	Fixes:  DLG 159385 fixes this issue in 2010.  SU\'09 fix I7701318 (E7701103) is released; SP\'07 SU is being developed.\r\n\r\nNCAL, SCAL, and CO impacted by Issue #2 variation (QAN 847572)  ? Mnemonic ?Split Report by Patient? can cause confusing headers in printed content\r\n	Description\r\nBatch job 34100 has a mnemonic called \"split report by patient.\"  When a job is configured to route reports to a printer this mnemonic behaves non-intuitively, suppressing page breaks between patients if it is set to yes.  If a job configured as such is also using a report with a running header or footer print group it can be hard to determine which information corresponds to which patient.  Information for multiple patients can appear on one page, and the header or footer will only display information for the first or last patient on the page, respectively.  It?s possible for a page to contain a header for patient A, and one line of information for patient A at the top, with the rest of the page containing information about patient B.  The effect is that the header for a given page displays information about a different patient than the body of the page.\r\n	NOTE: Jobs routing reports to BCA PCs are not affected.\r\nWorkaround: Always set \"split report by patient\" to\"no\" when routing to a printer.  This causes page breaks to occur between the end of one patient and the beginning of the next.\r\nFixes:  Page breaks will always be inserted between patients regardless of the value of \"split report by patient.\"  This fix is being developed in 2010 log 168714 and will be SU?ed back to SP\'07.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'Per PART\'s 12/10 update: NCAL, SCAL and CO impacted by second of new issues.\r\nShoba Selvarajan ran another query on 12/10.\r\n12/13/09: Sent f/up email to B. Shepardson re w/a; will it be implemented?\r\n12/02/09: Per A. Mure, NCAL does not use BATCH printing.\r\n12/01/09: Per B. Shepardson looks like ad hoc is not needed and impact is minimal; query still being reviewed.\r\n11/27:  search results received from Shoba (Epic)\r\nEpic (Shoba Selvarajan) will provide a code fix and notify PART of its development by December 11, 2009.\r\nAn ad hoc code fix was not requested or authorized at this time.  Regions are advised to install the fix when available.','Remove any affected header print groups from reports that meet the identified criteria and are included in batch jobs \r\nReplace the header print groups with similar print groups in the body of the report.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, CO, Exempla, OH, MAS, and GA will review the search results and choose an appropriate course of action as needed.','','By EOD 11/27/09, Epic is scheduled to provide PART with final search results showing all reports configured with the affected batch template; a list of affected print groups in those reports; and a list of possible replacement print groups. \r\nPART will forward the final search results to regions when available.\r\nNCAL, SCAL, NW, HI, CO, and Exempla will review their list of affected reports and print groups and replace affected print groups as needed to implement the workaround and as urgent mitigation. \r\n OH, MAS, and GA will review the final search results and determine if any action is necessary',NULL,'risk assessment by Dr. Allan Rogers',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-11-27 10:10:00','2009-12-21 11:51:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(406,5051199,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'CLINICALLY SEVERE and PERIODIC with BROAD SCOPE - SU\'07 to SU\'09 - Signed orders might not be processed due to <STORE> errors','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB, RX, OpTime, ED, Beacon, Anesthesia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-08 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Kristie Fowler',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'DEC09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/15/09: Per L. Labeaud: Still evaluating, no further updates at this time.','Signed orders may not reach their destination (e.g., Lab, printer, Pharmacy, etc.) if a <STORE> error occurs in the order transmittal queue (e.g., HADP or Foundations queues) that processes the order.  Currently, Kaiser uses the HADP orders transmital process.\r\n\r\nSpecifically, the <STORE> error indicates a memory overflow that can occur if one of the following programming point records (or a copy) is used in the Referral Filing (POS 1130) or Per Procedure Referral Test (POS 1120) programming point fields:\r\nLPP 5500 ? RFL Required Per Procedure with MC\r\nLPP 5550 ? RFL Required Per Procedure with MC (DFLTS)\r\nLPP 5610 ? RFL Filing Code for POS/MCS without MC\r\nLPP 17584 ? Preauth Required\r\n \r\nThis issue was previously escalated due to the possibility of the <STORE> error resulting in a Caché instability and a potential system downtime. At that time, a new programming point was provided to remedy the situation although it was effective only for HADP orders transmittal.  For Foundation orders transmittal queues, however, a code fix is needed in addition to the  new programming point.\r\nUPDATE 12/08/09:  Additional programming point identified\r\n\r\nFYI:\r\n\r\nEpic (Kristie Flowler) has informed us that an additional programming point that triggers this issue has been identified. \r\n  \r\nLPP 5600? RFL FILING CODE WITH MC PRESENT should be included in the list of programming points that can cause this. \r\n\r\nThis was included in the search but was not included in the original PART notification.\r\nRegions should be advised that, if it is determined that the programming points noted in the original PART document are not currently in Production in your region, you should also check for this programming point and install the EPIC recommended workaround.  \r\n\r\nAt least one region has already found this to be the case.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'12/8/09: PART update is included in description below.\r\n12/08/09: NCAL isn\'t impacted because the workaround is already in place from a previous item that actually wasn\'t Pt Safety (per B. Harper)','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-08 10:50:00','2009-12-21 02:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(407,5038350,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,' NO CURRENT IMPACT - Orders may not be placed correctly with Second Sign Orders','','',NULL,NULL,'Rx, OpTime, AMB (SU \'09)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-08 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Dustin Foster',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'P',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/08/09: Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of SU\'09 IU3','The Second Sign feature, new in SU\'09, allows a user to require that specific orders are reviewed and signed by two clinicians.  However, in specific Second Sign workflows, orders might not be placed or released correctly. Additionally, depending on the scenario, a second signature might be incorrectly marked as required or not required.  NOTE: the Second Sign feature is not the same as Cosigning.\r\n\r\nFollowing are the categories of scenarios that could occur as a result of this defect.\r\n\r\nRULE CONFIGURATION\r\n\r\n1. A rule may be configured so that the Second Sign check box is displayed to clinicians to give them the option to require a second signature for an order. In this rule, you can specify that the Second Sign check box be selected by default while still allowing the ordering clinician to clear the check box. \r\n\r\nWhen a rule is configured as described above and an ordering clinician clears the Second Sign check box for an order, a second signature is incorrectly still required. In this scenario, the order is not released until the second signature is obtained, even though the ordering clinician intentionally cleared the check box so as not to require a second signature for the order. As a result, the release of the order might be delayed, and the ordering clinician might not realize that the delay is due to the second signature being required. \r\n\r\n2. A rule may be configured that determines when a second signature is required, based on an attribute of the order such as how many times the order occurs. If a clinician changes that value for the order, the change might cause the order to require a second signature based on the rule configuration without notifying the ordering clinician. \r\n\r\nORDER MODIFICATION \r\n\r\n1. A modified order that requires a second signature might be incorrectly released before a patient is transferred when using the Pre-Transfer Medication Reconciliation Navigator. \r\n\r\n2. A modification to an order that requires a second signature might not be applied to the order upon a patient\'s arrival when using a Pre-Transfer Medication Reconciliation Navigator. \r\n\r\n3. When an order is modified, a new order is created unless the property that was modified was one of those listed in the Allowed Medication Modifications field on the Inpatient Allowed Order Modifications screen in EMR System Definitions. A clinician might not receive notification that an order requires a second signature when the order is modified and the new order is created. When the ordering clinician modifies the order, the Summary Sentence for the new order does not indicate that the order requires a second signature, and the Second Sign check box is not selected by default. \r\n\r\nFollowed-By Linked Orders\r\n\r\nFollowed-by linked orders are orders that are grouped so that they occur in a specific sequence. When a clinician modifies an order that is part of a linked group, the modification impacts the other orders in the group. For example, modifying the scheduled time of one order in the linked group changes the scheduling time of the other orders in the linked group. If one order in a linked group is designated as needing a second signature, the system requires all the orders to have a second signature to ensure that the entire group is either active or inactive.\r\n \r\nThe following issues can occur when requiring a second signature for followed-by linked orders: \r\n\r\n1. When a second clinician signs an order that is part of a linked group, the linked relationship between the orders is not saved. As a result, the orders can be modified individually so that their time sequences are out of order. When the orders appear in navigators and reports in a different time sequence than was intended, it can result in the orders being acted upon at the wrong times. \r\n2. When a second signature is required for an order that is part of a linked group, the order might be incorrectly pended, instead of released. This issue occurs only when doses of the order that requires a second signature have expired prior to the rest of the linked orders being signed by the second clinician.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-08 11:01:00','2009-12-08 11:27:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(408,5063507,1,'BEACON',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Treatment plan percentage dose modifications may be lost if clinician cancels while viewing the modification with order composer. ','','',NULL,NULL,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-11 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Liz Nichols lnichols@epicsystems.com',NULL,'5099',NULL,'Dose %age modifications for Beacon patients could be lost, resulting in improper or harmful med dosages given.  ','','','','adhoc requested by Kirk Ryan / PART','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','IM',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'BCON','N','S','P','B',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/11/09: NCAL authorized adhoc, at request of PART / Kirk Ryan ','Dose modifications in Beacon treatment plans can unexpectedly change back to the prior dose value.  This happens in the following scenario:\r\nThe user changes a percentage modification to the dose of a medication on the Dose Modification form in a Beacon Treatment Plan\r\nThe user then opens Order Composer to review the order\r\nThe user then clicks Cancel in the Order Composer. \r\n\r\nSample workflow:\r\n Highlight a medication in a Beacon treatment plan and click the Modify Dose button, e.g., Doxorubicin  60 MG/M2  \r\nIn the Dose Modification form, modify the dose by selecting a percentage button or entering a percentage value. Select either the Change This Order Only or Change All Orders for This Medication matching criteria option (radio button) and accept the dose modification.  For example, the dose is modified to 80% of the original dose of 60 MG/M3, which will change the dose value to 48 MG/M2.\r\nAfter accepting the dose modification, the medication will display with the modified dose value.  \r\nThe Doxorubicin modified dose is now 48 MG/M2 (changed from 60 MG/M2).\r\nOpen the Order Composer for the medication for which the dose was modified by clicking on the summary sentence.\r\nMake any or no changes in the Order Composer and then click Cancel to close the Order Composer. This should remove any changes made afteropening the order composer.  The dose will unexpectedly change to the value prior to using dose modification.  \r\nThe dose for Doxorubicin changed from 48 MG/M2 to 60 MG/M2 after clicking Cancel instead of remaining at 48 MG/M2. ',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'NCAL (Tom Stewart) has provided ad hoc authorization 5099.\r\nEpic (Liz Nickels) will notify PART by 12/18/09 of development status of the fix.\r\nAll regions are advised to install the ad hoc fix when available.\r\n','Any of the following workarounds are suggested:  \r\nChange the workflow to click Accept and not Cancel in the Order Composer after the order has been reviewed. All affected regions will notify ordering physicians to utilize this option.\r\nChange the workflow to close the treatment plan after the dose modification functionality is used\r\nRemove buttons that allow for dose modifications by percent\r\n','On 12/11/09 Beacon AC (Kirk Ryan) will send a communication to Beacon end users and to Beacon contacts in the impacted. \r\nOn 12/11/09 Beacon contacts in affected regions will notify all Beacon ordering physicians in their regions to modify their ordering workflow to perform the workaround.','',NULL,'Risk assessment by Dr. Scott Adelman\r\nDiscovered by another Epic customer\r\nCaused by I7512181/C75031529, installed in NCAL prod 11/6/09.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-11 09:54:00','2009-12-15 02:34:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(409,5074132,1,'INPAT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'SU09--Second Sign feature - No active order exists while a modified order or changed/reordered prescription awaits a second signature ','','',NULL,NULL,'Ambulatory, ED, Pharmacy, OpTime, Beacon, Radiant',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-17 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Dustin Foster',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NCI',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12-17-09:  Epic (Dustin Foster) will provide a code fix as part of SU\'09 IU2 and inform PART',' Second Sign is new functionality in SU\'09 that allows system configuration to require or recommend a second signature before an order is released. (This functionality is dfferent from Cosign functionality)\r\n\r\nWhen a clinician modifies an existing order and indicates that a second signature is required for the order, the system discontinues the original order immediately. However, the system does not replace the discontinued order with the modified order until the second signature is obtained. As a result, there is no active order in the system during the time period between the first clinician signature and the second clinician signature. During this time, the order is held by the system, but the held order does not appear along with other held orders in the Pended and Held Orders window or in the Signed & Held subsection of the Orders navigator section. The order is unable to be released or otherwise acted upon until the second signature is obtained. \r\n\r\nThis issue occurs in any inpatient or outpatient ordering workflow that permits an order modification for which a second signature is expected, including the change prescription workflow and reorder prescription workflow. The issue affects both inpatient and outpatient mode medication and procedure orders. Because Second Sign is not enabled for order discontinuation workflows, discontinued medication and procedure orders are not affected by this issue.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'The fix will be available in SU\'09 IU2.  NCAL will not install SU09 until after that release. ','Until regions install and validate the Special Update, Epic recommends that Second Sign functionality should not be enabled. \r\nDisable Second Sign functionality as follows:\r\nRemove 64-Second Sign from the list of Display Items in all active Order Composer configuration (OCC) records. \r\nRemove all Second Sign rules from EMR System Definitions and from all active profiles. ','','',NULL,'found in Epic internal testing\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-17 05:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(410,5077428,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'Clinically Moderate and Rare with Narrow Scope-  SU\'09 - Result values may display incorrectly in Lab Flowsheets if results reference ranges have a pipe (|) or underscore (_) character','','',NULL,NULL,'IP2, ED, Beacon, OpTime, Radiant, Anesthia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-18 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','Jason Ramaker',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/18/09: NCAL will not be impacted since they will upgrade to SU\'09 IU3 or higher.','Potential Problem Description:  Result values can display incorrectly in Lab Flowsheets if result component reference ranges contain a pipe (|) or underscore (_) characters.  Specifically, the flowsheet row is affected as follows:\r\nA pipe character in the lastest reference range causes result values in the flowsheet row to be shifted one column to the right\r\nAn underscore character in the latest reference range causes result values in the flowsheet row to be shifted to a new row.\r\n\r\nA component?s latest reference range can contain a pipe or underscore character if any of the following is true: \r\nResult data filed through an interface includes pipe or underscore characters in lab value reference ranges. \r\nA pipe or underscore character is included in the default reference range values specified in the component record. When a user enters a result for a lab order that contains such a component, the pipe or underscore character is pulled into the reference range by default in Enter/Edit Results. \r\nA user manually enters a pipe or underscore in the reference range when resulting the order in Enter/Edit Results. \r\n\r\nNOTE:  There are two similar issues in which a pipe character can affect Review Flowsheet display. Please ask your Epic TS for details if needed. \r\nEpic Care Concern reference Q-843836:  If a result value or comment contains one or more pipe characters, the corresponding flowsheet cell does not display the value correctly. \r\nEpic Care Concern reference Q-844846: If review flowsheets are set up to display either question response data or documentation flowsheet data, and a question response or set of documentation flowsheet data contains a pipe character, the review flowsheet does not display the data correctly. \r\n',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,274,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-18 03:00:00','2009-12-18 03:01:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(411,5080649,1,'AMB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'CLINICALLY SEVERE but RARE with NARROW SCOPE - SU\'09  - Automatic patient merges in MyChart may cause data discrepancies','','',NULL,NULL,'MyChart, IP, ED, OpTime, Beacon, EpicCare Link',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-18 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,'','',NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','','','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'O','NA',NULL,NULL,'0',NULL,'0',NULL,NULL,'SU09','N','N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'12/21/09: Since the fix is expected to be installed before IU3 and later, NCAL, SCAL, MAS, OH are not impacted.','A patient merge may not complete when MyChart accounts from both patients are automatically merged during the merge process. This issue occurs when both of the following are true:\r\nBoth patient records involved in the merge have a MyChart account\r\nThe Automatically merge WPR records? setting, in Patient Access System Definitions, is set to Yes\r\n\r\nDetails\r\nThe expected behavior of the patient merge is to combine the data of both records into one complete record. However, when the two records are automatically merged, the source patient record will not be deleted as expected. The target patient that results from the merge will not be able to log in to My Medical Record on kp.org and will have incomplete data in the patient record. For example, the target patient\'s record might contain an incomplete medication list. Continued use of either patient record might result in data integrity issues.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,274,141,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-12-18 03:21:00','2009-12-21 11:05:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
